(693, 'qTEgxrgzkl0', NULL, 'H.P. Kumar at Small Business Congress 2010', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'SMALL BUSINESS CONGRESS 2010', 'small business congress franchise entreprenuer ', '1.40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 2129, 'A', '2012-11-21 16:07:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(10, 'rDbc3gQAT8s', NULL, 'The franchise agenda', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Brian Duckett, The Franchise Co., UK, delivers a speech at FI2009 on “Business Opportunities in Franchise Marketing Sector”. He says when we enter a franchise business we need to have two different functions; firstly marketing what you originally do and secondly marketing your franchisee. Afterwards the plan turns to recruit, train, mentor and motivate the people who run your business and the one you in business with.', 'Franchise Business Entrepreneur Retail Business Opportunity ', '6:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 5, 3570, 'A', '2010-03-16 08:15:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(11, '0R8EQkvwG9M', NULL, 'Internet the hub for franchise enquiry', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Brian Duckett, The Franchise Co., UK, delivers a speech at FI2009 on “Business Opportunities in Franchise Marketing Sector”. He throws light on how internet has taken over franchise enquiry lead generation. Internet can be used in a number of ways to make your franchise offer look attractive. If one is going to ignore internet for franchise marketing, they you are going to lose business as compared to your competitors.', 'Franchise Business Entrepreneur Retail Business Opportunity ', '6:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3163, 'A', '2010-03-16 08:16:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(696, 'dRv6OyVWSUI', NULL, 'Dinesh Rai at Small Business Congress 2010', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'SMALL BUSINESS CONGRESS 2010', 'franchise business congress small entrepreneur ', '2.16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 2336, 'A', '2012-11-21 16:13:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(697, 'KZpk_q3TbkI', NULL, 'Dinesh Agarwal at Small Business Congress 2010', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'SMALL BUSINESS CONGRESS 2010', 'Franchise Entrepreneur Business Innovation ', '1.17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2094, 'A', '2012-11-21 16:15:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(14, 'dDwY704BZm8', NULL, 'Best business opportunity', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Rod Young, DC Strategy, Australia, delivers a speech at FI2009 on “Business Opportunities in Franchise Recruitment Sector”. He says before recruiting new franchisees you need to be positive that existing ones are giving you full returns and they are enjoying profit too. Because, when you grant a franchisee you are allowing that person to use your hard earned name in the market place. An ideal candidate would be the person, who is ready to change as per you, knows your consumer and will maintain the standard you want them to.', 'Franchise Retail Business Entrepreneur ', '6:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4738, 'A', '2010-03-16 08:19:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1041, '3DnEX8jMW2I', NULL, 'The growing M in Multi channel Retailing ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Franchise India - Asia\\\\\\\'s largest integrated franchise solution company held the annual Indian e-Retail Congress 2013 at The Claridges, Surajkund on 15th & 16th February 2013. This event provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading e-Retailers and Retailers and an understanding around how e-retail is re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.\\r\\nThe first day\\\\\\\'s sessions focused on introducing retail reinvention for an omni channel world with a welcome address by Ms. Ritu Marya-Editor in Chief, Retailer, Franchise India Holdings Ltd followed by speakers Ajit Joshi, Croma, Ambareesh Murty, Pepperfry.com and the Ministry of IT. The changing consumer & the anatomy of his purchase were discussed by Param Parmeswaran, Sulekha.com, Salil Kumar, Bagit Today and Nitin Bawankule, Google. Nikhil Raghavan, Bain Capital, Promod, Norwest Ventures, Mukul Arora, SAIF Partners, Prajakt Raut, Hatch and Anirudh Suri, India Internet Group (Advisors) pondered over where the money banks are rolling in retail. Subhendu Roy, AT Kearney, Balaji Reddipalli, Vice President Supply Chain & Commercial-- Pepperfry.com, Dr.Ing. Dietmar Jobst, DCSE and Sanjay Sethi, Shopclues spoke about the Omni channel Retail Supply Chain. The importance of the brand in the face of winning the price war was explored by Asif Merchant, Catwalk Worldwide, Mahesh Shah, Home Centre Lifestyle International, V D Wadhwa, Timex, Ankur Warikoo, GroupOn(Crazeal), Jaideep Rathore, DiGiworld and Rajiv Bajaj, Fila India. The day concluded with Ajay Kelkar, Hansa Cequity holding forth on why consumer intelligence is important.\\r\\nThe Congress witnessed the launch of e-Retail report 2013 which highlighted few concrete inputs on e-retail industry like Indian e-Retail is surging at the rate of 40 per cent and will reach Rs 7200 Crore mark by 2015. Indian retailers are moving to the Omni-channel, which represents the seamless customer experience across all available shopping channels, using a combination of mobile, social networks, brick-and mortar, online portal and whatever innovative channel one can integrate into the mix. A survey of around 500 people in India through which it is found that 24 per cent Indians are shop online once a month and the most picked products by them is apparel. Also, an average Indian is spending Rs 500 to Rs 2000 in one go. This range is considered to be the appropriate price range to take the advantage of free shipping, coupons and deals available. The maximum online buying is of apparels which account for 17 per cent of the online market. Accessories have emerged as the second biggest product category with 15 per cent market share. The other categories which are doing well are consumer durables with 13 per cent, books with 12 per cent, jewellery with 11 per cent, footwear with 10 per cent, beauty and health care with 8 per cent, home & furnishing with 7 per cent and, gifts & flowers with 5 percent.', 'franchise, business, entrepreneur ', '21.22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 11166, 'A', '2013-03-08 17:44:21', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0),
(15, 'N-yeGVgqxMc', NULL, 'Existing full returns of franchise', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Rod Young, DC Strategy, Australia, delivers a speech at FI2009 on “Business Opportunities in Franchise Recruitment Sector”. He says before recruiting new franchisees you need to be positive that existing ones are giving you full returns and they are enjoying profit too. Because, when you grant a franchisee you are allowing that person to use your hard earned name in the market place. An ideal candidate would be the person, who is ready to change as per you, knows your consumer and will maintain the standard you want them to.', 'Franchise Retail Business Entrepreneur ', '5:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4272, 'A', '2010-03-16 08:20:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(16, 'a9736-VTHGI', NULL, 'Store experience', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Manu Neelakandan, Design Director, Idiom Design speaking at FI2009 says it’s now time for smart designs which shouldn’t be intimidating but inviting and intelligent; it’s not about the store size but about the experience. Today store design has shifted from creative to smart designs which are more inviting and intelligent in nature. ', 'Franchise Retail Entrepreneur In-Store', '5:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3891, 'A', '2010-03-16 08:22:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(17, 'Rj2uAChjHG8', NULL, 'Store design', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Yuri Bolotin, Principal Design Portfolio, throws light on how come some stores have amazing sales and they aren’t of elaborate design? At the business event FI2009, he says it is not always about store design. It’s about product presentation; does the space represent you, your belief and your techniques and lastly the most important the customer and product should be one.', 'Business Retail In-Store Entrepreneur', '7:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3018, 'A', '2010-03-16 08:23:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(18, 'YAGgHEcwPuA', NULL, 'Role of relationship in business', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Think like a Customer by Brendan Dorrain - CEO, Global Retail Network at FI2009. In this business event he discusses about how relationships plays an important role in the success of any business. He believes that understanding consumer’s requirements makes all the difference. He even comments on future of retailing in India that is definitely bright. ', 'Business Retail Consumer Entrepreneur', '7:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 4, 4, 19, 3332, 'A', '2010-03-16 08:25:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(19, 'Szgy_Qe6yl8', NULL, 'Comnpany Logo plays an important in business ', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Think like a Customer by Brendan Dorrain- CEO, Global Retail Network at FI2009. In this business event he discusses about how his company is doing well in the global retail market. He believes that for running any promotional campaign for a company logo plays an important role. For brand efficiency logo type and symbol must work properly. ', 'Franchise Retail Business ', '7:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2515, 'A', '2010-03-16 08:26:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(20, 'aEiJF12XDeA', NULL, 'Customer loyality', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Mridumesh Rai, Head customer experience and sales, Globus, believes there is nothing like customer loyalty! Speaking at FI2009 he says whenever a new thing comes people jump towards it, consumer loyalty is always in question. Now you can’t define your target group, the consumers chooses you defines you, you don’t define your consumer.', 'Franchise customer business retail entrepreneur ', '8:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 29, 29, 73, 5402, 'A', '2010-03-16 08:27:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(21, 'WsVt-lo5rgI', NULL, 'Thinking the customers way', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Mridumesh Rai, Head customer experience and sales, Globus, believes there is nothing like customer loyalty! Speaking at FI2009 he says whenever a new thing comes people jump towards it, consumer loyalty is always in question. Now you can’t define your target group, the consumers chooses you defines you, you don’t define your consumer.', 'Business Retail Franchise ', '1:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 3227, 'A', '2010-03-16 08:28:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
