(66, 'zKB4C--uMmo', NULL, 'Education sector in India bears great opportunity', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Speaking on the Indian Education Congress 2011, Dilip Chenoy states that there is huge shortage of capacity in the education system of our country. The demographics of India states out of the 1.2 billion, 700 million people are in the working age group in which 200 million is graduate. He puts forward a question as to what remaining 500 million people do. The existing scenario in India has an opportunity of 22 billion dollar, time has proved that whenever there is a demand supply gap the private sector has taken an active part and have made a successful business out of it. He further stated the education sector in India has a great opportunity. He told in a survey done by NSDC, 22 sectors where taken wherein it was found between 2008-2022 these 22 sectors will require, 50 million people in addition to what it is today.rn', 'Franchise India Dilip Chenoy Indian Education Congress Education NSDC', '2:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 3647, 'A', '2011-05-20 03:03:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(67, 'wK_Yb4iWIbc', NULL, 'Dilip Chenoy at Indian Education Congress 2011', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Dilip Chenoy at Indian Education Congress 2011', 'Franchise India, Dilip Chenoy, Indian Education Congress, Education NSDC', '2:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2355, 'A', '2011-05-20 03:04:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
