(74, 'qqB0mBNAY0g', NULL, 'Growing Indian business worldwide', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, 'D.K. Jain\\\'s verbatim quote : I am very happy to see this conclave Entrepreneur India. This gives a very good opportunity for the younger generation to be a part of entrepreneurship. This is very much needed by the current generation because India has a large wealth of under the ground products like mining and other things. Holding this kind of conferences for India which will not only help bring entrepreneurs for the domestic market but will at the same time help international markets. This will grow India\\\'s revenue, India\\\'s image and India\\\'s business worldwide.', 'Franchise India D.K.Jain Luxor Group Entrepreneur Entrepreneur India 2011', '5:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 4001, 'A', '2011-07-25 03:54:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(788, 'C6KnLPHXBv4', NULL, 'Sanjiv R Pande at Indian Education Congress 2012', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2012', 'Franchise, education, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012,', '6.13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 503, 'D', '2012-11-26 17:17:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(789, 'RowSivkyghA', NULL, 'Sumanjyoti Khetan at Indian Education Congress 2012', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2012', 'Franchise, education, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012,', '2.44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 370, 'D', '2012-11-26 17:19:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(743, '18U5MgTnEjw', NULL, 'Preparing global citizen\'s', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'We need to think about how to prepare student\\\'s best at the classroom, how to prepare global citizen\\\'s best at the classroom. Our focus of today\\\'s classroom should be in educating global citizen means much more than exposure many nationalities, learning about multiple culture , or even emersion in other languages.', 'education congress business entrepreneur', '3.03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5574, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:00:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(744, 'X5f4uWm30DE', NULL, 'Jayashree Srivastava : Human Aspect of Education', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2011', 'education congress entrepreneur ', '3.04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3762, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:02:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(745, 'rCruXVTvGq0', NULL, 'Challenges in education system', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Why did we face huge failure at the level of our education system, be it primary or higher education? Because we don\\\'t have appropriate set of people in the education. We give away socialistic mindset and we need people who can understand what such a social cause like education is all about.', 'franchise business entrepreneur', '3.03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3591, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:04:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(76, 'PBSe_5hVcwg', NULL, 'What\'s your exit strategy', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, '\\\"At some stage if you want to come out of it and start something different then you need to have a thought out exit strategy but giving it a through early enough I think is important. And I think in that case entrepreneurs would be more successful when they are focused more on creating something fantastic. Rather than focus on creating money. Creating money is an outcome of creating something great. So don\\\'t focus on money focus on creating a great company.\\\"', 'entrepreneurs successful', '2:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 2697, 'A', '2011-07-25 03:57:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(77, 'iFxpMFg1TME', NULL, 'Building an institution', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, '\\\"My main objective when I joined the business as a second generation entrepreneur was to from a company try and build and institution so from a 100 odd people at that time how to build a 500 people company to 1000 people company. Today we are a 3,500 people company. At that time we were present in 5 cities today we are present in 100 cities. So my main objective was all about building an institution.\\\"', 'second generation entrepreneur', '2:43', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 2784, 'A', '2011-07-25 03:58:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(78, 'zO51s7vtBZk', NULL, 'Perfect meeting ground', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, '\\\"The synergy which I see here is lot of entrepreneurs that we met here are early or start-up stage and Indian Angel Network does invest in early stage and start-up entrepreneurs. So this was a perfect meeting ground for us. We do hope to connect and take things forward with many of the entrepreneurs we met here. On the other hand, we met a lot of VCs and investors which sort of make it interesting as we go forward.\\\"', 'entrepreneurs investors', '1:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3312, 'A', '2011-07-25 03:59:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(79, '9yI0m8PMo3g', NULL, 'Entrepreneurship and SIDBI', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking at Entrepreneur India 2011, Prakash Kumar stated he found the event very interesting wherein the audience was very inquisitive. He was thrilled to see such an audience which wanted to learn so much. Despite his presentation being over for more than an hour the audiences were still asking questions to Prakash about various topics and concerns. Prakash further spoke on the functioning of SIDBI and the various schemes offered by it. He said that the business models are definitely important and track record is important wherein the banks would look for the balance sheet and IT returns and CIBEL score for the last three years, these details are of prime importance to secure a loan stated Prakash. The project which the bank would fund would be one which is highly viable; it need not be one with high growth and high risk however it should be one which is scalable. Overall the credit worthiness and the quantum of credit which the bank can trust the borrower should be one which has been handled with care.', 'Franchise India Prakash Kumar SIDBI Entrepreneur India Business NZO', '4:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 4542, 'A', '2011-07-25 03:59:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(80, '52vh-34HvgE', NULL, 'The global indian brand', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The brand has been crafted with global insights, fit \r\nknowledge and retail practices, branded logo that perfectly complements the youth of modern generation.', 'insights knowledge', '2:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2391, 'A', '2011-07-26 03:43:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(81, 'M21BVh1idKg', NULL, 'Joining in the e-retail bandwagon', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Bestylish is sure to create a lot of buzz among the players already existing as well as the mass which prefers choices and providing convenience hand in hand', 'e-retail', '3:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2175, 'A', '2011-07-26 03:44:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(82, 'JpPw219Q164', NULL, 'Biking internationally', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Their objective was to introduce to the Indian market, bicycles made to International standards & with design & specifications similar to the best in the world.', 'Indian market', '3:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2388, 'A', '2011-07-26 03:46:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(83, '38NBamGKLdo', NULL, 'Footwear is here to stay', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Expo Riva Schuh India is a new exhibition event that goes beyond the mere display of products: it is the first trade show in India entirely dedicated to footwear and leatherwear', 'exhibition event', '2:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2532, 'A', '2011-07-26 03:47:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1146, 'oISo-aPp0iU', NULL, 'Ashok Ganguly, Former CBSE Chairman at Education Congress 2012 ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Indian Education Congress 2012', 'Franchise, business, entrepreneur, retailer, education, awards, conference, ', '09.22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2352, 'A', '2013-04-24 10:31:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(85, 'CsMAp78FUsE', NULL, 'Footwear at its finest', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'There are not many who are catering to the men\'s segment in particular. Franco Leone has done its bit in this regard in the \r\ncountry over the years and has had tremendous success with it.', 'Footwear', '3:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 3497, 'A', '2011-08-02 14:57:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(86, 'Yxk5WEtiyMA', NULL, 'Regulatory framework in education', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'There is a big gap in education market. If we look at higher education entity, they prevent themselves from making of profits, but in case of vocation training institutes, there are a lot of chances to build successful enterprise. And that is why there is whole lot of vocational training institutes who are able to recognize the opportunities that exist in the market. There is a need for regulatory framework to allow them to offer quality training and education as well as to make profits.', 'Rajesh Gopal Rajesh Gopal Technopark education enterprise higher education vocational education K12 education institute training vocational', '1:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4141, 'A', '2011-08-05 10:40:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(87, 'OCLmzzSGvKk', NULL, 'Education demands integration', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Concept of Boarding School is appropriate where everything needs to be integrated and 24*7 hour is the mandarin for the system. There will be no connectivity issues with the administration because kids, parents, teachers are all time connected with the system.', 'Amit Gupta Amit Gupta S. Chand Group K12', '1:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3017, 'A', '2011-08-05 10:41:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(88, 'fDZrCAt44Dc', NULL, 'Funding and investment in education', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Being a rising sector, Indian Education segment has left out close to 4 hundred million can\\\'t even read and write at all. So a conscious effort is required from both the government and private investors to scale up the education system from all perspective.', 'Franchise Business Entrepreneur Retail Business Opportunity funding ', '1:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 2866, 'A', '2011-08-05 10:42:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(89, 'RVRul4eztj4', NULL, 'Need for new age school system', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'There is a need for new age school system where students will grow their personality with skills taught at the classroom, will find knowledge from the classroom, from the text book as well as from the teachers. And will these skills they can be able to stand out of the crowd in the wide world. For that schools need to develop up-to-date curriculum design with new age tools and activities.', 'Franchise Business Entrepreneur Retail Business Opportunity', '1:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 4036, 'A', '2011-08-05 10:42:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(90, 'kFjsFPLASrc', NULL, 'Higher education should forge corporate alliances', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Institutes of higher education should forge corporate alliances with the industry. For that curriculum content should be developed in a way through which student can be able to proceed how they learn and they see themselves in their future professional. Case study methods should be included in the curriculum content so that students can decide what information they need to learn, what skill they need to gain in order to manage the situation effectively.', 'Franchise Business Entrepreneur Retail Business Opportunity', '1:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3945, 'A', '2011-08-05 10:43:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(91, '5RsEXfDvzv8', NULL, 'Ethics in education business', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The ethical owners of educational entity such as school owners, teachers, decision makers, educationalists should incorporate modern approach in curriculum like critical thinking skills, problem solving skills, examination etc. These skills should surely be taught in school to enhance student\\\'s reading and writing skills. India\\\'s knowledge economy indicator shows that we are far behind other developing country like China. Educationists should help India reach the super power the leads to be into the knowledge economy in having the goal fulfilled.', 'Vandana Gandhi Vandana Gandhi British Orchard Nurseries Early Child Development preschool', '1:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 4933, 'A', '2011-08-05 11:07:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(92, 'otvHq-QFMwU', NULL, 'Conscious brand building strategy in Education', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Every educational business should have conscious brand building strategy for their internal and external relationship. This brand building should have to be a very integrated part for strategy of the education business today. The brand should depict the sole of what you are trying to do, and the brand can help you connect all these various disconnected entities together ensuring that they give the same output, same values. \\r\\nWhen you are starting your business, identify what is the core sole of my business. It is not just the number of institutes, number of franchisees I am rolling out, what is the core sole I m rolling and that should be communicated effectively both to the external audiences which is students that you are wanting to take in, but also to your internal entities whether you teachers, support staffs, franchisees, everybody should know in one collective sole format.', 'Rajesh Sharma Rajesh Sharma Brand Capital (BCCI) The Times Group Education Building Scale Education franchise education brand building', '1:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 4560, 'A', '2011-08-05 11:08:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(93, '07FcMgTumr4', NULL, 'Early Child Development -- The New First Grade', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'There are no pre-schools who can identify the differences between the children, one has been to a preschool and one hasn\\\'t. Yet, it is true, in terms of skill development; pre-school children who go to preschools make a lot of difference when they come to regular school. They achieve some kind of organized activities in the preschool session, so pre-school owner should understand the needs and sensitivity of the children.', 'Indu Khetarpal Indu Khetarpal Salwan Public School Navtika', '1:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 403, 'D', '2011-08-05 11:09:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(94, 'VP5sT6eORZU', NULL, 'From a transmitter to a mentor', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Education system has always been driven by industry demand, and what we are looking at today, can\\\'t be generalized and applied to every school and every city or every community. And the more important thing is that the role of a teacher should be changed from a transmitter of education to a mentor. The way learning is being delivered should be changed and there is a need to technology in that way. Classroom should be learning studio where he can create his personal space.', 'Business Retail Franchise ', '1:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 4065, 'A', '2011-08-05 11:09:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(95, 'u5skXNVwTSg', NULL, '21st Century is about internet based learning', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Earlier students had to go to class to take the lesson, they had to go to library, market, look at book, take some chart etc. but today they are learning though technology, they became digital native. They don\\\'t have complete attention in the class room, they r not interested in what is happening in classroom. Rather they are much more interested in internet based learning.', 'Sanjiv Shamra Sanjiv Shamra S. Chand S. Chand Harcourt Education spaces 21st century learning 21st century education internet based technology', '1:51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2555, 'A', '2011-08-05 11:10:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(96, 'IJtP9eRNVC4', NULL, 'Betterment of vocational training', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Corporate and the govt sector have a challenging role to play for the betterment of vocational training. As the major industrial players need to get the skilled manpower from the vocational institutes, and as the vocational training is for enhancement of skill and knowledge, the corporate should support the vocational training institutes. And govt has played a very significant role where they have been helping the weaker section of the society through subsidies', 'Manish Agarwal Manish Agarwal Orion Eductech Vocational Education Vocational Training vocational training curriculum', '1:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 3802, 'A', '2011-08-05 11:11:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(97, 'cL3rxk-1SWg', NULL, 'Knowledge for gainful purposes', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The higher education means that how do you use this knowledge for gainful purposes. Now when we talk of higher education, knowledge, when we get mature students whose minds are almost developed, we should expect from him or her whether they are able to analyze the knowledge, whether they can contextualize knowledge, whether they can put into a system which solves problem, not only a local, global in nature, how criticalities that you evaluate alternatives, how critical it is that you optimize. In the corporate space sometime we see that most of the project get delayed, cost overrun, because people can\\\'t manage, and the ultimate is in the feedback look that how do you close the look. The students should learn from the education how to work with activity plan to achieve the objectives, how to achieve the goal how to make action plan. Then they should do the review and come back and see where did they do mistakes and how will they improve next time.', 'R.K. Verma Higher Education', '1:58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4288, 'A', '2011-08-06 12:47:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(98, 'cMdZBYOFl3I', NULL, 'Education should make a connection', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Today every Pre-school should give the children a positive influence in my little classroom, they should energize my teachers to tell her to make a connection, to tell to bring out in the child the best at his there in him or her, they should use the child as the way to develop his or her own future, should help mother understand how to take the charge of the development of their child.', 'Business Franchise Retail', '2:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 4613, 'A', '2011-08-06 12:48:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(99, 'YV9x7AbJs7o', NULL, 'Gap in education system', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Challenge there is not what to educate, the challenge itself is that there is not system to get educated. There is a big gap between the education we have and the education we need to have.', 'Osama Manzar Osama Manzar technology in education India\\\\\\\'s 21st century education', '2:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2644, 'A', '2011-08-06 12:48:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(100, 'PmBRKjmhzXg', NULL, 'Education yet to leverage technology', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Students have their own view of their education and career. But the fundamental question is why students are not encouraged to build their own future. If a student is engaged in an extracurricular activity, today\\\'s education in India does not encourage them. Students feel the need of technology, social media and internet in the education system. But Indian education system has not yet leveraged technology etc to make the course module more than line with the space with the growing economy', 'Kavya Gupta Kavya AIESEC Delhi University Human Aspect of Education', '2:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4505, 'A', '2011-08-06 12:50:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(101, '2oFa5K7sRnE', NULL, 'Global outlook of the education sector', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Integration of technology should be required in India\\\'s education system stated Rajshekhar, speaking on the Indian Education Congress 2011. With the prominence of technology, its usage can be taught only by the teachers stated Rajshekhar. Making the college and university education relevant was the need of the hour stated the Vice Chancellor. He further asserted the different forms of formal and vocational education and how the Private-Public Partnership model could help the education domain.rnIGNOU has been one of the oldest and one of the most renowned Central Universities of nationally and also renowned globally.rn', 'Franchise India,Rajshekhar Pillai, IGNOU ,Vice Chancellor, Education Congress 2011, Distance education', '2:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 5329, 'A', '2011-08-06 19:23:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(104, 'xY17H5hZyUo', NULL, 'Public-Private Partnership a necessity in India', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Neither the govt nor the private sector individually have the capability of the resources financial or human to meet that challenge. PPP is absolute necessity in India. Both the parties should respect the commitment between each other.', 'Ajit Kr. Motwani Ajit Motwani', '2:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 4547, 'A', '2011-08-06 19:26:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(105, 'QJPcXAObRWw', NULL, 'The Evolving K12 Landscape', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'What India will be in next 20/30 years from now? Every stakeholder should understand that what are the children doing today, and what do the parents want and what are the schools providing today? \\r\\nThat is the stake holder we all need to keep in mind today. Stake holders what the children are doing today, and the parents want and what the school are providing today.', 'Gulraj Shahpuri Gulraj Shahpuri Promise', '2:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 2837, 'A', '2011-08-06 19:27:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(937, 'XhlOYc7Z2DU', NULL, 'K Pandia Rajan at Estate Awards 2012 ', 3, '', NULL, '', 20, '4th Annual Biggest Real Estate Awards for Developers and Brokers.\\r\\nEstate Summit & Awards 2012 presented by Franchise India & Orbit. The 4th edition of the Estate Summit & Awards 2012 reunites the thought leaders of yesterday, and brings to the dais visionaries who have been front runners of this changing era of real estate dynamics together. The summit and awards will bring together a great lineage of developers, property brands, real estate professionals, urban planners, architects, designers, policy makers, government officials and brokers to explore best practices and strategies to best utilise the investment strength of the Indian buyer.', 'franchise, business, ', '7.56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3404, 'A', '2013-01-09 13:55:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(109, 'VMRaFGsvdnw', NULL, 'Keeping it Fair', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Absence of regulation in the direct selling sector is not only giving momentum to the illegitimate multi-level marketing companies but at the same time affecting the imagery of legitimate companies.IDSA is doing its bit in this regard.\r\nMs. Chavi Hemanth highlights the deficiencies.', 'direct selling sector', '3:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2130, 'A', '2011-08-11 15:57:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(110, 'M0IvvyhZjR0', NULL, 'Tara Jewels in India', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The jewelry manufactured by Tara Jewels is exported to jewelry retailers and chains all over the world. The company\\\'s exports are truly global and reach customers in Australia, China, Canada, European Union, South Africa, UAE, UK and USA.', 'Tara Jewels retailers', '4:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 4748, 'A', '2011-08-16 15:59:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(111, '0iBrxd3MvvU&feature=related', NULL, '‘Dukandar Mahakumbh’ by CNBC Awaaz', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Mr. Sachin Marya, CEO, Franchise India talks about growth opportunities for shopkeepers on ‘Dukandar Mahakumbh’, a special all day feature by CNBC for the retailers in India.', 'MAHAKUMBH_THINK_BIG SEG-1 MAHAKUMBH_THINK_BIG SEG-2 MAHAKUMBH_THINK_BIG SEG-3', '14:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 101, 'D', '2011-08-17 16:35:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(113, '1t9Ik3oXEQU', NULL, '‘Dukandar Mahakumbh’ by CNBC Awaaz', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Mr. Sachin Marya, CEO, Franchise India talks about growth opportunities for shopkeepers on ‘Dukandar Mahakumbh’, a special all day feature by CNBC for the retailers in India.', 'MAHAKUMBH_THINK_BIG SEG-1, MAHAKUMBH_THINK_BIG SEG-2, MAHAKUMBH_THINK_BIG SEG-3', '4:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 2583, 'A', '2011-08-17 16:48:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(114, '5VR1f6e-M8s', NULL, '‘Dukandar Mahakumbh’ by CNBC Awaaz', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Mr. Sachin Marya, CEO, Franchise India talks about growth opportunities for shopkeepers on ‘Dukandar Mahakumbh’, a special all day feature by CNBC for the retailers in India.', 'MAHAKUMBH_THINK_BIG SEG-1, MAHAKUMBH_THINK_BIG SEG-2, MAHAKUMBH_THINK_BIG SEG-3', '6:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 2702, 'A', '2011-08-17 16:50:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(878, '8HUZhtT9O04', NULL, 'Sachinn Sharma, Founder Agraneeh speaking at Franchise India 2012', 3, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Sachinn Sharma, Numerologist, Founder of Agraneeh\r\n\r\nFranchise India 2012, the 10th edition of Asia\'s biggest Franchise & Retail exhibition held its Franchise Awards 2012 & Star Retailer Awards 2012 on 4th November, 2012 at Shangri La\'s Eros Hotel, New Delhi. The splendid show was attended by the biggest and the most reputed names in the franchise and retail industry. The highlight of the evening was Franchise India\'s unique CSR initiative for enabling \'Mompreneurship\' in India launched by Shilpa Shetty. Story telling by Neelesh Misra, famous for his Yaadon Ka Idiot Box made for an entertaining session at the event.\r\n\r\nFranchise Awards 2012 are India\'s Topmost Honour in Franchising. Benchmarking excellence, the Awards celebrated and acknowledged contribution to one of India\'s most dynamic industries. The winners were those organisations that have shown outstanding business acumen, passion and achievement of franchise businesses and thus achieved sustainable growth across India. They were judged by an independent panel of experts and supported by the Indian Franchise Association (IFA) & Entrepreneur India Advisors. Franchisors, Franchisees, Master Franchisees and Entrepreneurs all over India had applied for the Awards considered to be the industry\'s top accolade.\r\n\r\nStar Retailer Awards is the only Awards of its kind which celebrates the best in Indian retailing. It is a singular platform for everyone from independent entrepreneurial retailers to the largest supermarket groups. These Awards celebrated the outstanding achievements across the retail fraternity. \r\n\r\nThe corporate social responsibility initiative of Franchise India 2012 this year was to launch the \'Mompreneur\'. The objective was to create an enabling ecosystem that will empower women and get them to draw on their inherent strengths and also overlay business opportunities most suited for mothers. Actor cum business entrepreneur Shilpa Shetty who has recently become a mother herself was roped in to raise awareness for the need for moms to be in business. The event showcased over 300 mom-friendly business opportunities and was attended by more than 25,000 people.\r\n\r\nFranchise India Awards 2012 and Star Retailer Awards are the most credible and prestigious received. Taking the commitments forward, the awards this year acknowledged the best performances in the industry in various categories.\r\n', 'franchise, business, entrepreneur, Numerologist, Agraneeh, Awards, Conference, ', '17.30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6725, 'A', '2012-12-06 18:37:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(120, 'a_TymMNuC00', NULL, 'Value generation in education', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Before starting an educational entity you need to have a clear idea bout how do you really look at value generation? Your priority should be in next gen curriculum, employable talent, skill, industry inputs.', 'Ravi S. Ramakrishnan Ravi Ramakrishnan RvaluE Learning System', '2:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2911, 'A', '2011-08-20 15:05:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(785, 'D3vvsN2sDco', NULL, 'Abhinav Dhar at Indian Education Congress 2012', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2012 organised by Franchise India & S. Chand', 'Franchise, education, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012,', '6.31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 345, 'D', '2012-11-26 16:54:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(786, '3BSPWSXnFpo', NULL, 'Pawan Kumar at Indian Restaurant Congress 2012', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2012 organised by Franchise India and Mrs. Bector\'s\r\n\r\n\r\nIndia`s Biggest National Restaurant forum in its 2nd edition focusing all the Restaurant professionals, Owners , Operators and stake holders from Restaurant industry to have a deliberate discussion on the growth of Restaurant Business in India. To discuss on the real time challenges ( in terms of Operation and financials ), imbibing best industry practices, Restaurant Franchising Know how, Networking with the industry people and to give recognition.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Indian Restaurant Congress brought together key representatives from the food service industry, trade bodies and associations, design professionals, product development companies, manufacturers, policy makers, investment groups and other stakeholders from the restaurant supplies and food industry.', 'Franchise, restaurant, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012,', '4.39', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 6166, 'A', '2012-11-26 16:55:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1143, 'qq2o9Jqhnkk', NULL, 'Neeraj Manchanda of NMA at Indian Education Congress 2012 ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Indian Education Congress 2012', 'Franchise, business, entrepreneur, retailer, education, awards, conference, ', '09.00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2451, 'A', '2013-04-24 10:27:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1144, 'KceXsjrLzOk', NULL, 'Madhulika Sen of Tagore International School at Indian Education Congress 2012 ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Indian Education Congress 2012', 'Franchise, business, entrepreneur, retailer, education, awards, conference, ', '08.33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 3468, 'A', '2013-04-24 10:29:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(127, 'VcZI3nMUpGM', NULL, 'Education\'s role as an effective tool dealing with 21st century challenges', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Values and ethics are undergoing a kind of change in perception of the young generation. It is important to understand how we can guide them so that this perception will be effective tools in their dealing with challenges that the globalization of 21st century is going to present.', 'education congress entrepreneur', '2.59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2671, 'A', '2011-08-20 18:41:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(128, 'rCruXVTvGq0', NULL, 'Challenges in education system', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Why did we face huge failure at the level of our education system, be it primary or higher education? Because we don\\\'t have appropriate set of people in the education. We give away socialistic mindset and we need people who can understand what such a social cause like education is all about.', 'franchise business entrepreneur', '3.03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 3591, 'A', '2011-08-20 18:42:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(129, '18U5MgTnEjw', NULL, 'Preparing global citizen\'s', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'We need to think about how to prepare student\\\'s best at the classroom, how to prepare global citizen\\\'s best at the classroom. Our focus of today\\\'s classroom should be in educating global citizen means much more than exposure many nationalities, learning about multiple culture , or even emersion in other languages.', 'education congress business entrepreneur', '3.03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 5574, 'A', '2011-08-20 18:42:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(130, 'X5f4uWm30DE', NULL, 'Jayashree Srivastava : Human Aspect of Education', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2011', 'education congress entrepreneur ', '3.04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3762, 'A', '2011-08-20 18:43:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(131, 'kaB5_z2LCyU', NULL, 'Developing Human Capital', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Teacher training is not a linear process. There are many roots to it, it would be very flexible, something which I think, would help teacher in the development of method of teaching. Such a training process actually help teacher learn how to improve upon it, evaluate it and keep going serve them.', 'Mamta Kapoor Mamta Kapoor Step By Step School Developing Human Capital', '3:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 1783, 'A', '2011-08-20 18:45:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(132, 'tNjXBZvNkE0', NULL, 'Collective thoughts give direction', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'I think events like Indian Restaurant Congress brings together people from all walks of the industry to begin with. And when people come together, they start thinking collectively. This collective thought gives direction and with this direction comes opportunity. When you start thinking of opportunity, which in this case is growth, you are collectively thinking of challenges. And challenges are best managed as a group. So when people come together, it is always a good thing. The idea behind such Congress is not money or business but industry as a whole. People benefit from their participation in such events while benefitting many others. So, it is a platform that enriches people and also businesses.', 'Restaurant together participation Sanjeev Kapoor business', '3:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 3289, 'A', '2011-08-30 17:26:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(133, 'dJaD_ugMVGw', NULL, 'We are able to take best practices', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, '\\\"When so many people from restaurant sector come together and when they see the overall umbrella issues that are there, it comes to their attention to solve these problems. All the vendors and suppliers present here know the major issues in the Indian restaurant sector and once they are covered and provide a solution to that, they make a good amount of profit and also industry issues get solved. Secondly, we are able to take best practices and put them across the sector. People with 2-3 restaurants may not be aware of best practices or how to implement them. When they meet people who are doing that, they are inspired to adopt these practices. \\\"', 'Practices United Restaurants profit sector', '3:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2289, 'A', '2011-08-30 17:27:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(134, 'h-PJx1NgZsY', NULL, 'Finding answers to the host of problems', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'It is an outstanding platform where people can engage with everyone. It brings together people willing to find answers to the host of problems surrounding them. This will definitely help to bring the best of business, not only in fine dining but the whole restaurant business. After a session like this, there are going to be new formats, may be in a year from now. We may see new branches popping up.', 'Mars Enterprises platform fine-dining format', '2:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 3, 3201, 'A', '2011-08-30 17:31:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(135, 'FR0fSrubdeE', NULL, 'Finding solutions are the agenda', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'It is a much evolved body which is bringing some of the biggest restaurateurs, hoteliers, suppliers and vendors together. I have personally in the last 23 years never really seen such a large gathering in the restaurant business alone. Restaurants have always been on the back seat. It is a very focused restaurant congress of this nature. It can do a lot for the industry just by bringing the people together, making them talk about the challenges, issues and find solutions to them. To that extent, it is a wonderful platform.', 'Indian Cookery Pvt Ltd hoteliers agenda', '2:58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4141, 'A', '2011-08-30 17:32:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(137, '8tVDy-auH8g', NULL, 'Tone on tone diamondtage is my USP', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'We have a plan for setting up more stores and the next store is definitely going to be in Mumbai. Our focus is on Indian ware, because we feel Indian designers without showcasing Indian collections is incomplete. The USP of our product is lot of color, tone on tone diamondtage. We prefer fashion shows because it does give you an edge.', 'Charu Indian ware fashion show fashion design', '2:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 4, 4, 10, 4410, 'A', '2011-09-02 15:31:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(138, '3s3nbJbzhqY', NULL, 'Mall-driven business', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, '\\\"We are looking to almost double our chain during the current financial year in 2012. Out of our 42 stores at present 20 are company-owned while 22 are franchised. By the end of the year we will have 30 company-owned stores and 30 franchised. We actually sign locations 2-3 years before the mall is actually declared operational so at the point of finalising the location we don\\\'t necessarily have a franchisee. When the mall comes close to opening we then start looking for franchisees. If we find somebody who is worth a while then we franchise otherwise we go ahead and open on our own.\\\"', 'Pattabhi Rama Rao Food Court franchise', '3:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 4812, 'A', '2011-09-02 15:53:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(140, 'KLRIidfKQQk', NULL, 'Out for a change', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'India is a strategic market for Vocollect when it comes to its voice solutions. The company wishes to tap this market and its many opportunities with its robust voice solution that will help in addressing the problem of escalating costs and improve the productivity of operations.', 'Vance lau Vocollect Voice-centric warehouse', '3:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2255, 'A', '2011-09-06 19:20:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(141, 'kcu8aFILmRY', NULL, 'The Decade That Was and the Decade That Will Be', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'How to make a successful entrepreneur? You need confidence. How confidence? Everybody can say that I have confidence. You need to have reality in confidence. Confidence without humility is arrogance. And confidence with humility makes you a successful a successful entrepreneur.', 'D.K. Jain Luxor Group Entrepreneur India Small Busniess Start-up', '5:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 1868, 'A', '2011-09-09 17:42:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(877, 'kX3KGhBkzkA', NULL, 'Difference between a Womenpreneur and Mompreneur ', 3, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Franchise India 2012, the 10th edition of Asia\\\'s biggest Franchise & Retail exhibition held its Franchise Awards 2012 & Star Retailer Awards 2012 on 4th November, 2012 at Shangri La\\\'s Eros Hotel, New Delhi. The splendid show was attended by the biggest and the most reputed names in the franchise and retail industry. The highlight of the evening was Franchise India\\\'s unique CSR initiative for enabling \\\'Mompreneurship\\\' in India launched by Shilpa Shetty. Story telling by Neelesh Misra, famous for his Yaadon Ka Idiot Box made for an entertaining session at the event.\\r\\n\\r\\nFranchise Awards 2012 are India\\\'s Topmost Honour in Franchising. Benchmarking excellence, the Awards celebrated and acknowledged contribution to one of India\\\'s most dynamic industries. The winners were those organisations that have shown outstanding business acumen, passion and achievement of franchise businesses and thus achieved sustainable growth across India. They were judged by an independent panel of experts and supported by the Indian Franchise Association (IFA) & Entrepreneur India Advisors. Franchisors, Franchisees, Master Franchisees and Entrepreneurs all over India had applied for the Awards considered to be the industry\\\'s top accolade.\\r\\n\\r\\nStar Retailer Awards is the only Awards of its kind which celebrates the best in Indian retailing. It is a singular platform for everyone from independent entrepreneurial retailers to the largest supermarket groups. These Awards celebrated the outstanding achievements across the retail fraternity. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe corporate social responsibility initiative of Franchise India 2012 this year was to launch the \\\'Mompreneur\\\'. The objective was to create an enabling ecosystem that will empower women and get them to draw on their inherent strengths and also overlay business opportunities most suited for mothers. Actor cum business entrepreneur Shilpa Shetty who has recently become a mother herself was roped in to raise awareness for the need for moms to be in business. The event showcased over 300 mom-friendly business opportunities and was attended by more than 25,000 people.\\r\\n\\r\\nFranchise India Awards 2012 and Star Retailer Awards are the most credible and prestigious received. Taking the commitments forward, the awards this year acknowledged the best performances in the industry in various categories.\\r\\n', 'franchise, business, entrepreneur, Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief ', '2.19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 205, 'D', '2012-12-06 18:24:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(783, 'HJiC4Rh97vs', NULL, 'Anshu Sahi at Indian Education Congress 2012', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2012 organised by Franchise India & S. Chand', 'Franchise, education, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012,', '6.36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 458, 'D', '2012-11-26 16:50:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(751, 'EvrtM9Vm9Hw', NULL, 'Innovations in education delivery', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'As the demand for education is increasing; population is seeking education, due to right to education, development in the field of knowledge, life-long education, innovation is a necessity in education system of India. Don\'t consider this innovation as the luxury to system.  With that it is necessary to recapitulate the goals of education where innovation in development of knowledge, development of skill and attitude can be implemented. Packaging of the content, process of delivery needs to be taken place in the education system.', 'franchise business entrepreneur', '2.51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3986, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:16:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(752, 'jznBKDX1HJM', NULL, 'Manoj Chawla : Innovations in education delivery', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Technology undoubtedly is the innovator in the education sector. But Innovation in other ways is also required. To make the collaborative education system for the students, faculty and teaching method needs to be synchronous so student\'s attention can happen in the real time. Education should be shifted to pure online. Be it online education, self based education, presentation by the student, case study method; everything needs to be integrated into education.', 'education congress entrepreneur', '2.50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 5757, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:18:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(143, '-hK-YvskSTk', NULL, 'Mukund Mohan : Stages for business start-up', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Mukund Mohan speaking on Entrepreneur India 2011 states the foundation of an entrepreneur is the basic three things which is needed. The first being the ability to ask the right question during ideation. The second stage is the validation phase to cross check whether the question is the right questions and whether the answer is consistent to the questions that are asked. The third stage is the stage to implement the ideas. Mukund who is the founder of four successful business made very relevant point stating asking the right questions is very important as then one would be aware as to where the problem lies and hence solve it accordingly.', 'Franchise India Mukund Mohan entrepreneur business new business stages', '3:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 4190, 'A', '2011-09-09 17:43:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(144, 'EfoE27FOV50', NULL, 'Idea is all about doing something different', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Idea is all about doing something different. The power of doing something different is idea. If everybody else has seen the thing, then it is not an idea.', 'OP Manchanda Dr. Lal\\\'s Path labs Entrepreneur India Small Busniess Start-up entrepreneurial idea idea implementation', '2:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2510, 'A', '2011-09-09 17:44:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(146, 'eXb0pyFP1j8', NULL, 'Pavan Vaish at Entrepreneur India 2011', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'You need some trigger in order to start thinking about being an entrepreneur. While you are going to set up your own business, you need to build a smart business model through which you have to keep satisfying your customer right from day one.', 'Pavan Vaish IBM Daksh entrepreneur India entrepreneur idea entrepreneur process business idea implementation', '3:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 4, 3091, 'A', '2011-09-09 17:47:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(147, '7Q126vkv3Uk', NULL, 'Money follows good business ideas', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'I believe, Entrepreneur is one who\\\'s height of ambition, depth of conviction and width of confidence is very important. And any talented entrepreneur should not worry about fund, because if he or she has good idea, money will follow him.', 'Pramod Rao entrepreneur India entrepreneur idea entrepreneur process business idea implementation', '3:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2837, 'A', '2011-09-09 17:47:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(148, '70CxVPPwFys', NULL, 'The Entrepreneurial Process: From Idea to Implementation', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Entrepreneurship is all about attitude to learn. I would say in attitude the humility to learn to keep observing is must. The best of way of learning is experience sharing. After you reached the certain stage of your entrepreneurial journey that is when you need to start putting process around your business, otherwise you will not be able to go ahead.', 'Rajiv Bajaj Bajaj Capital Ltd. entrepreneur India entrepreneur idea entrepreneur process business idea implementation', '3:43', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 3525, 'A', '2011-09-09 17:48:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(1045, 's1KCxvdZW9I', NULL, 'eRetail Technology for Today and Tomorrow : Puneet K Bhatia ', 4, '', NULL, '', 22, 'Franchise India - Asia\\\\\\\'s largest integrated franchise solution company held the annual Indian e-Retail Congress 2013 at The Claridges, Surajkund on 15th & 16th February 2013. This event provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading e-Retailers and Retailers and an understanding around how e-retail is re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.\\r\\nThe first day\\\\\\\'s sessions focused on introducing retail reinvention for an omni channel world with a welcome address by Ms. Ritu Marya-Editor in Chief, Retailer, Franchise India Holdings Ltd followed by speakers Ajit Joshi, Croma, Ambareesh Murty, Pepperfry.com and the Ministry of IT. The changing consumer & the anatomy of his purchase were discussed by Param Parmeswaran, Sulekha.com, Salil Kumar, Bagit Today and Nitin Bawankule, Google. Nikhil Raghavan, Bain Capital, Promod, Norwest Ventures, Mukul Arora, SAIF Partners, Prajakt Raut, Hatch and Anirudh Suri, India Internet Group (Advisors) pondered over where the money banks are rolling in retail. Subhendu Roy, AT Kearney, Balaji Reddipalli, Vice President Supply Chain & Commercial-- Pepperfry.com, Dr.Ing. Dietmar Jobst, DCSE and Sanjay Sethi, Shopclues spoke about the Omni channel Retail Supply Chain. The importance of the brand in the face of winning the price war was explored by Asif Merchant, Catwalk Worldwide, Mahesh Shah, Home Centre Lifestyle International, V D Wadhwa, Timex, Ankur Warikoo, GroupOn(Crazeal), Jaideep Rathore, DiGiworld and Rajiv Bajaj, Fila India. The day concluded with Ajay Kelkar, Hansa Cequity holding forth on why consumer intelligence is important.\\r\\nThe Congress witnessed the launch of e-Retail report 2013 which highlighted few concrete inputs on e-retail industry like Indian e-Retail is surging at the rate of 40 per cent and will reach Rs 7200 Crore mark by 2015. Indian retailers are moving to the Omni-channel, which represents the seamless customer experience across all available shopping channels, using a combination of mobile, social networks, brick-and mortar, online portal and whatever innovative channel one can integrate into the mix. A survey of around 500 people in India through which it is found that 24 per cent Indians are shop online once a month and the most picked products by them is apparel. Also, an average Indian is spending Rs 500 to Rs 2000 in one go. This range is considered to be the appropriate price range to take the advantage of free shipping, coupons and deals available. The maximum online buying is of apparels which account for 17 per cent of the online market. Accessories have emerged as the second biggest product category with 15 per cent market share. The other categories which are doing well are consumer durables with 13 per cent, books with 12 per cent, jewellery with 11 per cent, footwear with 10 per cent, beauty and health care with 8 per cent, home & furnishing with 7 per cent and, gifts & flowers with 5 percent.', 'eRetail, eCommerce, online,  Franchise, business, entrepreneur, retailer,', '14.08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 10746, 'A', '2013-03-08 17:47:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(151, 'tgR7ziLTnh8', NULL, ' Idea to Implementation', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Sam Chopra speaking on Entrepreneurship shared his experience and understanding of what ideation and implementaion is all about in a business venture. He calls idea as Eureka,as for him idea is of the utmost importance in business.Exchange of idea and conversation should be maintained with all so that ideas can be exchanged, even with spouse or partner. Passion breeds profitability and hence one should be passionate of the business , further despite having the idea, the passion what is also needed is thought process and research ; a fermentation stage of the idea.', 'Sam Chopra REMAX India entrepreneur India entrepreneur idea entrepreneur process business idea implementation', '2:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3170, 'A', '2011-09-09 17:51:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(152, 'ck-QlIdLUFc', NULL, 'Invest: Banks & FI: Startup Capital -- The Traditional way -- What has changed', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'What is the role of credit rating agency in small and medium size enterprises discussion? Business environment became complicated due to opening up of the global economy, due to influences of various business factors in the industry which did not exist before 1991. Today the exchange rate, inflation, the cost structure, the commodity prices affects each of us. In this scenario the most vulnerable set of player are the small and medium size enterprises in a country like India.', 'Sankar Chakraborti Ratings CRISIL Limited Startup Capital business capital', '2:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 3125, 'A', '2011-09-09 17:52:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(153, '2ouZOhRe9Wk', NULL, 'Grow legally in business ', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'While you are going to sell your equity to other\\\'s business, you need to believe on their ability. And you are also obligate to sell his 20% equity. This think needs to be kept in time in case of negotiation of equity sale.', 'Seema Jhingan Lex Council investment law legality funding', '3:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 5, 3223, 'A', '2011-09-09 17:52:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(154, '3OuoZ6NHfHs', NULL, 'Individual: Inside the Mind of the Entrepreneur', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'It was very hard to make people understand what exactly we are doing. That was the big challenge for us to build the product like Apnacircle. At 2006, nobody like Facebook, LinkedIn were not there, so people could not understand what we are doing? We tried to make our team believe and show and ask them to innovate. And gradually we came to success stage.', 'Yogesh Bansal ApnaCircle.com ITES enterprise dotcom entrepreneurship entrepreneur India entrepreneur idea entrepreneurship challenge', '2:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 2381, 'A', '2011-09-09 17:53:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(155, 'EwVfb-VgVXY', NULL, 'The next league of entrepreneurs', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Building a billion dollar company always requires some degree of ambition. It sounds simple but very difficult for more people to take that launched. When you are building a company, the fundamental factor for a make or break is in your ability to keep changing with the industry environment and to keep changing your business model. For that you have to open your eyes and ears on the market all the time, to make swift change in business model, your team, and your capability to serve your consumer in reaction to the market.', 'Aloke Bajpai Ixigo.com entrepreneur India entrepreneurship ability', '2:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 4259, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:23:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(156, 'wzlpOw6Mzn4', NULL, 'Innovation is a mindset', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Entrepreneurship is not a process, not a product, it is all about passion for innovation about how you wake up every morning and you think yourself what can I do differently, what can I do differently, am I adding enough value? If the answer is yes, I am sure you are in the process of innovation.', 'Ameer Shah Metropolis Healthcare Ltd innovation in entrepreneur entrepreneur India entrepreneurship idea', '3:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 2368, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:24:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(157, 'EFPcftC3lJ4', NULL, 'One industry provides opportunities to the other ', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Ankur Lal speaking on Innovation at the Entrepreneur India 2011 states : Innovation is not always inventing new things, often it is about putting old technologies back at work. There was a major news event on May 2nd this year, it was when Osama was killed by America, the first to break the news was not CNN, BBC or Times of India it was Twitter . What the major news companies, media companies could not do, it could not beat the power of social media, which was twitter . Incidentally twitter brings no new technology to the forth, it just innovates on usability and that gives it the strength of what it is. Can we question the business processes of our to keep pace with invention and change so that it not become a cabin baggage process, innovation is often right in front of us we just need to look at it differently.', 'Ankur Lal Infozech Software innovation in entrepreneur entrepreneur India entrepreneurship idea', '3:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 5196, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:25:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(158, 'MY0qIPDH0cg', NULL, 'Brand is Maya', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'If there is a definition of the brand, it is the perception about what people think of you. The brand is in your psychique. However you are building your brand, stay close to the truth. Never go away from whom you are or what your brand is at all.', 'Harish Bijoor Harish Bijoor consults Inc brand building brand positioning', '3:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 2259, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:26:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(159, 'RSaf-_xCu5Q', NULL, 'Social media to crowd source', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Today many companies have been generating sales purely though social media. And that used to be done by a few people. So social media even from B2B stand point, they have been able to leverage social media for lead generation.', 'Pradeep Chopra Digital Vidya Social media for business', '3:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2203, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:26:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(160, '1rbVYlkF8h0', NULL, '\"This is the time for Indian companies to go global\"', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian companies are looking at overseas acquisitions, which 10 year back nobody could have imagined that India can go ahead and acquire companies. But it is happening in India and they are looking at overseas franchising.', 'S. Vanket Wealthtree Partners overseas franchise', '3:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 12, 3847, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:27:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(161, '6L4Mf0WKb8M', NULL, 'If you donot innovate, you will be left behind', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Innovation is more related to how you take an inventive idea and a different way of looking at things and trying to find ways to add value to people.', 'R. Sriram Next Practice Retail TiE business innovation entrepreneurial innovation', '2:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2047, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:28:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(162, 'QYyEScMY5rA', NULL, 'Three things are important for your business: Revenue, merging, cash', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Instead of working with the top company, secure job, descent salary, stable lifestyle, when you are going to set up your own business, it is a tough decision. Revenue, merging, cash are equally important in the journey of your business. And even without cash you cannot run your business.', 'Rahul Sahgal', '2:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3620, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:30:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(163, 'zKFc_dD-Vy0', NULL, 'Social entrepreneurship today is profitable -- says Sanjay Choudhury', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Services sector is attractive, you can leverage on India\\\'s demographics, and the investment requirement would be less than the manufacturing sector. And today we should not ignore social entrepreneurs, because social entrepreneurship can be profitable today. Our mandate in NSDC is to get 150 million people skilled by 2020. It is a huge target and there is no instruction about how to leverage it. We encourage entrepreneur because biggest enablers would be today\\\'s entrepreneurs who would create jobs. That is why today\\\'s entrepreneurs are very close to NSDC\\\'s heart.', 'Ranjan Choudhury NSDC entrepreneur India service sector social entrepreneur social business', '3:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 4690, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:31:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(164, 'dxWKLz-wYao', NULL, 'Encourage today\'s young entrepreneurs', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'A young entrepreneur needs the support from both the public and government. Both government and public should understand that what he expects while starting his own business. But many times they don\\\'t get the help in proper way.', 'Subhasish Chakraborty DTDC Group entrepreneur India young entrepreneur', '2:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 12, 3912, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:32:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(165, '-UN7um4krAc', NULL, 'Growing to the next level', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on Entreprneur India 2011, Sunil Goyal spoke on the area of selling ones own business, he says he is not very sure if this is the right way to go about making a business grow from a million to a billion however he is confident this is also one way of enhancing and making ones business grow to the next level. He brings about an important point on the entrepreneur facet that thought all of the business traits is necessary, one of the prime concern of business building is a strong sales team and being able to sell ones idea business to others. Sunil brought in a practical bend to his speech wherein he laid example of Indian entrepreneurs who have made it big and at the same time there are those who have not been able to make it to the next level and there is more learning from failures than success. He cited the example of Vishal Megamart how it had to sell off its well-established business when it could not take care the expansion of its business in a big scale.', 'Franchise India Sunil Goyal Sopra Group Entrepreneur', '2:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 4403, 'A', '2011-09-12 15:33:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(166, 'qr4fzYnIts4', NULL, 'Food consumption and food expenditure in India is going up', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Food is as all of you know the biggest consumption category in India with 31% consumers expenditure. The overall expenditure on food is increasing in anywhere in restaurant, retail etc. Today we are at about 181 Billion Euros and we are going to touch 2221 billion Euros by 2010. So you can imagine the speed in food consumption and food expenditure.', 'Sanjay Khajuria food and beverages food consumption food expenditure', '4:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3407, 'A', '2011-09-12 16:51:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1239, 'rfIDWyvC5j8', NULL, 'eRetail Technology for Today and Tomorrow ', 4, '', NULL, '', 22, 'Franchise India - Asia\\\\\\\'s largest integrated franchise solution company held the annual Indian e-Retail Congress 2013 at The Claridges, Surajkund on 15th & 16th February 2013. This event provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading e-Retailers and Retailers and an understanding around how e-retail is re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.rnThe Congress witnessed the launch of e-Retail report 2013 which highlighted few concrete inputs on e-retail industry like Indian e-Retail is surging at the rate of 40 per cent and will reach Rs 7200 Crore mark by 2015. Indian retailers are moving to the Omni-channel, which represents the seamless customer experience across all available shopping channels, using a combination of mobile, social networks, brick-and mortar, online portal and whatever innovative channel one can integrate into the mix. A survey of around 500 people in India through which it is found that 24 per cent Indians are shop online once a month and the most picked products by them is apparel. Also, an average Indian is spending Rs 500 to Rs 2000 in one go. This range is considered to be the appropriate price range to take the advantage of free shipping, coupons and deals available. The maximum online buying is of apparels which account for 17 per cent of the online market. Accessories have emerged as the second biggest product category with 15 per cent market share. The other categories which are doing well are consumer durables with 13 per cent, books with 12 per cent, jewelery with 11 per cent, footwear with 10 per cent, beauty and health care with 8 per cent, home & furnishing with 7 per cent and, gifts & flowers with 5 percent.', 'franchise,business, entrepreneur, ', '9.10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 9194, 'A', '2013-06-11 16:21:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(168, 'mKGwZQ1f_VI', NULL, 'Building network will help you create exceptional enterprise.', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Exceptional enterprise model comes from the learning of the journey of entrepreneurship. And network and conference helps you find the way about how this org have evolved from an idea to large conglomerates.', 'Anjali Rai Ernst & Young entrepreneur India entrepreneurial spirit entrepreneur innovation', '3:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2652, 'A', '2011-09-23 12:58:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(169, 'yxNuTdjepTw', NULL, 'Confidence will make you reach the goal, gender is not a problem there -- says Anjana Vivek', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Women\\\'s Career path for entrepreneurship is very different. But for taking the challenge in career, every women needs to be confident.', 'Anjana Vivek Venturebean Consulting entrepreneur India entrepreneur spirit entrepreneur idea', '3:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 3, 3512, 'A', '2011-09-23 13:00:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(170, 'zV4tk8CHqKM', NULL, '\\\"Partnership is always good for starting a business\\\".', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'I have to have a balanced approach while making business strategy. It is always better for a business to start with a partner.', 'Arjun Khetan NAKS entrepreneur India entrepreneur investment strategic investment', '1:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 2135, 'A', '2011-09-23 13:02:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(171, 'tY91OltyFLw', NULL, '\\\"Registration of partnership agreement gives you a lot of legal benefits.\\\" -- says Ashu Thakur.', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'If you register your partnership, it really gives you some legal benefits. Anytime if you face any problem with your partner, you can show him. So it is recommended that you register your partnership and be registered by the RFO', 'Ashu Thakur Ashu Thakur and Associates entrepreneur legality entrepreneur India start-up legality', '3:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3133, 'A', '2011-09-23 13:03:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(172, 'YqC1TDaTtuI', NULL, '\\\"Digital media helps you engage with your customers\\\" -- Bala R. Girisaballa', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'What do digital media give your business? It gives you directly engagement with the customers. That is why participation in digital media is increasing these days', 'Bala R. Girisaballa Yahoo! Entrepreneur Network Yahoo entrepreneur digital media entrepreneur India', '2:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2506, 'A', '2011-09-23 13:04:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(719, 'gD013a4_6XY', NULL, 'Shivshankar R at Indian Restaurant Congress 2012', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2012\r\n\r\nIndia`s Biggest National Restaurant forum in its 2nd edition focusing all the Restaurant professionals, Owners , Operators and stake holders from Restaurant industry to have a deliberate discussion on the growth of Restaurant Business in India. To discuss on the real time challenges ( in terms of Operation and financials ), imbibing best industry practices, Restaurant Franchising Know how, Networking with the industry people and to give recognition.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Indian Restaurant Congress brought together key representatives from the food service industry, trade bodies and associations, design professionals, product development companies, manufacturers, policy makers, investment groups and other stakeholders from the restaurant supplies and food industry.', 'Restaurant, business, congress, food, awards, eat out, entrepreneur, cuisine, 2012,', '4.03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5681, 'A', '2012-11-23 11:44:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(174, '9GUlGEWdlSQ', NULL, 'Every Business starts Small', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Small business is the backbone of the economy of any country. Every enterprise starts from small size, even from household, eventually they become big and some of them become multinational. So there is no harm starting as very small enterprise.', 'Dinesh Rai Ministry of MSME msme small business India', '3:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 4, 3102, 'A', '2011-09-23 13:07:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(175, 'JQF40_zOWTc', NULL, '\\\"MSME is going to be gigantic sector in India\\\" -- says H.P. Kumar', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The MSME sector has grown in India over last 55 year. Small business, micro enterprises sector, unorganized sector has grown to be gigantic sector in the country. But we are not satisfied with this growth. We are looking forward more opportunities in terms of employment.', 'H.P. Kumar NSIC MSME small business India micro enterprises sector', '2:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3097, 'A', '2011-09-23 13:08:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(176, 'vzjnVWILmaY', NULL, 'Make your small business\\\'s success happen by building brand', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'When a small business is run by someone, it is not about desires and aspiration of his or her.', 'Harish Bijoor Harish Bijoor Consulting small business India brand building', '1:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2735, 'A', '2011-09-23 13:10:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(177, 'uHpa71x1q5o', NULL, '\\\"It is not product or service, it is brand what we consume brand\\\" -- says Jagdeep Kapoor', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Whatever you buy throughout the day, that is brand, it is not the product or services. We afford big amount of money to consume that brand because we want it.', 'Jagdeep Kapoor Samsika Marketing Consultant branding small business India', '2:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 11, 2999, 'A', '2011-09-23 13:11:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(178, 'ZUu375plHHU', NULL, '\\\"Consistency with challenges makes you reach the ultimate business goal\\\" -- says Ketan Dewan', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Be consistent with your challenges. Don\\\'t feel your business is wastage of time. Whenever challenge comes on the way and strikes you, take challenge until you break it.', 'Ketan Dewan KRD Vision small business India business challenges', '1:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2705, 'A', '2011-09-23 13:12:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(180, 'GhlMF9a3BZ0', NULL, 'Entrepreneurship is not about gender', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Challenges and difficulties that I faced being a women entrepreneur are almost equal to men entrepreneur.', 'Megha Poddar Siyaram Silk Mills Limited Siyaram Small Business India women entrepreneur', '3:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 2291, 'A', '2011-09-23 13:15:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(181, 'Jj97C0nRxOI', NULL, 'Wastage in food processing', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, '\"The role and importance of logistic in food processing is very important because if the logistics are not in place or organized, you can process the food but still you will have low efficiency and high level of waste of products.\"', 'Eric Oving Food Tech Holland food processing food logistic', '3:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 4, 4, 16, 3327, 'A', '2011-09-23 15:26:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(182, '_R9M1fAe84g', NULL, 'Extending product shelf life', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, '\"One of the major issues in bakery business is shelf life. Food safety can be done if you have secure supply of the ingredients and you store it properly but after baking the product is more or less clean and it should be kept clean. If you manage to do that then you can extend shelf life of product and that will be a healthy step for this market.\"', 'Onno Kuiper Rademaker BV bakery business food supply food & beverage food safety', '3:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5766, 'A', '2011-09-23 15:28:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(183, '7gVG9Xp-nVQ', NULL, 'Energy efficient technology', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, '\"In India it\'s not only the cold storage that has to be improved but there is problem in logistic movements too. The thing which needs to be improved in India includes the implementation of better cold storage instruments such as refrigerators with high capacity of energy saving and low input of energy which further will also help in saving money.\"', 'Rober de Vries IBK Refrigeration food logistic cold storage food safety', '3:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2903, 'A', '2011-09-23 15:29:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
