(212, '1W7Jtj-ibn0', NULL, 'IT challenges faced by SMB', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The articulated Ajay spoke on the \\\'IT challenges faced particularly by the SMB\\\'. He stated with internet being the platform of all business activity these days it was very important to keep a check on the ever increasing threat from the internet. The different threats of internet were discussed in details.', 'Ajay Kumar Joshi IT challenges faced by SMB', '3:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2531, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:14:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(215, 'WmEqG7gbbOw', NULL, 'Debt and Equity for SME Finance', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Alumni of IIM, Ahmedabad Ankur states in his view SMEs don\\\'t have finance either for debt or for equity. He further states the book \\\'Entrepreneural Finance\\\' shows 34 % business is failed in 2 years and 56% after 4 years. The reasons of failure could be many such as technological, product recession but one thing common was the financial management.', 'Ankur Sachdeva VP Marketing', '2:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3915, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:18:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(217, 'eumNDjOZDz4', NULL, 'Brands with purpose', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on brand, Karl stated brand is the soul of a company. He said that great brands have a larger purpose for instance Coke and Pepsi are the same product at the end of the day ,the difference being one talks about \\\'happiness\\\' the other talks about \\\'refresh\\\'. Social media today is the real world on steroids.', 'Karl Gomes Founder Agency Digi Brand', '3:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3300, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:20:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(219, 'MNMj9oX82ow', NULL, 'Marketing budget inversely proportionate to marketing IQ', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Mahesh speaking on marketing told marketing budget is inversely proportionate to marketing IQ, the more the IQ the less is the budget needed. He said that for marketing budget is not the prime factor in fact what is needed is the product has to be remarkably worthy enough for people to talk about it.', 'Mr.Mahesh Murthy Founder Pinstorm Marketing', '3:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2304, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:22:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(728, 'g77W1K9bJ1M', NULL, 'Rajeev Panjwani at Indian Restaurant Congress 2012', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2012\r\n\r\nIndia`s Biggest National Restaurant forum in its 2nd edition focusing all the Restaurant professionals, Owners , Operators and stake holders from Restaurant industry to have a deliberate discussion on the growth of Restaurant Business in India. To discuss on the real time challenges ( in terms of Operation and financials ), imbibing best industry practices, Restaurant Franchising Know how, Networking with the industry people and to give recognition.\r\n\r\nThe Indian Restaurant Congress brought together key representatives from the food service industry, trade bodies and associations, design professionals, product development companies, manufacturers, policy makers, investment groups and other stakeholders from the restaurant supplies and food industry.', 'Restaurant, business, congress, food, awards, eat out, entrepreneur, cuisine, 2012,', '4.32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6929, 'A', '2012-11-23 11:55:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(221, 'YFQtbeTGyxI', NULL, 'Winning strategy of a business plan', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The captivating Mukund spoke on the winning strategy of a business plan.He highlighted the business plan in particular has to be able to convey to the customers that they will be able to be with them through the problem because customers believe that somebody who indentifies the problem well also has the solution.', 'Mukund Mohan CEO Jivity Business Plan', '4:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2460, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:24:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(729, 'N5DC3-cEQ5c', NULL, 'Gokul Krishna at Indian Restaurant Congress 2012', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2012 organised by Franchise India and Mrs. Bector\'s\r\n\r\nIndia`s Biggest National Restaurant forum in its 2nd edition focusing all the Restaurant professionals, Owners , Operators and stake holders from Restaurant industry to have a deliberate discussion on the growth of Restaurant Business in India. To discuss on the real time challenges ( in terms of Operation and financials ), imbibing best industry practices, Restaurant Franchising Know how, Networking with the industry people and to give recognition.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Indian Restaurant Congress brought together key representatives from the food service industry, trade bodies and associations, design professionals, product development companies, manufacturers, policy makers, investment groups and other stakeholders from the restaurant supplies and food industry.', 'Restaurant, business, congress, food, awards, eat out, entrepreneur, cuisine, 2012,', '3.22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 6123, 'A', '2012-11-23 11:57:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(223, '5eLI33y-P9c', NULL, 'Cash is not a real mindset', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Nanette\\\'s speech was an inspiring one wherein she stated with all the experience she had in her life working as an entrepreneur and working with some of the world\\\'s best entrepreneurs\\\' such as Essel World, Star Plus, Disney Land and Mattel the creator of the Barbie doll opined money is a limitation only to those who think it is.', 'Nanette D\\\\\\\'sa CEO Brainworks Entrepreneurship', '3:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2778, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:26:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(226, 'X7LStf8BiNo', NULL, 'What entrepreneurship is all about?', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'For Prasanth coming to Mumbai is where he understood and saw as to what entrepreneurship is all about. The prime most concern in a business is a good model, when things change so fast one has to evolve stated Prasanth.', 'Mr. Prasanth Mohanachandran Co-Founder Agency Digi India Entrepreneurship', '2:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2312, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:28:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(227, 'whvBzVSfuIE', NULL, 'Building blocks to successful business', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Talking on the topic of building business Prasant expresses his view that inspiration for an entrepreneur and inspiration for the team that works for the entrepreneur can be different. In order to have a successful organisation the mindset and inspiration of both the employees and the entrepreneur should be understood.', 'Prasanth Bhaskar Founder & CEO plugHR Building Business', '3:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 5, 3571, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:29:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(730, 'lUz0TR2Z_f4', NULL, 'Manu Mohindra at Indian Restaurant Congress 2012', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2012 organised by Franchise India and Mrs. Bector\'s\r\n\r\n\r\nIndia`s Biggest National Restaurant forum in its 2nd edition focusing all the Restaurant professionals, Owners , Operators and stake holders from Restaurant industry to have a deliberate discussion on the growth of Restaurant Business in India. To discuss on the real time challenges ( in terms of Operation and financials ), imbibing best industry practices, Restaurant Franchising Know how, Networking with the industry people and to give recognition.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Indian Restaurant Congress brought together key representatives from the food service industry, trade bodies and associations, design professionals, product development companies, manufacturers, policy makers, investment groups and other stakeholders from the restaurant supplies and food industry.', 'Restaurant, business, congress, food, awards, eat out, entrepreneur, cuisine, 2012,', '1.52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 5985, 'A', '2012-11-23 11:58:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(731, 'j1h2b-kcBxA', NULL, 'Manish Mehrotra at Indian Restaurant Congress 2012', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2012 organised by Franchise India and Mrs. Bector\'s\r\n\r\nIndia`s Biggest National Restaurant forum in its 2nd edition focusing all the Restaurant professionals, Owners , Operators and stake holders from Restaurant industry to have a deliberate discussion on the growth of Restaurant Business in India. To discuss on the real time challenges ( in terms of Operation and financials ), imbibing best industry practices, Restaurant Franchising Know how, Networking with the industry people and to give recognition.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Indian Restaurant Congress brought together key representatives from the food service industry, trade bodies and associations, design professionals, product development companies, manufacturers, policy makers, investment groups and other stakeholders from the restaurant supplies and food industry.\r\n', 'Restaurant, business, congress, food, awards, eat out, entrepreneur, cuisine, 2012,', '3.47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6117, 'A', '2012-11-23 11:59:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(232, 'LzI4KvjtTrI', NULL, 'Outsourcing mechanics of business', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Directional media versus creational media is what is happening at present and hence a business in order to succeed should be an amalgamation of both stated Sidharth. He said that the focus of entrepreneurs should be on what they want to do best and the mechanics of the management should be left to experts.', 'Mr. Sidharth Gupta', '3:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2387, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:33:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(233, 'TH87hXqe9Gs', NULL, 'Office applications for SMEs', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Venguswany in his speech said that his organisation has always been working for the SMEs with devices being designed for them. Such as office set of application, email, domain, document management and business management applications, hr, admin, payroll software and applications. He concluded by saying that all business should look for solutions that can be constantly configured.', 'Franchise India Mr. Venguswamy Ramaswamy Application for SMB', '3:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 3637, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:34:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(234, 'zsMButYHXpI', NULL, 'Entrepreneurship is not paying utility bills', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Entrepreneurs start with a dream, and not to pay their monthly utility bills was the opening statement of Vishwas speaking on Entrepreneurship. A good business plan will let one know who the customer is and how will the customer be reached and if there is a continuous cash flow.', 'Mr. Vishwas Mahajan S.V.P Glodyne Technoserve Ltd. Entrepreneurship', '3:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 2856, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:35:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(235, 'pGeztqBp1QA', NULL, 'Marketing and its prime importance', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Nayan presented his view that for marketing what is of prime importance is to know the customers and whether it is the real customers and that if they exist. Alibaba.com is one such company despite employee strength of 20,000 globally works it works as an SME with guerilla marketing strategy.', 'Nayan Thakkar Head of Operations Alibaba.com Marketing', '2:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2472, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:35:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(236, 'Ha6f7trHchY', NULL, 'Products made today is for the global market', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Ninad speaking on product conveyed a very important factor of business that there are many geography and many products. Aptech with its presence in 40 countries stated it is even more difficult to do business out of India and the trick to stay ahead of the pack even is to have a global product. A product whose concept is global can be marketed anywhere in the globe.', 'Franchise India Ninad Karpe CEO & MD Aptech Product', '4:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2196, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:36:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(237, 'UxliXkiLmVo', NULL, 'Entrepreneurship as a way of life', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Nirmal the man who pioneered online broking in India said that it was just mere survival for him in the market for many years. With all the ups and downs he had seen there was a time when he wanted to sell his business for a million dollar and let go business. With patience and execution his company has become the giant player in the Indian online brokerage.', 'Nirmal Jain Founder & chairman India Infoline Group', '4:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 7, 3641, 'A', '2011-11-12 11:37:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(238, 'yooeW84KYSw', NULL, 'Private equity', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on the occasion Akhil stated Kaizen Private Equity has always been eager to invest in India\\\'s education industry. Kaizen offers business solutions based solely on the goals, needs and risk tolerance of the companies it caters. He emphasised the fact that entrepreneurs of today should understand the match between the investor and the investee.', 'Mr. Akhil Shahani Director', '3:04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4220, 'A', '2011-11-22 12:01:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(239, 'f0bg6nVci54', NULL, 'Venture capital', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on capital fund Anand initiated his speech by categorizing and explaining all the different pivots of business which ultimately makes a business thrive. For Anand it is \\\'team\\\' which is of utmost importance and thereafter the idea. While the organisation seeds fund it is important that they see the company going to an IPO in the next 7 to 10 years.', 'Mr. Anand Lunia ED & CFO Seedfund Capital Fund', '3:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2805, 'A', '2011-11-22 12:02:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(240, 'Iq0xTlbSovk', NULL, 'Failure at times is inevitable', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The knowledge solution expert Arun spoke on success and failure of a business. He stated every entity works for success however despite all planning and business model, failure at times is inevitable. The reasons could be several and one such unforecasted reason is government policies; which could change abruptly.', 'Arun K Khetan CEO & MD', '3:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 2365, 'A', '2011-11-22 12:04:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(242, 'R4ZQP6sOpxQ', NULL, 'Venture Capital Private Equity', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on Venture Capital and Private Equity Ravi stated some of the biggest example of Venture Capital funded was Oracle, Cisco Systems, Yahoo, Google, You Tube, PayPal etc. Ravi implanted businesses should acknowledge the genuine need of capital funding.', 'GV Ravi Shankar MD Sequoia Capital India Venture Private Equity', '2:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2230, 'A', '2011-11-22 12:05:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(243, 'HqDKuYixatU', NULL, 'Capital venture and grant', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Accounting software for non-profits, municipalities and other government agencies is the specialty of Acumen Fund. Meghna acknowledged businesses\\\' with a plan and model which can scale up and make profit for oneself and provide the investor with return money deserves venture capital. She also stated at times the business agenda is so spectacular that Grant Capital is also provided.', 'Meghna Rao Country Director', '3:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3643, 'A', '2011-11-22 12:06:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(244, 'zsvkQfJWumk', NULL, 'Role of team in Business', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Nitish\\\'s speech revolved around the team, the team being the most important pillar of any starting and establishing organisation. In order to navigate the space in terms of the lifecycle of the company a good team is of prime importance. According to Nitish one of the best ways to have 100 % commitment is to make the initial starter team as co-partners.', 'Nitish Aggarwal', '2:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2743, 'A', '2011-11-22 12:07:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(780, 'ydvgkIDslo4', NULL, 'Shantanu Prakash at Indian Education Congress 2012', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2012 organised by Franchise India & S. Chand', 'Franchise, education, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012,', '9.35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 509, 'D', '2012-11-26 15:47:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(246, 'KRJNzoEQykE', NULL, 'Stages of business ', 32, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Sanjay choose to speak about the different stages and phases experienced by Pangea3. Spending a million dollar on website creation and initiating business with just one power point presentation was something though unique did the trick for Pangea. Pangea specializes in legal process outsourcing, e-discovery, contract management, corporate governance, risk management, compliance etc.', 'Sanjay Kamlani Co-Founder Co-CEO Pangea3 LLC', '3:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 2968, 'A', '2011-11-22 12:08:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(777, 'Rj4LZHT1ng4', NULL, 'Building private label - Indian Salon Congress 2012', 27, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Salon Congress 2012', 'salon business congress entrepreneur ', '7.54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2072, 'A', '2012-11-26 14:01:47', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(778, 'cGec0fMOdrc', NULL, 'Dilip Chenoy : Indian Education Congress 2012', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2012', 'Franchise, education, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012,', '9.19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 344, 'D', '2012-11-26 15:44:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(779, 'UAIyCpi3lMA', NULL, 'Amit Gupta : Indian Education Congress 2012 : Podium', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2012', 'Franchise, education, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012,', '8.40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 368, 'D', '2012-11-26 15:46:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(790, 'dnU6xRDFj24', NULL, 'Asheeta Chhabra of Chhabra 555 at  Franchise India 2012', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Franchise India 2012, the 10th edition of Asia\\\'s biggest Franchise & Retail exhibition held its Franchise Awards 2012 & Star Retailer Awards 2012 on 4th November, 2012 at Shangri La\\\'s Eros Hotel, New Delhi. The splendid show was attended by the biggest and the most reputed names in the franchise and retail industry. The highlight of the evening was Franchise India\\\'s unique CSR initiative for enabling \\\'Mompreneurship\\\' in India launched by Shilpa Shetty. Story telling by Neelesh Misra, famous for his Yaadon Ka Idiot Box made for an entertaining session at the event.rnrnFranchise Awards 2012 are India\\\'s Topmost Honour in Franchising. Benchmarking excellence, the Awards celebrated and acknowledged contribution to one of India\\\'s most dynamic industries. The winners were those organisations that have shown outstanding business acumen, passion and achievement of franchise businesses and thus achieved sustainable growth across India. They were judged by an independent panel of experts and supported by the Indian Franchise Association (IFA) & Entrepreneur India Advisors. Franchisors, Franchisees, Master Franchisees and Entrepreneurs all over India had applied for the Awards considered to be the industry\\\'s top accolade.rnrnStar Retailer Awards is the only Awards of its kind which celebrates the best in Indian retailing. It is a singular platform for everyone from independent entrepreneurial retailers to the largest supermarket groups. These Awards celebrated the outstanding achievements across the retail fraternity. rnrnThe corporate social responsibility initiative of Franchise India 2012 this year was to launch the \\\'Mompreneur\\\'. The objective was to create an enabling ecosystem that will empower women and get them to draw on their inherent strengths and also overlay business opportunities most suited for mothers. Actor cum business entrepreneur Shilpa Shetty who has recently become a mother herself was roped in to raise awareness for the need for moms to be in business. The event showcased over 300 mom-friendly business opportunities and was attended by more than 25,000 people.rnrnFranchise India Awards 2012 and Star Retailer Awards are the most credible and prestigious received. Taking the commitments forward, the awards this year acknowledged the best performances in the industry in various categories.', 'Franchise, education, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012, awards, congress, Franchise India 2012, Sachin Marya, Business,', '1.06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5923, 'A', '2012-11-26 17:33:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(249, 'cWLSoliWPQQ', NULL, 'Neo-classic design specialists', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The Italian classic design furniture has always been considered a guarantee of elegance and fine furniture, and Arredo Classic combines its Italian style to high quality materials and best handcraft techniques.', 'lorena fulgini arredo classic italian design furniture', '3:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4166, 'A', '2011-11-28 12:28:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(250, 'ujpwxTtx5Cg', NULL, 'Classic american brand', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Tommy Hilfiger is one of the world\\\'s leading premium lifestyle brands which delivers superior styling, quality and value to consumers worldwide.', 'Shailesh chaturvedi tommy hilfiger american brand', '3:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3394, 'A', '2011-11-28 12:29:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(251, 'SgevKDHc8Qc', NULL, 'Endorsing the lavish', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Mr. Naynesh Pasari\\\'s unparalleled passion for international Luxury brands stimulated him to penetrate the luxury segment with venture ìLuxury Collections,î', 'ritmomundo hublo naynesh pasari watches', '4:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2832, 'A', '2011-11-28 12:30:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(253, 'snA_CbK6KUo', NULL, 'India International Trade Fair 2011 : International Participants', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The 31st edition of the popular annual mega trade fair, the India International Trade Fair (IITF), was held at Pragati Maidan, New Delhi from November 14 to 27, 2011. IITF is the largest incorporated Trade Fair with both B2B (Business to Business) and B2C (Business to Consumer) components. It presents an impressive range of products from artisans to MNCs covering diverse sectors primarily from consumer goods category. It is one of the largest trade fair in the world both in terms of exhibitor and visitor participation and has evolved its unique character as an iconic national event. The unique feature of the fair is the participation of almost all states and Union Territories of India apart formed Domestic and Foreign Countries.', 'IITF India International Trade Fair Franchise India India-Foreign Relations', '5:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 514, 'D', '2011-12-06 12:03:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(254, '2p8U7TPMerw', NULL, 'SME : India International Trade Fair 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The 31st edition of the popular annual mega trade fair, the India International Trade Fair (IITF), was held at Pragati Maidan, New Delhi from November 14 to 27, 2011. IITF is the largest incorporated Trade Fair with both B2B and B2C components. This event was thronged with a large presence of the SME sector of India. India\\\'s global presence had its initiation long time back with the prominent contribution of the Micro, Small and Medium Entrepreneurs\\\' of India. It has proved that was, it is and it shall remain the \\\'Backbone of India\\\'.', 'SME IITF Franchise India Small Business', '4:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 148, 'D', '2011-12-06 15:58:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(255, 'd85zZPE-tng', NULL, 'Mana Al Suwaidi - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Mana Al Suwaidi\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. A young, dynamic UAE national with over 10 years of experience in the field of senior management, event management, public relations, research & development, marketing, International Business and technical areas. In his current position as the Commercial Attache of the UAE to India, he has the responsibility of furthering trade between the UAE and India, a job he is well suited to handle, as he has had long-standing business relations with non-resident Indians (NRIs) as a UAE-based entrepreneur.', 'Mana Al Suwaidi Franchise India Embassy of UAE Commercial Attache', '2:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 7, 4141, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:20:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(256, 'lbgHvj5vZo8', NULL, 'Sanjeev Kapoor - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Sanjeev Kapoor\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Sanjeev Kapoor is the most celebrated face of Indian cuisine today. He is Chef extraordinaire, TV show host, author of best selling cookbooks, restaurant consultant, co-owner of TV channel and winner of several culinary awards. He is living his dream of making Indian cuisine the number one cuisine in the world and empowering Indian women through power of cooking to become self sufficient.', 'Sanjeev Kapoor Franchise India Chef Culinary expert', '1:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 4020, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:21:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(257, 'M0niSgRw-NA', NULL, 'Mukund Mohan - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Mukund Mohan\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Mukund Mohan is the Chief Executive Officer of Jivity, a social commerce company. He founded and sold BuzzGain, a leader in Do It Yourself PR software, to Meltwater in 2010. He has founded and successfully sold 3 Silicon Valley startups in the Internet & Enterprise software markets. He has held executive and management roles in Hewlett Packard (Mercury), Invois, Ariba and Cisco Systems.', 'Mukund Mohan Jivity Franchise India Delhi event', '3:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 4150, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:22:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(258, 'Mki5xJQKLP0', NULL, 'Navin Ladha - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Navin Ladha\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Navin is a retail and F&B expert, software architect, system analyst and is the Founder-CEO of RanceLab. He is a certified CCNA, CCDA, CNE with over 15 years of experience in various IT and IT related products, services and solutions. He has played vital role in delivering IT solutions that brought guaranteed growth in sales and profit of over 500 retail stores, restaurants and food courts. He regularly speaks at various business forums.', 'Navin Ladha Rance Computers Franchise India Computer IT', '1:04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 7, 4154, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:23:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(259, 'AvYIQAoof7o', NULL, 'Akbar Khwaja - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Akbar Khwaja\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Akbar has an extensive experience of 23 years in F&B business. He has owned and managed several restaurants, Pubs and Bars. Studied Engineering and earned a Business Management degree while working with US Pizza from 1995 and instrumental for expanding US Pizza to the present strength. He is proficient in developing franchising network for brands with unique and innovative franchising strategies. He is currently spearheading the company\\\'s initiatives to develop more brands in the food segment in the country.', 'Akbar Khwaja Franchise India United Restaurants Food and Beverage', '3:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4323, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:24:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(260, 'OjONnMg8hBs', NULL, 'Andrew McNair - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Andrew McNair\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Andrew McNair is Head of Operations at Shawarma Xpress. Drawing on his previous experience, he aims to progress the brand with refreshing concepts within the field of franchising. His formative years, after leaving catering college, were spent working in hotels, restaurants and the National Health Service Catering. He is based in Bahrain and previously worked with Wimpy International for 14 years and achieved the position of National Operations Manager, U.K.', 'Andrew McNair Franchise India Shawarma Xpress', '2:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 8, 5016, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:24:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(261, 'Vj-PU2aIe8I', NULL, 'Vandana Gandhi - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Vandana Gandhi\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. With a keen sense of entrepreneurship and dedication to provide quality preschool services, Vandana went on to earn her UK Cache Level 4 diploma for quality child care services and has ably grown the British Orchard Nursery to a highly reputed organization, which also hosts Dubai\\\'s first dedicated children\\\'s gym and fitness center. She believes that sport and physical development inculcate the necessary spirit and talent required to groom a successful child along with education.', 'Vandana Gandhi Franchise India British Orchard Nurseries Pre-school KG', '3:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5823, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:26:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(262, 'Zcwq_IFYU6c', NULL, 'Tony Maddock - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Tony Maddock\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Tony Maddock is the Managing Director of Solutions Franchising Group based in Melbourne, Australia. The company operates franchising services throughout Australia. He has had over thirty years of experience in retail and franchising throughout Australia, gaining experience at Woolworths and the successful Donut King franchises. In recent years, he has worked closely with The Coffee Club in franchisee recruitment and is currently working with a dozen profiles of Australian franchises providing recruitment, strategy, system development and training services.', 'Tony Maddock Franchise India Solutions Franchising Group Australia Franchise', '2:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 5, 3770, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:27:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(263, 'cjXSuG7Xg14', NULL, 'Asitava Sen - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Asitava Sen\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Asitava is the Senior Director and Head of Food & Agribusiness Research and Advisory for Rabobank Group in India. He is a Mechanical Engineer from Jadavpur University and has an MBA from XLRI, Jamshedpur. He has over 20 years of experience in management consulting, research and marketing focused around retail /wholesale, food, agribusiness and consumer industries.', 'Asitava Sen Franchise India Rabobank Delhi event Retail', '1:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 7, 4332, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:28:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(264, 'hX0DeoOkQuo', NULL, 'Kashyap Vadapalli - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Kashyap Vadapalli\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Kashyap has been successfully leading the supply-side business unit at eBay India since Jan 2010 and also recently assumed the responsibility to grow eBay\\\'s businesses in the emerging markets of Philippines and Malaysia. Before joining eBay, he worked for Google India, Tata Interactive Systems [India and USA] and Cadbury India respectively.', 'Kashyap Vadapalli Franchise India eBay Retail Shopping', '3:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 10, 3308, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:29:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(265, 'r_3J3oT6ZBU', NULL, 'Shailen Amin - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Shailen Amin\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Prior to setting his own business Shailen was the CFO for Millward Brown (a WPP Group company), responsible for Africa, Middle East & Asia Pacific. He also worked in WPP\\\'s mergers & acquisition team which reports directly in to WPP CEO Sir Martin Sorrell. Initially, he was based in New York where he was one of three principals responsible for North American acquisitions and later based out of head office in London, where he was responsible for all global M&A except the North American business.', 'Shailen Amin Franchise India BeStylish Personal grooming Fashion', '3:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 4467, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:29:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1043, 'NjvArSBRWO8', NULL, 'Internet Retail Consulting : Samarjeet Singh ', 4, '', NULL, '', 22, 'Franchise India - Asia\\\\\\\'s largest integrated franchise solution company held the annual Indian e-Retail Congress 2013 at The Claridges, Surajkund on 15th & 16th February 2013. This event provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading e-Retailers and Retailers and an understanding around how e-retail is re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.\\r\\nThe first day\\\\\\\'s sessions focused on introducing retail reinvention for an omni channel world with a welcome address by Ms. Ritu Marya-Editor in Chief, Retailer, Franchise India Holdings Ltd followed by speakers Ajit Joshi, Croma, Ambareesh Murty, Pepperfry.com and the Ministry of IT. The changing consumer & the anatomy of his purchase were discussed by Param Parmeswaran, Sulekha.com, Salil Kumar, Bagit Today and Nitin Bawankule, Google. Nikhil Raghavan, Bain Capital, Promod, Norwest Ventures, Mukul Arora, SAIF Partners, Prajakt Raut, Hatch and Anirudh Suri, India Internet Group (Advisors) pondered over where the money banks are rolling in retail. Subhendu Roy, AT Kearney, Balaji Reddipalli, Vice President Supply Chain & Commercial-- Pepperfry.com, Dr.Ing. Dietmar Jobst, DCSE and Sanjay Sethi, Shopclues spoke about the Omni channel Retail Supply Chain. The importance of the brand in the face of winning the price war was explored by Asif Merchant, Catwalk Worldwide, Mahesh Shah, Home Centre Lifestyle International, V D Wadhwa, Timex, Ankur Warikoo, GroupOn(Crazeal), Jaideep Rathore, DiGiworld and Rajiv Bajaj, Fila India. The day concluded with Ajay Kelkar, Hansa Cequity holding forth on why consumer intelligence is important.\\r\\nThe Congress witnessed the launch of e-Retail report 2013 which highlighted few concrete inputs on e-retail industry like Indian e-Retail is surging at the rate of 40 per cent and will reach Rs 7200 Crore mark by 2015. Indian retailers are moving to the Omni-channel, which represents the seamless customer experience across all available shopping channels, using a combination of mobile, social networks, brick-and mortar, online portal and whatever innovative channel one can integrate into the mix. A survey of around 500 people in India through which it is found that 24 per cent Indians are shop online once a month and the most picked products by them is apparel. Also, an average Indian is spending Rs 500 to Rs 2000 in one go. This range is considered to be the appropriate price range to take the advantage of free shipping, coupons and deals available. The maximum online buying is of apparels which account for 17 per cent of the online market. Accessories have emerged as the second biggest product category with 15 per cent market share. The other categories which are doing well are consumer durables with 13 per cent, books with 12 per cent, jewellery with 11 per cent, footwear with 10 per cent, beauty and health care with 8 per cent, home & furnishing with 7 per cent and, gifts & flowers with 5 percent.', 'eRetail, eCommerce, online,  Franchise, business, entrepreneur, retailer,', '6.57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 10695, 'A', '2013-03-08 17:46:01', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0),
(267, 'lXfhqiF0b-o', NULL, 'Ratan Jalan - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Ratan Jalan\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Ratan is an alumnus of IIT Kharagpur and Harvard Business School. Earlier, he was the CEO of Apollo Health and Lifestyle Limited, part of the Apollo Hospitals Group for almost a decade. He was awarded the Marketing Impact Award by S P Jain Institute of Management and has been nominated as one of the 50 most influential professionals in retailing.', 'Ratan Jalan Franchise India Medium Healthcare Wellness Retail', '2:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 4901, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:31:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(268, 'ja3PYnGWMTc', NULL, 'Shahnaz Husain - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Shahnaz Husain\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Shahnaz is a prominent Indian entrepreneur best known for her herbal cosmetics, particularly skin care products. Currently, the Shahnaz Husain Group has over 400 franchise clinics across the world covering over 138 countries. Her group\\\'s products are sold in leading global stores including Bloomingdale\\\'s (New York), Galleries Lafayette (Paris), Seibu (Japan), Harrodsand Selfridges (London), and La Rinaeccente (Milan). She has been awarded the Padma Shri, a civilian award by the Government of India in 2006, and Success Magazine\\\'s \\\"World\\\'s Greatest Woman Entrepreneur\\\" award in 1996.', 'Shahnaz Husain Franchise India Beauty Industry Personal grooming Fashion', '3:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 5, 5, 17, 6517, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:31:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(269, 'Rlbr3ny_JQA', NULL, 'Dr. Batra - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Dr. Batra\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Dr. Batra is the founder and owner of the world\\\'s first and largest homeopathic healthcare corporate group, with 87 branches in 34 cities and 3 countries. He has also been conferred with a host of Fellowships and Awards, including Pride and India Award, presented in New York City - other awardees include three Indian Prime Ministers.', 'Dr. Mukesh Batra Franchie India Batra Medicine Healthcare', '3:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 8, 5105, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:32:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(270, 'GaONq8lLHe4', NULL, 'Marc Ng - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Marc Ng\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Marc is the President & CEO of Berrylite Pte ltd owning five Berrylite stores selling 100 percent fat-free frozen yoghurt in Singapore. Marc is a graduate from the University of Southern California. In 2007-2008 he worked as Business Development Manager at Future Electronics Inc where he was responsible for the LED business in Asia-Pacific region. He aims to establish Berrylite as a household brand whereby everyone gets to enjoy.', 'Marc Ng Franchise India Berrylite Nautical Growth Delhi event Retail', '2:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 4867, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:33:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(271, 'sgfQe-_Yk2g', NULL, 'Janaka Wimalananda - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Janaka Wimalananda\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Janaka Wimalananda started hospitality carrier in Yokohama at World Expo, Japan-1989, having worked at Osaka World Expo, Japan-1990 as Outlet Manager. He was the operations manager at first ever Court Lodge Restaurant in Kobe, Japan-1991 and directly involved in setting up the restaurant. He also worked as Executive Director-Ceylon Company Group before forming Goldblock (Pvt) Ltd, and launching Loon Tao, Chinese Seafood Specialty Restaurant in 2008.', 'Janaka Wimalananda Franchise India Loon Tao Chinese Food Halal', '3:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4310, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:33:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(272, 'zWVQyTrICwI', NULL, 'Tony White - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Tony White\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. As Regional GM in Gloria Jean\\\'s Coffees Tony represents one of the fastest growing franchise brands in the world. He has been instrumental in the development of the brand across 23 countries in the past 5 years. He has taken over responsibility for the development of the brand in the Middle East and Africa where he supports 12 master franchise partners to develop the brand in their market. He has a passion for SME entrepreneurs and is a firm believer in the franchise model for business growth.', 'Tony White Franchise India Gloria Jean\\\'s Coffee Brands', '2:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3577, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:34:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(273, 'wC15O_68DPU', NULL, 'Ashish Patel - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Ashish Patel\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Ashish has spent 15 years in the industry playing multiple roles. His role canvas has taken different forms, such as an OD Consultant; Internal Change Agent; Member of Company Operating board; and as an Empanelled mentor. He has done extensive work in the areas of organisational diagnosis; leadership development; organisational culture and establishing employee connect; organisation strategy building etc. He has been associated with a number of clientele like HP, Tata Chemicals, Gujarat Gas/British Gas, Torrent Power, Claris Life Science, Haworth, Torrent Pharmaceuticals, Sodexo, Accor Services, Career Launcher, and Ambuja Cement, among others.', 'Ashish Patel Franchise India Euphoria Consultant', '2:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 6626, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:35:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(274, 'Qg5PE_Oie_k', NULL, 'Girish Khare - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Girish Khare\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Girish has done his post graduate specialization in Cinematography; he abandoned his first love to pursue a career in marketing and sales. He has worked across multiple cities in India, Taiwan, Middle East and Malaysia. Today he has over 25 years of marketing experience in various industries ranging from manufacturing to retail, media and IT.', 'Girish Khare Franchise India RewardPort Marketing', '1:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 4, 4890, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:36:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
