(732, 'BRyP_EScpu4', NULL, 'Mir Mazharuddin  at Indian Restaurant Congress 2012', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2012 organised by Franchise India and Mrs. Bector\'s\r\n\r\nIndia`s Biggest National Restaurant forum in its 2nd edition focusing all the Restaurant professionals, Owners , Operators and stake holders from Restaurant industry to have a deliberate discussion on the growth of Restaurant Business in India. To discuss on the real time challenges ( in terms of Operation and financials ), imbibing best industry practices, Restaurant Franchising Know how, Networking with the industry people and to give recognition.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Indian Restaurant Congress brought together key representatives from the food service industry, trade bodies and associations, design professionals, product development companies, manufacturers, policy makers, investment groups and other stakeholders from the restaurant supplies and food industry.', 'Restaurant, business, congress, food, awards, eat out, entrepreneur, cuisine, 2012,', '5.01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 5, 5, 25, 6172, 'A', '2012-11-23 12:01:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(277, 'JX3zGYhhw0M', NULL, 'Robert Rider - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Robert Rider\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Robert has many years of management consulting and M & A experience. He has worked in management positions for Capital Cities, ABC, Westingthouse and Secret Communications plus owning his own broadcast company Ridson, Inc. He has also been an angel investor, primarily in media and marketing. As a broadcast consultant and broker; he participated in the incredible growth and eventual consolidation of the radio industry.', 'Robert Rider Franchise India Bradford Lincensing Brand', '3:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 4092, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:37:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(279, 'Q7__5GLNfZc', NULL, 'Manoj Chawla - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Manoj Chawla\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Manoj carries over twenty five years of professional work experience, in a number of key domains - Profit Centre Management, Service Delivery, Operations Management, Franchise/Channel Development, Business Development (Corporate, Retail as well as Government). He has held a number of positions in India and the Middle East. Before joining Everonn, he was the SBU Head at NIS Sparta (a Reliance ADA Group Company). He has also worked with a host of IT & BPO training majors viz. Hero Mindmine, NIIT & Aptech in India, and ExecuTrain LLC in Dubai.', 'Manoj Chawla Franchise India Everonn Education Large Business', '3:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 4712, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:39:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(280, 'PuOxZKgv0Nk', NULL, 'Dilip Cherian - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Dilip Cherian\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. A pioneer of image management in India, Dilip is India\\\'s foremost communications & public affairs consultant, a political advisor and a practicing political & policy specialist of repute. He is a member of the Board of Governors in Advertising Standard Council of India, on the Governing Council of the National Institute of Design and the Ministry of Company Affairs, on the Board of Governors of the National Board of Film Certification and many other boards. He has been the Editor of business magazine, Business India and of newspaper, Observer of Business and Politics.', 'Dilip Cherian Perfect Relations Franchise India Image Management', '2:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 9, 5573, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:41:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(281, 'YLg6YeGOmx4', NULL, 'Dr. Arvind Kalia - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Dr. Arvind Kalia\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Dr. Kalia has written several books and journals like Management Mantra, Career & Time Management, Personality Development, Keys of Success , Success in Sales, Marketing Management to name a few. He has done his MDP from IIM Ahmedabad in Data Analysis and PhD. on Brand Positioning strategies of Selected Indian and Multinational Companies of Personal products University of Rajasthan. Before joining Rajisthan Patrika he was an Assistant Professor at R.A. Podar Institute of Management, University of Rajasthan, Jaipur', 'Arvind Kalia Patrika Group Franchise India News Journalism', '2:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 8, 6098, 'A', '2011-12-09 18:41:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(282, '-JD9erZX7Cw', NULL, 'Severin Zhilinskis,Chairman of East Europe Franchise Association - Franchise India 2011 ', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Severin Zhilinskis\\\\\\\'s speaking at Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Currently the Head of Sales LAB at Advance Advice and Director at Lithuanian Franchise Center, Severin is an expert in Franchising-creation and development, International Expansion, Seminars and EU Funding. He earlier held the position of Head of Franchising Department at Advanced Franchise. He holds a Degree in International Law and has co-authored the first two books on franchising written in Lithuanian \\\\\\\"Franchise Manual\\\\\\\" and \\\\\\\"Buying a Franchise: Highway to Business Success\\\\\\\". He has worked in several EU countries with areas such as International business, project implementation, managing EU structural funds projects. Severin also has experience in the wholesale business.', 'Severin Zhilinskis Franchise India UAB Lithuania International Business', '3:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 8, 4984, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:41:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(283, 'w70WEQtmT4A', NULL, 'Deepak Deshpande - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Deepak Deshpande\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Deepak is a veteran to the Retail and Brand Marketing industry, his stay in the industry has been for the past 32 years. His work experience in the footwear industry includes grass-root level retail and branding in India as well as North America (Canada & USA). His stints with Bata both in India and abroad, as well as Nike and Levi\\\'s amongst the various other international known brands make him a global professional in this sector.', 'Deepak Deshpande Franchise India TATA Retail Brand', '2:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 5340, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:42:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(791, 'oHNNmnMVIlg', NULL, 'C.K. Kumaravel of Naturals at Franchise India 2012', 27, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Franchise India 2012, the 10th edition of Asia\\\'s biggest Franchise & Retail exhibition held its Franchise Awards 2012 & Star Retailer Awards 2012 on 4th November, 2012 at Shangri La\\\'s Eros Hotel, New Delhi. The splendid show was attended by the biggest and the most reputed names in the franchise and retail industry. The highlight of the evening was Franchise India\\\'s unique CSR initiative for enabling \\\'Mompreneurship\\\' in India launched by Shilpa Shetty. Story telling by Neelesh Misra, famous for his Yaadon Ka Idiot Box made for an entertaining session at the event.rnrnFranchise Awards 2012 are India\\\'s Topmost Honour in Franchising. Benchmarking excellence, the Awards celebrated and acknowledged contribution to one of India\\\'s most dynamic industries. The winners were those organisations that have shown outstanding business acumen, passion and achievement of franchise businesses and thus achieved sustainable growth across India. They were judged by an independent panel of experts and supported by the Indian Franchise Association (IFA) & Entrepreneur India Advisors. Franchisors, Franchisees, Master Franchisees and Entrepreneurs all over India had applied for the Awards considered to be the industry\\\'s top accolade.rnrnStar Retailer Awards is the only Awards of its kind which celebrates the best in Indian retailing. It is a singular platform for everyone from independent entrepreneurial retailers to the largest supermarket groups. These Awards celebrated the outstanding achievements across the retail fraternity. rnrnThe corporate social responsibility initiative of Franchise India 2012 this year was to launch the \\\'Mompreneur\\\'. The objective was to create an enabling ecosystem that will empower women and get them to draw on their inherent strengths and also overlay business opportunities most suited for mothers. Actor cum business entrepreneur Shilpa Shetty who has recently become a mother herself was roped in to raise awareness for the need for moms to be in business. The event showcased over 300 mom-friendly business opportunities and was attended by more than 25,000 people.rnrnFranchise India Awards 2012 and Star Retailer Awards are the most credible and prestigious received. Taking the commitments forward, the awards this year acknowledged the best performances in the industry in various categories.', 'Franchise, education, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012, awards, congress, Franchise India 2012, Sachin Marya, Business,', '1.11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 6096, 'A', '2012-11-26 17:51:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(285, 'mqYfvnnGqqk', NULL, 'Devangshu Dutta - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Devangshu Dutta\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Devangshu is a specialist consulting firm focused on consumer goods and retail, and managing partner of PVC Partners, an early-stage venture accelerator. He began his career with the leading modern retail chain of that time in India, eventually heading the category that contributed 35% of the company\\\'s sales. He writes regularly in print and electronic media, and is frequently invited to speak at premier industry events internationally and in India. He also contributes to professional education through premier academic institutions in India and in the USA, as an Advisory Board member and as guest faculty.', 'Devangshu Dutta Franchise India Third Eyesight Consulting', '3:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 7, 6557, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:43:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(286, 'iBtfZHUJF2Q', NULL, 'Abhay Gupta - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Abhay Gupta\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Abhay believes that although the Indian retail industry has seen an upward boom in the past decade or so. Advent of spaces like Emporio has upgraded the retail space offering in totality and even an economic slowdown could not completely slow down the growth considerably. He feels that in this era of market capitalisation, bigger retailers would try to consolidate their positions by expanding further on or acquiring smaller players. His vision for BCC is to prominently make it the largest player in the field of luxury retailing.', 'Abhay Gupta Franchise India Blues Clothing Retail industry', '2:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 4101, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:44:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(287, 'ZBJSC_T6G-g', NULL, 'Pierre Hermans - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Pierre Hermans\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Pierre studied mechanical engineering in Eindhoven and afterwards he studied at Nijenrode University, where he specialised in Business Administration. In addition, he did various sales and management programmes, negotiation and leadership training at INSEAD in Fontainebleau, France. He has been directing several companies in India which serve the Commercial Banking community here, and lately, abroad. His expertise comprises: setting up high performance sales organisations; product development and innovative concepts; dealing with Far East factories; general and strategic management; and reorganisations.', 'Pierre Hermans Franchise India Syntech International Sales Strategic management', '3:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 4, 4, 14, 4965, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:45:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(288, 'Vuce7f93iuE', NULL, 'Naveen Rakhecha - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Naveen Rakhecha\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Naveen\\\'s career spans over 22 action-packed and successful years traversing across banking, office automation, logistics, retailing and franchising, the last 12 years of which, he has been involved in franchising. He was responsible for bringing Cartridge World to South Asia, which has revolutionised the printer cartridges market. He has been with AFL Pvt. Ltd since 1995 and has been the key driver in initially setting-up and successfully launching various new businesses including AFL Wiz Express, the domestic express business & Western Union Money Transfer.', 'Naveen Rakhecha Franchise India Cartridge World Printer Printing', '3:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 7369, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:45:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(289, 'QI70_DDEdJ4', NULL, 'Godfrey Fernandez - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Godfrey Fernandez\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Godfrey has an experience of 15 years as an entrepreneur and interacting with students and youth. He has been in association with various corporate through CSR for last 3 years. He heads all existing Franchisees in his company and is responsible to bring in new Franchisees. He is also a musician for the last 22 years and has contributed music to the company. He is also a conference speaker and has done training programmes for various workshops. His company has trained more than 85,000 students in the last 10 years. His company, head quartered in Bangalore has 11 franchisees in India, also with offices in Dubai and Maldives. Expansion and growth plan is to become PAN India and to grow South East Asia.', 'Godfrey Fernandez Franchise India Peoplepro Training Students', '3:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 3543, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:46:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(290, '3-21ia9MB1A', NULL, 'Tony Fitzpatrick - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Tony Fitzpatrick\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Tony is the managing partner with Franchise Your Business.ie, which provides a complete consultancy service for both starts up and established franchisors. The firm has offices in London and Dublin. With many years\\\' experience in growing businesses through franchising, he can take a client through the entire process. He advises on everything from franchise agreements to fees and royalties, operations manuals, lead generation, PR and more. He is a member of the Executive Board of the Irish Franchise Association and also serves on the Association\\\'s Membership Committee. He speaks at seminars for would-be franchisors and writes articles on the industry for newspapers and magazines.', 'Tony Fitzpatrick Franchise India Franchise Your Business', '3:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 4540, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:47:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(291, '9Rk1Iit6Css', NULL, 'Dawn Stallwood - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Dawn Stallwood\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Dawn heads Danetree, a commercial consultancy based in London providing commercial counsel and strategic advice for clients in UK, India, Australia and Hong Kong. She is a business angel investor and holds a number of non-executive directorships. Danetrees\\\' work with enterprising and ambitious businesses in aviation, hospitality, retail, leisure, fast food, travel, publishing, social media and healthcare technology. She provides insight and a no-nonsense approach to clients wishing to develop, scale their growth or secure investment, through franchising.', 'Dawn Stallwood Franchise India Danetree Associates Consultancy', '3:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 7067, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:48:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(292, '4aKPGpHItJI', NULL, 'Rob Rider - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Rob Rider\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Rob has many years of management consulting and M & A experience. He has worked in management positions for Capital Cities, ABC, Westingthouse and Secret Communications plus owning his own broadcast company. As a broadcast consultant and broker, he participated in the incredible growth and eventual consolidation of the radio industry in the US during the 1980\\\'s and 1990\\\'s. He has also been an angel investor, for the past 15 years primarily in media and marketing, internet based service providers, and internet security companies.', 'Rob Rider Franchise India', '2:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 5507, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:48:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(293, 'A77EALCVeLg', NULL, 'Anshu Dubey - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Anshu Dubey\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Anshu is the Retail Industry Leader for India and South Asia region at IBM Global Business Services. He is also the General Business Leader for East India and South Asia, across all industries. He has eighteen years of experience in Management and IT consulting. He has worked on consulting assignments for a variety of industries including retail, oil & gas, manufacturing, pharmaceuticals, consumer products and service. In his current role Mr. Dubey is overseeing the complete gamut of operations from marketing through sales, solutions, delivery to closure; involving developing relevant solutions and skills competency.', 'Anshu Dubey Franchise India IBM Management IT consulting', '1:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6353, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:49:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(294, 'nmZ1ymyGXZ8', NULL, 'Siju Narayan - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Siju Narayan\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Siju is a veteran of retail and institutional sales and marketing in India with 15 years of experience. Having worked with blue chip Indian and multinational corporations, he has gained expertise in managing various aspects of the demand and supply chain. For the past eight years, he has been involved with corporations in providing retailers in India technology solutions to help them land their business plans. He believes to stay ahead one should strictly follow customer centricity, supply chain visibilities, business collaboration models, e-commerce and the social impact on retailing.', 'Siju Narayan Franchise India Microsoft Retail Industry', '2:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4586, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:50:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(753, 'eRHezvwGHSM', NULL, 'Monika Halan : Education as an enterprise', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2011', 'franchise business entrepreneur education ', '2.39', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2727, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:27:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(754, 'k1pMHKth-qo', NULL, 'Developing Human Capital ', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Every educational entity should understand how to improve the quality training of the teachers and how to create the culture and system in the school environment which go beyond personality. With the training of the teachers, building curriculum support is also required.', 'franchise business entrepreneur ', '2.38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3784, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:28:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(296, 'zL7UCblpqMo', NULL, 'D.K. Jairath - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'D.K. Jairath\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. D. K. Jairath has been instrumental in defining the diversification plans of HSIL to become a Total Home Solutions Company, and now heads their new Home Interiors retail venture. During his rich career span of about 20 years, he has successfully managed multiple industry sectors, functions and geographies. His diversified stints across sectors like Automotive, Engineering, Consumer Durables, FMCG, Retail, Services.', 'D.K. Jairath Franchise India Hindware Home Retail', '3:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 9, 7002, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:52:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(297, 'Ji7ZfZ2b8x8', NULL, 'Prasun Chowdhury - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Prasun Chowdhury\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show Avenir is a management consulting company working with brands to significantly increase cash flow and profits. Prasun in more than 13 years of consulting has led key engagements with Fortune 50 organizations such as General Motors Europe and Philips International as well as medium sized organizations across the world. He has led and supervised consulting engagements that have delivered quantum increase in profits in very short periods of time.', 'Prasun Chowdhury Franchise India Avenir Management Retail', '3:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 4491, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:52:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(299, 'CXuXfia91xc', NULL, 'Jagdeep Chhabra - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Jagdeep Chhabra\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show Jagdeep is the entrepreneur behind the brand \\\"Chhabra 555\\\" who has been instrumental in expanding its reach across the country. With approximately 40 years of experience behind him, he has made his business one of the most organized entities in the Indian ethic-wear retail market.', 'Jagdeep Chhabra Franchise India Chhabra 555 Ethnic-wear Retail', '1:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3035, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:54:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(300, '66ZrAxsDlMk', NULL, 'Vineet Kanaujia - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Vineet Kanaujia\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show With a rich experience of around 10 years under his belt, Vineet joined Safexpress more than two years ago. Since then he has contributed extensively to the growth of the company. He is responsible for giving shape and direction to the marketing strategy of the company.', 'Vineet Kanaujia Franchise India Safeexpress Logistic', '2:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 3220, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:55:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(301, 'gwqfNrDuzLI', NULL, 'Asim Dalal - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Asim Dalal\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show Asim joined Bombay Swadeshi Stores Limited as Director in October, 1991 and in April, 1994 took over as Managing Director. His earlier assignments include a successful stint with Hill Samuel Bank Limited in London in their International Banking Division, followed by a stint in the Equity & Euro-products division of Societe Generale Strauss Turnbull Securities Limited in London. His main role at the \\\'The Bombay Store\\\' include expansion, business development and financial planning.', 'Asim Dalal Franchise India The Bombay Store Retail', '3:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 4859, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:56:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(302, 'rS4wmxbgInU', NULL, 'Ken Nisch - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Ken Nisch\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show Ken became JGA president in 1987 and chairman in 1995. He has worked on an international scope with responsibilities that include client liaison and total project design. His knowledge and entrepreneurial insight into consumer markets are integrated into prototype development, conceptual development, architectural direction, and strategic image positioning for retail operators, manufacturers, and brand marketers.', 'Ken Nisch Franchise India JGA Retail design', '3:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 5119, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:56:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(733, 'Hmj0pguKfTY', NULL, 'Jonathan Jordan at Indian Restaurant Congress 2012', 31, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2012 organised by Franchise India and Mrs. Bector\'s\r\n\r\nIndia`s Biggest National Restaurant forum in its 2nd edition focusing all the Restaurant professionals, Owners , Operators and stake holders from Restaurant industry to have a deliberate discussion on the growth of Restaurant Business in India. To discuss on the real time challenges ( in terms of Operation and financials ), imbibing best industry practices, Restaurant Franchising Know how, Networking with the industry people and to give recognition.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Indian Restaurant Congress brought together key representatives from the food service industry, trade bodies and associations, design professionals, product development companies, manufacturers, policy makers, investment groups and other stakeholders from the restaurant supplies and food industry.', 'Restaurant, business, congress, food, awards, eat out, entrepreneur, cuisine, 2012,', '5.05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5847, 'A', '2012-11-23 12:02:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(304, 'iffan7I5QA8', NULL, 'Rahul Gambhir - 9th International Franchise and Retail Show 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Rahul Gambhir\\\'s exclusive interview to Franchise India at the 9th International Franchise and Retail Show. Rahul has 16 years of experience in diverse industries ranging from FMCG to Financial Services to Fashion Industry. \\r\\nIn his previous role, he was heading the Red Bull operations in India.', 'Rahul Gambhir Franchise India Brand Licensing Tommy Hilfiger Fashion Accessories Red Bull Franchise', '3:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 5187, 'A', '2011-12-13 14:58:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(305, 'TmUGz1nDxIc', NULL, 'Fueling India as a start-up Nation', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'IndiaPreneurship, TiE and FMS, University of Delhi presented a one day conclave titled : Fueling India as a start-up nation. The agenda of the programme was to promote the cause of entrepreneurship. This panel discussion was one among the many informative and motivating sessions of the day. The panel moderator was Priyank Narayan, who is the founder of IndiaPreneurship. His organisation has been working with business schools across the world to bring talent to India to set up ventures in the country. Each of the panelist beautifully narrated as to how they answered their intuition and faced all challenges to become what they wanted to be ie., \\\'an Entrepreneur \\\'. The conclave was an action packed event with a number of expert speakers who shared their perspective of various aspects of entrepreneurship.', 'IndiaPreneurship Franchise India Priyank Narayan Entrepreneurship', '6:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 9, 5423, 'A', '2011-12-20 17:51:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(757, '-FaFY0TdyUk', NULL, 'Dr. Abha Adams :  Developing Human Capital', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Best performance school system should be judged on the basis of competent faculty, quality training, and continuous development of the faculty. And that can produce best possible instruction to every student and really effective practices in education.', 'franchise business education congress ', '2.24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3738, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:32:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(758, '1LCHyL7GVvs', NULL, 'Mastering Higher Education', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'There has been a lot expansion in education in India, but grass enrollment ratio (the percentage of total population in the age group of 18 to 23) is about 11 to 12 % where as the grass enrollment ratio in the whole world is 23% and for the developed country it is more than 56%. So it is understood that there is a need to expand many new university, college, IITs and that would increase the excellence in higher education. Recruitment of competent faculty is also necessary for the professional growth. Modernization and relevance of the syllabi (curriculum) is also important so that it can ensure excellence in teaching and learning method.', 'education congress education business ', '2:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3690, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:34:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(759, '2px75KJzKqg', NULL, 'Education spaces for 21st century learning', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Education should happen from the house, in any PR group, in the classroom under the tree and so on. But we need school to impart education. That school should have an architecture where students can be able to respond positively to the climate. They should feel protected and they should feel that the school is mother\'s home and extension.', 'franchise business entrepreneur ', '2.06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6236, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:37:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(761, 'bV7Wf91HgWs', NULL, 'Neeraj Manchanda : Education spaces for 21st century learning', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'This is time to need to understand where school design needs to go? Where kind of space we need to be looking at? A school should be a place where Learning environment, transparency, visibility is the priority.', 'franchise business entrepreneur education ', '2.20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3822, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:54:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(762, 'e0DpGNpyURA', NULL, 'Dr. Sudhir Kapur : Education as an enterprise', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'We need to make whole education system individual centric. It will be able to create skilled people. And for that vocational education should be integrated with mainstream education.', 'education congress business ', '2.19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3375, 'A', '2012-11-26 11:56:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(308, '4viG3peOelw', NULL, 'US or India business it has to be ', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Seema Giri speaking on Women Entrepreneurship spoke on how she started her entrepreneur journey. As she had started her business in the US she spoke as to how she established her business here in India. She also spoke about the SME of India and stated that the future is very bright for business in general and the SME in particular. Starting her business with zero funds and putting almost 30,000 US Dollars to her credit card, the business has done very well now. For Seema her business venture was all the more different as it was her husband who is the co-founder.', 'Seema Giri, Franchise India, Women Entrepreneur, Business', '02.41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 3072, 'A', '2012-01-09 17:24:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(309, 'K6DKiJPAPyU', NULL, 'From kitchen pickle to Mall ‘ Pickle’.', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Alakhnanda Kumar is one of the most successful women entrepreneurs in the recent business arena. An avid pickle lover, her love for pickles proved worthy as she continued her strive for pickles wherein she started her business; little did she know that it would be a grand success. She says that any agro based business gives profit almost immediately but at the same time it is also important to keep investing in business. She states the journey was not an easy one but it has been a game worth playing. SMEs for her are a major component for business and will help in the development of the economy dominantly.', 'Alakhnanda Kumar, Franchise India, Women Entrepreneur, Business', '01:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 3, 4388, 'A', '2012-01-09 17:30:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(310, 'D-oZGy4hefs', NULL, 'Talent management: A managed affaire', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Ester Martinez is a shining example of the intelligent and entrepreneur inclined women entrepreneurs. She started her entrepreneur journey seeing the gaps and the areas for enhancing the human resource and talent management industry; she was nurtured in. A complete end to end solution provider to companies for their hiring needs Ester opines she always wanted to take the Human Resource industry with her own edge. She also spoke on the attrition rate of various industries stating the figures are usually not the correct one with the real figures being much larger.  The youngsters are not looking for a job today but they are looking for a career and for people promise; said Ester, forecasting attrition rate to be much higher in 2012.', 'Ester Martinez, Franchise India, Women Entrepreneur, Business, People Matters ', '03:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 4564, 'A', '2012-01-09 17:32:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(311, 'NzWVpvGs-Gs', NULL, 'Bahamian - India business tie-up', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Bertha M. Cooper-Rousseau a successful entrepreneur of Bahamans is here in India to see the likelihood of her business expansion. A keen learner, she states at present she is more interested learning as to how business happens in India and thereafter once done with the learning process she is eager to explore the Indian market. On being asked about the challenges faced by women, she asserts the challenges are the same, be it here or in the Bahamans. She also states that the presence of SME is very dominant in her country as well. Her visit to India at present is absolutely business oriented wherein she intends to meet legal partners and collaborative associates. ', 'Bertha Cooper-Rousseau, Franchise India, Women Entrepreneur, Business', '03:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 3334, 'A', '2012-01-09 17:34:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(312, 'C2luC_tCoKU', NULL, 'Bringing together the women entrepreneurs’ conclave', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Dr. Ekta Saxena owns to her credit if not all, most of it to making the 2nd Women Entrepreneurship conclave an eventful one. She is presently associated with several organizations and heads Indus Business Academy’s Corporate Relations. The entire filtering process and thereafter bringing the best of the women entrepreneur to the podium is her task. She has been in close association with women entrepreneurs for a long time now. The business fraternity can expect other forth coming events on business and women entrepreneurs throughout the year under the management of Dr. Saxena. ', 'Dr.Ekta Saxena, Franchise India, Women Entrepreneur, Business, Indus Business Academy', '03:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 335, 'D', '2012-01-09 17:36:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(313, 'yeT7yjhTWGI', NULL, 'Women providing livelihood with dignity to Women', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Meenu Vadhera is an entrepreneur who has triumphed both as a social entrepreneur and as a women entrepreneur. She has been able to make a prominent forte; the reason being her work is first social deliverable and thereafter a profit making end. Her company Sakha Cabs provides trained women chauffeurs and women drivers in totality providing safer transport to women; the USP of Sakha Cabs is livelihood with dignity. Meenu states the need for such kind of service is so large in India and she states it would be great if other entrepreneurs’ also plan to venture in it.', 'Meenu Vadhera, Franchise India, Women Entrepreneur, Business, Sakha Cabs', '02:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 5461, 'A', '2012-01-09 17:41:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(314, 'w3cCvK29Ulo', NULL, 'Staying healthy the Women Entrepreneur Way', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Dr. Shikha Sharma is a famous celebrity dietician who has made a remarkable place for herself.  A qualified nutritionist she was not happy doing the hospital job she started with. She also witnessed that there could be much more done to what is already happening at the hospital arena. Hence taking this challenge to herself she started of her own nutrition centre which was self funded. SMEs and Women Entrepreneurs’ taking the lead in business is nothing new to her as she denoted with the hard work and dedication levied by them this was ought to be.', 'Dr. Shikha Sharma, Franchise India, Women Entrepreneur, Business', '04:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 5264, 'A', '2012-01-09 17:43:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(315, 'cXW0ILXMnVc', NULL, 'SME first timers at IITF  ', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, ' The India International Trade Fair is one of the biggest events in India; rather it takes to its credit being the biggest event nationally. With all benefiting with this event, the SME sector of India is one which also is all laurels about this ‘Mammoth Event’. Entrepreneur India, spoke with Anil Kathuria, a first timer exhibiting his products in the IITF 2011. The irony being, he has taken part in exhibitions of similar and greater magnitude across the globe but the IITF 2011 was his maiden exhibition in India. He speaks of a time when exhibitions such as PMA and other International events wherein the Indian SME sector is not given much importance, taking this as a challenge he made it a point to take part in all exhibitions globally. Positivity and a bright future was the conclusion by this self-made entrepreneur who has his display outlet in the famous Chandni Chowk of New Delhi. SME has a great future states he and also asserts the MSME Ministry is doing a great job.', 'Anil Kathuria, Franchise India, Entrepreneur, SME, IITF, MSME ', '02:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4995, 'A', '2012-01-10 10:53:47', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(317, 'RY7JmWYgP6M', NULL, 'Union Minister Virbhadra Singh very hopeful on SMEs', 3, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Positive, vibrant and very hopeful is what the Union Minister Virbhadra Singh’s opinion is about the SME sector of India. In an interview with Franchise India he stated that today the SME sector is not dealing with small things but has become a very highly sophisticated sector ; for instance the leather and diamond area. He lauded that the SME sector is one of the best sectors in India and it can be termed as the leading sector and one of the best contributors to the economy of India. The Minister also expressed his thought that though there is an independent bank which has assigned for just the MSME sector i.e., SIDBI; which is not sufficient to meet the requirement of this booming sector. He also cited the example of Korea, which is moving very fast in the SME arena and said that India can learn from other countries and implement in its own way.', 'Virbhadra Singh, Franchise India, MSME, Union Minister', '03:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 72, 'D', '2012-01-10 12:05:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(318, 'zgY_mXaXT7s', NULL, 'Book Launch : \\\'Take Charge\\\' by Franchise India President :Gaurav Marya', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, '\\\" Take Charge \\\" in the words of author Gaurav Marya, President Franchise India. The Father of Indian Franchising.rn', 'Gaurav Marya Franchise India Take Charge Business Enterpreneur', '00.50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 5, 3432, 'A', '2012-01-18 12:50:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(321, 'kHdp5dGr7Vw', NULL, '12th Five Year Plan to boost SME sector : R.K.Mathur, Secretary MSME', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Secretary, MSME , Govt. of India Mr. Radha Krishna Mathur speaking on the National Conference of MSME at the MSME office in New Delhi stated that the ministry  is basically meant for creating an environment that is competitive and adjustable for the SME.Mr. Mathur is very hopeful about the SME sector of India. Speaking on how the SME and the government can work together; he said that unless the problems and concerns of the SME are heard, the ministry would not be able to solve it. The other topics he spoke was on credit and skill, he is optimistic about the upcoming 12th Five Year Plan which he says will bring many good policies for the SME. He also asserted that the ministry will encourage successful entrepreneurs to become business partner institutions’ in providing training and assistance to the SME.', 'Franchise India, RK Mathur, Secretary , MSME, SME, Business , Training , Ministry, Government of India ', '06:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4779, 'A', '2012-01-19 12:08:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(322, 'zstazqQRSqY', NULL, 'Auto Expo 2012', 3, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Over 50 global brands , one lakh visitors a day, around 1500 participants from 23 countries, more than 50 new cars launched and unveiled .Hatchbacks, Sedans, SUVs, ATVs, Electric Vehicles, hybrid cars and concept cars. This isn’t all about the largest Indian Automobile Fair. The 11th Auto Expo 2012 which was held in the city recently was a week-long affair organized by Automotive Component Manufacturers Association of India, Confederation of Indian Industry   and     Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers. Global Giants such as Hyundai, Honda, Volkswagen, Fait, Renault, Audi, Tata, Chevrolet, Maruti Suzuki, Toyota, Mahindra, Skoda and BMW had their dominant presence. Franchise India brings to you the images from the 1st and 2nd day of this biennial International Event.', 'Franchise India, Auto Expo 2012, Biennial Event, International Event, Cars,', '04:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 325, 'D', '2012-01-21 18:31:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(323, 'zstazqQRSqY', NULL, 'Auto Expo 2012', 3, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Over 50 global brands , one lakh visitors a day, around 1500 participants from 23 countries, more than 50 new cars launched and unveiled .Hatchbacks, Sedans, SUVs, ATVs, Electric Vehicles, hybrid cars and concept cars. This isn’t all about the largest Indian Automobile Fair. The 11th Auto Expo 2012 which was held in the city recently was a week-long affair organized by Automotive Component Manufacturers Association of India, Confederation of Indian Industry   and     Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers. Global Giants such as Hyundai, Honda, Volkswagen, Fait, Renault, Audi, Tata, Chevrolet, Maruti Suzuki, Toyota, Mahindra, Skoda and BMW had their dominant presence. Franchise India brings to you the images from the 1st and 2nd day of this biennial International Event.', 'Franchise India, Auto Expo 2012, Biennial Event, International Event, Cars,', '04:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 325, 'D', '2012-01-21 18:36:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
