rtunities most suited for mothers. Actor cum business entrepreneur Shilpa Shetty who has recently become a mother herself was roped in to raise awareness for the need for moms to be in business. The event showcased over 300 mom-friendly business opportunities and was attended by more than 25,000 people.rnrnFranchise India Awards 2012 and Star Retailer Awards are the most credible and prestigious received. Taking the commitments forward, the awards this year acknowledged the best performances in the industry in various categories.', 'franchise business entrepreneur Gaurav Marya, entrepreneur ', '1.34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6305, 'A', '2012-11-27 10:22:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(375, 'DLLIzmcyupo', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress : a sustainable knowledge platform for excellence', 3, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Being a part of Indian Education Congress 2011, Amit is vibrant and very hopeful of the Indian Congress 2012. He stated his organisation has been lucky to be part of this conclave. He recalls his initial start up days, wherein his organisation started as a publishing house and today has emerged in all spheres of education. He asserts during his this journey he has faced challenges and apprehensions which still linger in education in the country at all levels.\\\" In 2011 we came across the education initiative of Franchise India for the first time. We discovered that there is an organisation which is committed and talking about the universe of education. The clarity needed in the system for raising the standards of  deliveries, policy makers, thought leaders , academicians, investors and suppliers all together in one platform for one single cause to look today and to look beyond to achieve what we want is going to be the landscape of education tomorrow”, said Amit. Amit further spoke about multiplicity of regulatory bodies and overlap of regulations laid down by different bodies which leads corruption. There is a complete un-acknowledgement of the role that the private sector can play in it. Amit hopes with the efforts of Franchise India and S. Chand the obstacles such as administrative challenges, corruption and all other hurdles which is obstructing the smooth functioning of education would be addressed and there after taken care in the Education Congress 2012.S. Chand is India\\\'s leading publishing company with unmatched market leadership over seven decades.Bringing people and knowledge together is core to the mission of S. Chand Group and this has translated into Empowering Minds. S. Chand Books have touched three generations of Indian educated community. Today S. Chand needs no introduction. Its continuous commitment and endeavor of publishing quality books and meeting the needs right from primary level books to higher academic books in Engineering, Management, Commerce, Basic Sciences and others has built unmatched equity.', 'Franchise India,Amit Gupta, S Chand, Education, Education Congress 2011', '5.06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 389, 'D', '2012-03-28 17:30:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(379, '3wLB1l_D1ng', NULL, 'Ashok Ganguly at Indian Education Congress 2011', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Ashok Ganguly speaking on the Indian Education Congress 2011 gave an insight of the education system in India and its ramification. He stated the elementary education in India has been categorized from Kindergarten to Cl. VIII; however the scenario in the secondary education is all together different. There are about 97 million students who fall under the 14-18 age groups; Ashok quoted figures from different breakdown of education system which proved the number decreases with the increase of class confirming the efficiency of secondary education in India is very low. The new world order was also opined upon wherein there is inter-dependence and inter-relationship in the education sector because of globalization. ', 'Franchise India Ashok Ganguly Indian Education Congress Education\\\\r\\\\n', '2.58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2807, 'A', '2012-03-30 12:01:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(781, 'YhusVx1UGqM', NULL, 'Sandra Swaroop at Indian Education Congress 2012', 28, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Education Congress 2012 organised by Franchise India & S. Chand', 'Franchise, education, congress, business, entrepreneur, 2012,', '8.26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 355, 'D', '2012-11-26 16:35:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
