(798, 'mTOQGfs6DyQ', NULL, 'Koen Pieters of Burg speaking at Franchise India 2012', 35, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Franchise India 2012, the 10th edition of Asia\\\'s biggest Franchise & Retail exhibition held its Franchise Awards 2012 & Star Retailer Awards 2012 on 4th November, 2012 at Shangri La\\\'s Eros Hotel, New Delhi. The splendid show was attended by the biggest and the most reputed names in the franchise and retail industry. The highlight of the evening was Franchise India\\\'s unique CSR initiative for enabling \\\'Mompreneurship\\\' in India launched by Shilpa Shetty. Story telling by Neelesh Misra, famous for his Yaadon Ka Idiot Box made for an entertaining session at the event.rnrnFranchise Awards 2012 are India\\\'s Topmost Honour in Franchising. Benchmarking excellence, the Awards celebrated and acknowledged contribution to one of India\\\'s most dynamic industries. The winners were those organisations that have shown outstanding business acumen, passion and achievement of franchise businesses and thus achieved sustainable growth across India. They were judged by an independent panel of experts and supported by the Indian Franchise Association (IFA) & Entrepreneur India Advisors. Franchisors, Franchisees, Master Franchisees and Entrepreneurs all over India had applied for the Awards considered to be the industry\\\'s top accolade.rnrnStar Retailer Awards is the only Awards of its kind which celebrates the best in Indian retailing. It is a singular platform for everyone from independent entrepreneurial retailers to the largest supermarket groups. These Awards celebrated the outstanding achievements across the retail fraternity. rnrnThe corporate social responsibility initiative of Franchise India 2012 this year was to launch the \\\'Mompreneur\\\'. The objective was to create an enabling ecosystem that will empower women and get them to draw on their inherent strengths and also overlay business opportunities most suited for mothers. Actor cum business entrepreneur Shilpa Shetty who has recently become a mother herself was roped in to raise awareness for the need for moms to be in business. The event showcased over 300 mom-friendly business opportunities and was attended by more than 25,000 people.rnrnFranchise India Awards 2012 and Star Retailer Awards are the most credible and prestigious received. Taking the commitments forward, the awards this year acknowledged the best performances in the industry in various categories.', 'franchise, business, entrepreneur, conference, congress,awards, Burg', '1.17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 6111, 'A', '2012-11-27 10:24:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(383, 'Mq_DzKKQmJk', NULL, 'Ashwin Raguraman at Entrepreneur India 2011', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on Entrepreneur India 2011, Ashwin spoke about his experience as a part of the Entrepreneur community. He stated he had joined NASCOM at a stage when NASCOM decided to put out this fund to support early stage entrepreneurs, technology entrepreneurs with innovative technology but needed support at the early stage from capital and mentoring perspective. To be able to convert an innovative technology into successful venture business he moved into NASCOM to operationalise the fund and to create it. He headed the innovation initiative at Nascom and he was involved with the fund and the start up community.  He further highlighted the industry and the kind of start up business which his organisation supported. Intellectual property was looked upon as a criterion which was on the priority. It is a great sign that entrepreneurship is starting and kicking in India with the Indian entrepreneur being more innovative enlightened Ashwin.', 'Franchise India, Ashwin Raguraman, Entrepreneur India, Business', '2.37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4178, 'A', '2012-03-31 11:29:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(384, 'YwO4F4OvciQ', NULL, 'Himanshu Gupta: Entrepreneur India 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking to Franchise India at Entrepreneur India 2011, Himanshu Gupta stated he found the functioning of business different in India. Being in the States for 8-10 years, he observed the functioning of business in India was absolutely different. In India he states there is less transparency and there is complexity of transaction, despite all the drawbacks he observed, what is best about the Indian market is that all Indians are working hard to do better. This is where IndiaPlus comes into the picture; any organisation which is looking for expansion or working capital any put forward the business agenda to IndiaPlus. He concluded by saying that there is plenty of money in India, all IndiaPlus is looking for is good entrepreneurs, business plan but people who are honest and are ready to work hard.', 'Franchise India, Himanshu Gupta, IndiaPlus, VC,Seedfund, Investors, Entrepreneur India', '3.41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 3799, 'A', '2012-03-31 11:41:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(774, '19Rw2Ck5G20', NULL, 'Personnel Training : Creating Service Perfection', 27, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Salon Congress 2012', 'franchise business salon entrepreneur', '7.34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2518, 'A', '2012-11-26 13:54:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(775, '6NcxVGnEqWc', NULL, 'Accelerating growth through strategic partnerships - Indian Salon Congress 2012', 27, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Salon Congress 2012', 'franchise salon congress business entrepreneur ', '8.20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1555, 'A', '2012-11-26 13:55:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(389, 'vwc8DegQYj0', NULL, 'Mukund Mohan at Entrepreneur India 2011', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking to Franchise India Mukund Mohan states that he heard about Franchise India and about the conference through a friend and also online when he came across the post of Pavan Vaish. Ever since then Mukund has been associated with Franchise India. Mukund states the difference that he observed at this conference was the quality of people at the panel is extremely good. As he lauded the speakers and panelist brought forward by Franchise India were one who are large players and have created big business entities. With an expert level of panelists the information and learning in this conference was excellent, he concludes with an optimistic note which is also one of the prime criteria of a business i.e., experimenting. As with experiments; innovation happen and failures in business also creates successful ventures.', 'Franchise India, Mukund Mohan, Jivity ', '3.02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4472, 'A', '2012-03-31 13:13:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(390, 'xegBSebEhUY', NULL, 'Om Manchanda at Entrepreneur India 2011', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on Entrepreneur India 2011 Dr. Manchanda appreciated the effort made by Franchise India and said it is a great initiative Franchise India has taken. He stated that he personally believes India as a country requires a lot of entrepreneurs and events like this certainly helps them to think solutions to the problems.  With the growth of entrepreneurship in India amongst the Indian population, this event is definitely going to help India affirmed Dr. Manchanda. Exploring entrepreneurship in India is said there are two most important things when you are looking for speed, every company needs to make sure efficiency does not come in its way. If one is always focused on efficiency speed tends to suffer so one needs to make execution speed is maintained in the earlier years, the resource planning should take place for the end point that one is  planning. If a company wants to grow from 10 Crore - 100 Crore the resources needs to be in place, because if the resources are not in place the organisation will fumble somewhere.', 'Franchise India, Mukund Mohan, Entrepreneur India, Business', '1.58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3833, 'A', '2012-03-31 13:22:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(391, 'WSBJCwNEPKc', NULL, 'Padmaja Ruparel at Entrepreneur India 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Padmaja Ruparel has a wide range of experience in starting and growing organizations related to IT, entrepreneurship & investing. Padmaja was part of the key team of Xansa India Ltd. Through the years, she moved across various roles in the company before exiting as Vice President -- Corporate Communications. While in Xansa, she built the communications, media and advertising strategy of the company in India. She is the President of Indian Angel Network (IAN), India\\\'s first and now the largest group of business angels, comprising the who\\\'s who of successful entrepreneurs and dynamic CEOs from India and overseas.', 'Franchise India, Padmaja Ruparel , Entrepreneur', '1.24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 129, 'D', '2012-03-31 13:25:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(392, 'IkskbECmp-U', NULL, 'Pavan Vaish at Entrepreneur India 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Pavan Vaish is currently the Global Chief Operating Officer & Board Member at UnitedLex Corporation; he earlier was the CEO at IBM Daksh Business Process Services and before that Director at Quadrant Infotech. A born entrepreneur with his past experience and education that of Harvard Business School, Stanford University and Carnegie Mellon University, he is one an independent business think tank of the country.\\r\\n', 'Franchise India, Pavan Vaish, IBM Daksh, Entrepreneur India', '2.23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 94, 'D', '2012-03-31 13:31:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(393, 'jTU7D4fcZ24', NULL, 'Prakash Kumar at Entrepreneur India 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking at Entrepreneur India 2011, Prakash Kumar stated he found the event very interesting wherein the audience was very inquisitive. He was thrilled to see such an audience which wanted to learn so much. Despite his presentation being over for more than an hour the audiences were still asking questions to Prakash about various topics and concerns. Prakash further spoke on the functioning of SIDBI and the various schemes offered by it. He said that the business models are definitely important and track record is important wherein the banks would look for the balance sheet and IT returns and CIBEL score for the last three years, these details are of prime importance to secure a loan stated Prakash. The project which the bank would fund would be one which is highly viable; it need not be one with high growth and high risk however it should be one which is scalable. Overall the credit worthiness and the quantum of credit which the bank can trust the borrower should be one which has been handled with care.', 'Prakash Kumar, Franchise India, SIDBI, Loan, Banking, Credit', '4.07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 190, 'D', '2012-03-31 13:33:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(394, 'qCRYiLDr6GQ', NULL, 'Pramoud Rao at Entrepreneur India 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on Entrepreneur India 2011 Pramoud Rao observed a lot of curiosity in the event about what the audiences wanted to do in their lives. He states times have changed, people have changed and environments have changed. He asserted when he looks at the current crop of entrepreneurs and the so called entrepreneurs there is a huge difference in what they were and what he and his contemporaries were. He highlighted the negative trend in the existing environment which could be both good and bad for the aspiring entrepreneurs : one such reason is information overload, the economic scenario is another area which he discussed about as the functioning of business is different now as earlier as then it was a closed economy. His message to the aspiring young youth of India who have taken entrepreneurship as a career, if there is conviction and if one loves the idea, and if one believes the dream one should chase the dream. Height of ambition and depth of conviction and his breadth of confidence is what makes one an entrepreneur concluded Pramoud.', 'Franchise India, Pramoud Rao, Zicom Electronic Security System, Entrepreneur India, Business ', '3.44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 7, 4433, 'A', '2012-03-31 13:50:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(395, 'Ph-o6j12pxY', NULL, 'Rajiv Bajaj at Entrepreneur India 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Rajiv Bajaj speaking on Entrepreneur India 2011 stated, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" My role in the Board is particularly to spread out the message of Entrepreneurs Organisation (EO is company run by Bajaj Group) through seminars such Entrepreneur India 2011. EO looks for good ideas and validation of those ideas and the scalability of the idea. As a financer I manage the the budge of the organisation and work with various sponsors. Being a part of Bajaj Capital and second generation entrepreneur, I am very comfortable in such environment of a seminar. Each generation of entrepreneurs have different characteristics, in every talk, every interaction you pick up ideas, community of likeminded people. When I joined the organisation it was from a company try and builds an institution, from a 100 odd people to a 500 people company. Today we are a 3500 company; I wanted to build an institution which further realises the scale of vision to achieve.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"', 'Franchise India, Rajiv Bajaj, Entrepreneur India, Business', '2.42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 146, 'D', '2012-03-31 14:26:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(396, 'p05-eQKsd78', NULL, 'S. Venkat at Entrepreneur India 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on Entrepreneur India 2011 S. Venkat on being asked about the role government in India said that government plays an important role wherein it provides information, data and policy support. The government also provides subsidy and relaxation in International Events and Trade Fairs. The role of Wealth Tree is to create a business stratergy for the exporting companies primarily those which fall under micro-small and medium category and works in the actual implementation of the strategy. His word of advice to the aspiring entrepreneur was not to take any short cuts. S. Venkat also shared important information about the export scenario of India.', 'Franchise India, S.Venkat, Wealth Tree Partners  \"Entrepreneur (Profession)\" Business', '5.57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 7, 3688, 'A', '2012-03-31 16:05:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(848, '5D5yFqJ7ZsM', NULL, 'DMS : In-Store Asia 2012', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'In store Asia 2012, is an annual Retail Design event which was held at FRDC sweeping major design awards at Pragati Maidan, New Delhi on 17th Feb 2012\\r\\n \\r\\nIn-Store Asia Expo has grown by 60%, and with Indian retail experiencing unprecedented growth, it is expected to grow tremendously further on. As with every passing day there are a million needs that crop up in the retail solutions and services space. The Expo at In-Store Asia is the platform where all the needs of brands and retailers, find an answer and an opportunity where exhibitors bag businesses that help them take the huge leap.\\r\\n \\r\\nThe Expo at In-Store Asia is of world-class, state-of-the-art retail solutions, services, technologies and ideas come together. It promises a holistic experience with its five distinct pavilions -- Absolute POP, Retail Signs, VM & Store Fix, Dynamic Environments and Designers Den. Each of these pavilions offers a comprehensive range of solutions and expertise. Alongside the five pavilions is the material lounge that showcases the latest and the best in the field of materials.\\r\\nThis year 2012, the expo witnessed 3500 visitors, 1800 sq. mt. of Expo space and more than 80 exhibitors of which 40% were new participants.', 'Franchise, business, entrepreneur, In-Store Asia 2012, 2012, Pragati Maidan,', '3.34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3792, 'A', '2012-11-28 17:24:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(879, 'BjEmxzrmP7c', NULL, 'Aloke Banerjee at Franchise India 2012', 3, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Franchise India 2012, the 10th edition of Asia\'s biggest Franchise & Retail exhibition held its Franchise Awards 2012 & Star Retailer Awards 2012 on 4th November, 2012 at Shangri La\'s Eros Hotel, New Delhi. The splendid show was attended by the biggest and the most reputed names in the franchise and retail industry. The highlight of the evening was Franchise India\'s unique CSR initiative for enabling \'Mompreneurship\' in India launched by Shilpa Shetty. Story telling by Neelesh Misra, famous for his Yaadon Ka Idiot Box made for an entertaining session at the event.\r\n\r\nFranchise Awards 2012 are India\'s Topmost Honour in Franchising. Benchmarking excellence, the Awards celebrated and acknowledged contribution to one of India\'s most dynamic industries. The winners were those organisations that have shown outstanding business acumen, passion and achievement of franchise businesses and thus achieved sustainable growth across India. They were judged by an independent panel of experts and supported by the Indian Franchise Association (IFA) & Entrepreneur India Advisors. Franchisors, Franchisees, Master Franchisees and Entrepreneurs all over India had applied for the Awards considered to be the industry\'s top accolade.\r\n\r\nStar Retailer Awards is the only Awards of its kind which celebrates the best in Indian retailing. It is a singular platform for everyone from independent entrepreneurial retailers to the largest supermarket groups. These Awards celebrated the outstanding achievements across the retail fraternity. \r\n\r\nThe corporate social responsibility initiative of Franchise India 2012 this year was to launch the \'Mompreneur\'. The objective was to create an enabling ecosystem that will empower women and get them to draw on their inherent strengths and also overlay business opportunities most suited for mothers. Actor cum business entrepreneur Shilpa Shetty who has recently become a mother herself was roped in to raise awareness for the need for moms to be in business. The event showcased over 300 mom-friendly business opportunities and was attended by more than 25,000 people.\r\n\r\nFranchise India Awards 2012 and Star Retailer Awards are the most credible and prestigious received. Taking the commitments forward, the awards this year acknowledged the best performances in the industry in various categories.', 'franchise, entrepreneur, ', '6.19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5545, 'A', '2012-12-07 11:10:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(399, '1yFBKBHCsFo', NULL, 'Sam Chopra at Entrepreneur India 2011', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on Entrepreneur India 2011 Sam Chopra stated he had a fantastic time in the conclave, as the conference was an exciting one with great participation, and a great foundation of networking event. He shared his own experience as to how he became an entrepreneur, he claimed his story to be one which was funny however with the changing time also became the backbone and became an inspiring one. He says how he started his business with just a manual which he got in return with the collaboration with Remax. He also spoke about the pros and cons of starting a business venture with a foreign conglomerate as his experience he did not receive much support and overall Remax India was started by he and his team. Entrepreneurial spirit is doing best with the available resources and doing it right concluded Sam.', 'Franchise India, Sam Chopra, Remax India, Entrepreneur, Business ', '03.04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 3742, 'A', '2012-03-31 16:33:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(400, 'dTUZmpJ8ArE', NULL, 'Sankar Chakraborti at Entrepreneur India 2011', 30, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Speaking on Entrepreneur India conclave Sankar stated it is a very good platform and this was where the leaders of tomorrow is to be found. The conference was thronged with new ideas, concepts and people from all the different industries of the business entity. Sankar further spoke about the functioning of CRISIL, where CRISIL has covered 30,000 SME’s under SME rating, this itself states it has a great level of pro-activeness at the players’ part to come forward and to take effective part in business creation. Rating process and how rating and the standardization and certification from rating companies’ helps the smooth functioning of the SME sector were other areas Sankar spoke about.', 'Franchise India, CRISIL, Sankar Chakraboti, Entrepreneur India, Business', '4.07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 9, 4016, 'A', '2012-03-31 16:42:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(401, 'QLKE2rPRAoc', NULL, 'Shri Virbhadra Singh, Union Minister at the Entrepreneur India Congress 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Union Minister MSME, Virbhadra Singh at Entrepreneur India 2011 stated it is not only the foreign countries but also Indian countries which are known for best practices. He said that we have to learn the best practices and learn new practices. There are so many companies in India which have foreign participation, there are companies in India which are completely foreign and there are companies which have a share in the company as well or have some amount of participation, all of these are doing very well. The Union Minister also spoke about the various location and area concern of the companies, if certain companies are in a particular area the government helps in the setting of the tools and machinery in that particular area. The minister further opined that each unit doesn\\\'t have to set up their own unit and machines and have a common use of the machines so that it cut down on the cost and increases the efficiency.', 'Franchise India, SME, MSME Shri Virbhadra Singh, Union Minister  Entrepreneur India Congress 2011 Business', '1.29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 155, 'D', '2012-03-31 16:45:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(402, 'faXirUmThcU ', NULL, 'Aloke Bajpai at Entrepreneur India 2011', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Bajpai ', 'Franchise India, Aloke Bajpai, Entrepreneur India 2011, Business', '2.51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 69, 'D', '2012-03-31 16:53:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
