ilers are moving to the Omni-channel, which represents the seamless customer experience across all available shopping channels, using a combination of mobile, social networks, brick-and mortar, online portal and whatever innovative channel one can integrate into the mix. A survey of around 500 people in India through which it is found that 24 per cent Indians are shop online once a month and the most picked products by them is apparel. Also, an average Indian is spending Rs 500 to Rs 2000 in one go. This range is considered to be the appropriate price range to take the advantage of free shipping, coupons and deals available. The maximum online buying is of apparels which account for 17 per cent of the online market. Accessories have emerged as the second biggest product category with 15 per cent market share. The other categories which are doing well are consumer durables with 13 per cent, books with 12 per cent, jewellery with 11 per cent, footwear with 10 per cent, beauty and health care with 8 per cent, home & furnishing with 7 per cent and, gifts & flowers with 5 percent.', 'franchise, business, entrepreneur ', '5.35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 10727, 'A', '2013-03-08 17:41:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1040, 'ecVdUNF9f9s', NULL, 'Leading eRetail sectors in India and where they are headed ', 4, '', NULL, '', 22, 'Franchise India - Asia\\\\\\\'s largest integrated franchise solution company held the annual Indian e-Retail Congress 2013 at The Claridges, Surajkund on 15th & 16th February 2013. This event provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading e-Retailers and Retailers and an understanding around how e-retail is re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.\\r\\nThe first day\\\\\\\'s sessions focused on introducing retail reinvention for an omni channel world with a welcome address by Ms. Ritu Marya-Editor in Chief, Retailer, Franchise India Holdings Ltd followed by speakers Ajit Joshi, Croma, Ambareesh Murty, Pepperfry.com and the Ministry of IT. The changing consumer & the anatomy of his purchase were discussed by Param Parmeswaran, Sulekha.com, Salil Kumar, Bagit Today and Nitin Bawankule, Google. Nikhil Raghavan, Bain Capital, Promod, Norwest Ventures, Mukul Arora, SAIF Partners, Prajakt Raut, Hatch and Anirudh Suri, India Internet Group (Advisors) pondered over where the money banks are rolling in retail. Subhendu Roy, AT Kearney, Balaji Reddipalli, Vice President Supply Chain & Commercial-- Pepperfry.com, Dr.Ing. Dietmar Jobst, DCSE and Sanjay Sethi, Shopclues spoke about the Omni channel Retail Supply Chain. The importance of the brand in the face of winning the price war was explored by Asif Merchant, Catwalk Worldwide, Mahesh Shah, Home Centre Lifestyle International, V D Wadhwa, Timex, Ankur Warikoo, GroupOn(Crazeal), Jaideep Rathore, DiGiworld and Rajiv Bajaj, Fila India. The day concluded with Ajay Kelkar, Hansa Cequity holding forth on why consumer intelligence is important.\\r\\nThe Congress witnessed the launch of e-Retail report 2013 which highlighted few concrete inputs on e-retail industry like Indian e-Retail is surging at the rate of 40 per cent and will reach Rs 7200 Crore mark by 2015. Indian retailers are moving to the Omni-channel, which represents the seamless customer experience across all available shopping channels, using a combination of mobile, social networks, brick-and mortar, online portal and whatever innovative channel one can integrate into the mix. A survey of around 500 people in India through which it is found that 24 per cent Indians are shop online once a month and the most picked products by them is apparel. Also, an average Indian is spending Rs 500 to Rs 2000 in one go. This range is considered to be the appropriate price range to take the advantage of free shipping, coupons and deals available. The maximum online buying is of apparels which account for 17 per cent of the online market. Accessories have emerged as the second biggest product category with 15 per cent market share. The other categories which are doing well are consumer durables with 13 per cent, books with 12 per cent, jewellery with 11 per cent, footwear with 10 per cent, beauty and health care with 8 per cent, home & furnishing with 7 per cent and, gifts & flowers with 5 percent.', 'franchise, business, entrepreneur ', '25.28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 10130, 'A', '2013-03-08 17:42:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(853, 'jCkuxKuj0Vg', NULL, '\\\'Direct sales a 150 billion USD business globally\\\' : Momir Popovic at Franchise India 2012', 3, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Franchise India 2012, the 10th edition of Asia\\\'s biggest Franchise & Retail exhibition held its Franchise Awards 2012 & Star Retailer Awards 2012 on 4th November, 2012 at Shangri La\\\'s Eros Hotel, New Delhi. The splendid show was attended by the biggest and the most reputed names in the franchise and retail industry. The highlight of the evening was Franchise India\\\'s unique CSR initiative for enabling \\\'Mompreneurship\\\' in India launched by Shilpa Shetty. Story telling by Neelesh Misra, famous for his Yaadon Ka Idiot Box made for an entertaining session at the event.\\r\\n\\r\\nFranchise Awards 2012 are India\\\'s Topmost Honour in Franchising. Benchmarking excellence, the Awards celebrated and acknowledged contribution to one of India\\\'s most dynamic industries. The winners were those organisations that have shown outstanding business acumen, passion and achievement of franchise businesses and thus achieved sustainable growth across India. They were judged by an independent panel of experts and supported by the Indian Franchise Association (IFA) & Entrepreneur India Advisors. Franchisors, Franchisees, Master Franchisees and Entrepreneurs all over India had applied for the Awards considered to be the industry\\\'s top accolade.\\r\\n\\r\\nStar Retailer Awards is the only Awards of its kind which celebrates the best in Indian retailing. It is a singular platform for everyone from independent entrepreneurial retailers to the largest supermarket groups. These Awards celebrated the outstanding achievements across the retail fraternity. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe corporate social responsibility initiative of Franchise India 2012 this year was to launch the \\\'Mompreneur\\\'. The objective was to create an enabling ecosystem that will empower women and get them to draw on their inherent strengths and also overlay business opportunities most suited for mothers. Actor cum business entrepreneur Shilpa Shetty who has recently become a mother herself was roped in to raise awareness for the need for moms to be in business. The event showcased over 300 mom-friendly business opportunities and was attended by more than 25,000 people.\\r\\n\\r\\nFranchise India Awards 2012 and Star Retailer Awards are the most credible and prestigious received. Taking the commitments forward, the awards this year acknowledged the best performances in the industry in various categories.', 'India Gets Business, A business for every Indian, Franchise, business, entrepreneur, awards, congress, 2012, Franchise India 2012, India, MSME, MNC, ', '8.41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6181, 'A', '2012-11-28 18:00:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
