(1232, 'DW0l1ER86x8', NULL, 'Consumer loyalty is changing very fast: How to keep product up head with time', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'A masterclass on building vibrant relationships in the market by dancing with the customer. We have for too long measured customer impact in terms of demographics and market share. We now need to focus deeper into the impact we make in the lives of individual customers. This calls for a more intimate knowledge of our customer.rnThere is no marketing or research agency that can deliver this knowledge to us, as experts focus too much on the numbers game, abstract averages and generic types. We need to directly enter into a conversation with our customers, to learn from them more about themselves, so we can make that value offering they want and need. Or better still invite them to design what they want! We need to do the tango with our customer!rnIt Takes Two to Tango builds a case for how we have emerged into a customer dominated, shape-shifting world. Building customer connect needs to be seen as investing into our customers as the most valuable asset of an enterprise.rnIt Takes Two to Tango shows how the route to building customer equity is only through delighting our customers with outstanding customer experience.rnIt Takes Two to Tango is about how we need to, and can, master the management of innovation.rnIt Takes Two to Tango talks about building the organisation as an organic ecosystem in which key members of the team are empowered to fulfil the entrepreneurial task of leading the tango with customers.rnIt Takes Two to Tango amends the famous Ogilvy quote to make it more relevant today: “The customer is not your spouse; she is your boss!”', 'franchise, business, ', '5.36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5028, 'A', '2013-05-22 12:05:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
