(1304, 'ZPhnZHYajDk', NULL, 'SIDBI : National Conference on Credit Flow to MSMEs ', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'A National Conference on Credit Flow to MSMEs & Employment Generation, organized by All India Confederation of Small and Micro Industries Associations (AICOSMIA), was held in New Delhi on 24th July 2013.  Shri Madhav Lal, IAS, Secretary, Ministry of Micro, Small & Medium Enterprises, was the Chief Guest.  In his address to the participants he stated that there is serious concern to ensure smooth and easy access of credit to MSMEs and the Government has initiated a number of measures in this regard.  Almost all credit related recommendations of the Task Force on MSME were implemented and it was a matter of satisfaction that in the recent years there was increase in both quantum and share of credit to MSE sector in total adjusted net banking credit.  Government has also initiated a number of schemes for employment generation and their functions are being monitored. He reaffirmed He reaffirmed that MSME Ministry would continue to redouble its effort to push growth and provide enough support to the sector for growth and diversification. He further  stated that he had taken note of the various points made by the participants and would give due consideration on them.  rnrnHighlighting on the purpose of setting up Small Industries Development Bank as a refinancing  institution for the support of MSEs, he outlined in brief the details of some of packages e..g. SIDBI Venture Capital, Risk Capital Fund, Energy Efficiency fund, financing of receivables by way of bill discounting and Syndicate Banking Scheme for promotion of entrepreneurship by addressing the needs of existing and budding entrepreneurs and also making available franchise opportunities.  Referring to Credit Guarantee Trust Fund Scheme, it was stated  that the scheme provided guarantee cover of up to 85% on collateral-free credit facility extended by lending institutions to new and existing MSEs for loans up to Rs.100 lakh. rnrnDwelling at length on the various services of NSIC, Shri Shri Yashbir Singh from MSIC mentioned that as regards flow of credit to MSMEs and job creation, NSIC operated a number of schemes such as credit against raw material procurement; payment of 70 per cent immediately on supplies against tender initiated through NSIC in addition to its flagship schemes of credit rating and subsidy of 25 per cent of payment made in this regard.  He also stated that NSIC had signed MOUs with a number of commercial banks in India for financing credit to MSMEs under its bank tie up schemes.  NSIC also impart training in entrepreneurship and also started a new initiative by entering into franchisee arrangements for helping unemployed people to set up new small business enterprises.  rnrnOfficials from Bank of Baroda, Syndicate Bank, PNB, SBI, referred to the various packages operated by them to provide credit to micro, small and medium enterprises.  Shri Josh from ESIC gave details of various ESIC schemes for the benefit of employees in a MSME unit.  He explained in detail the provision of cash less treatment facility to employees and their dependants.  Some of the delegates refereed to procedural problems with DGS&D; need for encouragement to MSEs to compete with competitors like China, scaling up exemption limit from Rs. 1.5 crore to atleast Rs. 3 crores, enhancing time limit for declaration as NPA from 3 months to minimum one year, anomaly in Service Tax, etc.  Strong references were also made for strengthening industrial associations like AICOSMIA to support R & D, Innnovation and quality upgradation by MSMEs for help carving a niche in the emerging competitive international environment.rnrnIn his welcome address at the beginning, Shri Sudarshan Sareen, National President, AICOSMIA, strongly stressed upon the imperative needs to ensure easy and affordable credit to MSMEs and give them all encouragement to create job opportunities since MSMEs are known for their employment generation potential and contribution to economic development of the country.rn                                   rn                                                                                               ', 'franchise, business, entrepreneur, ', '6.13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 8070, 'A', '2013-08-09 15:10:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
