(1418, 'THSuUUNPnVA', NULL, 'Franchise India Awards 2013 - Part I', 1, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Franchise India Awards 2013 was held on October 20th 2013 in New Delhi. The splendid show was attended by the biggest and the most reputed names in the franchise and retail industry. rnrnFranchise Awards 2013 are India\\\\\\\'s Topmost Honour in Franchising. Bench marking excellence, the Awards celebrated and acknowledged contribution to one of India\\\\\\\'s most dynamic industries. rnrnThe winners were those organisations that have shown outstanding business acumen, passion and achievement of franchise businesses and thus achieved sustainable growth across India. They were judged by an independent panel of experts and supported by the Indian Franchise Association (IFA) & Entrepreneur India Advisors. Franchisors, Franchisees, Master Franchisees and Entrepreneurs all over India had applied for the Awards considered to be the industry\\\\\\\'s top accolade. Star Retailer Awards is the only Awards of its kind which celebrates the best in Indian retailing. It is a singular platform for everyone from independent entrepreneurial retailers to the largest supermarket groups. These Awards celebrated the outstanding achievements across the retail fraternity.rnrn Franchise India Awards 2013 and Star Retailer Awards are the most credible and prestigious received. Taking the commitments forward, the awards this year acknowledged the best performances in the industry in various categories.', 'franchise, business, entrepreneur, awards, conference, exhibition,', '17.02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 4709, 'A', '2013-10-28 10:40:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1419, 'dGIby2JEeyc', NULL, 'Kiran Mazumdar-Shaw -Ineffective regulatory is deterring entrepreneurship in Bio-Tech sector', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Kiran Mazumdar-Shaw  is an Indian entrepreneur. She is the chairman & managing director of Biocon Limited a biotechnology company based in Bengaluru, India. rnShe is on the Forbes list of the world\\\\\\\'s 100 most powerful women and the Financial Times\\\\\\\' top 50 women in business list.', 'entrepreneur, business, Biocon', '1.47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 4816, 'A', '2013-11-13 13:45:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1420, 'AIve_nmF1pk', NULL, 'Believe in your Idea and go for it - Annu Grover of Nurturing Green ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Annu Grover is a first generation entrepreneur who has proved Innovation is indeed the buzz word today in the fast changing and evolving Indian economy.rnrnCurrently holds the position of Green Evangelist- MD, Nurturing Green and Founder & President EYEC-Empowerment of Youth for Environment Conservation', 'entrepreneur, business, ', '2.28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3992, 'A', '2013-11-13 13:47:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1421, 'Vff7tneNtLY', NULL, 'Vinod Khosla - Mobile technology to play a big role in education, especially rural education.', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Vinod Khosla is an Indian-American businessman and venture capitalist. Khosla was one of the co-founders of Sun Microsystems, and served as its first CEO and Chairman in the early 1980s. In 1986, he became a general partner of the venture capital firm Kleiner Perkins Caufield & Byers, where he remained through the early 2000s. In 2004 Khosla formed his own firm, Khosla Ventures, which focused on venture investments in various technology sectors, most notably clean technology.rnHe is a strong supporter of clean technology and said \\\\\\\"If it doesn\\\\\\\'t scale, it doesn\\\\\\\'t matter. Most of what we talk about today–hybrid, biodiesel, ethanol, solar photovoltaics, geothermal–I believe are irrelevant to the scale of the problem.\\\\\\\"', 'business, entrepreneur, mobile , technology, Vinod, Khosla, Vinod Khosla,', '1.13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 3, 6813, 'A', '2013-11-13 14:32:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
