(1619, '4u73bt4Pv2Q', NULL, 'Shailesh Chaturvedi speaking on brands and experiences with it', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Shailesh Chaturvedi, CEO and Director, Tommy Hilfiger Apparels India shares his views on reality of retail.besides, he also spoke about the development of premium brands and his experiences with the industry. ', 'Indian retail congress, retail industry, economy, growth, brands, Shailesh Chaturvedi          ', '07:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2042, 'A', '2015-02-05 09:15:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1620, 'NOiTvBAItJ0', NULL, 'Manish Mandhana on reality of retail ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Speaking at the Indian retail congress, Manish Mandhana Joint MD, Mandhana Industries shares his valuable knowledge on retail and brands.', 'Indian retail congress, retail industry, economy, growth, brands, Manish Mandhana', '06:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1844, 'A', '2015-02-05 09:16:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1621, 'TvG9VasdC7A', NULL, 'Bimal Sachdeva on innovation for growth ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Indian retail congress, retail industry, economy, growth, Bimal Sachdeva', 'Bimal Sachdeva, Chief Operating Officer - APAC, Dynamic Vertical Solutions shares his views on business and profitability, ensuring enterprise and strategic wins, channel management, and running customer loyalty development & enhancement programs.', '07:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1978, 'A', '2015-02-05 09:19:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1622, 'yQMxnxtVUPI', NULL, 'Vikram Raizada of luxury retail', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Vikram Raizada, Executive Director & Chief Executive Officer, Tara Jewels shares his views on the changing face of luxury retail industry and how Indian market is adapting the changes.', 'Indian retail congress, retail industry, economy, growth, luxury retail, Tara Jewels', '08:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3761, 'A', '2015-02-05 09:20:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1623, 'hrsBBuY4d0c', NULL, 'Sukanya Dutta Roy on changing face of luxury retail', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Sukanya Dutta Roy, Managing Director-Consumer Goods Business, Swarovski India sharing her expertise in merchandising and retail operations management. She also shared her views on changing face of luxury retail.', 'Indian retail congress, retail industry, economy, growth, luxury retail, Sukanya Dutta Roy', '04:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4462, 'A', '2015-02-05 09:21:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1624, 'N7WaWPUfS54', NULL, 'Pradeep Hirani on fashion and luxury retail', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Pradeep Hirani, Chairman, Kimaya Fashions shares his impeccable business acumen and entrepreneurial experience of fashion and luxury industry during the Indian Retail Congress 2014.', 'Indian retail congress, retail industry, economy, growth, luxury retail, Pradeep Hirani', '07:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3978, 'A', '2015-02-05 09:21:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1625, 'G4z-x0sxD68', NULL, 'Soigne Kothari on luxury retail ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Soigne Kothari Founder & President, Soigne K expresses her ideas on retail and luxury industry during the Indian retail congress.', 'Indian retail congress, retail industry, economy, growth, luxury retail, Soigne Kothari', '06:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3260, 'A', '2015-02-05 09:24:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1626, 'CnIsAlIEnyc', NULL, 'Contribution of MSME in the Indian economy: Madhav Lal at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'A pass out of St. Stephens College, Delhi University and Masters from John F. Kennedy School of Government, Harvard University in Public Administration, Madhav Lal is a career civil servant and joined the Indian Administrative Service in 1977.\r\nHe was appointed as Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry of Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises in February 2013 after his stint as Additional Secretary & Development Commissioner from 2008 to 2011. Concurrently, he is also a Director, of National Skill Development Corporation. He has served in the Department of Economic Affairs (Ministry of Finance) as Deputy Secretary from 1984 to 1988, and as Member (Finance and Administration) in the National Highways Authority of India from 1997 to 2000. \r\nWhile speaking on the on the flagship show, Franchise India 2014, Madhav Lal, IAS, Secretary, MSME (Chief Guest) discussed about the significance of SMEs and its contribution towards the Indian economy.', 'MSMEs, Madhav Lal, Indian economy, National Skill Development Corporation, Harvard University', '08:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 7322, 'A', '2015-02-05 10:33:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1627, 'ysEHAFkk4dw', NULL, 'How angel investors work: Sunil K Goyal from YourNest Angel Fund at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Sunil K Goyal currently runs YourNest Angel Fund, an early stage venture fund he conceptualized and founded in 2011. Prior to this Sunil has won recognition for playing instrumental roles in well-known business like Bharti Group & Dabur. \r\n\r\nSunil is an active member of TiE and a former member of Indian Angel Network & Mumbai Angels. He has led investments in diverse sectors. His passion for early stage ventures has led him to invest in 9 start-ups on his own, before he set-up YourNest, which plans to invest in 10-12 start-ups over the next few months. \r\nSunil is also qualified as a Financial Analyst, Business Economist, and Cost Accountant. While speaking on the on the flagship show, Franchise India 2014, Sunil K Goyal, Founder & Chief Executive Officer, YourNest shared the in depth detail of how angel investors work. ', 'YourNest Angel Fund, angel investors, venture fund, start-ups, Indian Angel Network, Bharti Group, Dabur.', '12:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 5534, 'A', '2015-02-05 10:34:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1628, 'JmnIRivTkYc', NULL, 'Angel investors play multiple roles for start-ups, said Padmaja Ruparel, President, Indian Angel Network at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Padmaja Ruparel is the President of Indian Angel Network (IAN), Indias first and Asias largest group of business angels, comprising the who is who of successful entrepreneurs and dynamic CEOs from India and overseas. \r\n\r\nRuparel built IAN from inception, which over five years has over 170 investors with a portfolio of 25 companies across multiple sectors and geographies. With an experience of over 25 years, Ruparel has been a key player in the entrepreneurial eco system of India. She operationalised the TiE Delhi chapter and has been the key in reviving the Indian Venture Capital Association and till March 2011, she was the CFO of the organisation. \r\n\r\nWhile speaking on the on the flagship show, Franchise India 2014, Padmaja Ruparel, President, Indian Angel Network discussed that how angel investors empower early stage companies with the money, advises and mentorship.', 'Indian Angel Network, entrepreneurs, incubator, TiE Delhi, Indian Venture Capital Association   ', '25:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 3451, 'A', '2015-02-05 10:36:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1629, 'PaIbN4_37RY', NULL, 'Crowd funding helps 1M biz ideas in 3 years, said Satish Kataria, Founder, Catapooolt at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Satish is the co-founder of Catapooolt and brings with him more than 14 years of experience across various domains including public relations, brand management, investor relations and fund management. Some of his unique achievements include pioneering Crowd Funding in India through Springboard Ventures in partnership with Grow VC International and was also involved with enabling start-ups through events, mentorship and fund support. \r\n\r\nWhile speaking on the on the flagship show, Franchise India 2014, Satish Kataria, Founder, Catapooolt shared that how crowd funding has helped one million business ideas to take ten million dollars fund in a span of just three years. ', 'Catapooolt, investors, funds, venture capital, crowd funding, start-ups  ', '07:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3793, 'A', '2015-02-05 10:37:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1630, 'FecRDNtwBPc', NULL, 'Rod Young, MD & Conference Chairman, DC Strategy, Australia at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Rod has over 30 years experience in franchising, licensing and business development in Australia, Europe, China, South East Asia, India and the United States and is considered one of the worlds leading franchise consultants. He currently serves as Chairman of Hairhouse Warehouse (Australian Franchisor of the Year 2011), and is the Executive Chairman and Global CEO of Cartridge World and serves on the Board of several national and international companies.\r\nA recognised authority in the area of franchising and business development, Rod has contributed extensively to major media including television, radio and press as well as being a regular speaker at seminars and conferences in Australia, the United States, China, India and Asia. While speaking at the Franchise India 2014, Rod Young, MD & Conference Chairman, DC Strategy, Australia shared his views on maximising the economic power of SMEs and making India an easier place to do business.', 'SMEs, franchisor, Australia, US, China, India, Cartridge World ', '11:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 4338, 'A', '2015-02-05 16:13:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1631, 'Q21WKSitNQo', NULL, 'How to build a sustainable educational business model: Rennu Dhillon, Founder, Genius Kids Inc & Genius Kids Development Inc at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Rennu Dhillon, DSc., born & brought up Kenya, East Africa and completed education in England, has been described as a woman of many talents. A well know Bay Area resident & community activist, Rennu has been in the United States since 1986. Her education includes a Bachelor of Science (Hons) Pharmacy & Doctorate of Science in Natural Sciences. \r\nShe is the founder of Genius Kids, recognized as the Harvard of Early Learning, is now a national franchise with over 16 locations in California, and scheduled to have over 30 locations in various parts of the country and world by 2015. Rennu believes that everyone is born a Genius and as educators and parents, it is our responsibility to Awaken the Inner Genius in our kids. While speaking at the Franchise India 2014, Rennu Dhillon, Founder, Genius Kids Inc & Genius Kids Development discussed about building a sustainable educational business model in the early education.', 'Genius Kids, early Learning, natural sciences, franchise, education ', '11:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6619, 'A', '2015-02-05 16:15:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1632, 'DTMS4GyKavY', NULL, 'Raman Bajaj, Managing Director, Educomp Child Care Private Limited at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Raman started his career as a software engineer with Sapient Corporation. He left Sapient to pursue his MBA from IIM Lucknow where he secured the top Investment Banking job with HSBC in London. Over the next 4 years, he worked in Investment Banking roles at HSBC and at Lazard, focusing on Financial Advisory, Business Restructuring and cross-border M&A transactions.\r\nIn 2008, he left Investment Banking and London, to return to India to work in the Education space. He joined Educomp senior management as Vice President of Corporate Affairs to focus on Corporate Strategy, Joint Ventures & Alliances, New Business Development and Investor Relations. He has been with Educomp for 6 years now and in June 2013, he was made Managing Director of Educomp Childcare Pvt Ltd, Educomps preschool division. Raman Bajaj, MD, Educomp Child Care Private Limited at Franchise Indi 2014 said that a global entrepreneurship monitor study conducted by GEM and Harvard Business Review revealed that across the world, 30 per cent of all businesses are currently being owned and managed by women. ', 'Educomp Child Care, IIM Lucknow, HSBC, education space, investor relations  ', '13:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 8052, 'A', '2015-02-05 16:16:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1633, 'QiLPx6hsTC0', NULL, 'Emphasizing the power of entrepreneurship in India: Rajnish Goenka, Chairman, Tobu Cycles at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Rajnish Goenka is the chairman of TOBU CYCLES GROUP. Beginning from scratch &ndash; he created a successful business Empire &ndash; spread over in USA, Dubai, China & India and his business activities includes bicycles, metal scraps, printing, packing, Promotions & real estate. He has intensively travelled across the globe.\r\nHe is actively involved in promoting Micro and Small enterprises in India by working with various Govt. Ministries and other bodies who are interested in the MSME welfare and growth and presently he is the Chairman and National Convenor of BJP Micro and Small Industry Cell. Rajnish Goenka, Chairman, Tobu Cycles at Franchise India 2014 said that from ages, entrepreneurship has been imbibed in the blood, culture and tradition of Indians.', 'Tobu Cycles, entrepreneurship, Micro and Small enterprises, real estate', '17:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6268, 'A', '2015-02-05 16:17:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1634, 'v07Y8-XJVJk', NULL, 'How to go about in entrepreneurship: Mahesh Gupta, Founder & Chairman, Kent RO at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Mahesh Gupta, a seasoned entrepreneur, is known worldwide for revolutionizing the water purifier industry in India. He is the Chairman of Kent RO Systems Ltd, an Indian healthcare products company, headquartered in Noida, Uttar Pradesh. It makes water purifiers based on the process of Reverse Osmosis (RO) purification. Over the years, the company has also diversified into air purifiers, vegetable and fruit purifiers and water softeners. \r\nHe started his entrepreneurial journey in 1999 from scratch by inventing the countrys first dual technology water purifier which was the answer to alarming problems of safe drinking water. In recognition of his contribution to the water purification industry, he was named as PURE WATER MAN of the country. He is also the Vice President of PHD Chamber of Commerce and Industry. Whiel speaking at the Franchise India 2014, Mahesh Gupta, Founder & Chairman, Kent RO shared his views on the present scenario of industrial market in the world and what is expected to happen in India and how to go about in entrepreneurship.', 'Kent RO, water purifier, water softeners, entrepreneurship, dual technology  ', '12:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 7, 5636, 'A', '2015-02-05 16:20:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1635, 'gwmf4yAwMYU', NULL, 'Estate Awards & Summit 2014', 3, '', NULL, '', 20, 'The 7th edition of the Estate Summit & Awards 2014 is an initiative by Franchise India and Estate World to deliberate on how to leverage the change that surrounds the Real Estate Industry to make the sector the best investment segment.   The conference was a conglomeration of 250+ leading developers, C- level real estate professionals, policy makers and government office holders. \r\nThe Estate Summit was concluded by Estate Awards 2014 that rewarded excellence, innovation and creativity in the real estate industry. The Estate Awards recognize the finest real estate projects, developers, brokers, architects and suppliers during a prestigious gala dinner attended by the most influential Real estate leaders and C-level property professionals.', 'Real Estate, retail, developer, broker, architect, realty, property show, property award, real estate summit', '23:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 4307, 'A', '2015-02-17 12:39:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1636, 'ckq-v-o99t0', NULL, 'Building a sustainable education business: Amol Arora, VP, MD, SHEMFORD & SHEMROCK Group of Schools at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Amol Arora is the Vice Chairman & Managing Director of SHEMFORD & SHEMROCK Group of Schools. An Engineering Graduate from Delhi College of Engineering of the Delhi University, Amol Arora has pursued MBA from the University of California-Irvine Campus, which offered him a faculty scholarship with an assistantship to do his MBA.\r\nAs a tribute to his leadership qualities while in the campus, he was elected as the President of the Indian Students Association and also earned an honorary lifetime membership of the Beta-Gamma-Sigma Society, an association of top management students in the USA. While speaking at the Franchise India 2014, Amol Arora, VP, MD, SHEMFORD & SHEMROCK Group of Schools talked about how to build a sustainable education business.', 'SHEMROCK Group, California, Beta-Gamma-Sigma Society, Amol Arora, education', '13:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 6079, 'A', '2015-02-19 14:26:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1637, 'KlnfRg9aNbQ', NULL, 'Preparing women to be an entrepreneur by Benu Sehgal', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Benu Sehgal is the Vice President, Mall Head of DLF Place, Saket. Prior to this, she was the Vice President Operations of IRPPL. At IRPPL, she was responsible for day to day functioning of The Great India Place mall, Metro Walk, Adventure Island and Worlds of Wonder amusement park. Sehgal has right skills or knowledge and knowhow of the quintessence of this industry. Prior to joining IRPPL she was Head HR at B4U, one of the worlds leading Bollywood television network. ', 'Women, Entrepreneur, DLF Place, Benu Sehgal, The Great India Place mall, Metro Walk ', '10:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3150, 'A', '2015-02-19 14:30:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(1638, 'IgEEpUk9myI', NULL, 'Consumption of beauty products is extremely low in India: Biju Antony, Head (Marketing), Baccarose Perfumes and Beauty Products at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'With over 25 years of experience in manufacturing, retail and distribution, Biju Anthony is one of the pioneers in launching international beauty brands in India. He is currently managing a large part of the business at Baccarose including its colour cosmetic and nail care business. Currently, Biju Antony is the Head (Marketing) at Baccarose Perfumes and Beauty Products. \\r\\nAnthony has an excellent track record of building sustainable businesses and profitable organizations in the luxury beauty space and personal care segment. He holds an advanced Masters Degree in Management from IIM-Bangalore. While speaking at the Franchise India 2014, Biju Antony, Head (Marketing), Baccarose Perfumes and Beauty Products highlighted that consumption of beauty products is extremely low in India as compared to other developed nations. Therefore training on beauty is an area where there are huge opportunities and that will also lead to the increase in the consumption of beauty products.', 'Beauty, Wellness, Baccarose Perfumes, Biju Anthony, IIM-Bangalore', '04:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 8379, 'A', '2015-02-19 14:32:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1639, '58ipnYLf9bk', NULL, 'Wants to 1000 successful women entrepreneurs of 3000 salons: C K Kumaravel, MD, Naturals Beauty Salons India Pvt Ltd at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Kumaravel is credited with eradicating the word housewife. Naturals grew from a small idea and its success story dates a decade back when the seeds for the salon were sown by his wife, K Veena. Today it is a 300 strong salon chain across the country. \r\nKumaravel belief is that women are as equal, if not more, efficient than men. According to him, Naturals strength is the easy and simple formula of helping an ordinary woman, who is passionate about becoming a business woman, by engaging her in franchising options and giving her adequate guidance and support to start and establish the business. Kumaravels mission is that with 10,000 job opportunities, he wants to create 1000 successful women entrepreneurs of 3000 salons and, thereby, 50,000 employment opportunities by 2016. ', 'Naturals Beauty Salons, C K Kumaravel, women, entrepreneur, employment opportunities ', '17:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5308, 'A', '2015-02-19 14:33:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1640, 'EUMpkRnM3eA', NULL, 'How to gain consumers trust: Dipak Agarwal, CEO and Head (Strategy), DLF Brands at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Dipak Agarwal has been associated with DLF Brands since its inception. He brings along his expertise of more than 20 years in retail, lifestyle and manufacturing businesses.\r\nA graduate from St. Xaviers College and Oxford Brooks University, UK, he is a Certified Chartered Accountant from UK, an MBA, CS and CMA. Prior to being with DLF Brands, he has worked in various capacities with Planet Retail Group and SSIPL Group wherein he had an opportunity to work with some of the leading international brands like Marks and Spencer, Nike, Levis, Accessorize, Guess and Next etc. Dipak Agarwal, CEO and Head (Strategy), DLF Brands at Franchise India 2014 said consumers needs are changing. Now they have emotional need of getting the right product at right time.', 'Dipak Agarwal, DLF Brands, SSIPL Group, Planet Retail Group, Oxford Brooks University  ', '09:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 5183, 'A', '2015-02-19 14:34:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1641, 'dQrU5UqqawA', NULL, 'Women must realize their strength : Rajni Aggarwal President, FIWE (Federation of Indian Women Entrepreneurs) at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Rajni Aggarwal, President of FIWE, is a Post Graduate from BITS, and Doctorate in education from Nagpur. As a first generation entrepreneurs she had, initially, set up a marketing organization in 1976, engaged in selling of Industrial plastic & Chemicals and subsequently established manufacturing facilities at Naraina Industrial Area, New Delhi in the field of electronic, including a component, audio systems & televisions. \r\nKeeping, in view her excellent performance, she was given National Award, as a Small Scale Entrepreneurs in 1987, by the President of India. She is the Present President of Federation of Indian Women Entrepreneurs (FIWE), Founder and Managing Director of Sears International Pvt. Ltd., Founder - CEO of Shree Ganpati Exports, New Delhi and Secretary General of International Federation of Women Entrepreneurs (IFWE). She is member on the Board of leading Government and Private Corporations in India. While speaking at Franchise India 2014, Rajni Aggarwal President, FIWE (Federation of Indian Women Entrepreneurs) said that how FIWE is helping women with a platform to interact, network and learn from each other.', 'Federation of Indian Women Entrepreneurs, women, Rajni Aggarwal, BITS, Shree Ganpati Exports', '18:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 6513, 'A', '2015-02-19 14:36:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1642, 'p-Qlo7FgHx8', NULL, 'Beauty and wellness industry to touch Rs.1 trillion by 2015: G Ramachandran, Director-Promoter, Gold Gym India at Franchise India 2014', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'G Ramachandran, Director-Promoter, Golds Gym India is a mentor capitalist with impeccable entrepreneurial spirit and financial expertise has evolved beyond spreadsheets and scripted new success stories from new economy start ups like Tower Capital, Karrox, Key Profiles, Safe House & USP Age. A perpetual quest to explore new horizons of a fast changing global scenario made G. Ramachandran to go through a metamorphosis and turn in to a mentor capitalist. At GOLDS GYM, G. Ramachandran is spearheading the global fitness leader with his new vision and fiscal stratagem.\r\n\r\nIn his past avatar G.R. (as he is popularly known) is a qualified Chartered Accountant (C.A.) and has done his articleship from Price Waterhouse Coopers. Has over 20 years experience in Investment Banking, Consulting, Business Process and Organizational Development. He had an incredible track record with Ernst & Young, JM Morgan Stanley, Citibank, Reliance Capital & The Times of India Group to name a few. G Ramachandran, Director-Promoter, Gold Gym India at Franchise India 2014 said that beauty and salon industry is growing by leaps and bounds and is expected to touch Rs.1 trillion by 2015.', 'Golds Gym, G. Ramachandran, beauty and salon industry, Price Waterhouse Coopers, Citibank, Reliance Capital ', '11:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 7138, 'A', '2015-02-19 14:37:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1643, 'bfZ14XZE2Vk', NULL, 'Real Estate is equal to economy of the country: Girish Pande, COO &ndash; Epms / Co- Human Capital, E-City Ventures at Franchise India 2014 ', 1, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Mumbai Based Girish Pande, is professional in strategic leadership position, with more than 24 years experience in varied businesses of hospitality, cinema exhibition and retail real estate and mall management. \r\n\r\nHe is COO and Director for EPMS (E -City Property Management Services), an Essel group enterprise, which is the largest comprehensive mall management company of India and set to be the leader till 2015 with assured mandate and targets of 30 million sq feet of minimum area under management. He also heads retail real estate of E-City ventures, malls with brand Fun Republic and owned by E-City ventures. While speaking at the Franchise India 2014, Girish Pande, COO &ndash; Epms / Co- Human Capital, E-City Ventures discussed about the future of Real Estate in India and stated that Real Estate is equal to economy of the country.', 'E-City Ventures, Real Estate, Essel group, E -City Property Management Services, Girish Pande ', '18:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 6114, 'A', '2015-02-19 14:38:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1644, 'gCOmZefPDvg', NULL, 'B&W professionals graced Curtain Raiser of 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015 in Chandigarh', 9, '', NULL, '', 45, 'Curtains to the most anticipated beauty event Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015 have been raised in Chandigarh in the presence of various industry professionals. In its 4th year, the event is all set to get bigger and better with addition of Wellness Industry into it.  Since its inception, Indian Salon & Wellness Congress has given better industry overview to the Salon and Wellness industry professionals striving to promote young talent, taken the lead on the digital front and has transformed the premier Salon & Wellness business. This year too will witness a perfect amalgamation of business advice from most established names in industry and elaborate discussions on factors contributing or may contribute in the growth of the industry.', 'India, salon, wellness industry, spa, Chandigarh ', '03:58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 6085, 'A', '2015-03-05 12:23:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1645, 'SvTOAkDsQF8', NULL, 'Philips offers breather from polluted air with range of purifiers', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Uncovering the gravity of air pollution, Phillips India, a brand known to deliver meaningful innovation in personal health and well-being, offers air-purifier range to reduce the growing risk of diseases caused due to inhale of impure air inside the house. To know more about Philips Air Purifier range, product pricing and target consumers, Wellness India talked to Jayati Singh Chakraborti, Business Head - Air, Philips India, at the sidelines of a uniquely crafted treasure hunt demo event organised by the brand to showcase special features of the product.', 'Philips, air pollution, purifier, personal care, health', '04:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 4862, 'A', '2015-03-05 14:10:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1646, 'rBaWtgtNlco', NULL, 'Vipul Amar on The V Renaissance', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Vipul Amar shares his views on his luxury brand: The V Renaissance during the Indian Luxury Expo. Further, he expresses his views on the potential of luxury retail in India.', 'retail, Luxury retail, Indian luxury expo, The V Renaissance', '03:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 3238, 'A', '2015-03-05 16:29:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1647, 'CGh6uFB_Et8', NULL, 'Chirag Sharma on Luxury Gifting ', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Chirag Sharma, COO of Thinking of You shares his views on Luxury retail and innovative gifting options during the Indian Luxury Expo. Besides, talks about how the concept of gifting has changed over the years.', 'retail, Luxury retail, e-retail, gifting, Chirag Sharma', '03:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 5, 3741, 'A', '2015-03-05 16:30:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1648, 'CbT4DZOcVXE', NULL, 'FICCI initiates to regularise Direct Selling ', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Direct selling market caught attention when top official of one of the prominent firms dealing in direct selling market was arrested. Initiating to regularise this segment of market, FICCI has send recommendations to government to design guidelines for direct sellers. To have a fair idea of recommendations, Retailer Media spoke to Shilpa Gupta, Head &ndash; Retail, FMCG, Luxury Gems & Jewelry, Direct Selling, FICCI at the sidelines of the recommendations, scenario in Direct Selling market and role of FICCI.', 'FICCI, Direct Selling, Retail', '05:58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 5314, 'A', '2015-03-07 08:58:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1649, '-jAPzf4HaGA', NULL, 'Essential Tax Reforms for boosting growth of MSME sector', 1, '', NULL, '', 11, 'Tax reforms are essential for the growth of the MSME sector. There are number of indirect taxes, which is hindering the growth of the MSME sector. Major tax reforms or doing away with double tax regime can help the sector to function at ease. Investors will invest and get attracted to the country and make India a business-friendly destination. Entrepreneur India talked Manguirish Pai Raiker, Co-Chairman, National Council for SMEs, ASSOCHAM to understand how a proper tax regime and a single window clearance can help the MSMEs in India.', 'Tax reforms, service tax, GST, MSME, tax regime', '03:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2699, 'A', '2015-03-07 16:36:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1650, '_dBFxxHF4UI', NULL, 'Innovation driven sectors to grow unabatedly: Gopal Srinivasan, TVS Capital', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'A third generation TVS family member, Srinivasan is also the Founder and Chairman of TVS Electronics Limited and a Director in the holding company TVS & Sons Ltd, and a member of the Board of several Group Companies. Over the course of his career spanning 25 years, he has founded several companies operating in diverse sectors including computer peripherals, technology & financial services with a combined revenue of over Rs 500 crore and with Asset Under Management (AUM) of Rs 1,100 crore. While speaking at the recently concluded Indian Private Equity & Venture Capital Association (IVCA) Conclave in New Delhi, Gopal Srinivasan, MD & CEO, TVS Capital, shared his views on the prevailing investor sentiment towards supporting the growing startup ecosystem in India.', 'TVS Capital, TVS Electronics Limited, CII, IVCA, Private Equity, Venture Capital  ', '03:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 5742, 'A', '2015-03-11 16:47:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1651, 'CEByPwrR15E', NULL, 'Anytime Fitness has elaborate expansion plans in India, says country Head', 1, '', NULL, '', 11, 'Globally renowned gym chain, Anytime Fitness has big expansion plans to spread awareness about health and fitness across India in 2015. In a conversation with Wellness India, Vikas Jain, MD, Anytime Fitness India unveiled the brand strategy, its 2700 clubs across the globe and much more. ', 'Anytime Fitness, gym, health, workout, exercise', '03:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3864, 'A', '2015-03-13 16:46:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1652, 'lEQR0pXWsjg', NULL, 'Digital payments, healthcare & SMAC space looks promising in 2015: Sateesh Andra, Ventureast', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Sateesh Andra is the Managing Partner at Ventureast, primarily overseeing the Ventureast Tenet Fund, a premier seed-stage VC Fund consisting of investments across technology (Mobility, Cloud, Internet) and technology-enabled (Education, Healthcare, Financial services, Cleantech and high-impact, invention-based social businesses) sectors. He has worked in or with venture-backed technology startups in US and India for the past fourteen years. With hands-on startup experience and in-depth knowledge of the dynamics of VC funding, he looks for highly motivated and energetic entrepreneurs as partners. While speaking at the recently concluded Indian Private Equity & Venture Capital Association (IVCA) Conclave in New Delhi, Andra discussed about the promising sectors that are likely to attract funds in 2015.', 'Ventureast, VC Fund, startups, entrepreneurs, digital payments, healthcare, SMAC ', '05:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 6539, 'A', '2015-03-13 17:50:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1653, 'b3ZLaxCMUbw', NULL, 'Luxury retail on a progressive path', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'In a candid conversation with Retailer team, Nakul Bajaj, CEO, Darveys.com, expresses his views on how eCommerce is contributing to the growth of luxury retail industry in India.', 'retail, retail industry, luxury retail, darveys.com, ecommerce', '06:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 3713, 'A', '2015-03-16 16:29:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1654, 'jmDws4LeFug', NULL, 'B&W Industry has potential to learn, earn and grow: Sachin Kamath', 2, '', NULL, '', 17, 'In the fourth edition of Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015, Sachin Kamath, Director &ndash; Employee & Customer Engagements, Enrich Salons & Academy expressed his views over the current scenario of the industry, the factors contributing in its growth, how Enrich is inculcating required skills and technical advancement in its employees and students and much more.', 'Salon, Wellness, Congress, conference, forum, growth', '06:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 3539, 'A', '2015-03-19 16:03:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1655, 't9nBt7DjvAU', NULL, 'Presenting Indian cuisine in a noble manner by Shaju Zacharia', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Chef Shaju Zacharia is the Senior Consultant with ASIANA SERVICES COMBINE. He has more than 30 years of experience in Food and Beverages industry. Talking to restaurant India he shares How can restaurant present the Indian cuisine in a noble manner.', 'Shaju Zacharia, Indian Cuisine, Restaurant, Food, Menu', '02:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3555, 'A', '2015-03-30 12:20:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1656, '7FXoeKA3ZsY', NULL, 'Food is more than just feeding your stomach believes Chef Saby', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Sabyasachi Gorai, lovingly called as chef Saby is one of the top chef in India. Talking to Restaurant India, he shares how to create an overall experience for the customers. ', 'Chef Saby, Celebrity Chef, Eating Out, Indian Restaurant, Food', '02:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 2701, 'A', '2015-03-30 12:21:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1657, '7QvK3fg5P24', NULL, 'No business will survive if a restaurateur wont make money by Arun K Agarwal ', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Arun K Agarwal is the CEO at Hibiscus Consult. Ina n exclusive interaction with restaurant India, he shares that No business will survive if a restaurateur wont make money.', 'Arun K Agarwal, Restaurant Consultant, Chef, Food and Beverages, Indian Food, QSR', '02:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 7, 2715, 'A', '2015-03-30 12:22:45', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 0, 0),
(1658, 'u_d-RSJEpzk', NULL, 'Reviving the lost foods of India by Osama Jalali', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Osama Jalali is the food writer, critic and food festival curator. Recently he has joined hands with Oberoi Group of hotels to Revive Rampur Cuisines. Listen to him as he shares about his work in reviving of traditional cuisines in India.', 'Osama Jalali, Food Critic, Rampur Cuisime, Gastronomy, Modern Indian Food, Indian Cuisine', '02:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 7, 4185, 'A', '2015-03-30 12:23:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1659, 'ahrM-xk6g6k', NULL, 'AYUSH Ministry has lucrative business scope: KVIC Deputy Chief', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Highlighting the key steps taken by Khadi & Village Commission to bring lucrative growth opportunities for youth, KS Rao, Deputy CEO of Khadi & Village Commission - Ministry of MSME, Government of India has expressed his views about AYUSH Ministry and its agenda to promote and improve the traditional science, how Make in India campaign would be a win-win situation for all and much more.', 'Khadi & Village Commission, AYUSH, Ministry, Government, wellness, beauty', '04:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3072, 'A', '2015-03-31 15:07:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1660, '08z9w6Ows2U', NULL, 'Govt gives phenomenal support for AYUSH upliftment: Schwabe India MD', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Wellness India talks to Ashish Kumar, Managing Director of Dr Willmar Schwabe India Pvt Ltd to understand what made them worlds largest homeopathy company, what are the challenges the brand faced while establishing them in Indian market, how the brand got associated with AYUSH ministry and receiving adequate government support.', 'Homeopathy, India, AYUSH, wellness, Ayurveda', '05:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2545, 'A', '2015-04-02 11:54:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1661, 'b6oN_G09Qe4', NULL, 'Concept of teaching needs to be change: Abha Sehgal', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting the challenges which educators face to provide brighter future to children, Abha Sehgal, Principal, Sanskriti School, said that educators should keep special focus on way of thinking i.e. creativity, problem solving, decision making, way the children work, collaborated working so that children can communicate well.', 'Sanskriti School, Indian Education', '09:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3349, 'A', '2015-04-02 15:27:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1662, 'BHNa98OvmWk', NULL, 'Technology is an integral part of our education system ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Amit Gupta, Executive Director of S. Chand Group in his key note highlighted the points on the 12th plan and policy of education and where it is going forward.  He also stated that technology plays an integral part of our education system as technology will cover all the aspects of educational delivery.', '12th plan, S. Chand Group, Education sector, Indian government, Education technology  ', '10:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3021, 'A', '2015-04-02 15:28:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1663, 'Hx5tKnVXFdI', NULL, 'Education is an emergent need for the country: Shayama Chona ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting the importance of education, Dr Shayama Chona, Padma Shri Bhushan Awardee, Founder, Tamana Special School, addressed education as empowerment, exposure, experience, expansion, explosion and emergent need for the country.', 'Indian Education, Tamana Special school', '13:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2873, 'A', '2015-04-02 15:30:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1664, 'yfhNDcGtcMM', NULL, 'Education sector imbibes shared value concept', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting the work of International Finance Corporation, which is the private sector arm of World Bank, Anil Sinha, Regional Head, Advisory Services South Asia, IFC- World Bank, has expressed his view on shared value concept in Education space, which can be adopted by enterprises to tackle some of societies development challenges. ', 'Shared value concept, World Bank, IFC', '07:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3873, 'A', '2015-04-02 15:32:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1665, '3LZoUHSvRIs', NULL, 'Skill shortage is a key reason for failure at entry level', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting the importance of vocational/skill education, Jaikant Singh, head of partnership, NSDC, put emphasis on respecting people in society who have acquired skill or vocational education. ', 'Skill, vocational education, NSDC ', '05:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 8, 3134, 'A', '2015-04-02 15:36:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1666, 'YbIkjxLR84E', NULL, 'Coordinate technology with teacher training to get better results', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting on the role of technology in Education, Rakesh Rathi, Head- Education Vertical, Ricoh India Ltd, said that education technology should be coordinated with teacher training and should be supported by curriculums in school context so that it enables students to get jobs. ', 'Ricoh India, Education technology, teacher training', '12:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2430, 'A', '2015-04-02 15:37:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1667, 'WFrcN-N3lgM', NULL, 'Learning needs to be promoted', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Kaisar Dopaishi, Principal, Singapore International School, in his keynote said that it is very important to deal with change management system to develop a school culture. He further put emphasis on promoting learning to develop robust school learning community.', 'Change management system, Singapore International School  ', '05:43', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2713, 'A', '2015-04-02 15:38:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1668, 'A5tH8GqufwU', NULL, 'Indians are lacking on education, which am spreading: Jawed Habib', 9, '', NULL, '', 43, 'Calls himself as The Scissor Man, Renowned Indian Hairstylist Jawed Habib (JH) does not need much introduction. The way he has carved a niche for himself in the Salon Industry is truly commendable. While interacting with Wellness India at the sidelines of 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015, The Hajjam himself gave a clear overview on lack of education brought a big gap in salon business and how he is bridging that gap by spreading awareness in every nook & corner of the country, and more.', 'hair salon, education, business, salons, Jawed Habib, franchise india', '03:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3704, 'A', '2015-04-04 09:24:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1669, 'OnahqGGgbtY', NULL, 'Fitness industry growth bank on awareness: Sheru Aangrish', 1, '', NULL, '', 11, 'A big name in fitness Industry, Sheru Aangrish is heading the Sports Fit venture, founded by Cricket Captain MS Dhoni, in India. He is a leading entrepreneur who started first Health and Fitness Expo of Asia under his brand name Sheru Classic to educate Indian consumers and spread fitness motivation among them. In an exclusive interaction with Wellness India, Aangrish talks about Sports fit, current scenario of fitness business, its scope, future prospects and more.', 'Fitness, growth, market, expansion, gyms, exercise, wellness', '04:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5950, 'A', '2015-04-04 09:26:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1670, 'eCs4ftwfG28', NULL, 'Indias solar energy sector requires $100 billion investment: Sumant Sinha, Chairman, ReNew Power Ventures ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Sumant Sinha is an Indian businessman. In 2010, he founded investment banking and consulting firm Savant Advisors and in 2011, he founded ReNew Power in Gurgaon. He is currently the Co-Chairman of Confederation ofIndian Industry (CII) committee on National Renewable Energy as well as theChairman of the Indian Wind Energy Association (IWEA), the apex body for wind energy industry in India, and a Founder Member of the Solar Power Developers Association. While interacting with Entrepreneur India on the eve of IVCA Conclave 2015, Sumant Sinha shared his views on the investment opportunity in the renewable energy space.', 'Renewable energy, IVCA, ReNew Power, Solar Power Developers Association, Indian Wind Energy Association, National Renewable Energy   ', '01:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 4083, 'A', '2015-04-04 10:35:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1671, 'g8m6-NFveZI', NULL, 'We aim to save mother nature by promoting organic products: Director SeaSoul', 9, '', NULL, '', 43, 'Momtrepreneur Manisha Chopra, who is the Director of SeaSoul Cosmeceuticals, shared a candid moment with Wellness India at the sidelines of 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015. Chopra told us about her unique product line, which is an amalgamation of precious natural ingredients, handpicked by her from across the globe to incorporate into her products and her constant efforts of saving Mother Nature by encouraging and spreading awareness about organic products and much more.', 'SeaSoul Cosmeceuticals, spa products, organic, wellness, Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015', '06:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4398, 'A', '2015-04-07 15:19:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1672, 'PmUEqJZnVDM', NULL, 'Atul ahuja on franchising ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Speaking at the Indian retail congress 2014, Atul Ahuja Vice President - Retail, Apollo Pharmacy expresses his views on new retail distribution and brand partnerships.', 'retail, Indian retail congress, Apollo Pharmacy', '02:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3701, 'A', '2015-04-08 14:15:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1673, 'H46Km29-vGI', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress & Awards', 8, '', NULL, '', 40, 'The Indian Education Congress brings together a diverse set of education entrepreneurs, institutional leaders, investors and suppliers in an engaging setting to explore and integrate principles of effective leadership, entrepreneurship, and management with the principles of imparting education that would produce both growth and equity.\r\nIndian Education Awards are the most prestigious awards that recognize excellence in education sector. Awardees receive national recognition and will be termed as best education entities in the country. The award winners will receive extensive media coverage and PR with the partners. Such an achievement & recognition have, according to our Award recipients, translated into further success in the education business. ', 'Education, K-12, Preschools, Education Convention, Education Awards, Education Congress, Higher Education, education summit, technology in education', '01:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3912, 'A', '2015-04-23 15:13:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1674, 'uPDx3LlYsW0', NULL, 'Indian Education Awards 2014 - Part 1', 8, '', NULL, '', 40, 'Indian Education Awards are the most prestigious awards that recognize excellence in education sector. Awardees receive national recognition and will be termed as best education entities in the country. The award winners will receive extensive media coverage and PR with the partners. Such an achievement & recognition have, according to our Award recipients, translated into further success in the education business. ', 'Education, K-12, Preschools, Education Awards, Higher Education, technology in education ', '07:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2607, 'A', '2015-04-24 10:52:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
