(1677, 'GxxvOpg1IS8', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: CSR law brings good news for Educational trust', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Krishna Khanna, Founder of  iWatch Foundation, throw light on the aspect of  the impact on social innovation or social issue as far as the new CSR Law is considered. He said that it is a unique law and India is only country with this type of law, where 2% of profit from public and private limited companies is ploughed back into the social causes.', 'iWatch foundation, CSR Law, Social issues, Social impact', '03:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3144, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:25:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1678, 'NLJyiweisTQ', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: CSR, an approach of giving back to society', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'MN Sanyal, Head of CSR, Thermax India, highlighted the corporate view of how they are trying to do CSR focusing on Education sector. He said that no business can succeed in a society that fades and that is the reason what they do is a business to achieve a commercial success in a ways that honour ethical values.', 'CSR, Corporate, Thermax India', '10:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 2374, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:26:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1679, 'RVxvISdjk0A', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Every preschool requires incubation centre - Dr. Shailendra Gupta', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting the key challenges in preschool education, Dr. Shailendra Gupta, Principal of Calox Institute of Education said if we cannot sustain the curiosity of a child we will not be able to do good in the knowledge economy.', 'Incubation centres, preschool education, Knowledge economy, Calox Institute of Education ', '09:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3453, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:28:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1680, '3zYP3l-Dkgc', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Preschool education is a key period for development', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Talking about bring new meaning in early childhood learning and its importance, Dr Shailendra Gupta, Principal of Calorx Institute of Education, said that all the major development in a child take place during their preschool education and if in this period it is not fully used then it obsolete over the time. ', 'Preschool education, Childhood learning, Calorx Institute of Education ', '22:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3584, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:30:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1681, '0Gqp-LHmiOw', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: New government requires more focus on higher education', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While expressing views on focus that the new government needs to have on higher education and steps we would need new government to take to revitalized the sector to gain some momentum, Dr. Nikhil Sinha, Vice Chancellor of Shiv Nadar University said that higher education is the key important area. It is the government responsibility to look into the sector on the immediate basis.', 'Higher education, Shiv Nadar University, Indian Government', '13:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 3965, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:34:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1682, 'yBHPLuePPOE', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Students should remain grounded with spiritual values: Lila Purushottam Das', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Dr. Lila Purushottam Das, Director of Bhaktivedanta Gurukula and International school gives a brief about his school, which was established by their founder acharya. He said that in addition to the teaching values, they want their students to be grounded in spiritual values.', 'Bhaktivedanta gurukula, International school', '08:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2943, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:36:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1683, 'kLsXM9ing_k', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Contributing to nation may help in achieving more ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting the solution to the problems in higher education, Dr. Amrendra Pani, Research Director of Association of Indian Universities, said to the present gathering that if they could contribute even little bit with all these difficulties than it would be great achievement for the nation. ', 'Association of Indian Universities, Higher Education', '10:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 3111, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:38:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1684, 'ZD20ZuR6QDQ', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Shaping lives through education business', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Anuraag Saxena, Regional Head-South Asia & ASEAN of  World Education Foundation, UK in his key note give a brief introduction about his organization, what they do? And why they are here? He said their organization work in the direction of transparency, advisory and capability building in order to provide better school system.', 'World Education Foundation, UK,  Education business', '24:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3400, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:40:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1685, 'gqWdk8AV-yI', NULL, 'Help institutes to develop open interface: Mahendra Bapna', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Putting emphasis on quality on graduates coming out of  university, Mahendra Bapna, Founder & CEO of  University-21 (Higher Education), said that large percentage of graduates lack critical thinking, attention of span, lack of comprehension skills and the reasoning skills. He further adds that it is hard to find graduate students who can even write five sentences properly.', 'Higher education, University-21(Higher Education), Vocational training ', '13:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2618, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:44:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1686, 'r4aiFTYZKCY', NULL, 'Need to set different benchmark in higher education: Vasu K Saksena', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Vasu K Saksena, Chief Executive Officer of Merittrac Services in his key note said that in higher education, we need to set different benchmark, different goals and a different way to work around what challenges we face. ', 'Merittrac Services, Higher Education', '11:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3532, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:45:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1687, 'L9o_b1eshWc', NULL, 'Not entirely comfortable with CSR Act: Siddharth Ramaligam', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While highlighting the issues of CSR act of one particular section, Siddharth Ramaligam, Senior Vice President of IDFC Foundation, said  he is fundamentally uneasy when somebody has to be told that what the social good is.', 'IDFC Foundation, CSR', '02:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2619, 'A', '2015-04-25 10:47:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1688, 'eoJPWqtXfSM', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Need to focus more on Education technology space', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting the benefits of Campus Dynamic, unit of UNIKUL Solutions private limited Pulakesh, Founder and Chief Executive Officer, UNIKUL Solutions Private Limited, said that they are focused on information technology which addresses the needs of educational institutions. ', 'Informational Technology, Campus Dynamic, UNIKUL Solutions, Educational institutions', '12:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3063, 'A', '2015-04-27 16:31:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1689, 'hIrcIU-047Q', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Employability is a major concern facing country', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Meeta W Sengupta, Founder, Centre for Education Strategy said that we as Indians need to export our unemployment to rest of the world, which means that we are not only training people for Indian business but we are also training them for rest of the world.', 'Indian Education Congress 2014, Education Strategy, Indian business', '06:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 2188, 'A', '2015-04-27 16:32:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1690, 'Meu9Wnq09eY', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Urge for promising institutions to retain students in India ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Addressing issues related to globalization and higher education, Prof. Rajen Harshe, Professor- International Studies, South Asean University, said  education institution in India have to be different or promising enough for student to get admission or to feel good here. He believes that universities are burden with too much agenda that is the reason why universities could not perform well. ', 'South Asean University, Foreign studies', '19:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3681, 'A', '2015-04-27 16:33:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1691, '5_XKtd7C2HI', NULL, 'India is a global education hub: Maria Mathai', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Maria Mathai, Advisor (India) to the President, University of Alberta, in her key note highlighted key differences between Indian and Canadian education which will help Indian institutions become world class in operation.', 'Indian Education, Canadian Education, University of Alberta', '18:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3208, 'A', '2015-04-27 16:34:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1692, '2lyln8y272M', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: CSR, not only option for corporate', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Manmohan Singh, Founder, Piramal Foundation, highlighted the ways in which one can help corporate/ government/ people to think beyond CSR. He said until unless we have right process to find out problems/issues, it is actually difficult to cause impact.', 'Corporate, CSR, Indian Education, Indian Education Congress 2014', '05:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2365, 'A', '2015-04-27 16:37:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1693, 'T5ksdFL_6TE', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Huge opportunities in education sector in next five years', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting at the opportunities in education sector in the next five years Vineet Gupta, Director, Jamboree Education, Founder & Trustee, Ashoka Universities said that to create education enterprises, we need to focus on creating high quality investment in education sector. He further adds that there are huge opportunities, markets and regulatory mechanism for education.  ', 'Ashoka universities, Jamboree education, Indian education', '19:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2492, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:10:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1694, '5zU8a02tqVA', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: E-commerce, answer to education barriers', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Putting emphasis at the word e-commerce, Vikrant Khorana, Vice president & Business Head &ndash; Non Ecommerce Business, PayU India highlighted the challenges faced by education institution in todays era. He said answer to these challenges is e-commerce, as it is technological era and one needs to move on.', 'E-commerce, Technological era, PayU, Indian Education Congress 2014', '10:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2785, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:11:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1695, 'eIZyJMxo2sM', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Education is all about making child happy', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Steve Rudolp, Director, Jiva Education  highlighted in his key note that education should be all about making child happy or happier and this can be achieved by the idea called multiple nature where they work on the model, Right Person in Right Part (RPRP). Through this model one can get to understand what the child nature is and where he/she needs to go so that he/she becomes RPRP.', 'Jiva Education, Multiple nature, RPRP, Indian Education Congress 2014', '07:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3563, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:12:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1696, 'GyEiXAmbsJM', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Education sector needs more focus on skill development', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting the importance of skill development, Dr. Darlie O Koshy, Director General & Chief Executive Officer, Institute of Apparel Management said Indias population needs to be skilled, otherwise India will miss out its greater development. He pointed out that Indian education sector has not really understood need for looking at skills at every level as skills are required for getting jobs and for this they need to change the Indian approach of understanding skill training.', 'Skill development, Indian Education, Institute of Apparel Management, Skilling India', '14:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 3927, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:13:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1697, 'xg8QgEHayW8', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Educators needs to understand their customers  ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting on disrupted education, Prof. (Dr.) Madan Mohan Pant, Founder & Mentor, Planet EDU said disruption in education is not in use of technology, it is in the personalization of the learning experience. He said that use of technology can bridge the gap between disrupted educations.', 'Disrupted education, Technology education, Planet EDU, Indian Education Congress 2014', '13:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3170, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:16:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1698, 'BPqzrj0xbNE', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Creating a much better education system', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting at the partnership with education sector, Parminder Gill, Co-Founder, EduSports  said, that if we  focus on  how learning happens, parent advocacy, economics and sustainability, then we would have far better education system. ', 'EduSport, Indian education, Indian Education Congress 2014', '09:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2980, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:17:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1699, 'xaOsluHP-WU', NULL, 'Food as an Offshoot of culture by Celebrity Chef Ranveer Brar', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'In an exclusive interview with Restaurant India, Chef Ranveer Brar, Celebrity Chef, Restaurateur, Writer and Food Stylist shares How food has emerged as a root to the culture focusing on the refinement of the cuisine. ', 'Chef Ranveer Brar, Cuisine, Lucknowi Cuisine, Mughlai Food, Food as Culture, Regional Cuisine, Menu, Celebrity Chef', '04:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2836, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:21:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1700, 'tb5jGze0kqU', NULL, 'GreenDust to become a Rs 300 billion company: Hitendra Chaturvedi', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Hitendra Chaturvedi is the Founder and CEO of Reverse Logistic Company GreenDust. Before starting GreenDust, Hitendra was the business unit head for Microsoft OEM business in India. And before Microsoft, he was instrumental in building an IT enabled reverse logistics company in the US (Newgistics). A computer engineer from IIT with an MS and MBA from US, Hitendra has over 20 years of experience in software/IT, multi-channel retail, and supply chain solutions. ', 'GreenDust, Reverse Logistic, supply chain, Hitendra Chaturvedi, entrepreneur, Newgistics', '06:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5701, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:24:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1701, 'uTpCskrkC1k', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress 2014: Coordinate technology with teacher training to get better results', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting on role of technology in education, Mr. Rakesh Rathi, Head- Education Vertical, Ricoh India Ltd, said education technology should be coordinated with teacher training and should be supported by curriculums in school context so that it enable students to get jobs. ', 'Ricoh India, Education technology, teacher training', '15:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2337, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:27:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1702, '68OGXh0e4Po', NULL, 'How your Restaurant will be preferred place over others by Saurabh Khanijo', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Talking at Indian Restaurant Congress 2014, Saurabh Khanijo, Chief Executive Officer, Welgrow Hotel Concepts Pvt Ltd shares How can your restaurant be a preferred place over other restaurants.', 'Restaurant, Indian Restaurant Congress 2014, Franchise India, Saurabh Khanijo, Food Brands', '03:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3334, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:30:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1703, 'WpXTMGVaNl0', NULL, 'How technology is helping in delivering best quality products by Vineet Narang', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Speaking at Indian Restaurant Congress 2014, Vineet Narang, Chief Executive Officer, Mobiquest Mobiles Technologies Pvt Ltd shares How technology is helping in the sharing of real time data.', 'Technology, Restaurant, Indian Restaurant Congress, Vineet Narang, Mobiquest', '08:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2986, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:35:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1704, 'E5KTPtwuv1U', NULL, 'What is the importance of location in restaurant building by Varun Kapur', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Talking at Indian Restaurant Congress 2014, Varun Kapur, Executive Director, Travel Food Services shares What has he kept in mind while choosing locations for his restaurants.', 'Varun Kapur, Indian Restaurant Congress, Travel Food Services, Franchise India, Restaurant', '07:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3836, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:36:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1705, '7AYdAmAPQvA', NULL, 'What makes western brands a success in India by Tanmay Kumar', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Speaking at Indian Restaurant Congress 2014, Tanmay Kumar, CFO, Burger King India shares Why western brands are a success in India.', 'Tanmay Kumar, CFO, Burger King, Fast Food, QSR Chain, Indian Restaurant Congress 2014, Franchise India', '03:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1878, 'A', '2015-04-29 09:37:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1706, 'spcKez9IuIk', NULL, 'Soon to launch a dedicated line of child care products: Kama Ayurveda Co-Founder', 9, '', NULL, '', 43, 'Based on the ancient science of holistic Ayurveda care, Kama Ayurveda offers herbal products, termed as treatments by the brand. Wellness India brings you the exclusive conversation with the Co-Founder of Kama Ayurveda, Vivek Sahni, who not only aspire to create a niche in wellness space, but aims to increase his products reach by using the word-of-mouth strategy, which is one of the USP and bloggers choice to give adequate limelight to the brand, making it a first pick of Crme de la Crme consumers. He also shared with us about his upcoming product line which is dedicated for toddlers, infants and growing children.', 'Child, infant care, products, Kama Ayurveda, herbal, ancient science', '03:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3901, 'A', '2015-04-30 14:18:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1707, '25jiVLcaJvU', NULL, 'We are open to strategic alliance & cross promotion: Advance Hair Studio India Head', 9, '', NULL, '', 43, 'In a rendezvous with Sanket Shah, CEO & Owner of Advance Hair Studio (AHS), Indian Subcontinent and Middle Eastern Region, Wellness India exclusively unveiled about his willingness for strategic alliance and reasons for not being ready to sub franchise his brand. Shah also talked about his expansion strategy in Indian metros, dedicated software used by him to stay connected with his team across the globe and about his client, Indian Cricket star Gautam Gambhir, with much more.', 'Advance Hair Studio, Sanket Shah, strategic alliance, expansion, software use, Gautam Gambhir', '05:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4489, 'A', '2015-04-30 14:22:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(1708, '3uYTMrdFTDY', NULL, 'Starting up a gems and jewellery enterprise', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Prasad Kapre, CEO, Silvostyle by PN Gadgil is the former Business Director in India for diamond brand De Beers and is credited with growing domestic brands like Nakshatra and Sangini. Pune-based PN Gadgil, the 183-year-old jewellery major in January this year had tied up with fashion designer Tarun Tahiliani to design the silver ornaments which it will grow under the Silvostyle brand. Kapre, at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014 talks about how the industry, which was so far considered as a turf for family businesses only, is getting increasingly organized with more professionals coming in and how the presence of digital is foraying in the industry. He further highlights key areas for an aspiring gems and jewellery entrepreneur to focus on including trust, quality, after sales service etc.', 'Gems and Jewellery, Gold, Startup, Family Business', '10:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6254, 'A', '2015-04-30 14:36:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1709, '35qgxJEldKY', NULL, 'Empowering Indian handloom', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Government-owned National Textile Corporation that looks after revival and upliftment of Indian textiles domestically and internationally has more around 90 stores across the country under the brand NTC. At the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Alokendra Banerjee, Director (Marketing), NTC highlights its offerings to empower local artisans and MSME clusters. According to Banerjee, NTC runs three brands, Brand India for handlooms and handicrafts, Indian Republic for menswear and Stree Vijay to empower women through direct selling. Also, NTC had earlier tied up with online retailer Flipkart to sell handlooms products sourced from more than 400 handloom clusters across the country.', 'National Textile Corporation, NTC, Women Empowerment, Flipkart, Handloom, Handicraft, Brick and Mortar, Clusters', '05:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5924, 'A', '2015-04-30 14:38:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1710, 'jol4fvS22Ik', NULL, 'Growing up Fit', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'After making a mark for herself in the film and glamour world, famed-actress Bipasha Basu along with actor Harman Baweja has launched her own beauty and fitness brand, Love Yourself (LYS), particularly for women. Named the Sexiest Woman in Asia by UK magazine Eastern Eye (2005 and 2007), Basu delivered the key note at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014. She shared the story of how her mother inspired her to come up with Love Yourself and how the brand tries to capture the inherent inner beauty of every woman that needs to be appreciated by herself.', 'Bipasha Basu, Women Fitness, Gym, Healthcare, Harman Baweja, Exercise', '03:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 5366, 'A', '2015-04-30 14:40:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1711, 'pmMjQLljgwk', NULL, 'Finding Growth Partner', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'French brand for designer luxury handmade handbags will be foraying into India to offer refine niche designer bags and allied products. The company already has its presence expanding in Japan and China through exclusive brand and multi brand outlets. Now in order to further increase its reach in Asia, Jamin Puech has its eyes set on India. At the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Christophe kapusta, Group Commercial Director, Jamin Puech talks about their intent to find right partner in India who understand their design philosophy that the brand claims to quite unique.', 'Master Franchise, Luxury Handbag, Partner, Design', '07:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4194, 'A', '2015-04-30 14:41:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1712, 'PL41T9YydLk', NULL, 'Testing the Indian Waters', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Billboard Connection, an out-of-home advertising agency and EmbroidMe, a promotional marketing company that offers custom embroidery and screen printing, comes under the US-based United Franchise Group (UFG). UFG is an umbrella company that houses multiple franchise systems specializing in personalized businesses such as embroidery, outdoor advertising, signage etc. At the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Daniel Peavy, President, Billboard Connection and EmbroidMe shares the journey of the group since 1970 and how they are planning to bring the two brands into India through master franchisee.', 'United Franchise Group, Advertisement, Marketing, India', '11:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6464, 'A', '2015-04-30 14:45:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1713, 'XiZpvXj3AkE', NULL, 'Testing the Indian Waters', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Billboard Connection, an out-of-home advertising agency and EmbroidMe, a promotional marketing company that offers custom embroidery and screen printing, comes under the US-based United Franchise Group (UFG). UFG is an umbrella company that houses multiple franchise systems specializing in personalized businesses such as embroidery, outdoor advertising, signage etc. At the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Daniel Peavy, President, Billboard Connection and EmbroidMe shares the journey of the group since 1970 and how they are planning to bring the two brands into India through master franchisee.', 'United Franchise Group, Advertisement, Marketing, India', '06:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 15, 6559, 'A', '2015-04-30 14:53:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1714, 'HuzTfBq3W40', NULL, 'Building up online fashion brand ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'KAZO is an apparel brand for women owned by Delhi-based B L International that designs, manufactures and supply garments. The company claims of being one of the most preferred fashion brands in retail market that focuses on producing clothes following international trends and fashion at an affordable price. The brand already has 22 stores pan India. Speaking at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Deepak Aggarwal, Director, KAZO Fashion talks about the challenges of growing and establishing a fashion brand online including brand perspective and its positioning.', 'Fashion, Online Retail, Kazo, Brand Positioning', '07:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 7246, 'A', '2015-04-30 14:55:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1715, 'I7ocgs9dnrA', NULL, 'The great Indian food consumption story', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Deval Tibrewalla, CEO & Director, Polo Foods is a 5th generation entrepreneur at Polo Towers Group which owns and operates Hotel Polo Towers, Shillongs only luxury hotel, which is also one of the largest hotels in the North East region. Apart from his passion for hospitality business, Tibrewalla also has keen interest in the organised food & beverage retail space in India. Polo Foods, is a new business entity of the Group which has been conceived by him. Polo Foods is the master franchisee for the US-based Great American Cookies in India and Forever Yogurt in India, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Bhutan, Myanmar and Nepal. It is also the master franchisee of Quiznos for East India. Speaking at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Tibrewalla talks about the Indian consumption story on the food side, why it is more about the QSR rather than fine dining or casual dining and which category make up for the larger business chunk in the market?', 'Polo Foods, QSR, Fine Dining, Food Consumption, Opportunity', '05:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6954, 'A', '2015-04-30 14:57:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1716, '7o1u5wCOQdc', NULL, 'The great Indian food consumption story', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Deval Tibrewalla, CEO & Director, Polo Foods is a 5th generation entrepreneur at Polo Towers Group which owns and operates Hotel Polo Towers, Shillongs only luxury hotel, which is also one of the largest hotels in the North East region. Apart from his passion for hospitality business, Tibrewalla also has keen interest in the organised food & beverage retail space in India. Polo Foods, is a new business entity of the Group which has been conceived by him. Polo Foods is the master franchisee for the US-based Great American Cookies in India and Forever Yogurt in India, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Bhutan, Myanmar and Nepal. It is also the master franchisee of Quiznos for East India. Speaking at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Tibrewalla talks about the Indian consumption story on the food side, why it is more about the QSR rather than fine dining or casual dining and which category make up for the larger business chunk in the market?', 'Polo Foods, QSR, Fine Dining, Food Consumption, Opportunity', '02:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 7383, 'A', '2015-04-30 15:02:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1717, 'nvqoUCrTfro', NULL, 'Going from local to National', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Since 2001, Dheeraj Gupta, MD, Jumbo King has been the force behind making the humble street food of Mumbai, Vada Pav into a brand that it is today. The company is the one of the leading food retail company in India in the QSR segment with more than 75 operational outlets across 15+ cities in India and targets 1,000 outlets by 2020. Sharing his thoughts on food industry at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Gupta said food industry in India is yet to take off unlike Mc Donalds, Dominos, Pizza Hut in the US. He however asserts that many Indian brands will get created over next 10-20 years as every food that has a market can be branded such as biryani, sweets etc. Gupta highlights the lack of resources and skills for seemingly good players to transform themselves into a national brand.', 'Food, Jumbo King, Brand, Snacks, McDonald’s, Vada Pav, Expansion, Growth', '04:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4349, 'A', '2015-04-30 15:03:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1718, '2VJe-RjWapc', NULL, 'Creating the women-first fitness brand', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Bollywood actor Harman Baweja along with actress and fitness freak Bipasha Basu recently launched, Love Yourself (LYS), a beauty and fitness brand for women. Discussing the idea behind launching LYS at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Baweja said, We found that there was a gap in the way women are being looked after in the fitness industry. Most of the gyms that exist have machines designed for men, and women happen to be a part of that purely because they do not have an option while local standalone gyms are not state of the art neither well equipped.', 'Bipasha Basu, Women Fitness, Gym, Healthcare, Harman Baweja, Exercise', '05:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5813, 'A', '2015-04-30 15:06:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1719, 'c0_hUXGHTr4', NULL, 'Cleaning up the growth path', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Joseph Manuszak is the Director of International Franchising and Development at HRI (Chem-Dry), based in the US. Chem-Dry is the worlds largest carpet cleaning franchise chain present in 45 countries and represented with little over 3,500 franchisees. Manuszak has significant experience in franchise development for new market penetration, turnaround operations, developing licensing business models. Manuszak led the early development of Dominos Pizza International in both Australia and Europe. At the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Manuszak shares the strategy they followed to enter India.', 'Franchise India, Expansion, Chem-Dry, Vacuum Cleaning,', '04:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4645, 'A', '2015-04-30 15:08:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1720, 'ccnT0UFlZH0', NULL, 'Equity - best asset class for investments', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Ketan Shah is the Associate Director - Information Technology and B2B Business, Angel Broking, a stock broking and wealth management company. After working for few years in the broking industry, Shah saw the potential of IT to enhance the business of broking and making it more structured. Shah, today, is also entrusted with the responsibility for the Franchise Business Development, which involves managing franchise partner experience, creating and implementing new franchise platform, conducting business analysis etc. In his session on services business at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, shah explains why an equity investment is the best bet for people wanting to invest their disposable income wisely. This is keeping in mind the volatile nature of market but looking at a long term horizon, Shah asserts that equity gives better and efficient returns when compared to other investment options such as FDs, bonds, gold.', 'Services Business, Equity Investment, Returns, Disposable Income, Market Volatility', '11:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5340, 'A', '2015-04-30 15:11:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1721, 'pu354Nee2ks', NULL, 'Finding the ideal franchise partner', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'The Cherry Tree is the UK-based producers of chutneys, pickles and preserves for over 30 years. The company sell its products exclusively to franchisees who retail it via food festivals, shows, outdoor events and fairs, shopping malls, boutique shops and food services. In the session on food business at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Mark Teideman, Founder, The Cherry Tree Ltd talks about the genesis of the company, its franchising philosophy for the brand Cherry Tree Preserves since 2007 and the importance of having an open relationship, being up front and focusing on lot of communication with the potential franchisees.', 'Franchise, The Cherry Tree, Partner, Chutneys, Pickles, Expansion', '04:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4383, 'A', '2015-04-30 15:13:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1722, 'FSXON6n0YTA', NULL, 'What to do before approaching franchisor?', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Mike Hanrahan started his management business in the domestic services sector in 1993. Ten years later having some 400 cleaners representing his brand on a weekly basis he founded domestic cleaning services firm, Maid2Clean. The franchise business was launched after 10 successful years of operation. Hanrahan has also authored a book titled The Lean Thinker - How to Franchise Your Business on a Shoestring Budget. Maid2Clean currently has 126 franchisees in 166 locations across the UK, Ireland, Malta and a bit in Canada. Talking about master licensing at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Hanrahan stresses on the importance of due diligence, understanding of the brand, company ethics and culture, customers say by the licensee before approaching the licensor.', 'Franchisor, Licensing, Brand, Due Diligence, Cleaning Service', '07:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4400, 'A', '2015-04-30 15:14:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1723, 'UA8NkccyCzc', NULL, 'What to do before approaching franchisor?', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Mike Hanrahan started his management business in the domestic services sector in 1993. Ten years later having some 400 cleaners representing his brand on a weekly basis he founded domestic cleaning services firm, Maid2Clean. The franchise business was launched after 10 successful years of operation. Hanrahan has also authored a book titled The Lean Thinker - How to Franchise Your Business on a Shoestring Budget. Maid2Clean currently has 126 franchisees in 166 locations across the UK, Ireland, Malta and a bit in Canada. Talking about master licensing at the 12th International Franchise and Retail Show, Franchise India 2014, Hanrahan stresses on the importance of due diligence, understanding of the brand, company ethics and culture, customers say by the licensee before approaching the licensor.', 'Franchisor, Licensing, Brand, Due Diligence, Cleaning Service', '05:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4650, 'A', '2015-04-30 15:16:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1724, 'GIaQCGqHglw', NULL, 'Marie Claire to debut in India', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Starting from a magazine, Marie Claire has set benchmarks while expanding to various segments, lifestyle being one of them. The brand is looking to enter the Indian market with launch of women wear. In a conversation with Retailer Media, Fabrice TAUPIN, Vice President - Licensing, Marie Claire Group talked about the journey of brand from glossy pages to lifestyle, licensing in India and preferred markets for expansion.', 'Marie Claire, lifestyle brand, licensing in India, women wear', '05:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2511, 'A', '2015-05-01 09:37:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1725, 'Gf-ON6apAyk', NULL, 'Private equity firms look for scalability in business:  Mousum Pal Choudhury, &#8206;Senior Vice President, Avigo Capital Partners', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Private equity capital comes in when the business is growing, working and is stabilized. At this stage, the requirement of growth capital is immense. India is emerging hub for growing companies, so, the requirement of private equity capital is the need of the hour.  During the Entrepreneur Summit 2014, Mr. Mousum Pal Choudhury, &#8206;Senior Vice President at Avigo Capital Partners, said, the private equity fund will definitely come in, if, there is scalability in business. Mostly private equity firms look for the scalability in business and to attract PE fund, companies need to maintain it.', 'Private Equity, Entrepreneurship, business, private equity fund, Avigo Capital Partners, Entrepreneur Summit 2014', '05:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2814, 'A', '2015-05-02 15:05:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1726, 'UECU-CvF2P0', NULL, 'HiDesign thinking of franchising the brand:  Narresh Mehta, Chief Operating Officer, HiDesign', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'During the Entrepreneur Summit 2014, many entrepreneurs gave their views about the growing trend of entrepreneurship in the country, Mr. Narresh Mehta, Chief Operating Officer, HiDesign, said that they want to improve their brand name in the potential market. The company is currently working towards achieving this goal. HiDesign is thinking of franchising the brand-a step that they will be taking for the first time. HiDesign will focus on producing products keeping in mind the taste of the customers.', 'HiDesign, Entrepreneurship, branding, HiDesign products, Entrepreneur Summit 2014', '06:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3493, 'A', '2015-05-02 15:06:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1727, 'cgcdb0NTS0Q', NULL, 'Bank funding is essential to MSMEs:  P S Rawat, Executive Director, Canara Bank', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Without bank funding, the entrepreneurship can be boosted in India. Finance plays a major role in the development of entrepreneurs in the country.  Opining his views during the Entrepreneur Summit 2014 Mr. P S Rawat, Executive Director, Canara Bank, said, that Canara Bank has always focused on MSME lending in the country and the loan disbursement to the MSMEs is also quite impressive. Canara Bank will further focus on companies who have taken franchising and help them with lending activities. ', 'Canara Bank, Entrepreneurship, bank funding, MSMEs, Franchising, Entrepreneur Summit 2014', '06:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3688, 'A', '2015-05-02 15:08:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1728, 'ATVKPjmDW1U', NULL, 'There is an opportunity in abundance in the online medium: Rahul Narvekar, CEO, Indianroots', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'The online penetration has picked up in India tremendously over the years. Mr. Rahul Narvekar, Founder CEO, Indianroots, said, during the Entrepreneur Summit 2014, that as long as people are liking your products and willing to purchase stuff online, there is no harm in selling products through the online platform. There is an opportunity in abundance in the online medium. ', 'Online, Entrepreneurship, customers, Entrepreneur Summit 2014, Indianroots, products online', '02:39', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 2581, 'A', '2015-05-02 15:09:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1729, 'qMmFJqKmU6s', NULL, 'Car renting business can provide high return of investment: Rajesh Loomba, Managing Director, Eco Rent a Car\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Eco Rent a Car, one of Indias leading car rental and ground transportation companies, is now looking for expansion. With the development of infrastructure in the country, the renting car business has picked up and there is huge potential of growth further. In the Entrepreneurship Summit 2014, Rajesh Loomba, Managing Director, Eco Rent a Car, said, car renting business can provide high return of investment.  ', 'Car renting, Eco car rent, Entrepreneurship, car rental, Entrepreneur Summit 2014, car renting business, entrepreneur', '06:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3678, 'A', '2015-05-02 15:11:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1730, 'mCkwqsXBju0', NULL, 'Tier 2 and Tier 3 markets have opportunity for growth: Samir Sahni, Director, JDS Apparel', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'There is a huge chunk of customers in the potential market that understands fashion and trends. During the Entrepreneurship Summit 2014, Mr. Samir Sahni, Director, JDS Apparel, said, they are trying to capture the customers and provide them with exquisite services through the online media. Focusing on Indian ethnic wears has helped them to capture the Indian market. Tier 2 and Tier 3 markets have the maximum potential and opportunity for growth for JDS Apparel. ', 'Fashion, Ethic wears, Entrepreneurship, online fashion, Entrepreneur Summit 2014, JDS Apparel', '06:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3622, 'A', '2015-05-02 15:12:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1731, 'm19afqedqLg', NULL, 'E-commerce firms are performing well: Sanjeev Asthana, Founder, I-Farm Venture Advisors', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Many e-commerce business are starting their business venture and soon they are closing down their shops on account of lack of scalability. Opining his views during the Entrepreneurship Summit 2014, Mr. Sanjeev Asthana, Founder &#8206;and Managing Partner, I-Farm Venture Advisors Pvt Ltd, said, the challenge for such firms is putting everything together in order to meet the business objectives. Companies that have availed small funding and have been running their business in the e-commerce space are performing well enough in the market.', 'E-commerce, small funding, venture fund, Entrepreneurship, online fashion, Entrepreneur Summit 2014, I-farm ventures, e-retailers', '03:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2566, 'A', '2015-05-02 15:14:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1732, 'XzQXgwu6qLo', NULL, 'We need to match the market requirement of India: Sayed Habib, Head of Buying & Business Development, Danube Home', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Opportunity in the Indian market in growing tremendously for home furnishing products. During the Entrepreneur Summit 2014, Mr Sayed Habib, Business Head Franchise, Head of Buying & Business Development, Danube Home, said, that the market sentiments of Dubai is different than that of India. Indian market is different in terms of product line, services, marketing, and market expectations. As the condition of India is different, Danube Home needs to match this market requirement.', 'Home furnishing, Danube Home, India Home furnishing, Entrepreneurship, Home furnishing products, Entrepreneur Summit 2014, Franchise, products', '11:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4557, 'A', '2015-05-02 15:16:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1733, 'kTvZOcDfWEk', NULL, 'Blend of innovation & commitment can achieve sustainable institutions - Part1', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While discussing building sustainable education, panellist highlighted that building a sustainable institutions means to build a brand which represent quality, excellence, focus on growth within the schools or across the schools. And if these are supported by the dose of innovation and extraordinary commitment than one can easily achieve sustainable institutions.', 'Sustainable education, Schools, Ryan International Group of Institutions, World Education Foundation, People Combine Education Initiatives, Delhi Public School- R K Puram', '22:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3505, 'A', '2015-05-05 09:22:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1734, '3yJ9axcH6yI', NULL, 'Brand building is a must for every educational institutes - Part2', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While discussing on what type of companies are going to spend in educational institutions or the educational entities which make them bigger, panellist highlighted even if one had a great education institute or entity the brand power has to be very large and one need to build it. So if one wants companies to invest in their educational institutes they clearly need to work on their brand building.', 'Brand building, Educational entities, Aurum Equity Partners LLP, Kaizen Management Advisors, Franchise India, Indus Balaji Private Equity, JGI Group of Institutions, ASPIRE Human Capital Management', '13:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3275, 'A', '2015-05-05 09:23:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1735, 'YkEcJmlVdW4', NULL, 'Brand building is a must for every educational institutes - Part1\r\n', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While discussing on what type of companies are going to spend in educational institutions or the educational entities which make them bigger, panellist highlighted even if one had a great education institute or entity the brand power has to be very large and one need to build it. So if one wants companies to invest in their educational institutes they clearly need to work on their brand building.', 'Brand building, Educational entities, Aurum Equity Partners LLP, Kaizen Management Advisors, Franchise India, Indus Balaji Private Equity, JGI Group of Institutions, ASPIRE Human Capital Management', '20:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2944, 'A', '2015-05-05 09:26:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1736, '96AVup6qElg', NULL, 'Blend of innovation & commitment can achieve sustainable institutions - Part2 ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While discussing building sustainable education, panellist highlighted that building a sustainable institutions means to build a brand which represent quality, excellence, focus on growth within the schools or across the schools. And if these are supported by the dose of innovation and extraordinary commitment than one can easily achieve sustainable institutions.', 'Sustainable education, Schools, Ryan International Group of Institutions, World Education Foundation, People Combine Education Initiatives, Delhi Public School- R K Puram', '17:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3609, 'A', '2015-05-05 09:27:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1737, 'RzZTH6PfZTQ', NULL, 'Attitude and behaviour development should be given more focus', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While highlighting the  importance of attitude, behaviour and softer element of being adaptable, creative and innovative Bhaskar Thyagarajan, Director of Bluesky Learning said that these elements are as equally important as the other aspect of the child development. He further said that they are focusing on the area of attitude and behaviour development but in a model that uses technology, experiential learning as a platform and create something saleable so that they are able to influence lot more student specially in towns and cities that down have access to. ', 'Bhaskar Thyagarajan, Bluesky Learning, Experimental learning, Child development', '06:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3568, 'A', '2015-05-05 09:30:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1738, 'cSINvrLvIKU', NULL, 'Learning leads to successful leader face', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting on the changes which schools need, Pramod Tripathi, Academic President of Greenwood High said we really do not see much of change in terms of schooling with the expectation of 10 percent schools which exist across the Indian Territory; still the methods of teaching in most of our school is traditional ways. But with time when things are changing obliviously, one need to see the technology, curriculum, student and teacher everyone has to change keeping in mind that globally every area is changing than why not learning as learning will lead to successful leader face. ', 'Future schools, Traditional education, Pramod Tripathi, Greenwood High  ', '13:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3879, 'A', '2015-05-05 09:32:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1739, '93NeHaJ9SQM', NULL, 'Need bring change in pedagogies to bring out best in a child', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting on the changes which schools need, Shalini Nambiar, Deputy Director of GEMS Education said we need to have a change in our pedagogies so that we can take out best in a child. She further said pulse of the schools is teacher and nothing can replace a teacher not even technology. So in 21st century the future schools, a lot of focus by the promoter when they are starting a school is all about the teachers.', 'Future schools, Shalini Nambiar, GEMS Education', '07:04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3513, 'A', '2015-05-05 09:33:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1740, 'CoXAoo1KC2Y', NULL, 'Quality of education is most significant parameter for nations development', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Sharad Jaipuria, Chairman of Jaipuria Institute of Management highlighted that the development of the individual, society and nation is closely linked to the talent and skills of its people and this can only be achieved when people have access to quality of education. ', 'Jaipuria Institute of Management, Sharad Jaipuria, Skill development, Quality education', '13:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 3151, 'A', '2015-05-05 09:34:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1741, 'n7kY4zBxkEc', NULL, 'Overhauling technology in Education space ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While highlighting tangible issues in putting technology programme together, panellist said education is preparing individual to be effective learners, contributors to a society that itself in the ethos of change. Technology in education follows a cycle. Wherever the technology is introduce in the market there is the hype in the market. Technology in education is todays scenario is the need of the hour.     ', 'Technology education, Discover Tomorrow Campaign, Ricoh India Ltd.', '07:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2499, 'A', '2015-05-05 09:41:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1742, 'fUSMvd043Gs', NULL, 'CSR will take our country to the top of the ladder', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While discussing on what one can offer to promote CSR, panellist highlighted that one need to identify right organisation or the individual those are able to attract talent, one that can create aspiration of those people. One need to developed necessary infrastructure where one can tap these potential and create human potential what will take our country to the top of the ladder. ', 'CSR, , iWatch Foundation, Piramal Foundation, IDFC Foundatin, Bhaktivedanta Gurukul and International School, Thermax India   ', '22:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2500, 'A', '2015-05-05 09:42:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1743, 'O8ORVQFHhtM', NULL, 'IP Protection laws sufficient enough', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Armed with a degree in engineering, Madhav Prabhala has more than 18 years of work experience across cross-functional delivery in television, online media and corporate trainings. He has contributed to Green Gold\\\'s licensing and brand building endeavors. Now, as an honorable member of LIMA, Prabhala suggests the benefit of LIMA membership to licensee and licensors and the possible steps by government for IP protection, along with briefing about the licensing industry in India.', 'Licensing in India, Indian Retail Congress 2015, IP Protection, character licensing, Chhota Bheem, LIMA', '05:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3945, 'A', '2015-05-05 12:17:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1744, 'gt-XgJCS3lg', NULL, 'Indianroots at other side of spectrum', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Indianroots, An NDTV ethnic retail venture bestowed the Pure Play eRetailer of the Year award atIndian Retail Congress 2015. In an exclusive conversation with Retailer, Rahul Narvekar, CEO & co-founder, Indianroots shared his thoughts about the inception of brand as an online-only venture, the success story while beingnot-so-open to COD, later on the gradual shift to COD and the market for online ethnic retail in India, where people are particular about the look and feel of ethnic wear.', 'ethnic retail, online retail, eCommerce, Indianroots, Rahul Narvekar, Indian Retail Congress 2015, dynamic pricing', '03:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3595, 'A', '2015-05-05 12:23:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1745, '5Fu_-3WL8vs', NULL, 'Marie Claire plans licensing with Bradford License India', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Marie Claire has teamed up with Bradford License India to expand its portfolio in India through licensing. Fabrice Taupin, Vice President - Licensing, Marie Claire Group shared his views about the licensing strategies, role of Bradford as a licensing partner and future ahead in market of India. ', 'Marie Claire, lifestyle brand, licensing in India, women’s wear, Bradford License India, Licensing Industry', '03:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 2123, 'A', '2015-05-05 15:36:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1746, '03EKfgyiExc', NULL, 'I have huge expansion plans with Monsoon salons: Vidya Tikari', 9, '', NULL, '', 43, 'She is stylish, sassy and chic. Celebrity make-up artist Vidya Tikari do not need an elaborate introduction. Deft at managing fashion extravaganzas, wedding season rush and professional make-up workshops, this self-motivated woman has achieved a lot in the beauty and make-up industry. After successfully making a niche in make-up industry, Tikari has now attained a new level of expertise, as a Business Woman, by joining hands with Rod Anker, a Celebrity stylist and Owner of Monsoon Salon. In a candid conversation with Wellness India, Tikari unveils some unknown facts about her career, business and her make-up brushes range and much more.', 'salons, make-up, beauty, Vidya Tikari, wellness, venture, business, cosmetics brands', '05:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 7269, 'A', '2015-05-06 09:28:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1747, 'UmcpE-G_-68', NULL, 'Back-to-school most lucrative in licensing', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Cartoon Network Enterprises (CNE), the licensing and merchandising arm of Turner Broadcasting System Asia Pacific, is expanding portfolio of its popular IP Ben 10 by leaps and bounds in South Asia. During Indian Retail Congress 2015, Anand Singh, Director-South Asia, Turner International Pvt. Ltd. shared his view point about the lucrative categories for licensing, the upcoming markets in South Asia, and new domains for lending out IPs. Also, she talked about LIMA and the benefits of LIMA membership for a licensee/ licensor. ', 'Cartoon Network, Turner, Ben 10, Anand Singh, LIMA, Licensing Industry, character licensing, Indian Retail Congress 2015', '05:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4214, 'A', '2015-05-06 09:32:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1748, '23qfKC1rSLs', NULL, 'Total Solutions Group: Revolutionizing the solution game ', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Malhotra, MD and Founder, Total Solutions Group talks about how his company is helping companies finding market entry strategy, operational excellence and working out innovative, out-of-the-box solutions to help them increase the top line and profitability. In a candid chat with Retailer media, Kapil also puts light on how solutions will pan out for the Indian ecosystem.', 'Kapil Malhotra, Total Solutions Group, Consulting, Tier 4 and Tier 5 cities, mystery audits ', '05:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2533, 'A', '2015-05-06 14:07:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1749, 'bcsYKfn3EY4', NULL, 'CDIT growing at 15% year-on-year', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Manish Sharma, Managing Director, Panasonic India and South Asia talks on how the CDIT is one of the blue-chip segments of the retail ecosystem in the country. Citing the relaxation of FDI norms of the 90s as one of the main reasons behind industrys boom, in a brief chat with the Retailer media, Bajaj believes that India is fast catching up with retail experiences of the West.', 'Manish Sharma, Panasonic, CDIT, steady growth, efficient supply chain, record growth, retail, West  ', '02:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2157, 'A', '2015-05-06 14:09:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1750, '_dbTH2CE1c0', NULL, 'Ecommerce will remain a fraction of the total retail market', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Piyush Kumar Sinha, Chairperson, IIM - A, Centre for Retailing believes that although consumers of today understand eCommerce fully, there are challenges that the industry is facing. The experience that any eTail player is providing to its consumer is not the best and therefore, the dynamics, he opines, have changed from being a pure retail perspective to price.', 'Piyush Kumar Sinha, IIM - A, centre for retailing, Indian retail congress and awards, eCommerce, mCommerce', '04:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2828, 'A', '2015-05-06 14:11:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1751, 'rIRO_uhgGZs', NULL, 'GreenDust to become a Rs 300 billion company: Hitendra Chaturvedi', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Hitendra Chaturvedi is the Founder and CEO of Reverse Logistic Company GreenDust. Before starting GreenDust, Hitendra was the business unit head for Microsoft OEM business in India. And before Microsoft, he was instrumental in building an IT enabled reverse logistics company in the US (Newgistics). A computer engineer from IIT with an MS and MBA from US, Hitendra has over 20 years of experience in software/IT, multi-channel retail, and supply chain solutions. ', 'GreenDust, Reverse Logistic, supply chain, Hitendra Chaturvedi, entrepreneur, Newgistics', '07:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5513, 'A', '2015-05-06 14:15:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1752, '-ccAd9FAVtU', NULL, 'Importance of Technology in boosting workforce productivity by Sachin Bhatia', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Speaking at Indian Restaurant Congress 2014, Sachin Bhatia, VP- Business Development, Drishti Soft Pvt Ltd points How can restaurateurs revolutionize Restaurant Industry by Technology deployment that enhances user experience, boosts workforce productivity, and reduces operational costs', 'Sachin Bhatia, Technology, Mobile Technology, Supply Chain, Restaurant, Food Business', '06:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2045, 'A', '2015-05-06 14:21:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1753, 'Nf3b_GUIOIQ', NULL, 'How technology has helped him come up with his venture Foodbox by Satish Chamyvelumani', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Speaking at Indian Restaurant Congress, Satish Chamyvelumani shares his experience of coming up with a 90-second delivery through supply chain innovation and technological enablement. And how Foodbox works with multiple restaurants within the city and retails through fully automated restaurants.', 'Innovation in Food, Food Business, Foodbox, Supply Chain', '11:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3615, 'A', '2015-05-06 14:23:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1754, 'pxtO8OUvCJw', NULL, 'How investment scenario in India has changed over the years by Siddharth Bafna', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Talking at Indian Restaurant Congress, Siddharth Bafna, Partner & Head (Corporate Finance), Lodha & Co believes, that there will be a lot of opportunities for new restaurant chains to emerge and for the able ones to raise venture capital or private equity in times to come.', 'Siddharth Bafna, Investor, PE, VC, Fund Raising, Restaurants', '02:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3408, 'A', '2015-05-06 14:24:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1755, '0TpzaFAqphM', NULL, 'Food business and eating habits of customers by Virender S Datta', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Talking at Indian Restaurant Congress, Chef Virender S Datta, Founder and Chairman, International Institute of Culinary Arts shares How food business scenario in India is changing with change in customers palate and taste.', 'Food Business, Chef, Dining Attitudes, Cuisine, Eating Habits, Virender S Datta', '11:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3282, 'A', '2015-05-06 14:26:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1756, 'eEEDVZKv_ZI', NULL, 'US-based Vantage Hospitality Head unveils franchise plans in Indian market', 1, '', NULL, '', 11, 'Vantage Hospitality, which entered in India recently through Master License Agreement with Miraya Hotel Management for Value Hotel and Value Inn Brands, has huge expansion plans. In an exclusive conversation with Franchise India Bureau, Roger Bloss, Founder, President & CEO, Vantage Hospitality Group shared his plans to tap untouched locations in the country, reason for the late entry of the brand into Indian market, discloses that if he gets the opportunity to sub-franchise his brand in India, he would surely go ahead.', 'Master Franchisee,  Vantage Hospitality, USA, expansion plans, Miraya Hotel Management, Value Inn Brand', '05:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 4141, 'A', '2015-05-07 12:14:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1757, '4gvxaZh34gI', NULL, 'Every SME needs location based discovery says Ronak Samantray, Co-Founder, Now Floats', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'An ex-employee of Microsoft, Ronak Samantaray founded Now Floats, which allows the users to create a website for their organization and update it through a simple mobile app. Aiming to use the power of internet to make a difference in the functioning of SMEs, he talked about the model of operation of Now Floats, the market size and how Now Floats is detangling the complications of a local business retailer. ', 'SME, Now Floats, Ronak Samantray, Indian Retail Congress 2015', '03:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3403, 'A', '2015-05-07 12:17:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1758, 'wS3C_PmcsNw', NULL, 'Being Human about fashion, celebrity and charity', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'While Being Human is better known for the Bhai connection, its clothing rights res exclusively with Mandhana Industries Ltd. during an interaction with Retailer media at Indian Retail Congress 2015, Manish Mandhana, the Managing Director of group narrates the saga of donning the role of retailer with inception of Being Human, take on online retail and the expansion strategies around the brand.', 'Being Human, Mandhana industries, Manish Mandhana, Salman Khan, eCommerce, Omnichannel strategies, Indian Retail Congress 2015', '02:58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4924, 'A', '2015-05-07 12:21:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1759, '8kbYlpya_ls', NULL, 'GOQii is not a new product, but a new category', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'In the present day, there may be many a tech entrepreneur are juggling with the idea of introducing and selling neatly packaged wearables, but what GOQii is doing is not only a notch above ordinary, it is taking charge of your own fitness and lifestyle goals by way of personal coaching. Lets talk to Abhishek, GOQii chief marketing officer and know how many lives and habits the tech-band has helped change and the company future plans.', 'Abhishek Sharma, GOQii, CMO, tech wearable, fitness and lifestyle industry, personal coaching', '06:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4610, 'A', '2015-05-07 12:32:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1760, 'pGqGw_BToIY', NULL, 'In supermarket retail, customers behave like optimists', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'The customers are becoming digitally literate and are embracing the option of going online for their purchases increasingly. While the barriers and hesitation of trying to buy online is going down, but last mile models are yet to evolve. Let us ask Damodar Mall, Chief Executive Officer, Grocery Retail at Reliance Retail, what are his take on the explosion of choice that is available for customers today.', 'E-commerce, Damodar Mall, Reliance Retail, Grocery, new products and categories', '02:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4159, 'A', '2015-05-07 12:36:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1761, 'cDg6pMKNWyk', NULL, 'Retail explosion to be mobile centric', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Given the retail world is going digital, mobile commerce is the next big evolution, said Samir Modi, Managing Director, Modi Enterprises while addressing at the Indian Retail Congress 2015. Also he spoke about the demands driven by geography, the operational model of Colorbar and expansion strategies. ', 'Samir Modi, Modi Enterprises, eCommerce, Omni-channel strategies, m-Commerce, Colorbar, Indian Retail Congress 2015', '03:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3601, 'A', '2015-05-08 09:05:47', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1762, '0vuyMfmcnM0', NULL, 'The organised players are growing faster in jewel segment', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'The gems and jewellery industry is growing at a steady 25 per cent CAGR, partly because of the rise in prices of raw materials Gold and Diamonds and partly because the market itself is growing as the economy is growing. Retailer media caught up with Sanjeev Agarwal, CEO, Gitanjali Exports Corporation Ltd to shed more light on the same.   ', 'Gitanjali exports, Asmi, Sangini, DeBeers, gems and jewellery market, Sanjeev Agarwal, eCommerce, mCommerce, market share, Tanishq, Reliance', '09:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4491, 'A', '2015-05-08 09:08:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1763, 'wgjsQtdBYNQ', NULL, 'Enamor on lingerie market and lack of awareness ', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Enamor is one of the premium lingerie brand operating in all possible formats of retail including MBO, EBO, online and offline. Speaking at Indian Retail Congress 2015, Chief Operating Officer of the brand - Preeti Gupta shared the insights of this segment of retail industry and the growth prospects along with special emphasis on the lack of education regarding innerwear and the advantage served by eCommerce. ', 'Preeti Gupta, Enamor India, Lingerie Industry, Indian Retail Congress 2015', '04:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3949, 'A', '2015-05-08 09:10:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1764, 'pqMKNnrmYbE', NULL, 'Chhota Bheem to compete with global superheroes', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Green Gold Animations, popularly known for their in-house character Chhota Bheem are monetizing every opportunity of licensing and merchandising around this IP. Speaking at Indian Retail Congress 2015, Srinivas Chilakalapudi, Chief Strategy Officer, Green Gold Animations emphasized on how Chhota Bheem has taken upon the international superheroes, innovative categories around it and its contribution to LIMA. ', 'Srinivas Chilakalapudi, Green Gold Animations, Licensing Industry, character licensing, Chhota Bheem, Indian superhero, Indian Retail Congress 2015', '03:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5140, 'A', '2015-05-08 09:12:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1765, '9Ni1lqyJuWw', NULL, 'India to taste first ever Black Burger by Rohit Malhotra', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Revealing first ever Black Burger in India, Rohit Malhotra, GM Operations, Barcelos India shares the journey of Black Burger which started from the US Japan and now India. And ingredients used in making the burger.', 'Burger, Burger Player, Barcelos India, Burger King, Peri Peri Chain', '02:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2029, 'A', '2015-05-08 12:43:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1766, 'ysXckdjyjWE', NULL, 'Celio talks of franchising, retail and eCommerce ', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Franchising is not just an expansion strategy, but also an opportunity for brand creation, says Rajiv Nair, Chief Executive Officer, Ceilo Future Fashion Limited during a conversation with Retailer media at Indian Retail Congress 2015.', 'Rajiv Nair, Ceilo Future Fashion, menswear, French brand, franchising, IRC 2015', '04:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3590, 'A', '2015-05-13 09:30:47', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1767, 'W6ISgQ-wRLc', NULL, 'Crossword is focusing into Tier II and Tier III penetration', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Retailer Media caught up with Kinjal Shah, CEO at Crossword Book Stores to know about their decision of penetrating into the Tier II and Tier III cities and their resolve to open at least 10 stores every year. As for metros, the only challenge the bookstore faces is in terms of selling music and films owing to increasing copyright violations and sees the \\\'Toy\\\' category coming up in a big way.', 'Kinjal Shah, Crossword Book Stores, growth plan, eCommerce, mCommerce', '06:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2757, 'A', '2015-05-13 09:33:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1768, 'Sf-ktxZUvIA', NULL, 'BigBasket has grown 25 times in the last three years', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'BigBasket.com, of which Abhinay Chaudhary is the Co-founder, has the lion share in the online grocery marketplace with 70-80 per cent market share. The only marketplace to be present in 5 cities in the country, which is witnessing a growth of 15-20 per cent month-on-month, BigBasket is ready to expand to newer cities.', 'Online grocery, BigBasket, Abhinay Chaudhary, mCommerce, Tier II cities ', '02:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3519, 'A', '2015-05-13 09:34:47', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(1769, '6YSroZl5KPU', NULL, 'Entrepreneur India 2014', 2, '', NULL, '', 17, 'Entrepreneur India 2014, the 4th National Convention on Entrepreneurship has become the marquee entrepreneurship event on building enterprising entrepreneurs in India. The event attracted over 300 leading entrepreneurs and members from the Indian investor community together with CEOs and professionals leading Growth oriented organizations. Held by Franchise India Media on 18th & 19th July 2014 at Hotel Vivanta by Taj, Surajkund, Delhi NCR.\r\nWith more than 400+ attendees, 70+ Global experts and 30+ award categories, along with global market reach through print and electronic media. \r\nThe mission of Entrepreneur India is to capture the business logic of the networked era while keeping a sharp eye for what is relevant, real, and actionable for opening a treasure trove of real possibilities for business to grow in a new world. Entrepreneur India 2014 aimed to reach out to the larger community by creating multiple platforms of interaction beyond the scope of the main event.\r\nEntrepreneur India is designed for business owners, women entrepreneurs, start-ups, and student enablers to provide the entire entrepreneurial ecosystem with a nurturing environment in which all could learn through the sharing of knowledge, experience information. The convention is designed on the theme of 7is which are: Inspire Ideate, Individualize, Incubate, Innovate, and Invest and internationalize. To celebrate entrepreneurs who have contributed extensively towards the growth of entrepreneurship in our country, Franchise India also organizes the prestigious Entrepreneur India Awards along with the convention. The awards give national recognition to the most inspiring entrepreneurial entities across the country in their respective sectors.', 'Entrepreneur Conference, Entrepreneur Awards, Entrepreneur Summit, Entrepreneur Exhibition, Pitch room, Start up funding, Business conference, National entrepreneur convention', '01:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 6688, 'A', '2015-05-13 15:01:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1770, 'k40UQPpthQM', NULL, 'Zopper to be the Google for buyers ', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'The Delhi-based price comparison start-up, Zopper which was earlier known for its user-generated product reviews, has re-branded itself to a platform where buyers can locate the merchants in their vicinity. Neeraj Jain, Co-Founder, Zopper talks to Retailer Media about the app , the research-online-purchase-offline trend and the strategies to promote online transaction.', 'Neeraj Jain, Zopper, eCommerce industry, hyperlocal marketplace', '04:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4197, 'A', '2015-05-13 15:03:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1771, 'vjwVwX716Ko', NULL, 'I doubt that Tier II and Tier III is not getting growth in eCommerce', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Anil Goteti, Senior Director - Business, Flipkart talks to the Retailer media about the opportunity Flipkart is providing to local home and furniture sellers to sell their products online and reach beyond the state boundaries. Although nascent, Goteti suggests, home and furniture is oen segment that is picking up fast.', 'Anil Goteti, Flipkart, home and furniture, eCommerce, tier II and tier III cities, mCommerce, mobile penetratio', '03:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5189, 'A', '2015-05-13 15:05:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1772, 'W5N-DAlu7cc', NULL, 'When I becomes we, illness becomes wellness: Naturals Salon Co-founder - Part 2 ', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'At the 4th Indian Salon and Wellness Congress 2015, leading salon chains Naturals Co-founder and MD, CK Kumaravel shared his views over growth opportunities lying ahead into the wellness space. He also raised the areas where the wellness professionals are lacking. The franchising king talked about 5000 years old Ancient science of Ayurveda which will revamp under AYUSH ministry and expressed his views over financial independence of women. He stressed on the fact, learn to earn more and much more.', 'CK Kumaravel, Naturals Salon, franchise business, wellness, growth', '10:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4409, 'A', '2015-05-14 15:36:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1773, 'J2q9Scv1OiE', NULL, 'When I becomes we, illness becomes wellness: Naturals Salon Co-founder - Part 1\r\n', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'At the 4th Indian Salon and Wellness Congress 2015, leading salon chains Naturals Co-founder and MD, CK Kumaravel shared his views over growth opportunities lying ahead into the wellness space. He also raised the areas where the wellness professionals are lacking. The franchising king talked about 5000 years old Ancient science of Ayurveda which will revamp under AYUSH ministry and expressed his views over financial independence of women. He stressed on the fact, learn to earn more and much more.', 'CK Kumaravel, Naturals Salon, franchise business, wellness, growth', '17:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4832, 'A', '2015-05-14 15:39:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1774, '8tm3DAQ7n0Y', NULL, 'Beauty industry is an exciting place to be at the moment: Blossom Kochhar', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Addressing the audience at the 4th Indian Salon and Wellness Congress 2015, veteran Beauty Expert Dr. Blossom Kochhar, Founder & Chairperson, Blossom Kochhar Group of Companies, shared her views over the consumers preferences and the concept of grooming in the wellness space, taken up by male consumers, its vast scope in the industry, bringing great opportunities for the wellness professionals, emerging market for child grooming etc. She also brought forward the issues concerning limited trained manpower and lack of knowledge of technical advance, which is affecting the overall industry growth and much more.', 'Beauty expert, wellness industry, male grooming, consumers, Blossom Kochhar', '11:43', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4716, 'A', '2015-05-14 15:40:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1775, 'B6oJLNdk1-Q', NULL, 'Issues pertaining to funding of salon business need to be addressed: Kashiff Khan', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Addressing the gathering at the 4th Indian Salon and Wellness Congress 2015, Kashiff Khan, Founder & Chairman, The K Group, shared some very interesting points pertaining to the funding of wellness business. He said the industry professionals and experts need to come together and become one voice to the financial institutions, government bodies and to the different government grants. Khan also noted that the franchising in India is yet to mature fully and much more.', 'fitness industry, Kashiff Khan, The K Group, wellness, growth, funding, eCommerce', '06:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 213, 'D', '2015-05-14 15:41:47', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1776, 'M5GA0QAzgrs', NULL, 'Distances are vanishing and boundaries are becoming smaller with technology: Sachin Kamat', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'While moderating one of the sessions at 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress, Sachin Kamat, Director, Employee & Customer Engagement, Enrich Salon and Academies, Mumbai highlighted 3Ps of wellness business; people, products and processes, which is revolutionized by technology. He said, technology can umpire our business, but it cannot replace it. The industry expert noted points like integration with manufacturers, modern and traditional trade, Return on time Invested and much more.', 'Sachin Kamat, Enrich salon, wellness industry, technology, trade, growth', '07:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2657, 'D', '2015-05-14 15:47:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1777, 'WSGsJqXK9G4', NULL, 'Service industry, the base is only foundation: Jawed Habib', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Known as the scissor man, Celebrity Hairstylist Jawed Habib was one of the esteemed speakers at the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress, who stressed on the need to spread awareness among professionals by educating them. The veteran hairstylist shared his current initiatives towards spreading education across every nook & corner of the country by organizing campaigns, opening JH salons and funding educational practices.', 'Jawed Habib, Salon, hairstylist, scissor man, wellness business, education', '06:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3200, 'A', '2015-05-14 15:48:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1778, 'Z3hF1D7Apz8', NULL, 'Employees are not trained enough to meet consumers expectations: Sandeep Ahuja', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Highlighting the issues concerning the future growth of beauty and wellness industry, Sandeep Ahuja, Managing Director & Group CEO, VLCC Healthcare Ltd, shared his views over dire need to hone skills of wellness professionals to meet high expectations of the consumers. He insisted on the service delivery standards to raised high. He also admitted that instead of imposing regulations and norms, self-restrain yourself and much more.', 'employee, staff training, wellness industry, salons, spas, beauty market, education', '08:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4849, 'A', '2015-05-14 15:49:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1779, 'NDLulUODpuk', NULL, 'Hospitality is the driving factor of service industry: Priscilla Corner', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Priscilla Corner, Managing Partner, June Tomkyns Salons, Kolkata expressed her views over driving factors of service industry. In her speech, the highlight point was hospitality. She insisted that with the mushrooming of salons and spas across India, the demand for high quality maintenance is a must, but hospitality is equally essential. Thus, the staff must be trained well to talk to the consumers gently and offer best possible support in selecting services.', 'hospitality, wellness, service industry, salons, spas, beauty, employees', '08:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4993, 'A', '2015-05-14 15:50:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1780, 'AKZeS_CUihI', NULL, 'Dire need to polish skills of industry professionals: Samir Srivastav', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Weighing the two important aspects of beauty and wellness business; employee and consumer, Indian Chief Executive Officer (CEO), Jean-Claude Biguine Salon & Spa, Samir Srivastav said, the employees are rough cut diamonds, the more you polish, the better they will shine. He also shared tips like advance planning, preparing a service calendar and uplifting service standards may brings home growth for a salon professional. He also commented on the ancient science of Ayurveda and evolving consumer behaviour of Indian consumers.', 'Jean-Claude Biguine, salon, spa, wellness industry, Ayurveda, services', '10:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6272, 'A', '2015-05-14 15:54:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1781, 'BG-CWBzRfwc', NULL, 'Empowering retailers with an end-to-end commerce platform', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Reshma Nagpal, Founder & CEO, E Bee Global Solutions Pvt. Ltd., caught up with Retailer Media and shared how the business helps retailers to grown in the market going omni-channel by using and end-to-end solution. ', 'Reshma Nagpal, E Bee, retail, omni-channel, Indian Retail Congress', '03:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2130, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:22:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1782, 'KIhe59y-rkk', NULL, 'Businesses solving the pain points of customers are worth investing', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Padmaja Ruparel, President, Indian Angel Network caught up with Retailer Media and shared her views on getting business plans from young startups and what makes them invest into these startups. Also she shared her vision on the future of retail industry in India.  ', 'Padmaja Ruparel, Indian Angel Network, Retail, eCommerce, Franchising', '06:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2370, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:24:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1783, 'cXndYgzTKvI', NULL, 'Customer trust in mobile payment is getting stronger day by day', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Nilay Patel, Chief Executive Officer, EasyPay Pvt. Ltd. caught up with Retailer Media and shared his views on the today and tomorrow of mobile payment industry in India and their initiative to gain customer trust in online payments.', 'Nilay Patel, EasyPay, m-Commerce, mobile payment, Indian Retail Congress ', '07:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3746, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:26:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1784, 'FB5P_kgo1nY', NULL, 'SMEs going digital will lead this industry to new heights ', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Manav Sethi, Group Head, Marketing and Digital Strategy, AskMe.com caught up with Retailer Media and shared this thoughts on the growth and opportunities that lies within the retail industry and how will the future look like.', 'Manav Sethi, AskMe.com, e-Commerce, m-Commerce, omni-channel retail', '05:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2418, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:27:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1785, '1Gw-SYwXYZ4', NULL, 'RICOH will grow along with the retail industry', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Jitender Sharma, Business Head- Strategic Business Vertical, RICOH caught up with Retailer Media and shared his thoughts on how retailers can use sources like RICOH to grow their businesses. He also believes that e-commerce will play a vital role in uplifting the market size.', 'Jitender Sharma, RICOH, retail, omni-channel, Indian Retail Congress', '06:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2080, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:31:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1786, 'JNgTrI-NMsQ', NULL, 'Tier II and III cities vital role in scaling up m-Commerce in India', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'At the Indian Retail Congress 2015, Hitendra Chaturvedi, CEO & Founder, GreenDust caught up with Retailer Media and shared his thoughts on scope of modern and traditional retail when it comes to e-commerce way. He also said that the internet is birth right of everyone and we should keep it free.', 'Hitendra Chaturvedi, GreenDust, e-Commerce, Net Neutrality, Indian Retail Congress', '06:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2946, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:34:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1852, 'yUXscIJvjpM', NULL, 'Customers expectation from retail is a big driving factor', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Dr. Anthony Kilili, Capability Director, Communication & Media, dunhumby India caught up with Retailer Media and shared his views and opinion on opportunities that lies within the Indian e-Commere market and believes that India has huge potential to grow much bigger and will soon reach at the top in the global market.', 'Anthony Kilili, dunhumby, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '03:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2442, 'A', '2015-05-22 09:09:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1851, 'D-kPqNaYNxg', NULL, 'Looking to organise the school and college merchandise space', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Ankur Gupta and Arpit Badjatya, &#8206;Co-Founders at Campus Mall Pvt. Ltd. are looking to organise the school and college merchandise space in the country. With service and deliverability being their strong, core areas, they seem to be quite confident about the future of online merchandising business in India.', 'Ankur Gupta and Arpit Badjatya, Campus Mall Pvt. Ltd, premier institutes, merchandise,  licensors, investments', '07:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4205, 'A', '2015-05-22 09:04:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1788, 'g8eiMl8T2XM', NULL, 'Indian Retail has reached a flux point. It is helping offline retail as well', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Shailesh Vickam Singh, Executive Director, Seedfund Ventures talks to us about Seedfund Ventures and kind of startup they pick. He also further elaborated his thoughts on the future of online retail market and how the online retail is helping offline retail to expand.', 'Sailesh Vickram Singh, Seedfund Ventures, online retail, franchising, Indian Retail Congress', '03:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2776, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:40:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1789, 'f1SadzNFu0w', NULL, 'Future acceptability of mobile payment industry in India', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Shashank Joshi, Managing Director, Money-On-Mobile talks to us about the present and the future of mobile payment industry in India and how m-Commerce will facilitate in the growth.', 'Shashank Joshi, Money-on-Mobile, The Reserve Bank of India, mCommerce, mobile payments ', '03:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3112, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:42:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1790, 'e2pCdatvmEw', NULL, 'Monetizing new car and used car buyers', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Umang Kumar, President, Cardekho.com & CEO, Gaadi.com caught up with Retailer Media and shared his views about the dynamics of auto industry in modern retail market and how Cardekho.com has managed to cope up in the competition.', 'Umang Kumar, Cardekho, Gaadi.com, Auto, Retail, Indian Retail Congress', '05:43', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2745, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:43:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1791, '0HJFC_rRNBU', NULL, 'Creating a green house controlled environment for Indian Startups', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Vikram Upadhyaya, Chief Mentor, Acclerator Evangelist &Angel Investor, GHV Acclerator talks to us about creating a controlled environment for pre series A startups and how will the retail market respond in the coming years.', 'Vikram Upadhyaya, GHV Accelerator, investment, Indian startups, e-commerce ', '02:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3262, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:44:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1792, 'gdb1RwcaxWY', NULL, 'Supermarket returns!', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'During the Indian Retail Congress, Vivek Biyani, Director, Future Group & Big Bazaar Direct spoke to Retailer Media on the consumerism that is back again in the supermarket industry and how the professionals will retain their consumers is very important. He is also looking at the Omni-Channel Retailing for Future Group and how to use it for scaling up the business.', 'Vivek Biyani, Big Bazaar, Supermarket, Omni- Channel Retailing, Indian Retail Congress', '01:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3424, 'A', '2015-05-16 09:47:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1793, '0h_NAytqxr8', NULL, 'Abhijit Ray, Co-founder & Managing Director, Unitus Capital', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Abhijit Ray co-founded Unitus Capital in 2008 where he successfully raised capital totalling $900 million for multiple social enterprises in the healthcare, education, microfinance, micro-pension, technology, agriculture sector across Asia. Abhijit is also a Board / Advisory Committee member in a couple of debt and equity fund. Speaking at the Entrepreneur India 2014, Ray highlighted that how social entrepreneurs address the demand of the mass market by delivering products and services in an affordable manner.', 'Unitus Capital, social enterprises, healthcare, education, microfinance', '06:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5348, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:14:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1794, 'wJngZ10YXwE', NULL, 'SME listing platform helps entrepreneurs raise funds: Ashish Chauhan, BSE', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Ashish Kumar Chauhan is the MD & CEO of the BSE Ltd., Asia first stock exchange. He serves on the Board of ICCL, CDSL, BSE Training Institute, BFSI Sector Skill Council and Marketplace Technologies Limited. He is also a member of the Board of Governors of IIIT D&M, Jabalpur and a few SEBI committees. He currently is the Chairman of the Advisory Committee on Technology of FMC, member of several SEBI committees. Speaking at the Entrepreneur India 2014, Chauhan mentioned how SME listing platform can help start-ups to raise funds.', 'BFSI, BSE, SEBI, SME, funds, Entrepreneur India    ', '20:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3253, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:16:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1795, 'yWBeWPPDs68', NULL, 'Credit ratings help SMEs to scale up business: D Ravishankar, Brickworks', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'D. Ravishankar is the Founder Director of Brickwork Ratings, a credit rating agency licensed by SEBI and approved by RBI. He is also the Chairman of the Criteria Committee and a member of the Rating Committee. He is a financial professional with a rich experience of over 25 years in the BFSI segment. Until December 2007, he was the Managing Director of Asia-Pacific Risk Solutions Business of Standard and Poor and was simultaneously heading the India Risk Solutions Business as Executive Director, CRISIL Limited. Ravishanka at Entrepreneur India 2014 highlighted how credits help SMEs to scale up the business. ', 'Brickworks, SMEs, BFSI, CRISIL, RBI, Entrepreneur India', '19:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3987, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:18:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1796, '2Ollcgap50s', NULL, 'Entrepreneur India Award Part 1', 2, '', NULL, '', 16, 'Entrepreneur of the year in Service Business-Money Services award goes to Mr. Shashank Joshi, MD, My Mobile Payments, which simplify payments. \r\nLisa S Rao, founder and Director, I Brands Beverage Ltd has been awarded the Innovative start-ups of the year. The award recognizes Lisa dedication and determination in a relatively short period of time.\r\nEntrepreneur of the year in creating business, e-retailer goes to Manu Agarwal, founder and CEO, Naptol Online Pvt. Ltd. \r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Business, recruitment and HR goes to Udit Mittal, MD, Unisons International Consulting Pvt. Ltd.\r\nSocial Entrepreneur of the year award goes to Navin M Raheja, Chairman and MD, Raheja Developers. \r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Business- Education award goes to Aradhana Khaitan Mahna, founder and MD, Manya Education Pvt. Ltd. \r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Businesses-Consultancy award goes to Varalakshmi Bogale, founder and principle, Green Inertia. \r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Business- SAS and IT Services award goes to Anand Prakash, Director, Zenhancer Technologies Pvt. Ltd.\r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Manufacturing Business-Engineering goes to S. Suresh Barola, Founder Head Operation, Barola Aero Spors.\r\nEntrepreneur of the year (Innovation in Financial Services) award goes to Gopal Verma, Chairman, E-Meditek Global Pvt. Ltd\r\nEntrepreneur of the year (Consumer Business) award goes to Avinash Jain, MD, Arise India Ltd.\r\nSerial entrepreneur of the year award goes to Manoj Agarwal, MD, Adhunik Metaliks Ltd (Adhunik Group)\r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Business- Travel award goes to Rajesh Loomba, MD, Eco Rent A Car.\r\nAcharya of the year/Business Mentor of the Year award goes to Romie Dutt, Executive Director, Sahara Q Shop Unique Products Range Ltd.', 'Entrepreneur India, Awards, Service Business,Innovation,Technology, IT Services, Manufacturing', '12:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 8778, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:20:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1797, 'A4bFBlEF8h0', NULL, 'Entrepreneur India Award Part 2', 2, '', NULL, '', 16, 'Dynamic Entrepreneur of the year (Business Transformation) award goes to Vineet Sharma, MD, Parragon Publishing.\r\nEntrepreneur of the year (Innovation in Technology) award goes to Diwakar Nigam, Chairman and CEO, Newgen Software Technologies Ltd.\r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Trading Business-Distributor award goes to Abhinav Khandelwal, MD, FCML Distributors Pvt. Ltd.\r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Business-SCM and Logistics award goes to Pawan Jain, CMD and founder, Safexpress Pvt. Ltd. \r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Business-financial award goes to Ajay Garg, Whole Time Director, SMC Group.\r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Business-Training award goes to Rohit Aggarwal, CEO, Koenig Solutions Ltd. \r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Business- Security award goes to Maj Manjit Rajain, Chairman, Tenon Group of companies. \r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Business-F&B award goes to Zoraward Kalra, Founder & MD, massive Restaurants Pvt. Ltd.\r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Service Business-Health, Beauty and Wellness award goes to Dr. Kishore Kumar, Chairman & MD, Cloudnine Hospitals.\r\nEntrepreneur of the year in Manufacturing Business-Technology award goes to Santosh Nair, CEO, Camson Biotechnologies.\r\n Entrepreneur of the year in Manufacturing Business-Printing goes to Saurabh Kochhar, Co-founder & MD, Printvenue.com.\r\nProfessional Entrepreneur of the year award goes to Rohit Chadda, Co-founder & CEO, Foodpanda India.\r\nCreative Entrepreneur of the Year award goes to Vikas Gutgutia, Founder & MD, Ferns N Petals Group.\r\nYoung Entrepreneur of the Year award goes to Ayan Chawla, Founder & CEO, Asian Fox developments.\r\nWoman Entrepreneur of the Year award goes to Grace Pinto, MD, Ryan international Group of Institutes.\r\nEntrepreneur of the Year award goes to Davendra Prakash Shah, Chairman, Parag Milk. ', 'Entrepreneur India, Awards, Service Business,Innovation,Technology, IT Services, Manufacturing', '14:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 10516, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:23:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1798, '_-XOMifFE9M', NULL, 'How to create ecosystem to develop entrepreneurship in India: H.P. Kumar, NSIC', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Dr. H. P. Kumar is the Chairman-cum-MD of National Small Industries Corporation, a Mini Ratna Public Sector organization of Government of India. He held senior positions of corporate head of finance & CEO of public sector corporations. He is the Chairman of SME Committee of AIMA and is on the Governing Councils of various professional bodies. Kumar at the Entrepreneur India 2014 highlighted the strength of MSMEs in India as compared to other countries.', 'Entrepreneurship, MSME, National Small Business Advisory Council of South Africa, National Small Industries Corporation  ', '18:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4918, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:25:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1799, 'PA5CkvWfzjA', NULL, 'How the internet has evolved the biz world by virtue of innovation: Prof. N K Goyal, CMAI  ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Prof. N K Goyal is the President of CMAI association of India. He is also the Chairman Emeritus of Telecom Equipment Manufacturers Association of India, Vice Chairman of International Telecom Union APT India and Member of Governing Board Telecom Equipment & Services Export Promotion Council (Govt. of India), Director National Fertilizers Ltd. At Entrepreneur India 2014, Goyal emphasized on how the advent of internet and social media has brought revolution in the business world by virtue of innovation.', 'CMAI, Telecom Equipment Manufacturers Association of India, Entrepreneur India, CES Las Vegas', '08:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3974, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:26:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1800, 'y8y4i4uNQug', NULL, 'Social entrepreneurship is about making difference in the lives of poor: Naveen Krishnan, SMV Wheels', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Naveen Krishna, Founder and Director, SMV Wheels Pvt Ltd, ventured into social entrepreneurship in order to make a difference in the lives of 2.8 million rickshaw drivers and pushcart operators in India by providing them better designed rickshaws/carts and support services on micro-leasing-cum-purchase basis to provide them ownership of their livelihood asset with a sense of dignity. Till date, it has benefited 2,040 customers, out of which 612 have already become the owner of their vehicle. Speaking at the Entrepreneur India 2014, Krishna said Social Entrepreneurship is one of the most challenging and satisfactory way to make the world a better place.', 'SMV Wheels, social entrepreneurship, Entrepreneur India, Naveen Krishna', '04:51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3520, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:27:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1801, 'yU7xOQ9ljJk', NULL, 'Rewired Youth: The family business for change', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Lohit Sahu, Director, Phyzok Learning Solutions, Ayaan Chawla, Founder & CEO, Asian Fox Developments and Pankaj Dinodia, CEO, Dinodia Capital Advisors at Entrepreneur India discussed about the best practices on how to continue to grow and work with family business. Dinodia advises several Indian family businesses, corporate clients, institutional investors on M&A. Sahu Phyzok has touched more than 1.5 lakh students to understand how the education delivery system can be made effective. Chawla is a young successful entrepreneur, investor, programmer & philanthropist.', 'Phyzok Learning Solutions, Asian Fox Developments, Dinodia Capital Advisors, entrepreneur, investor', '04:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2694, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:30:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1802, 'O-dS9AOfFw4', NULL, 'Rewired Youth: The family business for change - Part 2', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Lohit Sahu, Director, Phyzok Learning Solutions, Ayaan Chawla, Founder & CEO, Asian Fox Developments and Pankaj Dinodia, CEO, Dinodia Capital Advisors at Entrepreneur India discussed about the best practices on how to continue to grow and work with family business. Dinodia advises several Indian family businesses, corporate clients, institutional investors on M&A. Sahu Phyzok has touched more than 1.5 lakh students to understand how the education delivery system can be made effective. Chawla is a young successful entrepreneur, investor, programmer & philanthropist.', 'Phyzok Learning Solutions, Asian Fox Developments, Dinodia Capital Advisors, entrepreneur, investor', '20:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3512, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:32:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1803, 'ND0SA5a9La4', NULL, 'Using the power of business to do good for the Society', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Shri S.N. Tripathi, Joint Secretary (SME), MSME, Saloni Malhotra, Founder, DesiCrew, Akshay Saxena, Co-founder & President, Avanti, Naveen Krishna, Founder & MD, SMV Wheels, Abhijit Ray, Co-founder & Managing Director, Unitus Capital at Entrepreneur India 2014 discussed about building socially conscious companies without being at odds with a profit motive, repurposing an existing asset to fit a growing need and sustainability is becoming an industry standard.', 'MSME, DesiCrew, Unitus Capital, Entrepreneur, Avanti', '06:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3071, 'A', '2015-05-16 14:33:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1804, 'dkE7Kw5eWDo', NULL, 'Use the power of business to do good for the society', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Highlighting the importance of social entrepreneurship to improve and empower the bottom of the pyramid, the panelists focus on points like - Using the power of business to do good for the Society, Community and the Nation; Repurposing an existing asset to fit a growing need & Building socially conscious companies without being at odds with a profit motive. ', 'Social entrepreneurship, CSR, Social issues, Social impact, Entrepreneurship India 2014', '14:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2228, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:00:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1805, '0FhBBr88KPM', NULL, 'Profit-Motive balance should be maintained in social business   ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Highlighting the importance of social entrepreneurship to improve and empower the bottom of the pyramid, the panelists focus on points like - Using the power of business to do good for the Society, Community and the Nation; Repurposing an existing asset to fit a growing need & Building socially conscious companies without being at odds with a profit motive. ', 'Social entrepreneurship, CSR, Social issues, Social impact, Entrepreneurship India 2014', '12:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2262, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:02:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1806, 'G5zIZRBIVm4', NULL, 'Start-ups should focus on building customer proposition  ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing on the angel investment issue and what start-ups can do to ease the fund-raising process, the panelists talk about that start-ups should focus on translating the idea into action very effectively. They further discuss about other issues like Screening opportunities; What it takes to incubate small companies internally; Role as an evangelizer; Finding strategic partner for incubate companies; Exit options available, etc.', 'Investor Entrepreneur, Angel Investment, Start-up, Early-stage Funding, Entrepreneurship India 2014', '23:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3717, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:03:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1807, 'b1oYN5_M6yk', NULL, 'Getting right team key to fuel innovation in firms ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing on the interesting issue of how entrepreneurs can implement innovation in day-to-day business operations, the panelists focus on topics like how to identify, evaluate and innovate around opportunities; Should entrepreneurs bet big on innovation?; Developing innovative capability and putting new ideas into practice & How to measure the change through innovation. ', 'Innovation, Entrepreneur, Mahesh Murthy, Entrepreneurship India 2014', '23:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2062, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:04:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1808, 'kjKy4rZvixQ', NULL, 'While innovation is good, it can also harm organisations', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing on the interesting issue of how entrepreneurs can implement innovation in day-to-day business operations, the panelists focus on topics like how to identify, evaluate and innovate around opportunities; Should entrepreneurs bet big on innovation?; Developing innovative capability and putting new ideas into practice & How to measure the change through innovation.', 'Innovation, Entrepreneur, Mahesh Murthy, Entrepreneurship India 2014', '23:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1783, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:07:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1809, 'IyPhDrtiZXo', NULL, 'Dealing successful transitioning in family business ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'The panelists focus their discussion on issues like understanding the dynamics involved in family businesses; How to ensure continuity of family business across generations? How to go about succession planning; Synergising family and business values while growing rapidly & How to successfully manage the transitioning from family business to a corporate entity.', 'Family business, Young entrepreneurship, DTDC, Entrepreneurship India 2014', '18:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2580, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:08:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1810, 'BnofoJhsxlY', NULL, 'Taking the next leap in business', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing about how to create new opportunities & get your way in business and life by inspiring others, the panelists talk about taking the next leap in business & explore new markets.   ', 'Startups, Entrepreneur, PHD Chamber, Intex Tech, Entrepreneurship India 2014', '16:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2511, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:09:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1811, '3TYTKEqiJPc', NULL, 'Entrepreneurs should continuously evolve themselves', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing about how to create new opportunities & get your way in business and life by inspiring others, the panelists talk about taking the next leap in business & explore new markets. Other issues they discuss about is the quality of entrepreneurs & what should they do to achieve the next level of scale and growth.   ', 'Startups, Entrepreneur, PHD Chamber, Intex Tech, Entrepreneurship India 2014', '16:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3151, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:10:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1812, 'X16_n_3qmuA', NULL, 'Learning entrepreneurship from born entrepreneurs is useful', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing about how to utilise your best assets as an entrepreneur, the panelists talk about what inspire entrepreneurs to keep going; how can they go about building big businesses.', 'Startups, Entrepreneur, Oxigen Services, Teamlease Services, Entrepreneurship India 2014', '18:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2807, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:13:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1813, 'lR_iKU6-sGk', NULL, 'Indias venture capital scenario has improved significantly', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'The panelists here are discussing on important issues like how investors network operate and how they put deals together; How to raise capital for early stage or seed stage companies; Winning strategies from prominent PE investors on capital flows; What approach of scaling up do PE firms seek in a venture, and When and how would PE company take an exit.', 'Startups, Entrepreneur, Venture Capital, Funding, Entrepreneurship India 2014', '16:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1891, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:15:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1814, '84nawH2JBlE', NULL, 'India is a mobile-first country and mCommerce is Indias eCommerce', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Ankit Rawal, India - &#8206;Head Ad Sales - Performance | Emerging Markets (IN, SEA, MEA) at InMobi talks to us about the engaging ways to connect the users on the mobile Internet to advertisers on mobile apps and how mCommerce is booming in India, which is a mobile-first country.', 'Ankit Rawal, InMobi, mobile advertising, eCommerce, mCommerce', '04:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3517, 'A', '2015-05-16 15:18:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1816, 'Y7O7rqarpgA', NULL, 'Wellness have potential to generate 3 million jobs by 2015: KS Rao', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Accentuating on the natural herbs, culture and rich traditional sciences of India, KS Rao, Deputy CEO, Khadi & Village Commission - Ministry of MSME, Government of India has stressed on the wellness space, which according to him has huge potential to generate employment. He said, the overall wellness market in India is estimated at Rs490 billion in which, the wellness services alone comprise of 40% of this market. The industry is attracting large number of domestic entrants and international players.', 'wellness industry, job opportunity, Khadi & Village Commission, Ministry of MSME', '09:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3646, 'A', '2015-05-18 11:50:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1817, '_pQa4IhyiRQ', NULL, 'Franchising has played big role in transforming beauty bizz: Naunihal Singh', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'While addressing the prestigious guests at the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015, Naunihal Singh, Chief Executive Officer, Strands Salons Pvt Ltd said has given all credit to franchising for transforming the Salon business as a whole. According to Singh, the wellness industry has started evolving 15 years back. Based on education, quality standards and hospitality, if all has been given to the consumer, he/she would revisit the salon.', 'Naunihal Singh, Strands salons, Chandigarh, Punjab, wellness industry', '08:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5717, 'A', '2015-05-18 11:52:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1818, 'jI6txZkBXB8', NULL, 'Must take measures to give additional knowledge to staff: Roopa Ambekar', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Known for her interactive sessions and knowledge sharing attitude, Roopa Ambekar, Founder & Managing Director of Uber Med Spa & Style Lounge, has given a thoughtful insight over 70% non-doctors performing aesthetics practice in India. She raised concern over the ill-impacts of it on those who are highly skilled and are offering best aesthetics treatments. Thus, she suggested some essential tips and suggestions to create awareness and educate the staff.', 'aesthetics, market, laser therapy, treatment, laser procedure, beauty, wellness', '11:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3064, 'A', '2015-05-18 11:53:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1819, 'F4ftMUA6vD8', NULL, 'Looking young is not a distant dream for an average Indian: Sanjay Bhutani', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Addressing the gathering at the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015, Sanjay Bhutani, Managing Director- India & SAARC, Bausch & Lomb Eyecare (I) Pvt Ltd shared 6 factors driving global consumers behaviour including; aspiration, awareness, efficacy, standardization, opportunity and challenges. He also informed that about 51% of aesthetics market is in North America, which is growing at the rate of 9.7%. While in Asia, the aesthetics market is estimated to grow at a CAGR of 15% and in India, it is growing at over 20%, drawing a lead in Asia.', 'Aesthetics, Bausch & Lomb, Eyecare, laser treatment, beauty, wellness industry', '13:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3384, 'A', '2015-05-18 11:55:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1820, 'TRt1_bFg5E4', NULL, 'Technology is changing post encounter stage: Siddharth Dalal', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Addressing a special session on technology and its impact on wellness business, Siddharth Dalal, Co-Founder, BookMeIn.in shared his critical analysis over buying behaviour of the tech-savvy consumer who is well informed and have multiple options to invest in. He admitted the fact that if a business is not on internet today, then it is out of trade, and much more.', 'Technology, salon, spas, wellness industry, business, tech-savvy consumers', '22:43', 'V', NULL, 'en', 19, 19, 95, 3658, 'A', '2015-05-18 11:59:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1821, 'iQxL55_BG84', NULL, 'We handhold SMEs to get listed on stock exchange: Ajay Thakur  ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'At Entrepreneur Dialogue 2014, Mr. Ajay Thakur, Head, BSE-SME, shares his thoughts about the power of the capital market, its working and why should SMEs take the route of equity marketing to raise capital.     ', 'Startups, Entrepreneur, BSE, SME, MSME, stock market, capital market, Entrepreneur Dialogue 2014  ', '23:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2267, 'A', '2015-05-18 15:58:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1822, 'XzKRno1kyLw', NULL, 'Working towards growth and development of MSMEs', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Madhu Malti of NSIC shares her views about the MSME-specific schemes offered by NSIC for their growth and development. Raw material distribution scheme, single point registration, scheme for government purchase, exhibiton and buyers-sellers meet are few such schemes offered by NSIC.', 'Startups, Entrepreneur, SME, MSME, NSIC, Entrepreneur Dialogue 2014', '13:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2335, 'A', '2015-05-18 16:00:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1823, 'dHfHrIpGPpI', NULL, 'Entertainment not simple these days: Omaxe ', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Mohit Sawhney, Senior General Manager, Omaxe Ltd. talks of the changion definition of entertainment and the evolution of Malls in accordance to it. Speaking to the Retailer team at IRC 2015, he asserted that the upcoming mall at Greater Noida is created to be more of an entertainment destination rather than a mere retail space. ', 'Mohit Sawhney, Omaxe, Omaxe connaught place, IRC 2015, Retail Real Estate ', '02:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2892, 'A', '2015-05-19 09:40:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1824, 'XYb_IiYecGQ', NULL, 'Jewelry industry being organised & challenging ', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'During a candid conversation with Reatiler media at IRC 2015, Saurabh Gadgil, Chairman & MD, PNG Jewellers Pvt. Ltd. spoke about the silver jewelry line to be launched in association with Being Human, the decision to include silver in portfolio which was initially restricted to royal ornaments and the demand for customized jewelry in current time. ', 'Saurabh Gadgil, PNG Jewellers, jewellery industry online retail, interactive marketing, IRC 2015', '03:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3471, 'A', '2015-05-19 09:42:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1825, 'WxA4cZiYsxA', NULL, 'Large Format Retail gaining lot of importance ', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'The online market gets a noticeable contribution from CDIT segment as well, especially in case of mobile phone.  Sanjay Warke, Country Head, Toshiba India talks to Retailer media about the penetration of eCommerce and its impact on traditional retail. Also, he asserts about the Large Format Retail revolution happening in India.', 'Sanjay Warke, Toshiba, CDIT industry, white goods, IRC 2015, retail industry', '03:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4256, 'A', '2015-05-19 09:45:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1826, 'LSTllVRv5NQ', NULL, 'Designer store ONLY FOR GROOMS!', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Amit Behki, an entrepreneur-cum-designer talks about his intention behind opening Creative Stop. Why online brides should get designer clothes and not grooms. Creative Stop is an all-purpose store for men, whether it is his wedding or a corporate party.', 'Amit Behki, Creative Store, Designer, Wedding Clothes, Grooms', '04:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3605, 'A', '2015-05-19 09:48:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1827, 'sNpxJaBZSB8', NULL, 'Brand Licensing to increase revenue', 46, '', NULL, '', 13, 'Akshay Sangwan, Manager – Legal, Franchise India Group talks about the commercial and legal insight of brand licensing along with briefing the role of Bradford Licensing India in providing brand licensing support.  ', 'Akshay Sangwan, Franchise India, Bradford, brand licensing, licensing industry in India', '07:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 3116, 'A', '2015-05-19 09:52:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1828, 'M71XapTUKDU', NULL, 'Brands cannot operate without knowing the local consumer - Part 2', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'B D Nathani, Chief Executive Officer, G&D Trade Zone talks about his experience with licensing companies as well licensors. Speaking at 7th international Brand Licensing and Merchandising show, Nathani emphasized on the inability of foreign brands to operate licensing in India because of lack of knowledge about the tradition, culture and consumer behavior in here, which is why they choose a local licensee. ', 'B D Nathani, G&D Trade Zone, brand licensing, licensing industry in India', '18:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3993, 'A', '2015-05-19 09:53:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1829, 'zqdQktkICQI', NULL, 'Brands cannot operate without knowing the local consumer - Part 1', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'B D Nathani, Chief Executive Officer, G&D Trade Zone talks about his experience with licensing companies as well licensors. Speaking at 7th international Brand Licensing and Merchandising show, Nathani emphasized on the inability of foreign brands to operate licensing in India because of lack of knowledge about the tradition, culture and consumer behavior in here, which is why they choose a local licensee. ', 'B D Nathani, G&D Trade Zone, brand licensing, licensing industry in India', '15:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 13, 4327, 'A', '2015-05-19 09:55:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1830, 'c_pnxjpTgTs', NULL, 'Style guide must for licensing', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'Chris Evans, Managing Director, Oxford Ltd – the wholly owned subsidiary of Oxford University, talks about the brand protection and need of style sheet while licensing. Speaking at 7th international Brand Licensing and Merchandising show, he asserted that a serious licensor needs to document his offerings in form to style guide to ensure the proper functionality of the licensing deal. ', 'Chris Evans, Oxford Ltd, Oxford University, licensing industry in India, LIMA', '21:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3446, 'A', '2015-05-19 09:57:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1831, 'hFb5lJCNfaI', NULL, 'Correlation between brand licensing and franchising', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'Deepak Rao, Senior Partner, Rajani Singhania & Partners talks about the correlation between brand licensing and franchising. He asserted that benefit of franchising is that one need not to invest either in terms of equity or Real Estate. Also he emphasized on section 52 and 53 of trademarks act, things to look out for in agreement from the perspective of a franchise as well as a licensee.', 'trademarks act, Deepak Rao, Rajani Singhania & Partners, licensing industry in India, LIMA', '13:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2629, 'A', '2015-05-19 10:01:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1832, 'OPgZ6sYJiXM', NULL, 'Chhota Bheem most successful in licensing', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'Madhav Prabhala, Vice President – Licensing & Merchandising, Green Gold Licensing & Merchandising talks about character licensing and the trends in this category post inception of Chhota Bheem in Indian market. In his words, the popularity of Chhota Bheem has grown by leaps and bounds, thus expanding their portfolio in all domains and making them one of the most popular IPS owners in Asia.', 'Madhav Prabhala, Green Gold, licensing industry in India, Chhota Bheem, Character licensing', '24:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4055, 'A', '2015-05-19 10:02:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1833, 'X8y1p6wPGRE', NULL, 'Lawyers in role of business strategist: Safir Anand', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'Speaking at 7th international Brand Licensing and Merchandising show, Safir Anand, Sr. Partner, Anand and Anand discussed the practical element in typical transaction. He emphasized that in todays time, lawyers not only provide a solution to legal problem, but also coordinate with venture capitalists. Also, he briefed about the three facets that govern any business from legal perspective. ', 'licensing industry in India, Safir Anand, Anand and Anand, Bradford', '13:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3859, 'A', '2015-05-19 10:05:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1834, 'M7G6UUB54oQ', NULL, 'LIMA to promote professionalism in licensing - Part 2 ', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'While speaking at 7th international Brand Licensing and Merchandising show, Martin Brochstein, the Senior Vice President - Industry Relations and Information for LIMA Worldwide emphasized on the role of LIMA in promoting best practices in licensing industry. He explained about the reach & mission of LIMA, along with talking about Licensing University which focuses on various aspects of business from basics to legal and trademark to creative sides. Also he talked about the steps to faster professionalism in the licensing industry. ', 'LIMA, Martin Brochstein, brand licensing, licensing industry, Franchise India', '13:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4336, 'A', '2015-05-19 14:25:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(1835, '3_PiuWyNy4M', NULL, 'LIMA to promote professionalism in licensing - Part 1', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'While speaking at 7th international Brand Licensing and Merchandising show, Martin Brochstein, the Senior Vice President - Industry Relations and Information for LIMA Worldwide emphasized on the role of LIMA in promoting best practices in licensing industry. He explained about the reach & mission of LIMA, along with talking about Licensing University which focuses on various aspects of business from basics to legal and trademark to creative sides. Also he talked about the steps to faster professionalism in the licensing industry. ', 'LIMA, Martin Brochstein, brand licensing, licensing industry, Franchise India', '14:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4225, 'A', '2015-05-19 14:26:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1836, 'dTIUlCqC7iE', NULL, 'Sports leagues bridging the dearth of youth-entertainment', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'Pankaj Sikka, Chief Brand Strategist & COO, Wild East Group talks about the sports licensing segment in India, while emphasizing on the areas where the franchise owners lack i.e. the focus on licensed merchandise category. He asserted that while in India, the total revenue earner by sports team through licensing is 1-2 per cent, globally it crosses from 5-7 per cent. Also he spoke about the dearth of entertainment for youth in the country which was instantly encashed by IPL and other sports league.', 'sports licensing, licensing industry in India, IPL, Football league, Pro kabaddi league, KKR, Pankaj Sikka, Wild East Group', '08:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5275, 'A', '2015-05-19 14:27:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1837, 'QuPB1O2F-S0', NULL, 'IPL a successful business model', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'Riding on the popularity of Indian Premier League, retailers are getting their hands on the sports league licensed merchandise. Phaneendra P, General Manager, GMR Sports Pvt Ltd talks about IPL as a successful business model, the different streams of revenues flowing into IPL model and sports licensing being one of the,. Also, he spoke about the Delhi Daredevils sport bar café at T3 and the licensed apparels. ', 'sports licensing, licensing industry in India, IPL, Football league, Pro kabaddi league, Phaneendra P, GMR Sports', '03:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 4593, 'A', '2015-05-19 14:29:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1838, 'vhYRYQwrYjo', NULL, 'Automobiles to be great opportunity for licensing', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'Automobiles have a great opportunity of line extension via licensing, asserted Nagarajan Subramanian, Founder & Managing Partner, En Theos Consulting while speaking at 7th international Brand Licensing and Merchandising show. He focused on the motorcycle market in India, the segments for licensing in this market and the case studies of Hero MotoCorp, Harley-Davidson and Royal Enfield in India. ', 'brand licensing, licensing industry in India, automobile licensing, Royal Enfield, Harley Davidson, Hero MotoCorp, En Theos, Nagarajan Subramanian', '20:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5626, 'A', '2015-05-19 14:33:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1839, 'lQxHiL9rPKk', NULL, 'Sports licensing more than cricket and IPL', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'Vishal Sinha, Business Head, Amigo Sports Pvt. Ltd talks about the sports licensing with respect to the companys initiative in introducing FIFA retail way back in 2009. Also he talked about companys role in launching various other sports brands, opportunity with sports brands while licensing, the changing market dynamics and the future in sports licensing, while emphasizing on the spectrum of sports licensing beyond cricket and IPL. ', 'sports licensing, licensing industry in India, FIFA, Football league, Vishal Sinha, Amigo Sports ', '04:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 4392, 'A', '2015-05-19 14:35:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1871, 'zynn8u6x-v0', NULL, 'Customers expectation from a brand', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Alhuwalia, President & Country Head &ndash; Media & Entertainment & Sports Banking Group, Yes Bank spoke about the burgeoning trends in the Indian Luxury market. He also explained the changing consumer behavior for brands and new professionals are now the face of this new luxury.', 'Karan Alhuwalia, Yes Bank, Luxury, Indian Retail Congress', '02:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4684, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:09:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1872, 'oUw4JLbHqK8', NULL, 'Consumer expecting high from eRetail', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Abhishek Chakraborthy, Executive Director, DTDC explained about consumer expectations in eRetailing space. Also he added his views on being an e-commerce player, what right steps should be taken to address the challenges of fulfillment. ', 'Abhishek Chakraborthy, DTDC, Courier Services, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '04:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2206, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:11:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1870, 'rut5DVgtkOI', NULL, 'Indian hospitality market is huge!', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Binod Chaudhary, Owner, Ferm Group caught up with Retailer Media and shared his views and strategies about his entry to the Indian market in hospitality space. He believes India is way behind in hospitality market.', 'Binod Chaudhary, Fern Group, Hospitality, Hotels, Taj', '07:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3157, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:06:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1841, 'JbzhCthgib8', NULL, 'MobiQuest hook the customer touch points', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Vineet Narang, Chief Executive Officer, MobiQuest talk of the challenges in retail industry due to randomness in different department and how MobiQuest hook the customer touch points to drive the sales.', 'Vineet Narang, MobiQuest, IRC 2015, Omnichannel retail', '01:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3022, 'A', '2015-05-20 14:51:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1842, 'eOFQbkgIBvw', NULL, 'From the Right Idea to the Ideal Enterprise', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'All companies start with a similar idea. Validate your idea by testing product market fit, validating value added to your customers and iterating designs. Even the best ideas can fail- Bouncing Back is important. ', 'Entrepreneurship, idea, enterprise, entrepreneur', '21:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2723, 'A', '2015-05-20 14:56:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1843, 'ndOh19C5sG0', NULL, 'What it takes to launch a new product? ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Panelist answer questions around expansion. As per Akshali research is really important before launching a new product. Understand where your target market is. What are they expecting from the new products? According to Sanya, emotions add a human ground to a woman entrepreneur. According to Aradhana a woman can think about issues which a man cannot. ', 'women entrepreneur, Entrepreneurship, Sanya Dhir, Aradhana Khaitan Mahna, Sanya Dhir', '16:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2070, 'A', '2015-05-20 14:57:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1844, 'WENjFnWaShQ', NULL, 'REWIRED YOUTH', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Panelists answer audience questions about building a business. As per Pankaj Dinodia first ideas do not work. Entrepreneurship is about patience, passion, perseverance and persistence. As per Lohit Sahu, take learnings from similar businesses to create your business model. According to Ayaan Chawla understand the barriers of business before taking the leap of faith. ', 'Entrepreneurship, Ayaan Chawla, Lohit Sahu, Pankaj Dinodia', '09:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 2528, 'A', '2015-05-20 14:59:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1845, 'sWBAipN2xLM', NULL, 'THE IDEA ENTREPRENEUR', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Every business idea must know how to measure. Next is scalability, is its upscale, will it succeed in the long-term. Enterprises must outlive the life of the founder. That is why a scientific roadmap is important. ', 'Entrepreneurship, idea, enterprise, entrepreneur', '15:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2426, 'A', '2015-05-20 15:02:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1846, 'k6pJkk8vY-k', NULL, 'How can women lead the next decade in entrepreneurship?', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'The women entrepreneurs highlight their tales on how they got into entrepreneurship. Aradhana Khaitan Mahna unveils her entrepreneurial journey in education world running the master franchise of Princeton Review. Sanya Dhir discloses how she brought a new sphere of life into Karol Bagh Saree House by tying up with Yash Raj Films. While, Akshali Shah takes us through the inception of Gowardhan Foods and how she succeeded at family business starting premium dairy products.', 'women entrepreneur, Entrepreneurship, Sanya Dhir, Aradhana Khaitan Mahna, Sanya Dhir', '16:04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4533, 'A', '2015-05-20 15:06:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1847, '694iAnK0XXA', NULL, 'Women mean business', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'In this session panelists highlight what challenges they had to go through in their entrepreneurial journey. Akshali highlights people do not take daughters in family business seriously. Aradhana advises entrepreneurs to have relentless focus to succeed in your venture. Sanya informs how the company started produed manufacturing on their own removing the middlemen and also helped educating the weavers. ', 'women entrepreneur, Entrepreneurship, Sanya Dhir, Aradhana Khaitan Mahna, Sanya Dhir', '12:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3395, 'A', '2015-05-20 15:07:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1848, 'GMVs4qmxiC8', NULL, 'AYUSH ministry fascinated international consumers: Geeta Ramesh', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Bringing attention of the audience, at the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress, towards the AYUSH ministry, Gita Ramesh, Joint Managing Director, Kairali Ayurvedic Group said the overall turnover of AYUSH sector is about Rs 120 million. The products market is worth about Rs 40 billion and AYUSH export is about Rs 22.7 billion in 2013-14. In fact, over 32 billion people in US are practicing Yoga. This shows an undeniable bright future ahead for the wellness industry.', 'AYUSH, ancient science, Ayurveda, Kairali Ayurveda, massage, therapy, spa', '09:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3523, 'A', '2015-05-21 09:18:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1849, 'iv47vbhkzOM', NULL, 'Honeymoon for eCommerce to end soon: Sangeetha Mobiles', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'In an exclusive conversation with Retailer media, Subhash Chandra, Managing Director, Sangeetha Mobiles took a jibe on online retailers and said that the honeymoon for eCommerce can not last forever as they are driving only on sheer fact of lowest prices. Aslso he shared the vision of Sangeetha mobiles to raise number of stores from 350 to one thousand by the end of the year. ', 'Subhash Chandra, Sangeetha Mobiles, IRC 2015, Internet of things, eCommerce', '05:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4511, 'A', '2015-05-21 09:22:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1850, 'RPzaNDfsEd0', NULL, 'TaxiForSure will soon eliminate the entire person car market', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'G Raghunandan, Onwer, TaxiForSure caught up with Retailer Media and spoke about his vision on the future of Taxi Market. Taxi used to be a premium ride but now people are getting used to it and so the market has tremendous scope.', 'G Raghunandan, TaxiForSure, Can Aggregator, m-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '05:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2397, 'A', '2015-05-21 09:27:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1853, 'pQnyzAYbhbY', NULL, 'Democratising advertising and building one marketing platform is our mission', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Anubhav Sonthalia, COO, Sokrati.com has ventured into a space which is growing massively at the global front. The 40-50 billion dollar global online ad industry is pegged to be at 700 million dollars in India and is growing at a phenomenal space. Retailer Media caught up with ANubhav to know more about the industry.', 'Digital marketing, Internet advertising, ad and analytic, Sokrati, Anubhav Sonthalia', '04:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4066, 'A', '2015-05-22 09:10:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1854, 'D5blKAsKx1A', NULL, 'Innovative partnering models is the key to grow', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'During the Indian Retail Congress, Anurag Mathur, Partner, Price Waterhouse Coopers caught up with Retailer Media and shared his views on how the industry has grown and where will it lead to. He is also of the firm opinion that m-commerce is the way to go ahead in every end of the spectrum.', 'Anurag Mathur, PWC, m-commerce, SMBs, Indian Retail Congress', '03:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3331, 'A', '2015-05-22 09:11:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1855, '1fYlvjW1-Ro', NULL, 'Impact of web on the offline retail sales in India', 4, '', NULL, '', 22, 'm-Commerce is the next e-Commerce and this will change the entire offline retail space in the coming years. The sales are going to be well impacted by the online channels and retailer should route omni-channel retailing in their business model says Satish Meena, Forecast Analyst, Forrester Research at The Indian Retail Congress 2015.', 'Satish Meena, Retail, ecommerce, retail analysis, Indian Retail Congress', '04:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3499, 'A', '2015-05-22 09:12:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1856, 'O_nKjiQmPGE', NULL, 'Indian Retail & e-Retail Congress & Awards 2015 on Times Now', 4, '', NULL, '', 25, 'Indian Retail & eRetail Congress 2015, Indias biggest  thought leadership platform on retail & eRetail industry was held on April 17-18, 2015. Organized by Franchise India to showcase a product or service in the retail & eretail, supplier and allied industry. This national event was a grand success with over 600 successful retailers, eretailers, suppliers, manufacturers, industry veterans, key suppliers, consultants and individuals belonging to the Retail and eRetail category attended the event from across the country. The conference talked about all aspects of retail & eretail business in India and provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading e-Retailers and Retailers and an understanding around how they are re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.\r\n\r\nAlong with the Congress, Annual Indian Retail & eRetail Awards 2015 were also took place. The Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in Retail as well as e-Retail space. The award ceremony was aimed at felicitating people who have contributed towards the growth of Retail Industry in India. From Achievers, Innovators to Suppliers, the awards applauded their efforts in making the retails & e-retails presence felt in this increasingly competitive world.', 'Indian Retail Congress, Indian e-Retail Congress, Indian Retail Awards, Indian e-Retail Awards, Times Now, Indian Retail Congress Promo', '23:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 4474, 'A', '2015-05-25 09:20:47', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1857, 'WN5O3vaInaY', NULL, 'QSR a major client for Blue Star by B Thiagarajan', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Sharing with Restaurant India, B Thiagarajan, ED and President- AC & R Products Business, Blue Star reveals that QSR is one of the biggest client of Blue Star when it comes to business.', 'Blue Star, Cold Chain, AC , Food Industry, Food Chain, Food Supply', '03:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2545, 'A', '2015-05-25 09:25:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1858, 'je-2BvMSttY', NULL, 'How is Rasna placing itself as a health drink by Piruz Khambatta', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Talking about new strategies at Rasna, Piruz Khambatta, MD and Chairma, Rasna shares How Rasna is placing itself as a health drink in Indian market targeting on children on a broader angle. ', 'Rasna, Health Drink, Juices, Beverages Trend, Piruz Khambatta', '02:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2282, 'A', '2015-05-25 09:27:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1859, 'As6j-r8UGjM', NULL, 'Managing consumer relationship for other organisations', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Bijaei Jayaraj, Founder & CEO, Loylty Rewardz Mngt. Pvt. Ltd. caught up with Retailer Media and shared his vision on future of Loyalty programme in the Retail industry and how this will help boost the market size.', 'Bijaei Jayaraj, Loylty Rewardz, Banking, Consumer, Indian Retail Congress', '07:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3576, 'A', '2015-05-25 15:21:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1860, '67rnvvTHPhE', NULL, 'Indian will soon emerge to be largest penetration for smartphone users', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'During the Indian Retail Congress, Prashant Puri, CEO and Co-Founder, Adlift.com caught up with Retailer Media and shared his views on the present and future of the retail and e-retail market in India.', 'Prashant Puri, Adlift, consulting firm, retail, Indian Retail Congress', '03:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3530, 'A', '2015-05-25 15:22:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1861, 'HtWrC1q5R4w', NULL, 'No act to decide the lowest selling point ', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Though the MRP Act is the limit for highest price, there is no act globally which sets a bar of lowest selling price for retailer, said Shilpa Gupta, Head-Retail, FMCG, Gems & Jewellery Division, FICCI\r\nduring a candid conversation with Reatiler media at IRC 2015. Also, she asserted that as long as retailers maintain the quality, they have freehand to lower the price. ', 'Shilpa Gupta, FICCI, online retail, direct selling, dynamic pricing, IRC 2015', '02:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4162, 'A', '2015-05-25 15:24:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1862, 'mojiWm3K1q0', NULL, 'e-Commerce boom has given opportunities in parcel department too', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Vineet Pandey, Chief General Manager &ndash; Business Developement & Marketing Directorate, India Post caught up with Retailer Media shared his view on the current e-Commerce boom and how it affected postal department of the country.', 'Vineet Pandey, India Post, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress ', '04:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3852, 'A', '2015-05-25 15:30:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1863, 'GhEJqO-fsQ8', NULL, 'LightBox Ventures, seeding technology start-ups in India', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Sid Talwar, Co-Founder & Partner, Lightbox Ventures caught up with Retailer Media and shared his idea of investing in a particular company.', 'Sid Talwar, Lightbox Ventures, Investment, Indian Retail Congress', '01:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2807, 'A', '2015-05-25 15:32:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1864, 'yG8uR10JXVA', NULL, 'M-Commerce: An essential part in scaling Jabong', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Arun Chandra Mohan, CO-Founder, Jabong caught up with Retailer Media and shared the future expansion plans for Jabong and how mobile commerce will be an integral part in scaling up the business. ', 'Arun Chandra Mohan, Jabong, m-Commerce, Investment, Wassup', '03:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3308, 'A', '2015-05-25 15:35:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1865, 'OzWEi1mSQDs', NULL, 'Wassup, serving your daily laundry requirements', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'R Balachandar, Co-Founder, Wassup caught up with Retailer Media and shared his views exclusively on the business model of Wassup, an on-demand convenience brand. Also he explained the tie-up with Jabong. ', 'R Balachandar, Wassup, Jabong, Online Laundry, e-Commerce, m-Commerce', '05:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2647, 'A', '2015-05-25 15:36:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1866, 'Iwend6m7ugw', NULL, 'Trust factor in Pharmacy business is a must!', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards, Ashutosh Gard, Managing Director, Gurdian Lifecare Pvt. Ltd. spoke on the importance of trust factor in the Pharmacy business. He also shared his experiences on how to nurture a brand to thrive and grow.  ', 'Ashutosh Garg, Gurdian Lifecare, Pharma, Consumer, Retail, Indian Retail Congress', '05:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2889, 'A', '2015-05-25 15:39:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1867, 'lhgFDI-DX6g', NULL, 'Franchising partners are must for a business to grow', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Darpan Kapoor, Managing Director, Kapsons Fashion Pvt. Ltd. spoke on how partnering in franchising can be a better gig all together. India is a vast country and being alone you can not scale up your business.', 'Darpan Kapoor, Kapsons Fashion, Franchising, Indian Retail Congress', '03:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3836, 'A', '2015-05-25 15:42:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1868, 'bZinV0s5T50', NULL, 'Retail and eRetail are complimenting each other', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Inaugurating the Indian Retail and eRtail Congress and Awards 2014, Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India Holdings Limited addressed the guests explaining the agenda of the two-day summit. She further elaborated on how Retail and eRetail are running parallel in the ecosystem and opportunities that lies in India which can also be called as a shopkeeper nation.     ', 'Ritu Marya, Franchise India Holdings, Retail, eRetail, Indian Retail Congress', '13:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3327, 'A', '2015-05-25 15:44:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1869, 'c-2pxDQi1Hc', NULL, 'We will be expanding in 5 more cities by 2015 end: Navneet Singh, PepperTap', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'PepperTap is an on-demand grocery delivery service in India based out of Gurgaon. It kick started its operations on 26th November, 2014. It is a location based platform wherein goods are procured from already tied-up supermarkets. This allows customers to see a specific catalogue of their area based on their location. PepperTap has already raised series A round of funding of $10 million by Sequoia Capital and SAIF Partners and is in talks to close its series B round of funding.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn an interaction with EntrepreneurIndia.com, Navneet Singh and Milind Sharma, co-founders of PepperTap talked more about their business model, revenue structure and growth & expansion plans.', 'Entrepreneur, PepperTap, grocery, supermarket, VC fund, seed fund  ', '06:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3963, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:01:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1873, 'eXEiHwqlbXE', NULL, 'Dos and donts for a Retail brand ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Anurag Rajpal, Director & CEO, American Swan, spoke on the pain-points of a retail brand. Uniformity of pricing, omni-channel presence, online versus offline strategies were some of the main highlights of his session. ', 'Anurag Rajpal, American Swan, e-Commerce, Omni-channel, Indian Retail Congress', '12:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3023, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:12:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1874, 'VlylPfjhvdA', NULL, 'Bringing old generation online', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Atul Bhatnagar, COO, National Skill Development Corporation largely spoke about role of retail in banking sector. He also empathized on how to bring old generation people online and make e-Commerce more convenient for them.', 'Atul Bhatnagar , NSDC, Retail Banking, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '10:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3093, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:13:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1875, 'u1a7QX_Eh1Q', NULL, 'Discounting is the new era', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, B A Srinivasa, Director, Viveks &ndash; The Unlimited Shop spoke about the difference in 70s and todays market. He said 70s market was a sellers market and we have seen evolution in terms of easy availability of products through online.', 'B A Srinivasa, Viveks – The Unlimited Shop, Discounting, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '03:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2804, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:18:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1876, '5T9_KesT-fE', NULL, 'White-goods movement is the future', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Bablu Tewari, COO, International & e-Commerce, Gati highlighted the strength needed in an online delivery business where consumer expects delivery at the earliest. He said that this is a very lucrative business both from client and brand point of view.', 'Bablu Tewari, Gati, White-goods, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '10:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3629, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:19:57', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0),
(1877, 'GWfUGJZdJpw', NULL, 'It needs a lot of patience to become a Flipkart', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Bhawna Agarwal, CEO, Luxury Retail spoke about the challenges that come while evolving into a hybrid model. As per Bhavna, online travel made a market for itself after the launch of Yatra, MakeMyTrip, ClearTrip etc.', 'Bhawna Agarwal, Luxury Retail, e-Commerce, Travel, Indian Retail Congress', '04:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 10, 10, 50, 4912, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:21:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1878, 'w0G7NmenRIA', NULL, 'Cloud computing world and the changing consumer behavior ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Bikram Singh Bedi, Country Head- India, Amazon Seller Services shared Amazon experiences in cloud computing world and how they helped companies scale from start-ups to large firms. He also spoke about consumer behavior in the changing times.', 'Bikram Singh, Amazon Seller Services, Cloud Computing, Big Data, Indian Retail Congress', '24:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3636, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:22:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1879, 'B70L9bCShqY', NULL, 'Marketing should be a bit of both, online and offline', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Krsna Mehta, Director, India Circus Retail Pvt. Ltd. shared his experience with private level online space in India. He also said that to scale in this sector in particular it is best to use the various options available in terms of advertising whether be it online or offline or regular PRs.', 'Krsna Mehta, India Circus, Retail, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress ', '05:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3510, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:27:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1880, 'pjLvgaeUjQQ', NULL, 'Choice of products is wider in e-Retailing', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Mahesh Gupta, Founder & Chairman, Kent RO spoke on the success of e-Commerce in the service sector. He said what e-Retail is offering is fantastic in terms of convenience of buying and biggest advantage in this sector is the timeline. It can be done anytime and at any place.', 'Mahesh Gupta, Kent RO, Retail, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '11:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2815, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:28:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1881, 'VHCVDZY7r1g', NULL, 'Approaching brick-and-mortars through e-Commerce', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Nitin Bawankule, Industry Director- eCommerce (Local & Media), Google India spoke about the past, present and the future market share of e-Commerce in the country and also the consumer behavior and acceptance towards this industry.', 'Nitin Bawankule, Google India, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '11:39', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2516, 'A', '2015-05-26 09:29:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1882, 'JaLCmzhkc9Q', NULL, 'Future of cash and carry business in India', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Retailer Media caught up with Krish Iyer, President & CEO, Walmart India to know more about the revolutionized kirana store trends in India. He also shared his views on impact of e-Commerce into retail and how the young generation has shifted preferences towards online buying.', 'Krish Iyer, Walmart, Cash & Carry, e-Retail, SMEs', '09:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3619, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:03:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1883, 'hLPqKnjHLco', NULL, 'This is a re-branding period for wellness in India: Arpit Sharma', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Addressing the gathering at the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015, Arpit Sharma, CEO, Sevenseas Spa chain, has shared his views over Spa Tourism initiated by neighbouring Bhutan country. Sharma expressed his views over how Indian wellness industry can encash big on promoting its traditional practices of Ayurveda, therapies and other natural procedures to encourage wellness industry? He also gave an insight over Thai massage which is inspired by Indian Ayurveda and much more.', 'wellness industry, spa tourism, Ayurveda, travelers, business, Sevenseas spa', '02:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5679, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:09:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1884, 'gPgCidZA6cA', NULL, 'Spa therapies are the best cure to lifestyle diseases: Kapil Dhameja', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Speaking at the session on Spa: Business of Rejuvenation, at the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015, Kapil Dhameja, Co- Founder, Blue Terra spa, has shared his elaborate knowledge over various therapies being offered at the spas these days, which includes some common therapies like deep Tissue massage, Swedish Massage etc., which may help the consumers to beat lifestyle diseases easily.', 'Therapy, massage, spa, business, wellness industry, Blue Terra spa', '05:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3888, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:12:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1885, '0q6kczrpqIQ', NULL, 'People are willing to spend money on health: Sheru Aangrish', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Giving insight over gradually picking up Fitness industry which is shifting towards organised sector, Sheru Aangrish, Sports Entrepreneur, International Health & Fitness Guru, Founder & Chairman, Sheru Classic, explained, India has 51% of population which belongs to less than 25 years age category, while 62% of the population is from less than 35 years and so in the young India. The country has people who are fitness and health freaks and are willing to spend on it. This shows a huge growth opportunity in the fitness industry.', 'fitness, sports fit, Sheru Classic, health, gym, exercise, wellness industry', '08:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4826, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:13:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1886, 'GlnKnz7emSU', NULL, 'Education is essential to implement right procedure: Shivani Sharma', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Addressing the gathering at the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015, Shivani Sharma, Managing Director & Technical Head of Lure Nails, has shared her personal experience of establishing nail bars in Indian Wellness Industry. She gave her views over how essential is the clarity of technical procedure and knowledge of various techniques being used in implementing the nail art form. Comparing the same she explained the need of education in the wellness trade.', 'Nail bar, nail art, wellness industry, education, business', '05:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4318, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:14:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1887, 'PJ2pefqR7so', NULL, 'e-Commerce payment mechanism should be integrated by all means - Part 2', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Shashank Joshi, Managing Director, My Mobile Payments Ltd., MoneyOnMobile spoke about the consumer behavior for towards the payment mechanism in e-Commerce business. He was also of the firm opinion that mobile payment is the future of the e-Commerce business and a lot of enhancements can be done.', 'Shashank Joshi, MoneyOnMobile, Mobile Payment, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '04:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4412, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:17:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1888, 'aynY7Q3lrnM', NULL, 'e-Commerce payment mechanism should be integrated by all means - Part 1', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Shashank Joshi, Managing Director, My Mobile Payments Ltd., MoneyOnMobile spoke about the consumer behavior for towards the payment mechanism in e-Commerce business. He was also of the firm opinion that mobile payment is the future of the e-Commerce business and a lot of enhancements can be done.', 'Shashank Joshi, MoneyOnMobile, Mobile Payment, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '02:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4627, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:18:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1889, 'YvOqXajPOpA', NULL, 'We are living in a cloud age not a cave age', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Pramoud Rao, Promoter &ndash; Managing Director, Zicom Group spoke about technology and the costing involved in setting up security devices. He also spoke about monetizing the internet to make money and connecting devices using the power of cloud.', 'Pramoud Rao, Zicom, Cloud Computing, Retail, Indian Retail Congress', '11:43', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3309, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:23:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1890, 'WQUL1JjDs20', NULL, 'Mobile commerce is not an extension of the web', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Pranav Bhasin, Vice President &ndash; Online Products, Makemytrip.com shared his views on integration of mobile phones into any business. He also explained how mobile devices are compatible for businesses like hotels, hospitality and travel etc.', 'Pranav Bhasin, Makemytrip.com, m-Commerce, Travel, Indian Retail Congress', '09:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5350, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:23:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1891, '1nfgKR9EwX8', NULL, 'Customer experience should never be diluted', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Praveen Sinha, Founder, Jabong shared his views on retailing and e-retailing scenarios in India. He said that the market is not organized and this gives a great opportunity to the retailers.   ', 'Praveen Sinha, Jabong, Retail, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '08:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1765, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:24:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1892, 'NQXn-I-ULg8', NULL, 'Converting window shoppers to buyers', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Rahul Sethi, Co-Founder, LadyBlush.com spoke about the fast growing organized retail market of India. He also spoke about some of the major differences in the retail and e-retail business model and how consumers flip between the two.', 'Rahul Sethi, LadyBlush, e-Retail, Indian Retail Congress', '08:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 2542, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:25:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1893, 'hff49xuF15c', NULL, 'Baby-care category is open for e-Commere', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Rajesh Vohra, CEO, Chicco India spoke about the changing pattern in the baby care sector. He explained how people have changed their way of approach and how strongly they rely on researching about products. ', 'Rajesh Vohra, Chicco, Baby care, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '08:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1923, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:27:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1894, 'qnoNfy4QWyA', NULL, 'Innovation in e-Commerce services will happen in future', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Sachin Bhatia, Vice President & Co-Founder, Drishti Soft, spoke about the challenges in e-Commerce and how to fine-tune a business process and making communication a part of the process. He also explained the reason behind the increase of consumer expectation in e-Commerce services.', 'Sachin Bhatia, Drishti Soft, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '06:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3512, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:28:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1895, 'PoMyt7KI308', NULL, 'Home furniture business serious about e-Commerce', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Subodh Mehta, Sr. Vice President (Marketing), Godrej Interio spoke on the online and offline war. He also explained on how to enhance e-Commerce services in home furniture business. ', 'Subodh Mehta, Godrej Interio, Home furniture, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '09:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5179, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:29:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1896, 'qXMfqUdtadY', NULL, 'Every product or service have to be a part of e-Commerce soon', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Vasant Kumar, Executive Director, Max Retail shared his thoughts on the convergence that is happening in e-Commerce due to technology innovations. He also extended his speech on the interconnectivity of e-Commerce and how this has become a need for the retailers.', 'Vasant Kumar, Max Retail, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '10:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2612, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:30:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1897, 'xRDAeYFF0ow', NULL, 'Omni-channel is all about seamlessness ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Venneth Purushotaman, Sr. Vice President, Technology & Supply Chain, HyperCity Retail India Ltd spoke about how m-Commerce fit into the omni-channel strategy. He was also of the firm opinion that it iss the consumer who decides what channel to use and retailers has to be there on all those channels.', 'Venneth Purushotaman, HyperCity, Omni-channel, m-Commerce, India Retail Congress', '07:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3031, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:33:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1898, '3srWQlJyp88', NULL, 'Indian consumers today are price sensitive', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Vijesh Sharma, Founder & CMO, DonebyNone.com spoke about the behavior of Indian consumer in terms of pricing and discounting. He also said that consumers today are aware and pricing needs to be done very carefully. ', 'Vijesh Sharma, DonebyNone.com, Fashion, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '08:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2316, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:34:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1899, 'evwSFLfOw0Y', NULL, 'e-Commerce in furnishing is new and so the trust factor is low', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Vikram Chopra, Co-Founder, Fab Furnish spoke about the opportunity that lies in furnishing space and how the after- sale services helps you connect better with the customers. He also said online and offline are complementing each other and it just a way we give to customers to reach out to us.  ', 'Vikram Chopra, Fab Furnish, Home decor, Furnishing, e-Commerce, Indian Retail Congress', '05:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4943, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:35:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1900, 'QtDOFjhFfDY', NULL, 'e-Commerce and mobile are just few aspects of omni-channel retailing', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Vinod Bidarkoppa, CIO & Group Director (IT), Member of Board at Tesco HSC spoke about the significant shift in the consumer buying behavior from physical stores to online and how should retailers get ready for this trend.  He also emphasized on using mobile on every aspect of the business. ', 'Vinod Bidarkoppa, e-Commerce, omni-channel, Retail, Indian Retail Congress', '13:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4723, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:36:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1901, '2GfpMvMviIs', NULL, 'Delivering same value online is a challenge', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Vinod Krishnan, CIO, Walmart spoke about focus of e-Commerce and Omni-channel retailing. He also said that it is very important to reach out to consumers where they are and how they want to be reached. ', 'Vinod Krishnan, Walmart, e-Commerce, Reatil, Omni-channel, Indian Retail Congress', '09:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3531, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:38:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1902, 'QW-tGCP0bhs', NULL, 'Courier and logistics industry witnessing a paradigm shift', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Yashpal Hooda, Head Operations &ndash; B2C, Safexpress Private Limited spoke about the cultural shift happening in the cargo industry. He also extended his speech on new technology innovations that could help last mile delivery experience.', 'Yashpal Hooda, Safexpress, Courier and Logistics, Indian Retail Congress', '09:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3838, 'A', '2015-05-27 09:39:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1903, 'oqHXm41U93w', NULL, 'Entire wardrobe rather than specific fashion', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'Danish fashion company Bestseller currently operates menswear brand Jack and Jones, and women brands Vero Moda and Only in the Indian and will soon bring in its premium brand Selected to expand its India portfolio.  Ranjan Sharma, Chief Information Officer, Bestseller India talks to Retailer Media about the expansion plans of the company, their market in various cities and the omnichannel strategy in retail.', 'Ranjan Sharma, Bestseller India, Vero Moda, Only, Selected, Jack and Jones, fashion retail, , IRC 2015', '02:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4458, 'A', '2015-05-28 14:19:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1904, '1spqEBEC6KI', NULL, 'We stand alone & not in malls, says Kalyan Jewellers', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'To mark their presence in NCR, Kalyan Jewellers has announced the opening of two new showrooms in Gurgaon and Noida. In an exclusive conversation with Retailer Media, Ramesh Kalyanaraman, the Executive Director of Kalyan Jewellers talks about the principle of the brand to stand alone, which is why they keep away from malls. Also he spoke about the online trend of shopping for jewellery and the different demand of consumers in Noida. ', 'jewellery market, Kalyan Jewellers, Ramesh Kalyanaraman, online jewellery, Kalyan Jewellers in Noida', '03:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4674, 'A', '2015-05-28 14:22:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1905, 'pIubl7nSOHA', NULL, 'GAP enters Indian market in franchisee with Arvind Brands Ltd.', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'In a candid conversation with Retailer Media during the launch of GAP in India, Stefan Leban, Senior Vice President Gap International shared the reason behind associating with Arvind Brands and how GAP looks at the Indian market. He also said that Indians are fashionable and this gives us immense opportunity.', 'Stefan Leban, GAP International, Arvind Brands, Fashion, Retail', '01:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 4019, 'A', '2015-06-02 09:28:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1906, 'hhMF2S57vqA', NULL, 'Arvind Brands Ltd. launches GAP in India', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'On the occasion of GAP launch in India by Arvind brands, Retailer Media caught up with J. Suresh, Managing Director and CEO, Arvind Lifestyle Brands Ltd. to know more about the association between the two and how is Arvind Brands planning to make an impression in the market.', 'J Suresh, Arvind Brands, GAP India, Retail, Fashion', '03:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2607, 'A', '2015-06-02 09:31:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1907, '66W-XZab1TY', NULL, 'We have committed $75M fund for rural development of India: Judith Rodin, Rockefeller Foundation', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Judith Rodin is the president of the Rockefeller Foundation, a position she has held since 2005. From 1994 to 2004, Rodin served as the 7th permanent president of the University of Pennsylvania, and the first permanent female president of an Ivy League university. In 2003, Rodin was named to the PoliticsPA list of Pennsylvanias Most Politically Powerful Women.', 'Rockefeller Foundation, Judith Rodin, University of Pennsylvania, Ivy League university', '04:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 2967, 'A', '2015-06-02 09:34:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1908, '-RT2U8HxJjg', NULL, 'We are empowering entrepreneurs who provide energy services: Zia Khan, Rockefeller Foundation', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'As vice president for Initiatives and Strategy, Dr. Khan oversees the Foundations approach for achieving impact and realizing the organization mission and goals. He leads the program team in New York, Bangkok, and Nairobi and their work in searching for new opportunities, developing strategies, and executing initiatives. He also provides direction for the Foundation commitment to supporting new innovations and capacities in the sector.', 'Rockefeller Foundation, Entrepreneurs, Innovations, Energy service, Zia Khan   ', '05:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4341, 'A', '2015-06-02 09:37:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1909, 'B5uFdQmb4lw', NULL, 'India is a low-trust market and only technology can bridge the gap', 4, '', NULL, '', 23, 'During the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2014, Vishal Sharma, Vice President &ndash; Strategic Initiatives, ShopClues.com caught up with Retailer Media and spoke about the latest trends going in the logistics market and his future plans to uplift the category and provide a better consumer experience.', 'Vishal Sharma, ShopClues, Logistics, e-Commerce, Retail, Indian Retail Congress', '05:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3706, 'A', '2015-06-03 15:43:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1910, '_FfUVFhBwIk', NULL, 'Our ultimate objective is to tap tier II & III cities: Miraya Hotel CEO', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Miraya Hotel Management is a start-up franchiser which brought US-based Vantage Hospitality Group in India and  together, are opening their first Value Inn Hotel chain in India. In an exclusive conversation with Franchise India,  Sudhir Sinha, MD & CEO, Miraya Hotel Management Pvt Ltd shared his business plans with Vantage, their ultimate target to serve in tier II & III cities, plans to foray into potent wellness industry, challenges faced in franchising international brand in India and much more', 'Miraya Hotel Management, Start-up, Vantage Hospitality Group, Wellness industry', '05:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3851, 'A', '2015-06-09 15:32:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1911, 'SiRxTnrIi2g', NULL, 'Opening homoeopathy colleges in abroad will boost commercial success: Ashish Kumar ', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'At the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress, Ashish Kumar, Managing Director, Schwabe Pharma- Dr. Wilmar Schwabe India Pvt Ltd, talked about AYUSH - Homoeopathy and how the outreach of AYUSH has to be established, not only India, but far beyond the borders of India. Interestingly, Kumar brought in light about the Brazilian Ingredient Amazon which is used in various beauty products to improve its quality, used primarily by South american companies. Elaborating on the Homoeopathic treatment, Kumar talked about opening of Homoeopathy colleges to be opened in Southern states of India and in overseas in America, China and much more.', 'Schwabe India, Wellness Industry, AYUSH, Homoeopathy, Amazon', '08:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 5478, 'A', '2015-06-09 15:36:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1912, '_rXaROjiXzQ', NULL, 'Wellness Industry is giving commercial development: Dr. J L N Sastry', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Dr. J L N Sastry, Head- Healthcare Research Dabur Research & Development Centre (DRDC) has shared his views over Wellness Industry and significant role played by Ayurveda is curing various issues. He also talked about various cosmetics, hair issues, herbs used to cure it and much more to document the diseases and herbal cures of the same. He  talked about the gift of commercial development given by wellness industry to the country, bring forth the traditional practice of science and medicine as the means of earning and much more.', 'Wellness Industry is giving commercial development: Dr. J L N Sastry', '15:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5090, 'A', '2015-06-09 15:36:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1913, 'YWP9rfNEkKI', NULL, 'Fitness is no more a luxury, its a necessity: Snap Fitness CEO', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Dr Vikram, CEO & Director, Snap Fitness India talked about the sudden boost to fitness industry by growing awareness and rise in stress level due to changing lifestyle and competition. He said, when fitness activities would be offered as fun activity, the retention rate would be higher than expected. \r\nThe CEO of leading fitness chains Snap Fitness elaborated on various fitness programmes like Biggest Looser Challenge and much more to explains the formula of making a top notch position in Fitness industry.', 'fitness industry, wellness, gym, exercise, stress, business, health', '06:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4016, 'A', '2015-06-09 15:38:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1914, 'pnDcXCru2tw', NULL, 'As long as the mind is young, we should not look older outside: Dr. Jahanara F Khan', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Dr. Jahanara F Khan, Chief Consultant, Laser Medical Centre & Ageless Clinic Dhaka, Bangladesh gave a clear picture of how anti-ageing treatments like Botox, fillers, PRP and lasers may help an individual to lock the young look and lead them to rejoice their youth for years. to explain the science and technique behind the same, she gave example of gracefully aged Bollywood actresses like Rekha and Hema Malini. The gorgeous Dermatologist herself, Khan talked about various aesthetic procedures, techniques and surgeries offered at her centre in neighbouring country Bangladesh and much more.', 'anti-ageing, dermatology, laser treatments, aesthetics, wellness industry', '07:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4516, 'A', '2015-06-09 15:39:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(1915, 'BAWo3xLRwyA', NULL, 'We aim to take fitness industry towards organised from unorganised: Harman Baweja', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Actor Harman Baweja, who is also the Co-Founder of LYS Fitness and is a big fitness enthusiast himself graced the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2015 by his enlightening speech on Fitness Business. The actor disclosed his journey of becoming fat to fit and how travelling to parts of the country made him aware of the unstructured and unorganised scenario of fitness practice in India, which the actor is trying to bring towards a much structured way of business and bring much educated and aware approach to expand business further.', 'Bollywood actor, Harman Baweja, fitness industry, wellness, gym, exercise, health', '09:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4995, 'A', '2015-06-09 15:41:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1916, 'BAn0spzYK7w', NULL, 'Indian consumers are ruining health by running after wealth: Neeraj Mehta', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Known for his spectacular fitness training and expertise of giving an ideal figure or body shape to the Bollywood actors like Priyanka Chopra, Celebrity fitness expert Neeraj Mehta talked about how fitness has become a need of the hour in the stressful lives of consumers and how the industry is heading towards an organised structure after being an unorganized business model.  ', 'exercise, fitness industry, gyms, wellness industry, fat, obesity', '11:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6100, 'A', '2015-06-09 15:44:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1917, 'O1t_-2K3KT8', NULL, 'Cult fashion brand H&M all set to hit the Indian Market this fiscal', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Retailer Media caught up with Dhatri Bhatt, Head - Communications at H&M Hennes & Mauritz India Retail Pvt. Ltd., who shared H&M India strategy and the dynamic collection H&M will offer to its Indian consumers.', 'Dhatri Bhatt, H&M India, Fashion, Retail', '02:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4214, 'A', '2015-06-10 09:16:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1918, 'HjR-RCvuO68', NULL, 'How CCD has evolved from a cappuccino cafe to an experience cafe', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'CCD has grown from a cappuccino cafe to an experience cafe over the years. Talking on the same lines, Bidisha Nagaraj, Group President- Marketing, Coffee Day shares, how the brand has focused on bringing the overall experience at its cafes and not only focusing on serving food.', 'Cafe, Coffee Segment, Cafe Coffee Day, CCD', '03:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 3597, 'A', '2015-06-10 09:19:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1919, 'MQStKX2kB2Y', NULL, 'Anouk launches Disney collections', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'During the launch of Disney collection by Anouk (Myntra), Ruchi Kelan, Head Designer, Anouk – Myntra caught up with Retailer Media and shared the details on the variety and quality of these all new collections. She also said m-Commerce has help Myntra getting more customers. ', 'Ruchi Kelan, Anouk, Myntra, Fashion, m-Commerce', '02:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 3450, 'A', '2015-06-10 09:22:15', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0),
(1922, 'atCZ9vpUDKs', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress & Awards 2015 on Times Now', 8, '', NULL, '', 40, 'Indian Education Congress 2015, India biggest  thought leadership platform on Education industry was held on June 10 - 11, 2015. Organized by Franchise India to showcase a product or service in the education space, suppliers and allied industries. This national event was a grand success with over 600 successful educationists, school & college principals, manufacturers, industry veterans, key suppliers, consultants and individuals belonging to the Education category attended the event from across the country. The conference talked about all aspects of Education sector in India and provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading educationists and an understanding around how they are re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe event were concluded by gala awards night- Indian Education Awards 2015.  The Indian Education Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in Education space. The award ceremony felicitated visionaries who have contributed significantly towards the growth of Education Industry in India. From Achievers, Innovators to Suppliers, the awards applauded their efforts in making the Education presence felt in this increasingly competitive world.', 'Indian Education Congress, Indian Education Awards, Times Now, Indian Education Congress Promo, Dilip Chenoy, Kiran Bedi, Pawan Aggarwal, Education Summit, B2B education conference, education awards, education expo, education exhibition, education meet , industry conference ', '0:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6023, 'A', '2015-06-26 16:02:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1921, 'e6HyA_yztko', NULL, 'How Cafe Delhi Heights has grown as a brand', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Vikrant Batra opened his first Cafe Delhi Heights in 2009 and since then he has never looked back when it comes to growth of the brand. Exclusively talking to Restaurant India, he shares the growth plans of the brand mentioning the cities he is targeting for expansion of the cafe Delhi Heights outlets.', 'Cafe Delhi Heights, Casual Dining Chain, Food Service, Restaurant, Vikrant Batra', '05:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4008, 'A', '2015-06-25 15:23:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1923, 'crGBX0AwAQE', NULL, 'Need to respect blue collar jobs: Srish Agarwal', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Being into a business of online digital assessment programme, Mr. Srish Agarwal, Founder & CEO at Testofy highlighted the measuring needs and outcome of skilling India. He believes along with skilling one need to do additional task like need to keep a tap on how one is measuring what is happening so that efforts do not go in vein. Just measuring is not going to work, add feefback to it. He says that we need to add value, attitude from the beginning so that student and people start respecting blue collar jobs. ', 'Srish Agarwal, Skill Development, Testofy, Bule collar jobs', '06:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3563, 'A', '2015-06-29 15:27:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1924, 'VcmqJipK0lQ', NULL, 'Build & Lease to be a great model for schools', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Speaking at Education Congress 2015, Pranav Ansal, MD, Ansal Properties & Infrastructure explained about the Build-&-Lease model of schools opted by Ansal Properties & Infrastructure and the huge market acceptance for this model due to increased land prices and infrastructure cost. ', 'Realty market, Ansal group, Pranav Ansal, Education congress 2015', '04:43', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3105, 'A', '2015-06-29 15:42:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1925, 'DzW14z11-LE', NULL, 'We would not enter the affordable segment, says Ambience Ltd', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Speaking at Education Congress 2015, Raj Singh Gehlot, CMD, Ambience Ltd, the developer popularly known for Ambience Mall, denied to enter the affordable segment of Real Estate citing that they are niche developer catering to premium spaces. Further he spoke about the impact of eCommerce in Real Estate and expected possibilities of revival of the sector.', 'Realty market, Ambience mall, RS Gehlot, Education congress 2015', '04:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3317, 'A', '2015-06-29 15:44:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1926, '1Tb9BCoBtmU', NULL, 'Education plays key role in developing entrepreneurial mind-set', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'In a candid conversation with Entrepreneur India, Dr. Urvashi Makkar, Director  & Professor, Institute of Management Studies (IMS), Ghaziabad share her views on how education sector is shaping up in the course ahead, the global trends and the challenges in higher education. Being an educationist, she says, educations first step undoubtedly is to gain knowledge but that knowledge has to be transformed in the skills also. With more than 20 years of experience in academics, training and consultancy, she says one need to dream big to gain success in their life.  ', 'IMS Ghaziabad, Dr. Urvashi Makkar, Higher Education, Entrepreneurial culture, Business education   ', '06:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5027, 'A', '2015-07-01 14:39:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1927, 'mqyBgvbTk4w', NULL, 'Indian Education system need to be transform', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Amit Gupta, Director & Secretary, Global Knowledge Network Society & Chairman &ndash; Education Committee in his keynote highlighted that Indias basis education need to be transform. He believes that while skilling children, the education which one provides should link to the skill or revolves around it. To meet our local economy requirement, we need to provide skill along with the basic education.  He further put emphasis on the higher education system and the enrolment which need to be evolving with time. ', 'Indian Education, Higher Education Skilling India, Amit Gupta', '14:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2802, 'A', '2015-07-02 14:18:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1928, 'wv11-qsDlg4', NULL, 'One need to have multiple skills to excel in future', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Highlighting the challenges in education sector especially in convincing people about the animation and gaming industry Ashish S Kulkarni, Chairman, FICCI Animation and Gaming Forum & MCCIA Animation & Gaming Committee said animation is not learning computer or it is not about engineering, it an enabler, the skill which one required is arts. He believes one need to really see to what their institutional design is and if they are able to change the institutional design in a very constructive form and bring about the respect and the level playing field for the people to be empowered with the certification which can actually be parallel to the very formal university education system than we will be able to create people to look after the university in creative way.', 'Animation and Gaming Industry, Skilling India, Ashish S Kulkarni, MCCIA Animation & Gaming Committee', '10:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5413, 'A', '2015-07-02 14:20:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1929, 'HU4jS7g-9_c', NULL, 'Education system demands for change', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Dilip Chenoy, Managing Director & CEO, National Skill Development Corporation (NSDC), highlighted the key challenges which education sector is facing. He believes big challenge is the classroom and education system which have not change till date. Also, he put emphasis on the current government policy for education sector. He underline that in today scenario the seed of learning, aspiration of children and the way education is delivered to them is rashly changing. ', 'Skill Development, NSDC, Dilip Chenoy, Skilling India  ', '17:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2990, 'A', '2015-07-02 14:21:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1930, 'sSPcz2ZlTrE', NULL, 'World seems to come at a point where technology will transfer knowledge', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Today technology is playing the major role in imparting education to young minds. Being the Director of Educomp Schools, one of the largest education company in India with its presence in each of the education verticals marked with technology-enabled products, Bindu Rana highlighted in her keynote that today she is seeing the world coming to that point where one have technology not only to transfer not information but knowledge also. She believes most of the teachers in our country have evolved from the stage where technology seems to set fear factor them and have become comfortable with technology.', 'Digital Education, Educomp Schools, Technology-enabled Products, Bindu Rana      ', '06:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3487, 'A', '2015-07-02 14:22:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1931, 'UZJnbecJieA', NULL, 'Supply Chain Challenges by Restaurant by Manish Agarwal', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'In an exclusive interaction with Restaurant India, Manish Agarwal, VP, Gati Kausar shares how Gati-Kausar is trying to build an integrated cold chain supply by ensuring restaurants and hotels food safety, reducing their logistics cost.', 'Gati Kausar, Cold Chain, Supply Chain, Integrated Supply, Restaurant Supply, Food Safety, Manish Agarwal', '05:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5385, 'A', '2015-07-03 15:58:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1932, 'nyeAZ3h8KLo', NULL, 'Indian food processing industry as key sector under Make-in-India by Atul Chaturvedi', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'While addressing the session at FICCI on food potentials and its growth in the country, Atul Chaturvedi, Joint Secretary, DIPP shared his view on the growth of food processing industry in India, inviting both global and local investors to invest in the countries food sector.', 'Atul Chaturvedi, DIPP, Make-in-India, Food Processing, Restaurant Industry, Government of India', '05:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3439, 'A', '2015-07-03 16:00:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1933, '6nmpE7yo5h8', NULL, 'How Indian food industry is creating largest opportunity for job by Piyush Patodia', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Piyush Patodia, ED, Grant Thornton India while unlocking the Food Service Report at FICCI shared that Indian food service industry is one of the vibrant industry generating one of the larger number of employment opportunity.', 'Piyush Patodia, Food Service Report, FICCI Report, Indian Restaurant Reports, Franchise India, Restaurant Industry', '02:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3185, 'A', '2015-07-03 16:01:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1934, 'ahB3O-kV4n8', NULL, 'India, Australia have potential to leverage their collaboration on skill development', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Dr. Amanda Day, Counsellor - Education, Australian High Commission in her keynote highlighted the collaborations among India and Australia in context to skill development.  She believes that there is huge opportunity for India and Australia to look at on how they can leverage the collaboration which they already have. She further highlighted on the need to enhance their transnational skills. ', 'India, Australia, Skill Development, Transnational Skills, Amanda Day, Australian High Commission  ', '09:58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2536, 'A', '2015-07-03 16:06:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1935, 'nOAkuSgKoHY', NULL, 'Use technology to make it pool of knowledge: Ekta Sodha, CEO, Sodha Schools         ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Ekta Sodha, Chief Executive Officer, Sodha Schools highlighted in her keynote that people need to understand use of technology  to make it pool of knowledge for the students. When people talk about innovating the school or classroom, the first thing which come in their mind is the infrastructure. They talk about changing building and furniture but they never think about technology and its use.  She believes that when one think about digitization of education it is the pedagogy one should concentrate on. ', 'Sodha Schools, Digitization Education, Ekta Sodha', '06:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5637, 'A', '2015-07-03 16:09:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1936, 'DJJKUlVPYyQ', NULL, 'Impart education and skill at the same time', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While throwing light on skill development which the need of the hour, Mr. Ganesh Natarajan, Vice Chairman & CEO, Zensar Technologies said, if we are really able to make millions of people skilled in the sector they chose to get trained in and if we can build these pathways to education, we will not only create a country which have all the skilled required to get a livelihood but more importantly we will be able to ensure that we have a educated, literate and skilled country.', 'Skill Development, Ganesh Natarajan, Skilling India, Zensar Technologies', '06:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 3627, 'A', '2015-07-03 16:10:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1937, 'djoGCQMg3v0', NULL, 'Quality of skills depends upon basic education: Om Pathak', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Om Pathak, Founder & Chairman, Delhi Public School Society, Ghaziabad & Sela Qui International School highlighted in his keynote about the importance of skills and education. He believes if one need skills than he need to have good quality of basic knowledge and education without which over layer of skills is not possible. He further says no knowledge and no education is complete without skills and therefore these two run parallel to each other. There is the need to look at education and skills in more integral way rather than to look at them as two separate entities. Quality of skills is largely depended upon the quality for basic education.', 'Skill Development, Basic Education, Delhi Public School Society, Sela Qui International, Om Pathak', '18:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3873, 'A', '2015-07-03 16:11:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1938, 'lx16swZqTao', NULL, 'Technology cannot replace teachers', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Pramod Sharma, Director & Principal at Genesis Global School highlighted the importance and role of teacher in his keynote. He believes that despite of technology being used in classrooms or there access to information on one click of a button but still teachers basic role as the nurturer, motivator will remain and can never be taken away. No matter how much content one have, still we need a teacher to motivate the child, to keep its sprit up and encourage him to take up new challenges in their life.', 'Pramod Sharma, Genesis Global School, Technology in Classroom', '04:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3634, 'A', '2015-07-03 16:14:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1939, 'rK7TRzv5JAk', NULL, 'Vanesa Care to launch 7 more products in 9 months, says Brand CMO', 9, '', NULL, '', 43, 'Leading FMCG Company Vanesa Care, which has created a buzz in the market with its premium range of deodorants &ndash; Denver, endorsed by Bollywood actor Saif Ali Khan & Envy 1000, endorsed by actor Irfan Khan, is seeing good market growth in the wellness industry. Significantly, the company has obtained a 5 per cent share in the overall fragrance market in the last quarter. This year, the company aimed to touch 7.5 per cent growth, unveiled Saurabh Gupta, CMO, Vanesa care, in an exclusive talk with Wellness India and more.', 'Vanesa Care, deodorant, fragrance business, FMCG, personal care', '04:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3928, 'A', '2015-07-06 09:14:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1940, 'zNkvC06cSVI', NULL, 'Indian Salon & Wellness Congress Awards 2015', 9, '', NULL, '', 44, 'Started in 2012, Franchise India Holdings Private Limited initiated event has recognized and reward the beauty industry professionals at the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress Awards 2015. The event was hosted by Bollywood actress Lillete Dubey. Industry veterans felicitated professionals like Shear Genius Academy & Services Pvt Ltd as the Salon of the Year Non- Metro; Headmasters Salon Pvt Ltd bagged laurel for Regional Standalone Salon of the Year- Premium; Regional Salon Chain of the Year- North bagged by Looks Salon while for the Southern region, YLG Salon was the winner in the same category. Further, Mirrors Salon & spa received award for Regional Standalone Salon of the year (Premium) &ndash; South while Saks Hair & Beauty Salon received award in the same category for West region. Likewise, Headturners Salon received award in the same category for North and Head Turners Hair & Spa Salon bagged it for the Eastern region.  ', 'Salon Congress 2015, Wellness Industry, Awards, salon& spa', '09:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5162, 'A', '2015-07-06 09:19:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1941, 'jjZxGbNFh64', NULL, '4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress Awards 2015', 9, '', NULL, '', 44, 'One of the leading honours in the beauty industry, the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress Awards 2015 acknowledged quality service and high standards maintained by salon professionals like VLCC Institute for Best creative resource supplier of the year; Enrich Hair & Skin Solutions Private Limited for Best HR practice of the year; RITU KOLENTINE`S for Hair Trend Pioneer of the Year; Blue Terra Spa for the Customer service excellence award &ndash; AYUSH; Bio-Sols India Private Limited for Products supplier of the year - Salon/ Spa; HEALTHKART for Beauty & Wellness products Retailer/e-Retailer of the Year; Tekno Derm Mediequip Private Limited for Equipments/ tools supplier of the year - Salon & Spa; PARIS DE SALON for Best design salon of the year and Naturals Salon & Spa for the National salon chain of the year.', 'Salon Congress 2015, Wellness Industry, Awards, salon& spa', '21:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6166, 'A', '2015-07-06 09:21:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1942, 'z1Jw4PuaNqM', NULL, '4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress Awards 2015', 9, '', NULL, '', 44, 'The 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress Awards 2015 quality service and high standards maintained by VLCC Wellness Limited for Outstanding contribution to the Aesthetics Industry; SeaSoul Cosmeceuticals Private Limited for Debutant Cosmetic Treatment Player of the Year; Uber Medspa & Style Lounge for Debutant Aesthetics player of the year; SNAP FITNESS for National fitness chain of the year; Lloyds Luxuries Limited for Debutant salon of the year; Mr. Kashiff Khan, Co-Founder and Managing Director, SFL Fitness Private Limited for Entrepreneurial excellence award for Fitness leadership; Mr. Naunihal Singh- CEO, Strands Salons Pvt Ltd for Entrepreneurial excellence award for salon leadership; Mr. Abhilash K Ramesh- Director, KAIRALI AYURVEDIC GROUP and last but not the least, Ms June Tomkyns, June Tomkyns Beauty Parlour for Life Time Achievement Award.', 'Salon Congress 2015, Wellness Industry, Awards, salon& spa', '19:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5310, 'A', '2015-07-07 12:48:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1943, 'W6rJ5ALQA7Y', NULL, 'Time to open arms for mergers, acquisition and tie-up: Jatin Walia', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Jatin Walia, Director - Business Development, Body Spa International Pvt Ltd talked about his business, which he has established in 2004, comparing the wellness industry scenario from then till date. He talked about the fitness industry which was mushrooming in the wellness space ever since the term wellness has been introduced. Walia also talked about how franchising had organised the industry successfully. He also spread light over the scope of merger, acquisitions and consolidations in the wellness space. Walia also highlighted the essentials of wellness industry which includes hygiene, Ayurveda, quality services and much more.', 'Salon Congress, wellness industry, franchise, merger, acquisition, tie-up', '06:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4401, 'A', '2015-07-08 08:58:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1944, 'HZxHqscuMWs', NULL, 'Organic products maintain skin while saving Mother Nature: Manisha Chopra', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Manisha Chopra, Director, SeaSoul Cosmeceuticals Pvt Ltd talked about the organic skin care products market; need to switch to natural products instead of artificially crafted chemical rich cosmetics. The lady gave brief about her natural skin care brand SeaSoul during the grand endeavour and spoken about the impacts of Chemical rich skin care products, dominating the Indian market.  She also insisted on the using organic and nature friendly products in the salons and spas. She also insisted on the training of the therapists and education related with the ingredients of the products, maintain trust by using reliable products and much more.', 'Salon Congress, wellness industry, beauty business, skin care products', '10:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5017, 'A', '2015-07-08 08:59:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1945, 'zQ4OklVPhXw', NULL, 'Wellness industry is making people happy: Ritu Marya', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Addressing the gathering at the 4th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress, Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India Holdings Pvt Ltd, shared gratitude towards the people making the event a grand success year-on-year &ndash; the Wellness Industry professionals. She also showed her confidence over the upcoming growth in the industry with changing technology, evolving market practices, new ideas of venturing into the untouched spaces and delivering improved quality of services to the consumers. Marya also noted the wellbeing of the industry and global markets, how its making people happy and foreseen opportunities of the space. She also related the industry with the ever evolving industry with the retail market, consumer demand and much more.', 'Salon Congress, wellness industry, beauty business, franchise', '20:43', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4689, 'A', '2015-07-08 09:01:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1946, 'DsNqzVhjiDU', NULL, 'Wellness industry is evolving with healthy changes: Shipra Sharma', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Shipra Sharma, Founder, Tattva Spa talked about the Business of Rejuvenation in the spa industry. The lady is handling 28 centres across Indian in 15 cities, served over 3 Lakh guests and trained multiple professionals to create a niche for themselves. Sharma gave an overview on the Global spa industry which has seen exponential growth in the past decade and a lot of market opportunities are foreseen in the Indian wellness space in comparison with the global trade. She also analyzed the markets of day spas in Indian and the queries raised by PE investors while approached by her with her team. To understand the wellness Industry, challenges and opportunities pertaining to the same, here is the must watch analysis.', 'Salon Congress, wellness industry, spa business, franchise, Global wellness industry', '06:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5310, 'A', '2015-07-08 09:03:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1947, 'NUEyPP7EXOI', NULL, 'Need to cater challenges to seek opportunity in education space  ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Avinash Mishra, Sr. Portfolio Associate at Acumem Fund, India highlighted the challenges which investors face while investing in a firm, in his keynote. According to him main challenge is to rein the expectation of scale as budding company need to scale overnight. He also highlighted the trends that are prevailing in the market for investing in education companies. He believes that combination of a product and service work better than either alone and is the latest trend in the market.', 'Acumem Fund, Venture Capital, Education, Education Franchising, Avinash Mishra   ', '05:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3115, 'A', '2015-07-08 09:08:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1948, 'HOnvFi-tAcw', NULL, 'Increasing parental activism will result business to respond to the increasing activism', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While sharing his experience in investing in education sector Imran Jafar, Partner, Gaja Capital highlighted the two massive trends which will transform the Indian education sector in coming years. He believes that increasing parental activism and consumers of education, which are the students will result business to respond to the increasing activism.', 'Investment in Education, Imran Jafar, Gaja Capital', '06:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3235, 'A', '2015-07-08 09:09:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1949, 'rlyRP6ydPBI', NULL, 'Empowering young people is not only about entanglement', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'In candid conversation with Entrepreneur India, Dilip Chenoy, Managing Director & CEO of the National Skill Development Corporation (NSDC) highlighted on the ways in which technology is being used in imparting education and skills to young minds. Also, he put emphasis on the current government policy for education sector. He underline that in today scenario the seed of learning, aspiration of children and the way education is delivered to them is rashly changing.', 'Skilling India, Education in India, Dilip Chenoy, NSDC', '05:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2883, 'A', '2015-07-10 16:52:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1950, 'YtJNy5fXXNI', NULL, 'School focusing only on academics are not working towards high quality education', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'In candid conversation with Entrepreneur India, Dr. Anita Madan who is the Curriculum Development Head at Euro Kids highlighted the scope in the early education sector. She said people have now started to realise the importance of the foundation years of the children and lot of parents have also started to send their children to preschool as the want to build foundation skills in them. She believes curriculum plays a very important role in laying foundation of little ones. According to her curriculum should have balance of academics but lot in terms of CQ (Creative quotient), emotional quotient, social quotient and intelligence quotient.', 'Anita Madan, Preschool Education, Euro Kids', '04:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5463, 'A', '2015-07-13 09:17:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1951, 'uvoH5DvsGwg', NULL, 'Schools should incorporate skill teaching in their curriculum', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Bindu Rana, Director, Educomp Schools, in candid conversation with Entrepreneur India shares her views on how Indian education industry is shaping up in the course ahead and what can be done to make the industry more developed one. She believes that right know education industry is at the Crux of changing the entire education scenario in our country because right know we have the political will to do so. She highlighted that our concentration in this particular time should be on bringing up those who really need our support and empower those who are really doing well at this point of time. ', 'Indian Education Industry, Bindu Rana, Educomp Schools, Skill Teaching', '05:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2891, 'A', '2015-07-13 09:18:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1952, 'hJJE3barUZ0', NULL, 'Education is going to be prime focus in coming years', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Being the Chairman and CEO of Imperial College Bangalore, Dr. Hari Krishna Maram carries rich experience in the field of management and management education, spanning over a decade. He serves as the Governing Council Member at AIMA (All India Management Association). Dr. Maram has published a numerous books, research papers, and also travelled extensively to over 35 countries to get a global perspective on management. To better understand the higher education sector and how it is evolving in India, Franchise India interacted with him.', 'Higher Education, Imperial College Bangalore, Digital Education', '05:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4736, 'A', '2015-07-13 09:19:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1953, 'TBylqThs-2U', NULL, 'Need to encourage skill set in the mind of folks', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Eika Chaturvedi Banerjee, CEO of Future Learning, a Future Group company which is one of India\\\'s leading Skills, Talent and Leadership Development organisations. Banerjee has rich industry exposure and leadership experience of 15 years spanning key corporate Business Leadership roles with blue-chip organizations. Her entrepreneurial journey as the Founder & MD of Finsutra, a boutique Leadership Development, Executive Coaching & Skills Training company was full of insightful. She is closely associated with the National Council of Women- India, the FICCI Ladies organization and the Ex-servicemen Wives Welfare Association. \r\nIn Conversation with Entrepreneur India, Banerjee highlighted that vocational education needs to get the respected deserves for us to have an alternative to white collar employment. She believes that we need to encourage skill set in the mind and one need to start it at the school level. ', 'Skill Development, Future Learning, Eika Chaturvedi Banerjee', '05:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5128, 'A', '2015-07-13 09:21:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1954, 'tju4w5u1DjY', NULL, 'Over politicisation is the main problem in higher education', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'T.P. Sreenivasan being the Vice-Chairman and Executive Head of the Kerala State Higher Education Council with the rank of Vice-Chancellor has nearly 20 years of experience in multilateral diplomacy and has represented India at a number of international conferences organised by the United Nations, the Commonwealth and the Nonaligned Movement. He is the first to be posted to the United States thrice, the first to hold the two crucial positions of Deputy Permanent Representative to the United Nations and Deputy Chief of Mission in the embassy in Washington. \r\nIn conversation with Entrepreneur India, T.P. Sreenivasan highlighted the challenges and the issues which higher education is currently facing. According to him over politicisation is the main problem as everything is decided on the bases of party and power and they tend to put people in place that may not really fit into the academic requirement.  ', 'Kerala State Higher Education Council, Higher education, T.P. Sreenivasan', '05:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3333, 'A', '2015-07-13 09:22:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1955, '7h1XrE5c4Rc', NULL, 'Indian education sector can become education destination for world', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Vineet Gupta, an Entrepreneur with interests in the education and pharmaceutical business is Managing Director at Jamboree Education and Trustee at Ashoka University.  In outspoken conversation with Entrepreneur India he highlighted the opportunity which Indian education industry has to become one the world class education hub for the students. He believes that there is the tremendous opportunity in the education sector to become the education destination for the world. And If we get our higher education institution right than we could be the place where world sends it children to be educated. ', 'Higher Education, Vineet Gupta, Jamboree Education, Ashoka University', '04:43', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4316, 'A', '2015-07-13 09:23:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1956, 'rLLj5vXuSJ8', NULL, 'Make learning more fun', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Vittal Bhandary has conceptualised Little Elly chain of preschools with the vision of nurturing great values in children, combining them harmoniously with early childhood education. It took twenty five years of single-minded focus, great passion, concerted effort and deep understanding about the dynamics of childcare to lead an accomplished team of professionals and developing an organization, whose prime focus is early childhood care. His journey began by setting up successful preschool and childcare environments in the Middle East. From a single pre-school set-up in BTM Layout in 2008, the Little Elly group of Institutions, which comprise Franchisees and Training Centres, are spread all over the country, providing individualized and well researched learning methods to aid in the overall development of a child.\r\nFranchise India interacted with him to know more about early childhood education, challenges it face and what are their expectation from the government.', 'Early Childhood Education, Preschool, Little Elly, Child Development', '06:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5378, 'A', '2015-07-13 09:25:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1957, 'meJ045B7QXk', NULL, 'High quality education should be left free: Om Pathak', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Om Pathak, a soldier, civil servant and an educationist, is the founder & Chairman of Delhi Public School Society, Ghaziabad that now runs four schools in North India and is also the founder & Chairman of SelaQui International School in Dehradun - one of the leading fully residential schools in the India. He has been associated with education for more than 34 years. In order to develop better understanding about current education scenario, challenges it face, and how can we help students to achieve high quality higher education, Franchise India interacted with him.', 'Higher education, DPS Society, SelaQui International School, Om Pathak, High Quality Education', '08:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4412, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:05:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1958, 'XzyjRUEe5Ds', NULL, 'Need to develop entrepreneurial mindset: Prof. Krishna Kumar Pande', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Prof. Krishna Kumar Pande is a seasoned professional and administrator having a rich experience in institution building and has to his credit the establishment of six professional institutions in Engineering & Management from concept planning to operations, including two Universities. He also heads an NGO and presently spearheads the Community College for the Kumaon University and is actively associated with improving the skills of the youth of Uttarakhand. He has trained over 4,000 schools drop-outs of Uttarakhand. In conversation with Franchise India he highlighted the role of skill development in education,  importance of entrepreneurial mindset,  and how can one provide high quality of education our budding generation.', 'Higher Education, Entrepreneurship Education, Teerthanker Mahaveer University, Business Schools, Skill Development   ', '05:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4677, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:06:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1959, 'h5Gz6V3qsME', NULL, 'Experifun brings radically new way of learning science', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Rakesh, Co-Founder and CEO at Experifun, an innovation driven startup bringing radically new way of learning science and computers. Being an alumnus of IIM Ahmedabad and IIT BHU, Kumar started his career in technology and travelled across the world in his 14+ years of corporate experience before starting Experifun. He has a wide experience in the field of technology and managing businesses.\r\nFranchise India interacted with him to know more about Experifun, how it is useful for children, challenges he faced and about his entrepreneurial journey.', 'Experifun, Edutech Startup, Innovative Education  ', '06:39', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4889, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:07:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1960, 'ff5CF8pplmg', NULL, 'Curriculum needs to design to provide holistic development of child', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'In conversation with Franchise India Arshiya Afsar, Executive Director at Iris Florets School shares her view on early childhood education. She highlighted the current scenario of early childhood education, role of technology to provide high quality education to toddlers and the budding opportunities for the sector. She also pointed out the challenges and the issues prevailing in the sector which need to be addressed immediately.', 'Preschool education, Early Childhood Development, Iris Florets ', '06:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3808, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:08:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1961, '-617rTwvU7k', NULL, 'Place where every child feels special', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Anita Malhotra, with a deep-rooted commitment to education believes in providing her students with cutting edge in Technology along with a strong foundation in life skills. An educationist of high repute, she has been with the Delhi Public School Society & its school for 30 years, first as a teacher & then evolved as a principal. A recipient of the State Teachers Award, besides numerous other awards for her contribution in the field of education, she has successfully introduced and implemented radical measures with her comprehensive know &ndash;how in Technology and Education. \r\nWhile Interacting with Franchise India, Anita Malhotra highlighted the growth of lotus Valley International School, Gurgaon and how it is helping in providing high quality education to young generation.', 'Education & Training, lotus Valley International School Gurgaon   ', '03:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4871, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:11:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1962, 'QEbAEpswwIQ', NULL, 'HBS contributes in imparting high quality education to young generation', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Anjali Raina , Executive Director of the Harvard Business School India Research Centre  holds an MBA from the IIM, Calcutta. Under Anjalis leadership, the HBS IRC has facilitated the writing of over 171case studies on Indian Business Practice and supported 69research projects. She has co-authored several case studies such as Aadhaar: Indias Unique Identification System, TeamLease: Putting India to Work (II) Legally and many more. She is a Director on the Board of Harvard Business Publishing, India, the Regional President (Western Region) of NHRDN, Trustee to LIFE Trust, an Advisory Member on the Board of HBS Club of India.\r\nIn conversation with Franchise India, she highlighted the scenario of higher education in India and how HBS is imparting high quality education to our young generation. ', 'Higher Education, Havard Business School India, Anjali Raina ', '02:58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4484, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:13:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1963, 'MBLGkZ75xjQ', NULL, 'Early learning is all about bringing unstructured play to their homes', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Arunprasad Durairaj, co-founder and CEO, Flintobox, an early child development startup designing and developing contents for kids under 7 years, believes that the existing early education system for children needs an upgrade and is passionate about bringing it himself. His professional experience includes an M&A specialist role at Samsung Korea and roles at VC funds investing in early stage US healthcare startups. He holds an MBA from Tuck School of Business at Dartmouth and a bachelor of engineering from Madurai Kamaraj University, India.\r\nIn conversation with Franchise India, he shares his entrepreneurial journey and his experience in preschool market.', 'School Kits, Preschool Education, Flintobox, Early Child Development', '04:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6028, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:14:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1964, 'F03Zg60Z8Mc', NULL, 'Vocational education will bring next growth level change in education space', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Dr. Amanda Day is Counsellor (Education) at Australian High Commission, New Delhi. Dr. Day has worked for the Australian Department of Education and Training since 2007, primarily in school education policy. Her focus has been on assessment and reporting through the National Assessment Program, which includes both domestic and international student assessment. Dr. Day began her career as a Japanese high school teacher in Canberra. She holds a PhD in nineteenth century Australian History from the Australian National University.\r\nFranchise India interacted with her to know more about the ties up between India and Australia for education & training.', 'India, Austrailia, Skill Development, Education & Training, Australian High Commission', '05:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4889, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:15:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1965, 'rVVnw31vi14', NULL, 'CSR is not something outside you, it is integral to you, says Kiran Bedi  ', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Dr. Kiran Bedi joined the officer ranks of Indian Police Service in 1972 and became the first woman in India to do so. Currently, her NGOs are running B-Schools in partnership with Universities and Vocational Institutes for Indian youth. She has been voted as MSN Most Admired Indian Female Icon 2011 and amongst top 10 women Icons of 2013 by The Economic Times. Franchise India interacted with her to know more about Navjyoti and India Vision foundation, how it is contributing in CSR and social entrepreneurship. ', 'Kiran Bedi, CSR, Social Entrepreneurship, Navjyoti, India Vision Foundation, Vocational Education', '03:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4990, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:18:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1966, 'tYNjmg7BZxE', NULL, 'Early education space carry lot of potential in it: Sukhvinder Singh, Business Head, Kidzee', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Sukhvinder Singh Bindra has been part of Zee Learn for over a year now and is responsible for the overall strategy, operations and Business Development of Kidzee Preschools. As a key member of the leadership team, Sukhvinder has aggressively driven the growth of the Kidzee business in India with his acute sense of streamlining operations, franchisee growth and profitability. Franchise India interacted with him to develop better understanding of current market scenario and the opportunities for preschool sector to grow in the market.', 'Preschool Education, Early Childhood Development, Zee Learn', '07:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5094, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:20:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1967, 'sUOHYos0YsY', NULL, 'Education sector provides huge opportunity for investors  ', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Vijay Shukla co-founded Setu Ventures, a company providing professional and financial assistance to early stage companies and entrepreneurs and ValueFirst, Indias leading enterprise-focused digital media company.\r\nHe has over 20 years of industry experience and specializes in the areas of management consulting, strategy, business development and engineering. An engineering graduate from IIT-BHU, Varanasi and MBA from XLRI Jamshedpur, Vijay has mastered the art of evaluating business strategies and organizational processes through his career with working in the domains of education, public sector, entrepreneurship, information and mobile technology, FMCG and management consulting services.\r\nTo develop better understanding in the field of investment and entrepreneurship, Franchise India Interacted with him.', 'Eduvisors, Edupreneur, Entrepreneurship, Investment, Digital Education, Vijay Shukla  ', '08:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 7415, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:21:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1968, 'TN4GcX9UI4k', NULL, 'Need to evolve Pedagogy: Vineet Whig', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Vineet Whig carries over twenty three years of rich experience across the education, corporate and vocational training, and publishing domains. He has worked in a variety of leadership roles at NIIT, Wipro, iDiscoveri Education, and Pearson VUE prior to joining Encyclopaedia Britannica last year. At Britannica South Asia, Vineet as Chief Operating Officer has the oversight of the learning solutions and product development functions for K-12 and Higher Education. His key mandate is to develop and deliver innovative solutions which are specific and uniquely tailored to each market context and needs.\r\nFranchise India interacted with him to develop better understanding of education sector.', 'K12 Education, Britannica, Changing Dynamics, Education & Training', '03:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5249, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:22:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1969, 'FAFtS1KO22Q', NULL, 'Imparting education through mobile platform', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Sanjay Purohit, an expert in business innovation and process transformation has extensive experience of leading transformation projects across several industries and organizations. He has experience in technology, textiles and outsourcing services industries and has worked in USA, India and Singapore.\r\nFranchise India interacted with him to know more about mobile based learning, role of technology in imparting education and current scenario of e-learning market in India.', 'M-learning, iProf, Higher Education, Sanjay Purohit ', '03:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 5066, 'A', '2015-07-14 09:24:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1970, 'SD4QPFNX8rY', NULL, 'CSR will allow children to live better life', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Karuna Shriram is an Educationist and a Social Worker. Her commitment in the field of education and social welfare for over two decades has given concrete shape directly to various education policies and welfare programmes. She works with various NGOs like Aarth - Aastha, Salaam Baalak Trust, DSWSC, Tamana and others in various capacities including being a member of the Board. Shriram is a member of the Japan Committee of Asian University for Women Bangladesh. She is also a member of PHD Task Force on Women & Child Development, Rotary Club of Delhi Midtown and a Paul Harris Fellow.\r\nHaving such a depth knowledge in social work, Franchise India Interacted with her to develop better understanding of challenges in education sector which can be achieved by social business and role of CSR in education space.', 'CSR, Bansi Dhar School, Social Business, Child Development', '04:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5181, 'A', '2015-07-20 09:46:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1971, 'T0AyzuqEtkI', NULL, 'Education companies carry huge potential: Neha Grover', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Ms. Neha Grover is responsible for top-down analysis and investment opportunities in sectors such as Education, Textiles, and Agri-inputs, and has evaluated and recommended investments on a bottom-up basis in other sectors in the listed space. She brings to the table about 10 years of experience. Grover is also responsible for finance, accounts, compliance, fund administration, and risk management. She is one of the key architects of the business innovation initiatives, which involved adapting the traditional Indian Private Equity model to generate higher returns for investors with no incremental risk.\r\nFranchise India interacted with her to develop better understanding of investments in education space and what are challenges investors face while investing.', 'Investment Opportunities, Baring Private Equity, Education ', '07:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6573, 'A', '2015-07-20 09:47:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(1972, '7OhPuiL6Mmk', NULL, 'Private sector needs encouragement: Amit Gupta', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Amit Gupta has depth understanding of Education landscape from K-12 to higher Education. He is Chairman of education Committee of PHD Chamber, member school education committee FICCI and in Management Committee of ASSOCHAM. Recently, Amit worked with CBSE for their foray into the development of an international curriculum adapted for students studying in Indian schools outside of India. Furthermore he collaborated with them on the formulation of professional development and leadership programs for teacher and in project Udaan. He has implemented many initiatives in education internationally in cooperation with ministries, corporate and international organizations such as NMEICT in India and USAID, GTZ, IFC and NAED overseas.\r\nFranchise India interacted with him to know about government initiatives, scenario of education in India and what all government need to do to provide high quality and affordable education to our young generation.', 'Skill Development, Higher education, PHD Chamber, Amit Gupta   ', '08:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 6, 6, 30, 4553, 'A', '2015-07-20 09:49:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1973, 'uNqKGp76-E0', NULL, 'Animation skills allow you to tell your story in most powerful manner', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Ashish S K has set up world-class animation studios in India and created the finest original Indian animated contents. He is the creator and executive producer of the magnum opus animated feature film Krishna aur Kans. It is Indias first animated stereoscopy 3D feature film, released in three languages - Hindi, English and Tamil. The latest feather in his cap is the animated tele-series Shaktimaan, which is now telecasted on Nick channel.\r\nFranchise India interacted with Ashish to develop better understanding of animation industry and its role in education space.', 'Animation, Skill Development, Storytelling, FICCI', '06:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 5, 5, 25, 3788, 'A', '2015-07-20 09:50:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1974, 'PRyfz08ANAo', NULL, 'Prime motive should not be profit for education institutes', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Prabhat is co-founder of chain of K-12 schools and Play Schools under the brand Pathways World Schools and Pathways Early Years. He started his carrier at an early age by joining the family business of natural dimensional stones. He chairs/co-chairs various education committees at premium business chambers in India. He engages with the government towards nation building by aligning private initiatives with government agenda to build excellence in education delivery. Franchise India interacted with him to know more about his entrepreneurial journey and how he see education sector shaping up in course ahead?', 'K12education, Pathways World School, Prabhat Jain, Edu Start-ups, Entrepreneur ', '06:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5143, 'A', '2015-07-20 16:05:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1975, 'M8EvZqSKouY', NULL, 'Digitization of education is not just about being a smart school', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Anirudh Gupta, Chief Executive Officer of DCM Group of Institutions during his keynote highlighted the importance of digitization of education. He believes that education institutes or schools need to be digitizes otherwise they will be perish. He further shares that digitization of education is not only about putting equipment or technology in classrooms, technology has to be embedded in day to day functioning of school. ', 'Digitization of Education, DCM Group of Institutions, Tech Education', '10:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5597, 'A', '2015-07-20 17:06:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1976, 'L5vCsR0PSNY', NULL, 'Skills along with community development will work wonders for a person', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'During her keynote, Eika Chaturvedi Banerjee highlighted the need of skilling Indian youth to achieve economic growth. Having a rich industry exposure and leadership experience of 15 years Banerjee further pointed out skilling by itself adds no value to it, person need to learn community development along with it.', 'Skill Development, Future Learning, Indian retail, Eika Chaturvedi Banerjee, Skilling India ', '13:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2858, 'A', '2015-07-20 17:09:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1977, 'GKZk_AkBAk4', NULL, 'Higher education is about creating lifelong learners: Anjali Raina ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Anjali Raina, Executive Director at Harvard Business School India Research in her keynote shares her view on how education institutions can prepare young graduate for 21st century. She believes that lifelong learning is what educational institution should be equipping for. She further underline that higher education institutions are no to prepare people for jobs as they are not a job providing organization, there main motive is to prepare people for lifelong. Higher education is not only about developing competence, one also needs to build character, character where one can be trusted.', 'Higher Education, Harvard Business School India Research, Lifelong Learning, Anjali Raina   ', '10:39', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 5645, 'A', '2015-07-21 09:39:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1978, '6_xIQvYRmiw', NULL, 'Parents contribute largely towards the success of preschool programme ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While throwing light on measurement of effectiveness of preschool programme, Arshiya Afsar, Executive Director, Iris Florets said, if preschool educators really want to measure the effectiveness of their programme than they need to join hands with the childs parent they want to educate.  She also adds that this could be only possible if preschool educators have standardized instruction materials. So to nurture the future of kids one need to use the opportunity wisely.', 'Preschool, Iris Florets, Arshiya Afsar, Primary Education ', '10:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 5036, 'A', '2015-07-21 09:41:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1979, 'w3bOQ_gl2RY', NULL, 'Flintobox: answer to the growing need of early learning in India', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Being a Co &ndash;Founder of Flintobox, Arunprasad Durairaj in his keynote speak about his organization, what it is all about, challenges they faced during establishing themselves in the market and how they see the early education sector for business. Flintobox is the early learning company that deliver content for kids less than 7 years.', 'Early learning, Preschool, Flintobox, Hands on Learning, Arunprasad Durairaj ', '08:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4924, 'A', '2015-07-21 09:42:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1980, 'oIgLryzBXEc', NULL, 'WondernBoxx allow kids to learn while playing', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Deepanshu Arora, Co &ndash;Founder of WonderBoxx is his keynote highlighted about their product and there organization. He put emphasis on what all wonderboxx is about and how it works. Usually, parents take stress seeing their kids spend more time in front of idiot box or engaged on hi-tech gadgets. To end all the unwanted worries of parents, Delhi-based innovative startup come-up with an exclusive Wonderboxx for children to learn while playing.', 'Preschool, Early Learning, Deepanshu Arora, WonderBoxx', '11:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4495, 'A', '2015-07-21 09:43:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1981, 'sAfVAd6jOKw', NULL, 'How healthy snacking is building growth in food business in India by Vikram Agarwal', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'In an exclusive interaction to Restaurant India, Vikram Agarwal shares How India is getting addicted to the healthy snacking concept with global brands entering the space.', 'Cornitos, Nachos, Healthy Snacking, Greendot, Healthy Food, Mexican Food', '05:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 4623, 'A', '2015-08-04 09:11:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1982, 'JiFFzLVIG_o', NULL, 'Technology has power to disseminate knowledgeacross the world:  Shantanu Rooj, Schoolguru.in', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Shantanus passion for entrepreneurship has allowed him to open his new venture in the form of Schoolguru in year 2012. It is academic support services organization providing technology based academic services to Indian universities.  Rooj is a CBSE All India Topper and a Gold Medalist in Engineering from IIT (BHU) Varanasi and has successfully completed his Masters in Business Administration from JamnalalBajaj Institute of Management Studies, Mumbai.  He has an experience of more than 17 years in the field of Information Technology Architecting and Consulting. \r\nEntrepreneur India interacted with him to develop better understanding of distance learning, its current scenario in India and how schoolguru is helping in bridging the existing market gap.   ', 'Distance Learning, Online Education, Schoolguru, Shantanu Rooj, Edupreneur ', '09:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 6919, 'A', '2015-08-04 13:57:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1983, 'Xo3x4rI_81w', NULL, 'Entrepreneur India 2015 on Times Now', 2, '', NULL, '', 17, 'Entrepreneur India 2015, Indias biggest  thought leadership platform on Entrepreneur industry was held on July 22 - 23, 2015 at J.W. Marriott, New Delhi. Organized by Franchise India, the 5th National Convention on Entrepreneurship has become the marquee entrepreneurship event on building enterprising entrepreneurs in India. The event attracted over 500 leading entrepreneurs and members from the Indian investor community together with CEOs and professionals leading Growth oriented organizations. The show also witnessed the mega launch of Entrepreneur Media Inc in India, parent company of Entrepreneur Magazine & Entrepreneur.com, and was facilitated by our Guest of Honor Mr. Ryan Shea, President & COO of Entrepreneur Media Inc. as well as Mr. Rajiv Pratap Rudy, Union Minister of State Skill Development and Entrepreneurship (Independent Charge) & Parliamentary Affairs, Government of India. \\r\\n\\r\\nAlong with the Congress, Annual Entrepreneur India 2015 Awards were also took place. The Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in Entrepreneurial space. The award ceremony was aimed at felicitating successful startups, Entrepreneurs and the people who are supporting them. From Achievers, Innovators to Suppliers, the awards applauded their efforts in making the Entrepreneurs presence felt in this increasingly competitive world.', 'Entrepreneur India 2015,Franchise India, Entrepreneur Conference, Entrepreneur Awards, Entrepreneur Summit, Entrepreneur Exhibition, Pitch room, Start up funding, Business conference, National entrepreneur convention, Times Now, Ryan Shea, Rajiv Pratap Rudy, Entrepreneur Magazine, Entrepreneur.com, Entrepreneur Magazine, Entrepreneur India 2015 promo', '0:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 5768, 'A', '2015-08-06 17:12:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1984, '7BF6WlRd7I0', NULL, 'Entrepreneur India 2015 (Times Now Episode)', 2, '', NULL, '', 16, 'Entrepreneur India 2015, Indias biggest thought leadership platform on Entrepreneur industry was held on July 22 - 23, 2015 at J.W. Marriott, New Delhi. Organized by Franchise India, the 5th National Convention on Entrepreneurship has become the marquee entrepreneurship event on building enterprising entrepreneurs in India. The event attracted over 500 leading entrepreneurs and members from the Indian investor community together with CEOs and professionals leading Growth oriented organizations. The show also witnessed the mega launch of Entrepreneur Media Inc in India, parent company of Entrepreneur Magazine & Entrepreneur.com, and was facilitated by our Guest of Honor Mr. Ryan Shea, President & COO of Entrepreneur Media Inc. as well as Mr. Rajiv Pratap Rudy, Union Minister of State Skill Development and Entrepreneurship (Independent Charge) & Parliamentary Affairs, Government of India. \r\n\r\nAlong with the Congress, Annual Entrepreneur India 2015 Awards were also took place. The Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in Entrepreneurial space. The award ceremony was aimed at felicitating successful startups, Entrepreneurs and the people who are supporting them. From Achievers, Innovators to Suppliers, the awards applauded their efforts in making the Entrepreneurs presence felt in this increasingly competitive world.', 'Entrepreneur India 2015, Entrepreneur Awards, Entrepreneur Convention, Entrepreneur Summit, Ryan Shea, Rajiv Pratap Rudy, Entrepreneur Magazine, Start up funding, Pitchroom, Entrepreneur Exhibition, Entrepreneur Conference, Business Conference', '26:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5274, 'A', '2015-08-19 17:45:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1985, 'lnnSZIGZnuU', NULL, 'How taste has made a  difference in eating habits of Indians by Dhiren Kanwar', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'In an exclusive interaction to Restaurant India, Dhiren Kanwar, Country Head- India, Area GM- South Asia & Customer Service Associate, Puratos shares How customer taste in  India is changing and the marketing approach to grow in this fast growing market.', 'Puratos, Bakery Supplier, Food Supplier, Food taste', '04:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1860, 'A', '2015-09-15 09:03:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1986, 'WvggpHI-bjw', NULL, 'Balancing life between chef and entrepreneur', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Masterchef Sanjeev Kapoor is known as the Rachel Ray of India. His restaurants Sanjeev Kapoors Khazana, The Yellow Chilli, Signature, Hong Kong and Options are considered the best in their categories not only in India but abroad as well. Talking at Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, he shares How has he grown from a chef to an Entrepreneur focusing on the business part of the food.', 'Chef, Food Business, Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, Sanjeev Kapoor, Masterchef', '05:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2510, 'A', '2015-09-17 16:43:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1987, 'LR8DbrOCo70', NULL, 'Changing colours of Indian food by Chef Vicky Ratnani', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Chef Vicky is a Global Indian Chef in a true sense. He is also Director Culinary for Everstone Capital and is currently setting up various restaurant brands including - The Disgruntled Chef in India. Speaking at Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, Vicky pointed How Indian food has grown over the years.', 'Vicky Ratnani, Celebrity Chef, Everstone Capital, F&B Asia Ventures, Burger King, Indian Restaurant Congress 2015', '03:51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2704, 'A', '2015-09-17 16:45:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1988, 'n5ORWZxvrUU', NULL, 'People should reconsider what innovation really means: Dr. Shiva  &ndash;Part 1', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Dr. Shiva is the inventor of email and a world-renowned Systems Scientist. He is a polymath and holds four degrees from Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT). Further, he is also a recipient of many national and international awards. Recently, he has been awarded as Serial Entrepreneur of the Year. While addressing the audiences in the Entrepreneur India 2015 show, Shiva share his story which he hopes that it will not only inspire people to only innovate but also to reconsider what innovation really means and what it means to be revolutionary. ', 'Email Inventor, Entrepreneur, Dr. V.A. Shiva Ayyadurai, System Scientist', '24:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3742, 'A', '2015-09-22 16:22:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1989, 'MfhNN0Mc-TI', NULL, 'Galvanising a new age of Innovation in India: Dr. Shiva &ndash; Part 2', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Being an American scientist of Indian origin, inventor and entrepreneur, Dr. Shiva Ayyadurai as a 14 year school boy, in the year 1979, developed an electronic version of an interoffice mail system which is called Email which was copyrighted in the year 1982. With the vision is to galvanize a new age of Indian Innovation Dr Shiva wants to implant a unique seed of culture in every Indian to enable them uncoil their DNA needed to reclaim their indisputable heritage of Innovation.', 'System Scientist, Email inventor, Dr. V.A. Shiva Ayyadurai, India, Entrepreneur', '13:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4236, 'A', '2015-09-22 16:24:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1990, '7fpYdGvO_GA', NULL, 'How Technology and Entertainment connecting people by Priyank Sukhija', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Priyank Sukhija, is one of the most successful restaurateur who started his first restaurant when he was a college student 15 years ago. He currently operates more than 20 fine and casual dining restaurants across Delhi-NCR. Speaking at Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, Sukhija tells about his new ventures in the pipeline. ', 'Restaurants, Food, Technology, Food Business, Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, Priyank Sukhija, Lazeez Affaire Group', '04:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3276, 'A', '2015-09-23 09:16:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1991, 'R0Pixax9ASQ', NULL, 'The Bludgeoning phase of Restaurant Industry by Zorawar Kalra', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Zorawar Kalra is one of the youngest restaurateurs today. He is the Founder and MD of Massive Restaurants Pvt Ltd which has some of the amazing brands like Farzi Cafe, Masala Library, Made In Punjab and the newly opened Papaya and Mithai. Addressing the audience at 5th Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, he shares The new age twist of modern Indian food and how is it gaining ground in India. ', 'Restaurants, Indian Food, Food Business, Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, Zorawar Kalra, Massive Restaurants, F Cafe', '02:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3436, 'A', '2015-09-23 09:17:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1992, 'KzBPiDsvR_g', NULL, 'Entrepreneurship is the lonely battle of singular track to a bumpy landscape', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Ajai Chowdhry is one of the six founder members of HCL, who began his journey more than three decades ago with a dream to give India its very own microcomputer. Chowdhry has been a key force in driving the growth of HCL and led the foundation of HCL overseas operations, starting with Singapore in 1980s and later expanded to the other South Asian Markets. While addressing the audiences at the Entrepreneur India 2015 show, Chowdhry shares his view on supporting and mentoring growing entrepreneurs. He believe that for a young person to embark on the path of entrepreneurship they need certain qualities. One should have passion, fearlessness and dedication to become an entrepreneur. They should be armed with education, knowledge, and expertise of mentors and an ecosystem that supports and fosters their efforts.', 'Entrepreneurship, Ajai Chowdhry, HCL, Start-up, Mentoring, Entrepreneur India 2015 ', '09:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5406, 'A', '2015-09-25 16:14:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1993, 'ikvLz1BNQtI', NULL, 'Is India really the nation of Angels?', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Harshads passion for finance inspired him to create his own investment advisory and wealth management company Intercontinental Investments in 2005, followed by Excelman India in 2006. Further, with his interest in investment banking and desire to help early-stage ventures, Harshad founded ah! Ventures (2009) and CLUB ah! Network (2012). In the past 10 years, Harshad has grown his ventures into reputed, self-sufficient businesses that fuel their own growth. While addressing the audiences at the Entrepreneur India 2015 show, Harshad highlighted certain facts and figures which state that India even lacks behind Canada in term of angel investments. He stated that it is really important for India to keep the pace with changing time.', 'Angel investors, Harshad Lahoti, ah! Ventures, Entrepreneur India 2015, Entrepreneurship  ', '06:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4223, 'A', '2015-09-25 16:15:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1994, 'nmKJf31aSNE', NULL, 'India should scale-up opportunities to build world-class businesses', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Rajesh during his keynote shares the importance of entrepreneurship in the country. He believes that Ministry of Skill Development and Entrepreneurship is still a start-up and as start-up they have been tasked to lay down the framework to ensure that demography dividend turns out to be asset and not a liability for them. He furthers highlighted that it is every essential to build an ecosystem for entrepreneurs and create more opportunities for them at all levels. He believes that India need to realize the scale-up opportunities to build a new generation of world-beating business.   ', 'Ministry of Skill Development and Entrepreneurship, Entrepreneur India 2015, Demographic Dividend, Start-up, Rajesh Agrawal', '13:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2701, 'A', '2015-09-25 16:16:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1995, 'gfb-X_LvCts', NULL, 'Fast is no more good enough. Today businesses have to be real time', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Being associated with Bharti Airtel, Ashish Arora has been instrumental in drawing a strategic roadmap for the Airtel Corporate Business - the B2B arm that caters to growing businesses and entrepreneurs in India. Arora comes with over 18 years of experience in sales, marketing and business operations and has led critical business units at HCL and Sify. While addressing the audiences at Entrepreneur India 2015 show, Arora highlighted the growth drivers that are helping corporate to scale up their business in todays time. He further placed emphasis on the way the technology is enabling one to be able to leverage these growth drivers in their business.', 'Bharti Airtel, Entrepreneur show 2015, Entrepreneur, Corporates, Ashish Arora', '11:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3616, 'A', '2015-09-25 16:19:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1996, 'e5peHOtkr8E', NULL, 'There should be an ecosystem to encourage entrepreneurs', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Ravindra Nath is the Chairman and Managing Director of National Small Industries Corporation (NSIC), a Public Sector organization of Government of India. With experience of around 30 years in various areas of finance, accounts and management, Nath has held many senior positions of corporate head of finance in public and private sectors. He has developed many new programs which have been implemented through NSIC for promotion and growth of MSMEs as well as Entrepreneurship development in the country. At Entrepreneur Show 2015, Nath shares his thoughts on building an ecosystem for entrepreneurship so that more and more opportunities are created for entrepreneurs at all levels.', 'Entrepreneur Show 2015, Government of India, NSIC, Ravindra Nath, Entrepreneurship, Entrepreneurs', '20:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4304, 'A', '2015-09-25 16:20:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1997, 'avr9U-zXyNk', NULL, 'Kent RO to enter into Air Purifier category; open to invest in tech solution', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'With an aim to offer extensive wellness to Indian consumers, Leading Water Purifier brand - Kent RO is set to enter into Air Purifier category. Known for maintaining high quality standards, the brand has also expressed its willingness towards investing in technically advance start-up project. In an exclusive conversation with WI Bureau, Mahesh Gupta, CEO, Kent RO disclosed his extensive plans related with his successfully outperforming venture and more.  ', 'Kent RO, Air Purifier, Wellness, Water purifier, Business growth', '04:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4031, 'A', '2015-10-01 17:39:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1998, 'Dk1k_YyaTic', NULL, 'Superman deodorants mark our foray in licensing', 46, '', NULL, '', 48, 'Vanesa Care has inked a strategic partnership with Cartoon Network Enterprises (CNE), the licensing and merchandising arm of media conglomerate Turner International India to introduce its first ever DENVER Superman co-branded deodorants for the Superman fans. Moving further, Vanesa Care has also acquired license for Batman and plans to introduce Batman branded deodorants and perfumes. Saurabh Gupta, CMO, Vanesa Care talks to License India about the different approach and marketing strategy towards bothe the superheroes and the much-needed handholding provided by licensor. ', 'Vanesa Care, Cartoon Network Enterprises, Turner International India, Saurabh Gupta, DENVER Superman, DENVER deodorants, Licensing in India, Brand Licensing', '07:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3803, 'A', '2015-10-05 09:18:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(1999, '-0rCsIU2ihA', NULL, 'Betting high on Indian beauty market; Plans to open factory in future: Bottega President', 9, '', NULL, '', 43, 'Italian skincare brand, Bottega di LungaVita has  entered into Indian beauty market in 2013. The international brand is holding a reputed position in the European markets with 20 per cent market share in skin care segment. In span of two years, the brand has established a very strongest presence in the Indian market as well, especially in northern region. Gradually moving towards Western region in cities like Goa, Mumbai etc, the brand have risen to approx 130 points of sale, with 6 flagship stores - 2 in Delhi , and 1 each in Mizoram , Chandigarh , Ludhiana and Goa. In a recent visit to India, WI Bureau shared a candid moment with ALBERTO DONATI, Brand Owner & President, Bottega Di Lungavita, Officina Farmaceutica Italiana (OFI), who is laying high hopes on Indian beauty market.', 'Bottega Di Lungavita, Italian brand, Wellness, Beauty business, anti-wrinkle products ', '05:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5603, 'A', '2015-10-06 16:02:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2000, '87Wml6JtSlA', NULL, 'How Global Brands view India as a Market by Alpha Maiava', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Alpha Maiava, joined the Sumo International team in 2014 as Franchise Sales & International Growth Manager. He has an extensive experience in sales, marketing, management and hospitality. Talking at 5th Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, Alpha shares his expansion plan for Indian market. ', 'Global Brands, Sumo Sushi & Bento, Franchising, Restaurant, Japanese Restaurant, 5th Indian Restaurant Congress, Franchise India', '02:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3034, 'A', '2015-10-06 16:43:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2001, 'S5B1choBO60', NULL, 'Challenges in Restaurant Business by Narendra Malhotra', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Narendra Malhotra has over 25 years of rich, cross cultural experience in F&B retail. Speaking at 5th Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, he tells us about Challenges pertaining in Restaurant Business.', 'Oriental Cuisines, Restaurant, Restaurant Congress, Franchise India, Narendra Malhotra, Food Biz', '03:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2095, 'A', '2015-10-06 16:44:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2002, 'a9Yv8cr0SpE', NULL, 'Helping Start-up Grow by Derek Kightlinger', 7, '', NULL, '', 35, 'Derek Kightlinger is a consumer goods and retail consultant in the New Delhi office of Boston Consulting Group, Sharing his thought leaderships at 5th Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, Derek shares How BCG is helping business grow.', 'BCG, Food Business, Investment, Start-up, Food Funding, 5th Indian Restaurant Congress 2015, Franchise India', '01:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2812, 'A', '2015-10-06 16:50:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2003, '_dYhJN5WZ6c', NULL, 'Understanding consumers in all it periphery - Part 1', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'In a panel discussion held at the Indian Retail and eRetail Congress 2015 organised by Franchise India some prominent retailers shared their thoughts on how to build a sustainable brand that exceeds consumer demands and fulfill their expectations. They also spoke on maintaining a balance with merchandising, channels, pricing and the store format strategy to achieve a superior position in the market. ', 'Indian Retail Congress, Retail, Electronics, Fashion & Lifestyle, Consulting', '17:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3918, 'A', '2015-10-30 08:54:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
