(2109, 'CekhACmfmH8', NULL, 'Understanding the science of business valuation game  ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing on the topic such as when is the  right time for the founders to raise fund, the panelist talks about the targeting right investors, know your business and the your consumer well, research properly etc. during their discussion they throw lights on what can someone else money and mind do to your business, understanding the science of the business etc. ', 'Entrepreneur, Investor, Entrepreneur India show 2015, Startup Investment, Funding, Startup, Growth Strategies ', '09:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2977, 'A', '2016-01-16 12:13:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2110, 'lHdySbMWXsY', NULL, 'My family is all about Entrepreneurship: Pankaj Munjal, Hero Motors Group  ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Pankaj Munjal of Hero Motors Group shares his views about the new India outlook in the fast-changing global economy. He narrated his entrepreneurial journey and told the audiences that how his family managed to set up such a big empire in this fast moving economy.', 'Hero Motors Group, Entrepreneur, Entrepreneur India show 2015, Pankaj Munjal  ', '18:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2161, 'A', '2016-01-16 13:55:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2111, 'lcX3vS4wypg', NULL, 'How technology is innovating real estate industry', 3, '', NULL, '', 18, 'Advitiya Sharma, one of the Founders of Housing.com has made innovation and optimism for Housing as its mission. Sharma, at Entrepreneur Dialogue 2015 shares his thought on how millennial entrepreneur are ready to change the world. He put emphasis on how to building traction to grow a young startup. He believes that todays generation is born with the entrepreneurial genes as they are capable of translating an idea into profit.', 'Housing.com. Entrepreneur Show 2015, Millennial, Entrepreneurship, Advitiya Sharma, Entrepreneurial Genes, Innovation   ', '15:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3836, 'A', '2016-01-20 09:10:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2112, 'pxDkc46-C0E', NULL, 'Action is more important than knowledge important', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Harkesh Mittal is Adviser, Member Secretary at National Science & Technology Entrepreneurship Development Board (NSTEDB). An alumni of the National Dairy Research Institute (1981) and IIM Ahmedabad, Mittal has been instrumental in giving a new vibrancy to promoting the innovation and entrepreneurial acumen among a wide section of Indian entrepreneurs ranging from simple rural industries to high end technological enterprises. While addressing the audiences at Entrepreneur India show 2015, Mittal share his thoughts on building business agility in disruptive technology idea. He believes that one should look beyond the software innovations and promote the ideas in a hardware innovation. He furthers says that corporate, academia plays key role in promoting technology entrepreneurship.', 'Entrepreneurship, Innovation, NSTEDB, Ministry of Science & Technology, Entrepreneur India show 2015, Tech Entrepreneur   ', '23:02', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 4825, 'A', '2016-01-20 09:13:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2113, 'AvLLH3KuchQ', NULL, 'How to turn demographic dividend into assets', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Rajesh during his keynote shares the importance of entrepreneurship in the country. He believes that as a ministry, Ministry of skill development and entrepreneurship which is a new creation by government of India is still a start-up and as start-up they have been tasked to lay down the frame work for how to ensure that demography dividend is really turns out to be asset and not a liability for them. He furthers highlighted that it is every essential to build an ecosystem for entrepreneurs and create more opportunities for them at all levels. He believes that India need to realize the scale-up opportunities to build a new generation of world-beating business.', 'Ministry of Skill Development and Entrepreneurship, Entrepreneur India 2015, Demographic Dividend, Start-up, Rajesh Agrawal', '15:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2881, 'A', '2016-01-20 09:18:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2114, '84Bb4GuVbvw', NULL, 'Business Beyond Borders: Making Your Business a Universal Entity - Part 1\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing on the topic such as taking your business to the global market, the panelist talks about the targeting right investors, know your business and the your consumer well, research properly etc. during their discussion they throw lights on what can someone else money and mind do to your business, understanding the science of the business etc.', 'Entrepreneur India 2015, Entrepreneur, Global Markets, Startups, Early Stage Funding, Indian Business', '16:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3270, 'A', '2016-01-22 17:15:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2115, 'CHd8lcrZop8', NULL, 'Business Beyond Borders: Making Your Business a Universal Entity - Part 2', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing on the topic such as taking your business to the global market, the panelist talks about the targeting right investors, know your business and the your consumer well, research properly etc. during their discussion they throw lights on what can someone else money and mind do to your business, understanding the science of the business etc.', 'Entrepreneur India 2015, Entrepreneur, Global Markets, Startups, Early Stage Funding, Indian Business', '23:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3357, 'A', '2016-01-22 17:16:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2116, 'lpupQgA_amw', NULL, 'MSME Sector is Nursery of Innovation and Enterprises, Says Rajnish Goenka   ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Mr. Rajnish Goenka, National Convener-BJP-Micro & Small Industry Cell shares his views about the business opportunity of being both a producing and a consumer nation. He discuss on the topics like building a globally competitive marketplace, how entrepreneurs can maximize Make in India vision for growth and what it means for small business entrepreneurs to move up the ladder.', 'Entrepreneur, Entrepreneur India show 2015, Tobu Cycles, Young Entrepreneurs, Rajnish Goenka, Make in India, Marketplace, Global vision', '14:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3264, 'A', '2016-01-28 14:24:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2117, 'oQC6TpJUmOQ', NULL, 'Young Business Changing India and the World - Part 1', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing on the topic such as the new age sector in which budding entrepreneurs can deal in, the panellist talks about building the local marketplace, advancement of mobile technologies and its impact on their business. They also throw light on the online healthcare sectors where they highlighted that it is one of gearing sectors for the big game.', 'Entrepreneur India 2015, Entrepreneur, Young Business, Global Markets, Startups, Hyper local startups, Digital Era', '20:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5037, 'A', '2016-01-28 14:27:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2118, 'zmaXtlWNVqQ', NULL, 'Young Business Changing India and the World - Part 2', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing on the topic such as the new age sector in which budding entrepreneurs can deal in, the panellist talks about building the local marketplace, advancement of mobile technologies and its impact on their business. They also throw light on the online healthcare sectors where they highlighted that it is one of gearing sectors for the big game.', 'Entrepreneur India 2015, Entrepreneur, Young Business, Global Markets, Startups, Hyper local startups, Digital Era', '18:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4578, 'A', '2016-01-28 14:28:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2119, 'LrzSW7ltlkI', NULL, 'Young Business Changing India and the World - Part 3', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing on the topic such as the new age sector in which budding entrepreneurs can deal in, the panellist talks about building the local marketplace, advancement of mobile technologies and its impact on their business. They also throw light on the online healthcare sectors where they highlighted that it is one of gearing sectors for the big game.', 'Entrepreneur India 2015, Entrepreneur, Young Business, Global Markets, Startups, Hyper local startups, Digital Era', '14:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5343, 'A', '2016-01-28 14:30:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2120, 'CRCEqplNmNQ', NULL, 'Is healthcare opportunity favourite for women entrepreneurs? \r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Anu Acharya, a healthtech expert, particulatly in genomics, a serial entrepreneur and World Economic Forums Young Global Leader shares with Entrepreneur India whether healthcare for women is the first choice for entrepreneurship, current growth at Mapmygenome and more.', 'Anu Acharya, Maymygenome, Women Entrepreneurship, Genomics, Healthtech, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '04:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3053, 'A', '2016-02-11 11:54:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2121, 'eeo1lcGivVY', NULL, 'Betting on non-digital scalable businesses\\r\\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'DSG Consumer Partners, founded by Deepak Shahdadpuri, is an early-Series A focused fund backing non-digital/offline businesses early on. Shahdadpuri tells Entrepreneur India why tech businesses are glamourous and whether angel investors are losing the opportunity of backing promising early stage start-ups to large investors', 'Deepak Shahdadpuri, DSG Consumer Partners, Early Stage Investor, Non Digital, Hedge Funds, Entrepreneur India\\r\\n', '03:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3250, 'A', '2016-02-11 11:55:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2122, 'fh-2Xq4wzgU', NULL, 'Rise in PE investments to continue in 2016\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Among the top PE players in India, Everstone Capital led by Dhanpal Jhaveri, a corporate finance and strategy expert, last year raised $730 million for its third fund. Jhaveri in a discussion with Entrepreneur India gives an outlook for PE for 2016 including expectations from the government, foreign investment and exit trends.', 'Dhanpal Jhaveri, Everstone Capital, Private Equity, Exit, Foreign Investment, Startup India, GST\r\n', '04:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3011, 'A', '2016-02-11 11:56:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2123, 'lSO_yUh4i5w', NULL, 'Doing an OYO Rooms in diagnostics\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Dr A Velumani, scientist turned entrepreneur and running worlds largest thyroid testing laboratory, Thyrocare, as he claims is currently testing an aggregator model of affordable testing in labs. In a chat with Entrepreneur India, Velumani talks about opportunity and franchise expansion of Thyrocare.', 'Dr Velumani, Thyrocare, Franchising, OYO Rooms, Diagnostics, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '05:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2609, 'A', '2016-02-11 11:58:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2124, 'kga_raLlpjg', NULL, 'Succession should be merit-based not heritage\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Indian consumer goods stalwart Harsh Mariwala  successfully transformed Marico from a family business to a professionally managed firm worth Rs 5,700 crore in turnover. Mariwala shares his pearls of wisdom with Entrepreneur India over succession planning, cultural change, challenges and more in a family business.', 'Harsh Mariwala, Marico, Family Business, Succession planning, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '02:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2784, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:00:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2125, '4PbtEPJFXzs', NULL, 'Inclusion most important during  cultural change in business\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Navroze Godrej is the fourth generation entrepreneur at 119-year old Godrej Group. Godrej has been with the family business since 2009 while he says he often thought of venturing on his own and might soon take the plunge. He shares his learning from his father and experience so far talking to Entrepreneur India.', 'Navroze Godrej, Godrej & Boyce, Innovation, Technology, Entrepreneur India, Family Business\r\n', '02:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1704, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:01:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2126, 'YMWTZqqqGaM', NULL, 'Horizontal vs Vertical Marketplace - Pick Your Winner\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Niren Shah is the MD at India arm of global VC and growth equity firm Norwest Venture Partners. Interacting with Entrepreneur India, Shah puts in perspective the debate over horizontal and vertical marketplace in terms of opportunity in India. His personal favourite however remains vertical space. Shah has advised the firm\'s investments in companies like Quikr, Yes Bank, Pepperfry, Swiggy etc.', 'Niren Shah, Norwest Venture Partners, Horizontal Marketplace, Vertical Marketplace, GMV, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '05:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2913, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:03:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2127, 'DepZ0ssfAGk', NULL, 'Need for a robust angel investment ecosystem\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'One of the biggest start-up evangelists and leading IT entrepreneurs in India, Saurabh Srivastava, talking to Entrepreneur India, reflects on the need for more robust growth of angel investment in India, parallel to entrepreneurship and the current developments surrounding it. Srivastava is the founder of India\'s biggest angel network, Indian Angel Network having more than 350 members globally including Sanjeev Bikhchandani, co-founder of Info Edge; Sunil Munjal, MD, Hero Cycles etc.', 'Saurabh Srivastava, Indian Angel Network, Startups, Silicon Valley, Angel Investment, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '06:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1870, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:04:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2128, 'klfBnaFcU-k', NULL, 'Ecosystem not conducive for hardware startup revolution?\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Shirish Sankhe, among Indias top experts on infrastructure and public sector practices. In a dialogue with Entrepreneur India, he suggests areas which needs tremendous focus, especially on the government side, to boost manufacturing/hardware start-ups to flourish and broader view on Indias objective to achieve around 10% GDP. Sankhe currently surving as director at McKinsey India has co-authored several reports on policies to achieve rapid economic growth for India.', 'Shirish Sankhe, McKinsey India, Manufacturing, Hardware startups, Make in India, Design in India, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '03:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3233, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:06:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2129, 'UDuxQy6TZWk', NULL, 'From corporate czar to start-up hustler\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Former Group CEO of healtcare giant Fortis Healthcare, Vishal Bali put on entrepreneur hat leaving his flourshing corporate career. It all changed when his elderly father told him how challenging visiting hospitals is for elderly patients for their periodic check-ups. Bali talks about his transition and life as a start-up entrepreneur in a chat with Entrepreneur India.', 'Vishal Bali, Medwell Ventures, Fortis Healthcare, Home Healthcare, Chronic Disease, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '04:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3852, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:08:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2130, 'uPUFcKMT4sw', NULL, 'Engaging with start-ups to tap innovation\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Anand Deshpande running the Pune-based global software development firm Persistent Systems is focusing on working with start-up by engaging with them through investment opportunities. He details out the action plan for the firm along with new opportunity and investment from the new fund launched recently for start-ups in a dialogue with Entrepreneur India.', 'Anand Deshpande, Persistent Systems, Software Businesses, Startups, Innovation, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '02:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2204, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:16:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2131, 'x6WSj62YA6o', NULL, 'Fashion discover-ability through social network gaining ground ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Roposo which helps women to discover latest trends in fashion curated and updated from different brands and e-commerce destinations was started by Avinash Saxena and two other IIT-Delhi alumni and has more than 2 million users currently. In an interaction with Entrepreneur India, Saxena shares the journey so far and market opportunity at large.', 'Avinash Saxena, Roposo, Online Fashion, Social Network, E-commerce, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '04:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 1, 4153, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:17:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2132, 'qseBfCSjnkk', NULL, 'Entrepreneurship without purpose has no meaning', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'A marketing wizard, one of most sought after investors, excellent corporate speaker, brand advisor etc., Mahesh Murthy wears multiple hats with ease. In his current role he runs early stage investment firm, Exceed Fund. Talking to Entrepreneur India, Murthy stresses on why entrepreneurs should always be surrounded by meaningful people to build a great team, which can either make or break the venture.', 'Mahesh Murthy, Exceed Fund, Angel Investment, Team Building, Startup India, Facebook Free Basics\r\n', '03:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2771, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:19:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2133, '7BeyAhMKizQ', NULL, 'Can Fintech start-ups disrupt banking?\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Mswipe founded by Manish Patel, who was earlier running an alcoholic beverages distribution company, is Indias largest independent mobile POS merchant acquirer and network provider, as it claims. With number of fintech start-ups focusing on specialised banking verticals such as payments, lending etc, does banking stand disrupted in the near future? Patel explains what can be expected and where the disruption lies apart from the current growth at Mswipe talking to Entrepreneur India.', 'Manish Patel, Mswipe Technologies, mpos, Fintech, Banking, NFC, Payments\r\n', '05:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3161, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:20:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2134, '_y5iQxPMOYM', NULL, 'No one builds a company to sell', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Mohit Dubey did not build Carwale for 11 long years to get acquired by a company which is 2-3 times smaller in size. He sold it as, it was right for the business, as he puts it. He shares his learning and the action behind the deal and the road ahead in a chat with Entrepreneur India.', 'Mohit Dubey, Carwale, Cartrade, Acquisition, Used Cars, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '04:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3473, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:22:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2135, 'LnA1si2Mt74', NULL, 'When finding love TrulyMadly goes digital\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Launched in August 2014, TrulyMadly aims to capture the Indian youth looking for likeminded singles, has already seen over 10 lakh app downloads and monthly growth of above 100%. Sachin Bhatia talks about creating a brand in a massive Indian market dominated by youth and unique challenges to it in a chat with Entrepreneur India.', 'Sachin Bhatia, TrulyMadly, Dating Apps, Online Matchmaking, Social Networking, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '04:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 2402, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:24:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2136, 'N75t-U947qw', NULL, 'I do not worry about competition for Tinder in India\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'US-based popular dating app Tinder which launched in India, first market outside the US, in January 2016 to tap on the nascent and unorganised online dating space. Taru Kapoor, a product and growth strategy specialist has been put at the top to establish and grow Tinder in India. In a chat with Entrepreneur India, Kapoor talks about safety as an important area of focus followed by market size and competition which does not bother her at all.', 'Taru Kapoor, Tinder India, Dating Apps, Online Matchmaking, Social Network, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '03:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4987, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:25:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2137, '14OVRwmZYvs', NULL, 'Wearables will replace smartphones in next 3-5 years\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'From the face of Indian gaming industry to leading the domestic wearable market, Vishal Gondal has helped start-up ecosystem grow bottom-up. In conversation with Entrepreneur India Gondal says wearables today are what smartphones were around 5-6 years back. He also shares GOQii\'s current scale-up and much more.', 'Vishal Gondal, GOQii, Wearables, Facebook Free Basics, Smartphone Growth, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '05:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5889, 'A', '2016-02-11 12:27:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2138, 'FgBBRQSrOsQ', NULL, 'The Franchise Agreement-Legal Considerations', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Akshat joined Kaden Boriss as a Partner in 2012. He has structured, negotiated and drafted a wide range of business transactions for foreign investors, multinational corporations and domestic entities drawing from his experience with business formation, corporate governance, information technology, exchange control & foreign investment laws, intellectual property protection, real estate and labour & employment laws. Talking at Franchise India, he shares the structure of a franchise agreement.', 'Franchise India, Akshat Sulalit, KadenBoriss, Franchise Knowledge Series 2014', '11:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4607, 'A', '2016-02-15 14:13:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2139, 'rjz4n6IuT5c', NULL, 'Getting Started-The Building Blocks of a Strategic Franchise Business Plan', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Mike Hanrahan, after ten years having some 400 cleaners representing his brand on a weekly basis he founded Maid2Clean Franchise Ltd on a shoestring budget. The franchise business was launched after 10 successful years of operation. He has spoken at various Franchising, Entrepreneurship & Small Business Conferences and Seminars. He is also the Manchester Metropolitan University Alumni Ambassador. Talking at Franchise India, he unveils the different Franchise business. ', 'Franchise India, Mike Hanrahan, Maid 2 Clean, Franchise Knowledge Series 2014', '14:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3021, 'A', '2016-02-15 14:14:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2140, 'W2CHgot-coQ', NULL, 'Finding the right match- How to Identify, Attract & Recruit the Right Partner', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Rod is endorsed by the Franchise Council of Australia. His involvement in India over many years not only places him at the centre of franchising in India but he has developed and delivered specific modules of the Franchise Knowledge Series. Talking at Franchise India, he talks how to identify true franchise partner and communicate with them on their terms.', 'Franchise India, Franchise Knowledge Series 2014, Rod Young, DC Strategy', '24:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2573, 'A', '2016-02-15 14:15:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2141, 'HjH84skwmoU', NULL, 'The ecosystem and entrepreneurship Vision India 2020', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Rod Young has over 30 years experience in franchising, licensing and business development in Australia, Europe, China, South East Asia, India and the United States and is considered one of the worlds leading franchise consultants. Rod addresses the inaugural session.', 'Franchise India, Franchise Knowledge Series 2014, Rod Young, DC Strategy', '24:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2908, 'A', '2016-02-15 14:16:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2142, 'Ns_5a1JmUgQ', NULL, 'Bringing franchise industry together: Ritu Marya ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India, says the World Franchise Congress is a special platform for the whole franchise industry. She shares with the audience that regardless of how franchise industry is growing, one thing has remained the same that is the hunger of people to look for an opportunity and to start a business to become their own boss. This, she says, is the standing point of franchising. The editor also reveals bringing the worlds largest magazine on entrepreneurship- Entrepreneur Media- which is empowering franchising and entrepreneurship.    ', '1st World Franchise Congress, Ritu Marya, Franchise India, franchising, entrepreneurship  ', '12:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2854, 'A', '2016-02-16 09:19:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2143, 'TeJgdIZWnKY', NULL, 'We consider our business partners as co-founders: Vijay Thadani', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Vijay Thadani, Co-Founder, Vice Chairman and MD NIIT Ltd, enlightens the audience about the contribution of franchising in building the business. He talks about why the company preferred the term business partner system instead of franchise system, chemistry between franchisee and franchisor, what it takes to build a franchise performance company and why the chain has all franchisees who are first generation entrepreneurs.', 'Entrepreneurs, IIT Ltd, franchising, franchisors, business partners    ', '26:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4535, 'A', '2016-02-16 09:20:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2144, 'tdIEafH95ac', NULL, 'How to build a business into a powerful entity: Shiv Shivakumar', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Shiv Shivakumar, Chairman & CEO, PepsiCo India, shares the idea behind the franchise world congress and lists top five business categories for the next five years. He also throws light on enablers and opportunities in franchising in India.', 'Opportunities in franchising, business categories, entrepreneurs, franchise business   ', '14:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3057, 'A', '2016-02-16 09:22:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2145, 'ZDhbsc92zZU', NULL, 'Skill development going to help franchise industry  ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Rajiv Pratap Rudy speaks about the benefits and challenges for the skilled development program of the Indian government and how the energy of a large number of youths can be channelised to help grow the economy.  He adds that the skilled manpower can also help the franchise world.', 'Skill development, franchise world, franchisees, skilled manpower in franchise industry', '16:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5602, 'A', '2016-02-16 09:22:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2146, 'iPDhPojnix4', NULL, 'Grow like a franchisee - Part 1', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Harish Mehta has over three decades of corporate experience in senior management roles, within corporate finance, strategy and planning, fund raising, brand building and supply chain management functions. Talking at Franchise India, he shares how to think and grow as a franchisee. ', 'Franchise India, Harish Mehta, Action COACH', '22:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 3816, 'A', '2016-02-22 11:28:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2147, 'n1WXcK7FgaU', NULL, 'Grow like a franchisee - Part 2', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Harish Mehta has over three decades of corporate experience in senior management roles, within corporate finance, strategy and planning, fund raising, brand building and supply chain management functions. Talking at Franchise India, he shares how to think and grow as a franchisee. ', 'Franchise India, Harish Mehta, Action COACH', '23:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3925, 'A', '2016-02-22 11:29:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2148, '4QAGkVr7T14', NULL, 'Celebrity licensing', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'In an interaction with Franchise India, Job Van Dijik shares celebrity value for licensing.', 'Franchise India, Brand Licensing 2014, Job Van Dijk, Tempting Brands AG- Route 66 ', '10:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2050, 'A', '2016-02-22 11:30:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2149, 'tQ2qC7E7qrg', NULL, 'Sports Licensing', 46, '', NULL, '', 47, 'As the Co-Founder & Managing Partner of TYREK, LLC, having served in both the Public & Private sectors at the Cabinet level with 20 plus business experience. Talking at Franchise India, he speaks about how to become a licensee. ', 'Franchise India, Brand Licensing 2014, Michael Okebiyi, Tyrek LLC', '10:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4032, 'A', '2016-02-22 11:31:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2150, 'M6mo67POIo8', NULL, 'Early Childhood Education is Need of the Hour', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Indian Education Congress 2015, Anita Madan of Euro Kids International Pvt. Ltd, shares her thoughts about high quality early childhood education for 21st century. She said that early childhood education is there from decades now but something like high quality early childhood is something that we require and it is the need of the hour.', 'Early childhood education, early learning, Education in India, Primary Education, Indian Education Congress 2015, Euro Kids International, Education Business  ', '10:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3382, 'A', '2016-02-24 11:36:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2151, 'G-m6cIo4flk', NULL, 'Life is itself an Entrepreneur', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Indian Education Congress 2015, Harsh Mishra, Founder & President of (iSEED) shares his thoughts about the national perspective on entrepreneurship education. While addressing the gathering, he highlighted the topics such as impact of entrepreneurship education strategies and measures, entrepreneurship in vocational education and training, stimulating entrepreneurial mindsets of young people, etc.', 'Harsh Mishra, iSEED, Indian Education Congress 2015, Entrepreneurship, Education in India, Enterprise Development, Entrepreneur  ', '13:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2914, 'A', '2016-02-24 11:37:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2152, 'JLNj6oR1COE', NULL, 'If you have good entrepreneurial skills in your life till 12, you will do well in future', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'While addressing the gathering at Indian Education Congress 2015, Dr. Jawahar Surisetti, President, Religion of Youth share his thoughts about the how entrepreneurial skills should be inculcated into primary education and it is imperative.', 'Entrepreneurship, Indian Education Congress 2015, Religion of Youth, Jawahar Surisethi, Entrepreneurship Education, Entrepreneur', '07:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2712, 'A', '2016-02-24 11:38:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2153, 'OkQstQlEiiI', NULL, 'This is how Wheebox is making difference to education industry ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Nirmal Singh is the Co-founder and CEO of Wheebox. While addressing the gathering he described about his startup and highlighted that how his startup is contributing to Indian education in an innovative way.', 'Innovation, Education Startup, Indian Education Congress 2015, Wheebox, Nirmal Singh, Education in India ', '04:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 2642, 'A', '2016-02-24 11:39:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2154, '-mvJYMk34oA', NULL, 'Indias Youth should be provided with on the job training ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Indian Education Congress 2015, Prof. Krishna Kumar Pande of Teerthanker University, shares his thoughts about the national perspective on entrepreneurship education. While addressing the gathering, he highlighted the topics such as impact of entrepreneurship education strategies and measures, entrepreneurship in vocational education and training, stimulating entrepreneurial mindsets of young people, etc.', 'Entrepreneurship, Indian Education Congress 2015, Entrepreneurship Education, Entrepreneur, Teerthanker University, Krishna Kumar Pande', '08:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 3688, 'A', '2016-02-24 11:40:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2155, 'dQm9EjMvVfo', NULL, 'Providing innovative bathroom solutions  ', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'At a store launch of popular bathroom furniture brand VitrA in New Delhi, Serhan Ates Yagiz, Country Manager spoke to Retailer Media and shared his views on some of the market trends, competition and retail culture in the country. He also shared his views on how dynamic the market is and being foreign what all it takes to grab a leadership position here.', 'VitrA, Bathroom Furniture, Retail, Store Launch', '05:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 9, 5076, 'A', '2016-02-29 17:14:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2156, 't4QKDeDfcWU', NULL, 'Indian Salon & Wellness Congress & Awards 2016 on ET Now &ndash; Promo', 9, '', NULL, '', 44, 'Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2016, Indias biggest  thought leadership platform on Salon & Wellness industry was held on March 1st, at Hotel Pullman, New Delhi. Organized by Franchise India & Wella, the 5th National Convention on Salon & Wellness has become the marquee wellness event on building & growing enterprises in India. The event attracted over 500 leading owners from the salon & wellness community together with CEOs and professionals leading Growth oriented organizations. \r\nAlong with the Congress, 5th Annual Indian Salon & Wellness Awards 2016 and parallel exhibition also took place. The Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in Salon & Wellness space. The award ceremony was aimed at felicitating successful startups, Chain Owners and the people who are supporting them. From Achievers, Innovators to Suppliers, the awards applauded their efforts in making the salon & wellness presence felt in this increasingly competitive world.', 'Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2016, Indian Salon & Wellness Awards 2016, Indian Salon & Wellness Exhibition 2016, Beauty & Wellness Industry, Beauty Convention, Wellness Convention, ET Now Promo, Business Conference, Salon & Wellness meet, B2B wellness conference, Spa Summit, Salon Summit, Fitness Summit.', '01:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 5522, 'A', '2016-03-12 14:24:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2157, 'sn7grgT1J6k', NULL, 'Entrepreneurship Ecosystem by Gaurav Marya at TEDx Event  ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Mr. Gaurav Marya - famously known as the Franchise King put focus on Entrepreneurship Ecosystem having three parts: Invention, Entrepreneur, and Execution at TEDxFORESchool.\r\n\r\nMr. Marya went to US in a franchise show in search of business and got the idea of franchising. He then started Franchise India Holdings Limited and now his company holds over 120 franchise shows like those every year.\r\n\r\nHe started Franchise India Holdings Limited which spearheaded the franchise revolution in India and has gone on to become Indias largest integrated franchise and retail Solution Company. The company sells over 2500 business every Year.\r\n\r\nHe also said that to be an Entrepreneur, an individual needs firstly to build a Brand, the get the Key Team (Inner Circle) and last but not the least is to get Early Success. ', 'Entrepreneurship, TEDxFORESchool, Franchise India, Gaurav Marya, Entrepreneur', '18:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4982, 'A', '2016-04-22 12:25:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2189, '4DyLwLLSHaE', NULL, 'Why an entrepreneur should raise funds internally\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Speaking to Entrepreneur India, Chirag Kulkarni, Founder of Insight fully said that if an entrepreneur is not doing something that he is passionate about, it is not something worth doing. He should stand for his people and the company. An entrepreneur should raise fund internally through his customers first and not the investors. ', 'Chirag Kulkarni,  Qualities of entrepreneurship, fund raising, valuing people, start-up policy, Entrepreneur India ', '0:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1589, 'A', '2016-05-19 13:09:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2179, 'CySf4YY7WGw', NULL, 'How digital marketing can shape the future of your startup\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Narrating the exponential growth of digital Industry Harneet Bhalla, Digital Marketing Expert believes this is the right time for entrepreneurs to get into the digital marketing industry which has boomed in the last 10-15 years. He observes that the new start-ups are really active in this space as it does not take lot of money and resources to get digital campaigning started with social media platforms. They are going to use digital marketing for long years. And 70 per cent of the marketing budget is going to shift to digital marketing in the next couple of years.   ', 'Right time, Entrepreneurs, digital marketing, overall area, active start-ups, money, resources, Entrepreneur India', '03:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2432, 'A', '2016-05-19 12:39:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2190, 'mXqSv26o1Z8', NULL, 'How Good mentors can make a business successful?\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Talking about entrepreneurs, Christopher Carter Smith, Founder, The Campfire Effect/ kCross said that the founders are missing the opportunities of human connect while being so focused on growing their business. He also talked about his self-funded business and the interesting tale of cracking the first deal with Wells Fargo bank in US, tough start-up days, his wish of finding mentors much sooner and advising Indian entrepreneurs to find good mentors.    ', 'Entrepreneurs, Missing opportunities, human connect, tale of cracking first deal, advising entrepreneurs, find good mentors, Entrepreneur India', '02:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2178, 'A', '2016-05-20 12:52:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2188, 'JEXlNh4L9TY', NULL, 'Magic happens when you mix passion and focus with a great team\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'The man in the space of wearable technology, Vishal Gondal, Founder & CEO, Goqii, talks about the key entrepreneurial skills that one needs to succeed. He says the main requirement for an entrepreneur is to be passionate and to be focused. When you combine passion and focus it gives you result.  He feels that the entire ecosystem is mature and evolving much faster than we thought but that also makes it highly competitive so just having an idea is not enough, one need to do a lot more work and prove lot more point before somebody takes him seriously.', 'Wearable technology, entrepreneurial qualities, passion, focus, funding, India Games, investors, ecosystem, shine, perform, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '03:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 4, 4, 20, 1995, 'A', '2016-05-19 13:07:47', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2187, 'hbso0TQZbcQ', NULL, 'How Startup India can become a great motivation for Indian entrepreneurs\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Gaurav Wadhwa, Founder, Gamooz narrates his entrepreneurial qualities. He strongly felt the need to do something that would change the world for good. He said it was never the urge to earn money. Gaurav talks about his startup journey and also, how government can play a huge role here. Founders are aware that the first three years are not profitable, in the policy the tax rebate should be for the first three years of profit, if your are behind something then you will achieve it one day or other.', 'Need, change, world, reason, focus, team, augmented reality, start-up India, tax rebate, profit, achieve, Entrepreneur India', '07:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3393, 'A', '2016-05-19 13:06:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2184, 'NCLJ0ragEnY', NULL, 'How research will make a difference in Indias growth?\\r\\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Talking to Entrepreneur India, Niraj Shah, Co-National Director, BNI India, said that in the last 10 years, whole entrepreneurial ecosystem has flourished in India. It is certainly becoming easier to do business and people have much more interest in being an entrepreneur. 25-30 years old of entrepreneurs are going to take this wave to a whole new level. With the governments focus on Start-ups, India is going to thrive. Research centre under the start-up policy is going to have huge impact. ', 'entrepreneurial ecosystem, easier, business, people, interest, big wave, govt, start-up India, private investors, successful entrepreneurs, decade of start-ups, start-up policy, research centre, huge impact, entrepreneur India', '03:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1522, 'A', '2016-05-19 12:53:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2185, '3WE_KQ4LrWQ', NULL, 'In the agitation of rising and dying businesses, we will see something new\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'The Romanian consultant Ciprian Moga, Managing Partner, iQuest Consulting analyse that the  India is very fervent market which is rising and dying everyday. This entrepreneural agitation (spurt) will be something very interesting and very new. There is very much willingness among Indian people to be themselves as an entrepreneur. People are open to the  ideas so the potential is big in India so it remains to be seen that how much consulting business will answer to this demand.', 'Consulting, analyse, India, fervent market, agitation, agility, ability, entrepreneur environment, start-up, VC, support, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '02:51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2633, 'A', '2016-05-19 13:01:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2186, '5La255-n8QU', NULL, 'Starting up is a tedious exercise, but it gets easier\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Ajith Karimpana, Founder & CEO, Furlenco largely emphasizes on the perceiverence which he thinks is the mantra of the success for any start-up. He says that the entrepreneur should have perceiverence, he need to be able to at a problem for some time to get a real answer. He should be ok if he is not having money for initial two to three years of his venture. And he should have passion for what and why he is doing it. Talking about his venture started with bootstrap funding initially, he said for the first two years I and my friend invested in the business and that the traction is good for anyone starting new. ', 'Preceiverence, real answer, money, investor, traction, GST, journey, tedious exercise, Entrepreneur India  \r\n', '03:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2723, 'A', '2016-05-19 13:03:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2183, 'ufOL2Ac00pw', NULL, 'The various risks of startups\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Observing the thriving entrepreneural ecosystem in India Mhir Vora, AVP, Technical, (Mumbai & Goa) Underwritting & Risk Engineering, Bajaj Allianz strongly promotes the India as the only bright spot in the world economy. There are several digital based initiative where there is thriving ecosystem. One can see runaway success of several digital initiatives. With start-up policy all the budding entrepreneurs will get some support. Bajaj Allianz, Like VCs, are providing funding we are there to provide solutions. For assets liabilities and debts there is risk and associate solutions.', 'India, Bright Spot, economy, ecosystem, thriving, budding entrepreneurs, promote, start-ups, own risk, outsourceable, support, solutions, asset liabilities, debts, risk, solutions, Entrepreneur India', '03:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2727, 'A', '2016-05-19 12:51:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2180, 'TJV8NWnWWBM', NULL, 'I see only great things for India entrepreneurs\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Jim Beach feels that the startup ecosystem in India is booming and there is enthusiasm to learn about entrepreneurship. He feels that India can get 15 per cent of its GDP from the entrepreneurship and doubling the number of entrepreneurs can be achieved by 2020. He suggests that the existing Indian entrepreneurs need to together and act as mentor to develop another generation of entrepreneurs. He insisted that the start-up policy is a great idea. ', 'Exploding entrepreneurship, GDP, numbers, youngster entrepreneur, Indian entrepreneur, mentors, generation, start-up policy, Entrepreneur India\r\n', '02:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1991, 'A', '2016-05-19 12:41:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2181, '1IOKgBcBwO8', NULL, 'Entrepreneur Should Be Intellectual, Responsible and Most of All, A Leader\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Kanwal Rekhi, who is among the leading startup investors, spoke to Entrepreneur India about the qualities of an entrepreneur. He said founders should have intellectual artisty while owning the responsibilities and should have leadership qualities. Rekhi is a venture capitalist leading Inventus Capital along with co-founders John Dougery, Manu Rekhi, Parag Dhol, Sami, Kumar and Rutvik Doshi. He co-founded The IndUS Entrepreneurs (TiE) to promote Indian entrepreneurship and was TiE President through the late 90s.    ', 'Kanwal Rekhi, qualities of entrepreneur, valuation, betting areas, start-up policy, investment, Entrepreneur India', '04:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1663, 'A', '2016-05-19 12:42:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2182, '96JVMJYKGPc', NULL, 'Why exiting a business is a bad idea?\\r\\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Before investing in startups, Mahesh Murthy, Founder & CEO, Seedfund, looks for qualities in the founder such as a real insight into the problem that the entrepreneur is trying to solve, the person should have the backbone to resist all waves against him. While investing, among other criteria, he looks for exit options, acquisition opportunity, opportunity of taking the venture public, he foresees the dominant 70-90 per cent market share of the company in 5-7 years. He feels entrepreneurs should never want to exit their business, entrepreneur should only look at getting out if he believes that he can build a bigger business in co-operation with somebody. ', 'backbone, real insight, resist, waves, rebels, criteria, exit options, acquisition opportunity, public, market share, bugger business, start-up policy, noise and shine, stuck, exit issue, organic food, news media, space technologies, fund, Entrepreneur India\\r\\n', '04:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3868, 'A', '2016-05-19 12:45:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2170, 'qw0-puHJT3M', NULL, 'The emergence of Online Video content market\r\n', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'India had eCommerce phase, taxi aggregators, hyper local, food delivery start-ups and now it is  logical for VCs to invest money on original video content platforms. Soon online video start-up will evolve. There are no large number of start-ups in the online video platform space. There are players like Hotstar, NetFlix, Ditto, Sony Live and then there is Spook and Hook among others funded by deep pockets. There is no winner at the moment it will take probably another two years to see couple of video platform evolve into large profitable centres for acquisition to happen. There is large opportunity for entrepreneurs for creating a video platform which is independent in its true sense. India is unique market hence the winner platform would be the one which will be more closer to what the Indian audience wants in terms of the multilingual aspect of the country and the usability going into the rural market which is just going up with the connectivity spreading out.  ', 'eCommerce, taxi aggregator, hyper local, food delivery, VCs, evolve, online video, platform, Hotstar, Netfilix, Ditto, Sony Live, Spook, Hook, acquisition, entrepreneurs, Indian audience, usability, connectivity, Entrepreneur India', '04:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3146, 'D', '2016-05-09 09:35:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2172, 'i410SNArcUU', NULL, 'Indian Retail & e-Retail Congress & Awards 2016 Promo on Times Now', 4, '', NULL, '', 24, 'Indian Retail & eRetail Congress 2016, Indias biggest thought leadership platform on Retail & eRetail industry was held on April 29-30, 2016 at Hotel Hyatt Regency, Gurgaon. Organized by Franchise India to showcase a product or service in the retail & eretail, supplier and allied industry. This national event was a grand success with over 600 successful retailers, eretailers, suppliers, manufacturers, industry veterans, key suppliers, consultants and individuals belonging to the Retail and eRetail category attended the event from across the country. The conference talked about all aspects of retail & eretail business in India and provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading e-Retailers and Retailers and an understanding around how they are re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.\r\n\r\nAlong with the Congress, Annual Indian Retail & eRetail Awards 2016 were also took place. The Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in Retail as well as e-Retail space. The award ceremony was aimed at felicitating people who have contributed towards the growth of Retail Industry in India. From Achievers, Innovators to Suppliers, the awards applauded their efforts in making the retails & e-retails presence felt in this increasingly competitive world.', 'Indian Retail Congress, Indian e-Retail Congress, Indian Retail Awards, Indian e-Retail Awards, Times Now, Indian Retail Congress Promo, Retail Convention, e-Retail Convention, Retail Exhibition, e-Retail Exhibition, B2B Retail Conference, Retail & eRetail meet', '0:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 5, 5, 25, 7280, 'A', '2016-05-13 09:27:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
