(2173, 'c1hD_kbx370', NULL, 'Indian Retail & e-Retail Congress & Awards 2016 Episode on Times Now', 4, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Indian Retail & eRetail Congress 2016, Indias biggest  thought leadership platform on Retail & eRetail industry was held on April 29-30, 2016 at Hotel Hyatt Regency, Gurgaon. Organized by Franchise India to showcase a product or service in the retail & eretail, supplier and allied industry. This national event was a grand success with over 600 successful retailers, eretailers, suppliers, manufacturers, industry veterans, key suppliers, consultants and individuals belonging to the Retail and eRetail category attended the event from across the country. The conference talked about all aspects of retail & eretail business in India and provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading e-Retailers and Retailers and an understanding around how they are re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.\r\n\r\nAlong with the Congress, Annual Indian Retail & eRetail Awards 2016 were also took place. The Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in Retail as well as e-Retail space. The award ceremony was aimed at felicitating people who have contributed towards the growth of Retail Industry in India. From Achievers, Innovators to Suppliers, the awards applauded their efforts in making the retails & e-retails presence felt in this increasingly competitive world.', 'Indian Retail Congress, Indian e-Retail Congress, Indian Retail Awards, Indian e-Retail Awards, Times Now, Indian Retail Congress Episode, Retail Convention, e-Retail Convention, Retail Exhibition, e-Retail Exhibition, B2B Retail Conference, Retail & eRetail meet, Times Now Episode', '22:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 5881, 'A', '2016-05-17 12:53:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 1, 0, 0),
(2174, 'SfOxw8Sfftw', NULL, 'Need of high quality early childhood education ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Vittal Bhandary, Founder & MD, Little Elly Pre-Schools, shares his thoughts about the high quality early childhood education for 21st century and why there is a need to build serious case for early learning education.', 'Education India, Little Elly Pre-Schools, Early education, Indian Education Congress 2015 ', '07:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2751, 'A', '2016-05-18 17:37:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2175, 'XXiRhitZwJI', NULL, 'Learnings has no boundaries', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Soundar Rajan of Cox & Kings Ltd highlighted the educational tours done by Cox & Kings. While addressing the gathering he shares about the Cox &Kings brand called Udaan.', 'Education India, Early education, Indian Education Congress 2015, Cox & Kings Ltd, Soundar Rajan. ', '16:04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1508, 'A', '2016-05-18 17:38:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2176, 'lwRoyorvo0o', NULL, 'Building Serious Business Case for Early Learning Education ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Sukhvinder Singh, Business Head, Kidzee shares his thought about providing high quality early childhood education. He highlighted on the topics like measurement of effectiveness of preschool programmes, scope of prescribed preschool syllabus etc. ', 'Education India, Early education, Indian Education Congress 2015, Kidzee, Sukhvinder Singh', '23:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3131, 'A', '2016-05-18 17:39:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2177, 'K5pYMvGNLD0', NULL, 'Education and Entrepreneurship has to go together', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Entrepreneurship is not about just making money, its also about how you execute the idea and it is here that education plays a very major role. Discussing how entrepreneurship and education can go together, Aakash Chaudary, MD of Aakash Educational Services with the famous coaching institutes under its umbrella says that education is a social initiative but should be run in a professional way so that it benefits the world with the right objective.  He further talks about entrepreneurship as a subject and schools.', 'Entrepreneur, education, edtech, Aakash Institute, entrepreneurship schools, government initiative', '03:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3006, 'A', '2016-05-19 10:38:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2178, 'ywC8BUu-nPo', NULL, 'We are not afraid to fail and that makes us different and better', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'With a handful of experience in entrepreneurship Anirudh Pandita, Co-Founder, Pocket Aces says that an entrepreneur have to be risk taking, innovative, humble, should have an idea which other people do not really believe in and execute against an opportunity that exist. He comments that the entrepreneurship scenario in India has always been great and it has never been a better time to be an entrepreneur. India is entrepreneur led country and its good that the government is also supporting it.', 'Entrepreneur, risk taking, innovative, angel investor, first deal, condition, government, Entrepreneur India ', '03:51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2429, 'A', '2016-05-19 10:39:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2191, '_fs2gZxZJV8', NULL, 'Let Every Entrepreneur Understand That Their Papers Should Tell Their Story: Rajive Chawla', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'At Entrepreneur Dialogue, Mr. Rajiv Chawla shares his perspective on entrepreneurship from a bankers point of view. He says that bankers have to give loans as a part of their job but sometimes the entrepreneur may not be credit worthy. Talking about funding he says that much depends upon how and where one looks for finance. ', 'Entrepreneur Dialogue Delhi, Entrepreneur, Banks, Funding, Loans, Finance, Balance Sheets, Startups, Small Businesses ', '17:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2169, 'A', '2016-05-20 12:57:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2192, 'TV4BjXI1Zes', NULL, 'A Banker Is Ready To Give You Money, But How Will You Raise Equity From Your Side?', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Chairman of Jairaj Group, Rajive Chawla talks about the various points an entrepreneur should keep in mind while dealing with a banker and asking for loan. He emphasizes on the importance of choosing the right banker based on your business domain.  He further discusses that the banker will bring their side of investment as they are a bank but how will you raise equity from your side?', 'Entrepreneur Dialogue Delhi, Entrepreneur, Funding, Loans, Finance, equity, pitching funds, investors, Startups, Small Businesses', '16:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2253, 'A', '2016-05-20 12:59:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2193, 'ngqHbAS6IFE', NULL, 'The Vicious Cycle of Funding an Entrepreneur Goes Through', 2, '', NULL, '', 0, 'Even if banks give you funds, an entrepreneur can always run short on collateral and this remains a major problem for them. Where a lot of companies set aside a particular fund for building a brand name, Shimant Chadha reveals his strategy of giving equity to media companies which not only help them save money on advertising but also get attention in the right way from investors and their users.', 'Entrepreneur Dialogue Delhi, Entrepreneur, Funding, Loans, Finance, Collateral, Media, Brand name, Brand Building, Startups, Small Businesses', '13:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2529, 'A', '2016-05-20 13:00:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2194, 'N4SH7HvWaWI', NULL, 'Nine brand Shastras Model to Help You Build Your Business Brand ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Differentiating between advertising companies and brand consultancies, Jagdeep Kapoor shares his strategic and straightforward module for entrepreneurs to grow their businesses multi -fold with the least amount of expenditure but also remaining in the leads. A Brand Guru, Jagdeep Kapoor discusses the rights and wrongs of building a brand for your business.', 'Entrepreneur Dialogue Mumbai, Entrepreneur, Brands, Building Brands, Advertising, Business Mantras, Marketing, Startups, Small Businesses', '19:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3066, 'A', '2016-05-20 13:02:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2195, 'Cw0Y9qm2nvI', NULL, 'You Do not Need Money to Build A Brand, You Just Need Communication', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Discussing the shastras behind building a successful brand, Brand Guru Jagdeep Kapoor talks about the brand awareness. He breaks the myth that to build brand awareness you always need money. Instead, to build a brand you do not need money, you need communication. Advertising is just a paid form of that communication.', 'Entrepreneur Dialogue Mumbai, Entrepreneur, Brands, Building Brands, Advertising, Business Mantras, Marketing, Consumer Engagement, Small Businesses, Startups', '20:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2330, 'A', '2016-05-20 13:10:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2196, 'xbJlF3KZwJg', NULL, 'In India, You Do not Need to Have IP Driven Companies for Ventures to Become Successful', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Talking about raising capital, which in the initial stages comes majorly from equity, Vinod Murali discusses the concept of venture debt. He shares how they have helped companies raise funds when all the boxes that make them eligible are crossed. He further talks about the various options young and new ventures can explore when looking for funding.', 'Entrepreneur Dialogue Mumbai, Entrepreneur, Marketing, Finance, Equity, Company Growth, Small Businesses, Venture Debt, Startups ', '14:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1757, 'A', '2016-05-20 13:11:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2197, 'icHP1HGR_78', NULL, 'An Entrepreneur Has To Work Day in and Day Out on His Ideas to Build Something Unique ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Building businesses for a first generation entrepreneur is not easy. They need capital and that comes from equity and until and unless you have equity these SMEs and new entrepreneurs cannot grow. So, Vishal Tulsyan shares how they came up with a company that helped these new ventures acquire equity. He further emphasizes on the importance on working on idea again and again to build something unique. ', 'Entrepreneur Dialogue Mumbai, Entrepreneur, Finance, Equity, Company Growth, Small Businesses, First Generation Entrepreneurs', '18:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2235, 'A', '2016-05-20 13:13:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2198, 'uv_O1V8VsUY', NULL, 'Preparing Graduates for the 21st century workplace', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Vice chairman and Executive Head of Kerala State Higher Education Council, T.P. Sreenivasan shares his thought about the modern higher education and what needs to improve in it to provide high quality education to the students so that they can be made ready to excel in professional world.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Higher Education, T.P. Sreenivasan, Kerala State Higher Education Council     ', '20:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3205, 'A', '2016-05-20 13:21:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2199, '_MPUf9-lCzI', NULL, 'Building Capacity Through Cross-Border Education', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Vineet Gupta Managing Director, Jamboree Education & Trustee, Ashoka University shares his thought about the modern higher education. While addressing the audience, he highlighted the topics such as bringing culture of work-based learning in Indian higher education, how to build a culture for universities to be funded by business and not by government alone and the challenges for Indian universities governance.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Higher Education, Vineet Gupta, Ashoka University, High Quality Education', '12:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2683, 'A', '2016-05-20 13:22:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2200, 'XJEWahH_fcI', NULL, 'Bring a culture of work-based learning in Indian higher education', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Vishwesh Kulkarni, President, Yashaswi Group shares his thought about the skill development and its importance in higher education. While addressing the audience, he highlighted the topics such as bringing culture of work-based learning in Indian higher education, how to build a culture for universities to be funded by business and not by government alone and the challenges for Indian universities governance.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Higher Education, Skill development, Yashaswi Group, Vishwesh Kulkarni', '09:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2806, 'A', '2016-05-20 13:24:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2201, 'ActhpCrcMVg', NULL, 'Quality manpower is the biggest challenge of Salon industry: Naunihal Singh', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Narrating the saga of his entrepreneurial journey at the 5th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2016, Founder & CEO of Strands Salons Pvt Ltd, Naunihal Singh shared the challenges faced by him while creating his brand presence of over 70 salons. Listen and learn the salon industry tit-bits from this industry expert.', 'Salon2016, Strands salon, franchise opportunity, Wellness', '10:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1624, 'A', '2016-05-23 16:47:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2202, 'a8Lohzkhn_Q', NULL, 'Naunihal Singh suggest 6S of Indian Salon Industry', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Delivering keynote at the 5th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2016, Founder & CEO of Strands Salons Pvt Ltd, Naunihal Singh suggested 6S for the industry professionals to keep in mind, which includes skill, speed, sincerity, serious target, social engagement and spiritual thought process. To know more about these 6S, check out this video. ', 'Salon2016, Strands salon, franchise opportunity, Wellness', '12:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2619, 'A', '2016-05-23 16:49:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2203, 'St73LbPmNYU', NULL, 'Proud to create 300+ women entrepreneurs & 7000 direct jobs: CK Kumaravel', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Known as the King of Salon franchise, Naturals salon has always encouraged 2 things- women entrepreneurs and franchising. At the 5th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2016, CK Kumaravel, Co-Founder & CEO of Naturals Salon chain unveiled some undisclosed opportunities of entrepreneurship in Salon business. Check out the video for more.', 'Salon2016, Naturals salon, job opportunity, women entrepreneur, franchise', '10:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2730, 'A', '2016-05-23 16:51:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2204, '8N7hlcHRQ7I', NULL, 'Introspect & flex business muscles, real industry opportunity is still untouched: Ritu Marya', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Defining the existing and untouched business opportunities in Indian Salon & Wellness Industry, Editor in Chief of Franchise India Holdings, Ritu Marya addressed the elite club of an oldest industry. She emphasised on the fact that the in Indian market, opportunities for salon and beauty professionals are gigantic as the real business has not even started yet. To know more about her research backed views, log on to this video.', 'Salon2016, business opportunity, franchise', '09:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3426, 'A', '2016-05-23 16:52:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2205, '8z0D2vE4k08', NULL, 'Join hands with leader, learn & create your own franchise: Shahnawaz Nayyer', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Highlighting the growth blocking points of Indian Salon industry, Shahnawaz Nayyer, Head Sales, Wella Professionals India shared his much productive observation regarding the industry and suggested ways to boost overall industry growth. Check out the video to learn more.', 'Salon2016, franchise opportunity, Wella Professionals, business growth', '05:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2836, 'A', '2016-05-23 17:11:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2206, 'g1f3UpxchTE', NULL, 'Understanding customer behaviour is no game in Salon business: Sudheer Koneru', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Sharing the intricate data analysis of the Indian Salon & wellness industry, Founder & CEO of Zenoti explained the importance of an organised system on place to capture consumer data in salons, organising the whole ecosystem with the help of technology and critically comparing the top, average and low performing salons in the industry to help them improve well. Must watch this insightful analysis to improve your business growth.  ', 'Salon2016, Zenoti, business opportunity, salon industry analysis', '03:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2811, 'A', '2016-05-23 17:13:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2207, '9-CPBSvKPpA', NULL, 'Beauty & Wellness 2020: Wellness wallet share and future growth', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'At the 5th Indian Salon & Wellness Congress 2016, panellist CK Kumaravel, Co-Founder & CEO, Naturals salon shared views with Shahnawaz Nayyer, Head Sales, Wella Professionals talked about the consumer driven industry, role played by young India as the core consumer group, importance of education in making the industry growth much productive. Tune in to create better understanding of the industry.', 'Salon2016, Naturals Salon, Wella Professional, Business promotion', '10:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3810, 'A', '2016-05-23 17:14:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2208, 'aP7LYMJnZes', NULL, 'Growth driving factors and scalability of Indian Beauty industry', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'An insightful discussion between Vikram Gupta, Founder & Managing Director, Ivy Cap Ventures Ltd, Sachin Garg, Angel Investor & CEO, Arisol Technologies, Arjun Chhabra, Director-Friends & Co. & Co-Founder- Sparlour, Vishal Mehra, Group Director, Sanghvi Brands, Vishal Sharma, Executive Director, Everstone Capital Advisors & Sudheer Koneru, Founder & CEO, Zenoti. The panelists critically analysed their observation about the industry growth and how it could be scaled up. To learn more, listen to the much productive discussion between the esteemed experts.', 'Salon2016, PwC, Sanghvi Brands, Everstone Capital, Zenoti', '21:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3683, 'A', '2016-05-23 17:16:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2209, '09iYA09dhiM', NULL, 'Challenges of scaling up and ways to combat constantly emerging issues', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'The lead talk points in this discussion was emerging brands need to know when they set out on this path of being noticed, expand and grow business through franchising, retailing and understanding the challenges and opportunities when reaching for international market. Know more about the retail opportunities and technology driven avenue of opportunities suggested by Vikram Gupta, Founder & Managing Director, Ivy Cap Ventures Ltd, Sachin Garg, Angel Investor & CEO, Arisol Technologies, Arjun Chhabra, Director-Friends & Co. & Co-Founder- Sparlour, Vishal Mehra, Group Director, Sanghvi Brands, Vishal Sharma, Executive Director, Everstone Capital Advisors & Sudheer Koneru, Founder & CEO, Zenoti.', 'Salon2016, PwC, Sanghvi Brands, Everstone Capital, Zenoti', '14:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3479, 'A', '2016-05-23 17:23:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2210, 'zjF5lQky7xc', NULL, 'Taking Indian Beauty industry to global benchmarks', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'The beauty & aesthetics industry is seeing chain growth and brand resonance, the need is to build leadership by developing consistent business practices that support the direction of the organization. The discussion was opined by Rajat Wahi, Partner, Management Consulting, Head-Consumer, Retail and Agri Sector, KPMG India joined by Blessing A Manikandan, CEO, Paulsons Beauty, Istayak Ansari, Co-Owner & Director Lloyds Luxuries (Truefitt & Hill Barber Shop, Mumbai), Rod Anker, Owner & Founder, Rod Anker Salons, Bharti Taneja, Founder & CEO, Alps Beauty Clinics & Academy, Pushkraj Shenai, Chief Executive Officer, Lakm Lever Pvt. Ltd, Samir Srivastava, CEO, Jean Claude Biguine (India).', 'Salon2016, KPMG, Lakmé Lever, Jean Claude Biguine, Truefitt& Hill Barber Shop', '12:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4431, 'A', '2016-05-23 17:24:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2211, '-xEmiXipGV4', NULL, 'Understanding the Global benchmark of salon business and lifting Indian standards high', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Rajat Wahi, Partner, Management Consulting, Head-Consumer, Retail and Agri Sector, KPMG India was joined by Blessing A Manikandan, CEO, Paulsons Beauty, Istayak Ansari, Co-Owner & Director Lloyds Luxuries (Truefitt & Hill Barber Shop, Mumbai), Rod Anker, Owner & Founder, Rod Anker Salons, Bharti Taneja, Founder & CEO, Alps Beauty Clinics & Academy, Pushkraj Shenai, Chief Executive Officer, Lakme Lever Pvt. Ltd, Samir Srivastava, CEO, Jean Claude Biguine (India) in this session. The experts shared views about bringing globally renowned brands to India and comparing a new brand in the country.', 'Salon2016, KPMG, Lakmé Lever, Jean Claude Biguine, Truefitt& Hill Barber Shop', '15:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3728, 'A', '2016-05-24 12:05:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2212, 'DhtquuIWiJ0', NULL, 'Structure, mindset and franchise of Salon brands: An administrative detail', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Rajat Wahi, Partner, Management Consulting, Head-Consumer, Retail and Agri Sector, KPMG India talked to Blessing A Manikandan, CEO, Paulsons Beauty, Istayak Ansari, Co-Owner & Director Lloyds Luxuries (Truefitt & Hill Barber Shop, Mumbai), Rod Anker, Owner & Founder, Rod Anker Salons, Bharti Taneja, Founder & CEO, Alps Beauty Clinics & Academy, Pushkraj Shenai, Chief Executive Officer, Lakme Lever Pvt. Ltd, Samir Srivastava, CEO, Jean Claude Biguine (India) to share their views over the stigma attached to the industry and how gradually the industry is moving ahead with new innovations and changes.', 'Salon2016, KPMG, Lakme Lever, Jean Claude Biguine, Truefitt& Hill Barber Shop', '21:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4351, 'A', '2016-05-24 12:08:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2213, 'yUITNNQNdFA', NULL, 'Wellness business: Turning welcoming changes into lasting approach', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'The panelist Rajesh Mundra, Founder & CEO-Truworth Wellness, & President-TiE Rajasthan, Dr. Jamuna B Pai, Chairperson & Founder, Blush Clinic and Dr. Talavane Krishna, Founder and Chairman, Indus Valley Ayurvedic Centre and Sanjay Bhutani, Managing Director &ndash; India and SAARC, Bausch and Lomb India Pvt Ltd was joined by Ritu Marya, Editor in Chief, Franchise India Holdings Pvt Ltd. The experts brought their views over changing dynamics of med spas and leading spas in the country.  ', 'Salon2016, Blush Clinics, Indus Valley Ayurveda, Bausch and Lomb, Truworth Wellness', '13:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4298, 'A', '2016-05-24 12:10:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2214, 'FyNW1zgA-So', NULL, 'Bouteque-ing Spa & AYUSH Products as Business extension: An insightful discussion', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'The panelist Rajesh Mundra, Founder & CEO-Truworth Wellness, & President-TiE Rajasthan, Dr. Jamuna B Pai, Chairperson & Founder, Blush Clinic and Dr. Talavane Krishna, Founder and Chairman, Indus Valley Ayurvedic Centre and Sanjay Bhutani, Managing Director &ndash; India and SAARC, Bausch and Lomb India Pvt Ltd brought on table the current and future demands of Indian spa industry, which is fuelling growth with the gradually picking med spa and aesthetical practices.', 'Salon2016, Blush Clinics, Indus Valley Ayurveda, Bausch and Lomb, Truworth Wellness', '15:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 4096, 'A', '2016-05-24 12:12:12', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2215, 'dlGLaB21hUM', NULL, 'Fitness industry: Perched for a soaring take-off in Indian market', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Fitness has lured the middle class and become the most eyed industry of India. Accounts to over $24 billion franchise industry, fitness industry is waiting to be expanded and exploited to achieve the complete potential. The discussion was established between Hemant Aangrish, Co-Founder, Sheru Classic, Amaresh Ojha, Founder, Gympik.com and Jag Chima, CEO-Physique Global & Founder-The London Group (Kris Gethin Gym), the industry veterans and experts, backed with strong knowledge on fitness.', 'Salon2016, Gympik, Kris Gethin, Sportsfit, Sheru Classic', '13:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3455, 'A', '2016-05-24 15:33:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2216, 'gKe36vvyPHs', NULL, 'Brining standardisation in Indian aesthetics business with med spa concept', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Emphasising on the power of word of mouth and educating consumers are the keys to bring standardisation in the industry. The discussion was joined by panelist Rajesh Mundra, Founder & CEO-Truworth Wellness, & President-TiE Rajasthan, Dr. Jamuna B Pai, Chairperson & Founder, Blush Clinic and Dr. Talavane Krishna, Founder and Chairman, Indus Valley Ayurvedic Centre and Sanjay Bhutani, Managing Director &ndash; India.', 'Salon2016, Blush Clinics, Indus Valley Ayurveda, Bausch and Lomb, Truworth Wellness', '09:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4302, 'A', '2016-05-24 15:34:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2217, 'k_vmVyQhBVE', NULL, 'Innovation in fitness industry in terms of equipment & forms of fitness', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'The panelists Hemant Aangrish, Co-Founder, Sheru Classic, Amaresh Ojha, Founder, Gympik.com and Jag Chima, CEO-Physique Global & Founder-The London Group (Kris Gethin Gym), the industry veterans and experts, backed with strong knowledge on fitness, shared views, passion and learning about fitness business in India and how innovative practices can improve the industry standards and improving the business opportunities.', 'Salon2016, Gympik, Kris Gethin, Sportsfit, Sheru Classic', '12:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2534, 'A', '2016-05-24 15:36:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2218, 'i_BBGCNS148', NULL, 'Challenges and opportunities of retail & eRtail strategies in beauty business', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'In salon & spa retailing, making an effective and profitable existence through retailing or eTailing is not difficult. In-salon offers test market ready, professional treatments and beyond conventional business culture, enough sources to retail and make potential consumers. The discussion was joined by Rishi Seth, Co-Founder, My Envy Box, Sanjeev Mehta, Managing Director-Emerald Isle Luxe Private Ltd, Spa Ceylon Luxury Ayurveda, Subham Virmani, Director- Sales & Strategy, Esskay Beauty Resources Pvt. Ltd. India, Manisha Chopra, Co-founder & Director, Seasoul Cosmeceuticals Pvt. Ltd, Vaibhav Mittal, Founder, Lovely Lifestyle and Bikram Sapra, Managing Director, JB Skincare Pvt Ltd.', 'Salon2016, My Envy Box, Spa Ceylon, Esskay Beauty Resources, Seasoul Cosmeceuticals', '23:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5087, 'A', '2016-05-24 15:37:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2219, 'YhCafFU28B4', NULL, 'Economics of Retailing in Salon: Bundling Products and Services', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'What are people really buying when it comes to organic products, what role salons play in marketing and selling of natural base products and gradually picking up retailing of nutrition wellness, the common matters were addressed by Rishi Seth, Co-Founder, My Envy Box, Sanjeev Mehta, Managing Director-Emerald Isle Luxe Private Ltd, Spa Ceylon Luxury Ayurveda, Subham Virmani, Director- Sales & Strategy, Esskay Beauty Resources Pvt. Ltd. India, Manisha Chopra, Co-founder & Director, Seasoul Cosmeceuticals Pvt. Ltd, Vaibhav Mittal, Founder, Lovely Lifestyle and Bikram Sapra, Managing Director, JB Skincare Pvt Ltd.', 'Salon2016, My Envy Box, Spa Ceylon, Esskay Beauty Resources, Seasoul Cosmeceuticals', '12:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4038, 'A', '2016-05-25 09:25:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2220, '9kxPoG8TZS0', NULL, 'Economics of Retailing in Salon: Bundling Products and Services', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Need for regulatory change in wellness and health space and brining positive changes in the industry in terms of making an organised process in the wellness retail. The panelists  Rishi Seth, Co-Founder, My Envy Box, Sanjeev Mehta, Managing Director-Emerald Isle Luxe Private Ltd, Spa Ceylon Luxury Ayurveda, Subham Virmani, Director- Sales & Strategy, Esskay Beauty Resources Pvt. Ltd. India, Manisha Chopra, Co-founder & Director, Seasoul Cosmeceuticals Pvt. Ltd, Vaibhav Mittal, Founder, Lovely Lifestyle and Bikram Sapra, Managing Director, JB Skincare Pvt Ltd talked about the need of regulatory body.', 'Salon2016, My Envy Box, Spa Ceylon, Esskay Beauty Resources, Seasoul Cosmeceuticals', '10:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5061, 'A', '2016-05-25 09:27:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2221, 'KsaJPRKgZRQ', NULL, 'Wellness 2.0: Future growth of innovation driven sector of India', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'The esteemed panelist Dr. Prem Jagyasi, Award Winning Leader, Speaker, Influencer & MD & CEO- Dr. Prem & Associates, Ashish Kumar, Co-Founder, Gajty Wellness and Ankit Arora, Chief Executive Officer, Streamline Services India, P&G retail, Olaplex India and Bomb Cosmetics India shared views on wellness 2.0, an innovation driven sector by individual entrepreneurs and start-ups. Reckoning the need of wellness, shift in consumer behaviour has turned a new chapter of opportunity for Beauty Wellness service providers & alternative wellness.', 'Salon2016, Dr. Prem & Associates, Gajty Wellness, Olaplex, Bomb Cosmetics', '23:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4121, 'A', '2016-05-25 09:29:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2222, 'gSPmDii2mNs', NULL, 'Where And How To Find Investment For Your Statrup?', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'The panel talks about the stage investment and how an entrepreneur should go about it and what is the right time for it. Speaking on the same, Nitin Jain of Cipher Capital adds how this concept is non-existent in India and many start-ups majorly receive funds from the 3 Fs &ndash; Friends, Family and Fool. Further D Ravishankar, talk about the traditional way of receiving funds, that is through banker, and how that should be approached. ', 'Investment, capital, Entrepreneurs Show 2014, Startups, Seed Funding, Pitching investors', '12:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1963, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:04:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2223, 'zME02CAoJDk', NULL, 'What Makes An Entrepreneur?', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Recalling the concept of Jugaad in India, Pradeep Mishra talks about how in India out-of-the-box thinking is being put to use in business recently. Taking this forward he begins to describe what makes an entrepreneur and believes that apart from his traits, taste and abilities, everyone working with an entrepreneur who helps him become who he is, is also an entrepreneur.  ', 'Entrepreneurs Show 2014, Startups, Entrepreneurs, Entrepreneurship, Entrepreneurial Mindset, Qualities, traits, Problem Solving, business', '12:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1695, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:05:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2224, 'wpwDaxRc9Wc', NULL, 'You Must Be Looking For Funding, But Do You Know The Type Of Funding?', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Initiating the discussion, Ananth starts the discussion with what are the different kinds of funding available and how to avail it. Where equity and debt remains a popular, getting funds directly from you customer is by far the best option as not only does it give you validation but it is also the right way.  ', 'Entrepreneurs Show 2014, Startups, Entrepreneurs, Investors, Pitching Investors, Funding, Debt, Private Equity', '24:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1620, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:06:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2225, 'S0vzGIhzuUU', NULL, 'What Happened When a Startup or SME Asks Bank for a Loan', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Taking questions from the audience, the panel talks about the process of a bank granting loans to startups and how interest is applied to that. Further the panel answers the question on limits put by government on SME loans, i.e. 100 crore and if that amount will be raised in the near future. ', 'Entrepreneurs Show 2014, Startups, Entrepreneurs, Funding, Banks, Loans, Debt, Pitching Investors, SMEs', '16:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1614, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:08:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2226, 'fV0FFjiMBd4', NULL, 'I Have Never met A Successful Unhappy Entrepreneur, But I Have Met Many Successful Unhappy Employees', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Taking questions from the audience, Pramod talks about entrepreneurship and the decision to leave everything behind, old job or even house to start a new venture of your own. They talk about how if there is a desire to start something new, one must act on it and take the plunge. ', 'Entrepreneurs Show 2014, Startups, Entrepreneurs', '21:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2369, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:10:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2227, 'Cxinzisk_hk', NULL, 'How India Can Utilize the Opportunity Given BY IoT', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Rajiv talks about the gradually evolving industry of internet of things (IoT) and its scope in India. A wireless network between objects, IoT has various dimensions, which Rajiv tries to explain through his presentation that could be utilized in our day to day life. A relevantly new industry, IoT has the scope to open doors to new opportunities and also establish a dynamic control of industry and daily life.  ', 'Entrepreneur Show 2014, Startups, SMEs, Entrepreneurs, IoT, Internet, Online Businesses, Connectivity, Network, World Wide Web', '19:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2262, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:15:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2228, '-eJUPHMyMpw', NULL, 'Indias Entrepreneurial Journey: How Far We have Come', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Ritu Marya welcomes all to the Entrepreneur Show and maps the journey of entrepreneurship in India. She begins how in the early 2000s people were a little reluctant to start their own business, and how the term Entrepreneur was mission. However, we have all come a long way and now people are actually looking for ways and the time when they will start something of their own.', 'Entrepreneur Show 2014, Startups, SMEs, Entrepreneurs, Entrepreneurship, Entrepreneurial Mindset, Businesses, Businessman, New Ventures', '11:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2387, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:16:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2229, 'In9ZNqQHrcY', NULL, 'How Our Smallest Dream Led To the Company Franchise India We See Today', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'The term Entrepreneurship was non-existent in India the late 1900s. However, it was very much popular in America where people waited for their American Dream to come true. With this dream, when Gaurav Marya returned to India, he conceptualized the idea of Franchise India. Though, the company struggled for many years, they never gave up on this dream and now, after all these years, they are helping other entrepreneurs to make this dream true. ', 'Entrepreneur Show 2014, Startups, SMEs, Entrepreneurs, Entrepreneurship, Franchise India, Entrepreneurial Journey', '10:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3196, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:18:47', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2230, '37eZMjm5LMc', NULL, 'Anything That You are Cribbing About in the world, Can be Used as a Business Opportunity ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Taking us back to the 90s, Saloni talks about how once calling was a luxury with Rs 15 per call but Reliance made it available to every auto wala or maid for their own gain. Similarly, people keep cribbing about the various problems they see every day but do nothing about it. Instead, they should take these problems and try to look it from a business perspective which could make a big difference in the world around us.', 'Entrepreneur Show 2014, Startups, SMEs, Entrepreneurs, Entrepreneurship, Social entrepreneurship, SMEs, Social Initiatives', '03:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 2824, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:19:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2231, 'cu7MTteWJEQ', NULL, 'Your Objective As An Entrepreneur Should Be To Bring Capital For Your Business', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Sanjay Bansal emphasizes on the importance of capital in a business and how good established businesses can die due to lack of capital. Many entrepreneurs are not fortunate enough to inherit money from family and for them funds like seed funding and angel investors have been a boon. He talks about how technology startups have been in focus lately, but in the eyes of investors, all that matters are a good story, slid management and ethical standards.', 'Entrepreneur Show 2014, Startups, SMEs, Entrepreneurs, Entrepreneurship, Capital', '11:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1874, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:21:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2232, 'bOY929n6IZE', NULL, 'Need of skill enhancement for the better productivity', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Founder & Director of Les Transformation, Rishabh Khanna shares his view on the need of skill enhancement, exploiting the exchange program, educating the teachers abreast with ever evolving innovative teaching technology etc.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Higher Education, Skill development, les Transformation, Technology, Innovation', '17:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2646, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:24:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2233, 'gYKQUgKu-00', NULL, 'Creating A Professional Identity of teaching personnel', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Prof. Rajaram S Sharma, Joint Director, CIET- NCERT shares about the enhancing and updating teachers with new age teaching skills. He throws light on how important it is to impart skills to teacher as teaching is all about learning as discovering.  ', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Teaching, Skill development, les Transformation, Technology, Innovation, Teaching Professional', '14:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 2817, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:25:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2234, 'P_vtd6c3CAk', NULL, 'This startup is Designing Science Gadgets For Your Young Ones ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Rakesh Kumar, Founder, Experifun shares about his entrepreneurial journey, how he conceptualized the startup idea and what need they are addressing. While addressing the gathering he throws light on the classroom learning and how technology has changed it. ', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Startups, Edutech, Experifun, Technology, Innovation', '08:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2295, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:26:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2235, 'ZwnSfWdE9Ys', NULL, 'How Technology can Be Game Changer For The Education ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Rajiv Arora of Microsoft Corporation highlighted the role of technology in education while addressing the gathering. He believes that technology can become the game changer for the education industry. He further adds that to use innovation in its full capacity one need to work with technology to that they can compete with the current scenario.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Technology, Innovation, Microsoft Corporation, Rajiv Arora', '15:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2631, 'A', '2016-05-26 15:28:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2236, 'R_92TwHtUsc', NULL, 'Skill Development- The Need of Hour ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Roy Newey of Pitman Training Group shares about the measuring need and outcome of skilling India and what are the current challenges and roadmap for skill ready India.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Technology, Innovation, Skill Development, Pitman Training Group', '10:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2026, 'A', '2016-05-27 09:30:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2237, 'LKJbHQzA9eM', NULL, 'Change the mindset, change the rules: Optimum utilization of existing resources', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Rayan Pinto of Rayan International Group of Institution shares about building future schools today and how K-12 education has been changed over the last few years.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, K-12 education, Digital Learning, Rayan Pinto, Rayan International Group of Institution', '07:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2938, 'A', '2016-05-27 09:31:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2238, '3_JLGfYCDOQ', NULL, 'Change the mindset, change the rules: Optimum utilization of existing resources', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Sooraj Ramachandran, Director, Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan, Middle East shares about changing dynamics of K-12 education in past few years. His emphasis was on the impact online education and how it can benefit the school going children.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, K-12 education, Digital Learning, Sooraj Ramachandran, Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan, Middle East', '04:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3467, 'A', '2016-05-27 09:33:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2239, 'vOt5_NW7RhU', NULL, 'How School Going Children Can Benefit From The Dynamic Of K-12 Education', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Sooraj Ramachandran, Director, Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan, Middle East shares about changing dynamics of K-12 education in past few years. His emphasis was on the impact online education and how it can benefit the school going children.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, K-12 Education, Digital Learning, VIBGYOR High Group of Schools, Rustom Kerawalla, Technology, innovation', '03:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3455, 'A', '2016-05-27 09:34:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2240, 'Yg24sCSSWkk', NULL, 'The Transformation Of Education In India With Digitization', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Sooraj Ramachandran, Director, Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan shares about invest in K-12 education, how imparting digital education will transform the current education scenario.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, K-12 Education, Digital Learning, Encylopedia Britannica-South Asia, Vineet Whig, Technology, innovation', '03:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1975, 'D', '2016-05-27 09:36:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2241, '7M6Wh5ItC9Y', NULL, 'Current State & Strategic Future of Franchising ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Andy Williams, Franchise Commercial Beverages, PepsiCo., UK is responsible for leading Global Franchise function, with particular focus on strengthening the Franchise network across the company. Speaking on the same note, he shares the state of franchising in India.', 'World Franchise Congress 2015, PepsiCo,  Beverages', '15:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1967, 'A', '2016-05-31 17:12:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2242, 'Xa26iskErbk', NULL, 'Capital Market Trends & Business Valuations in Franchising', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'A discussion on how franchisees are funding their new units either through debt or their own cash, franchisors has low capital requirements and thus are generally more profitable. ', 'World Franchise Congress 2015, Franchise India, Franchising, Franchisee, Franchisors', '13:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2298, 'A', '2016-05-31 17:13:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2243, 'xyyO9syS1YA', NULL, '2020 vision of franchising ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Samudra Bhattacharya, Vice President- Franchise, India Region, leads the engagement with PepsiCo Franchise partners across India, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Bhutan and Nepal. Talking at the congress, he addresses the franchise journey in India and how both Franchise India and PepsiCo will together evolve.', 'World Franchise Congress 2015, PepsiCo, Franchise India', '10:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2511, 'A', '2016-05-31 17:15:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2244, 'BMTeHwpHa6Q', NULL, 'This Is How One Can Build Future Schools Today ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Ravi Shankar, CEO and Chairman, brainSTARS Services Private Limited shares his thoughts on building future schools today. He put emphasis on how one can improve school culture in ways that better meet the academic, social, technical and needs of 21st century students.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, K-12 Education, Digital Learning, brainSTARS Services PVT. Ltd., Innovation, Technology, Ravi Shankar ', '04:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3022, 'A', '2016-06-06 11:40:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2245, 'OGxIhv5NI0I', NULL, 'Future of Learning: Is Pedagogical Innovation Effective? ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Vijayshree PS, Head- Strategy at brainSTARS Services Private Limited shares his thoughts on future learning and how innovation plays it role in providing high quality education.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, K-12 Education, Digital Learning, brainSTARS Services PVT. Ltd., Innovation, Technology, Future Learning ', '21:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2842, 'A', '2016-06-06 11:41:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2246, 'iY_6h7ixyo0', NULL, 'Identifying The Next Big Business ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Vijay Shukla, Managing Partner, Eduvisors shares his thoughts on investment opportunity in education space. He highlighted on the investment scenario in the education space and what need to done to encourage these startup so that they provide quality education to the young ones.', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Investment, Edtech startup, Digital Learning, Eduvisors, Innovation, Technology, Future Learning, Investors, Investment Opportunity. ', '06:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2663, 'A', '2016-06-06 11:42:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2247, 'rVDmZTofABg', NULL, 'These Things Need To Be change to make growth sustainable in India ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Prachi Windlass, Director- India Education, Michael and Susan Dell Foundation (MSDF) shares his thoughts on what all need to be change in India so that youngster can get high quality of education. She also highlighted the risk and challenges that an investor has to face while investing in education startup or a company. ', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Investment, Edtech startup, Digital Learning, Michael and Susan Dell Foundation, Innovation, Technology, Future Learning, Investors, Investment Opportunity, Prachi Windlass', '06:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2362, 'A', '2016-06-06 11:43:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2248, 'csM6APfjv94', NULL, 'Investment Opportunities In Indias Education Space ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Sanjay Bansal of Aurum Equity Partners LLP shares his thoughts on investment opportunity in education space. While addressing the gathering he highlighted the challenges and the risk faced by an investor when he invests in education companies. ', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Investment, Edtech startup, Digital Learning, Innovation, Technology, Future Learning, Investors, Investment Opportunity, Sanjay Bansal, Aurum Equity Partners LLP.', '09:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2553, 'A', '2016-06-06 11:46:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2249, '5EwIpdMt8Mw', NULL, 'Scale In Education: Decoding The Growth Mystery', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At Education Dialogue 2015, Neha Grover of Baring Private Equity Partners (India) Pvt. Ltd.  shares her thoughts on investment opportunity in education space. While addressing the gathering he highlighted the challenges and the risk faced by an investor when he invests in education companies. ', 'Education India, Indian Education Congress 2015, Investment, Edtech startup, Digital Learning, Innovation, Technology, Future Learning, Investors, Investment Opportunity, Neha Grover, Baring Private Equity Partners', '04:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2562, 'A', '2016-06-06 11:48:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2250, '0vG1xc6yDvU', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress & Awards 2016 Promo on Times Now', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Indian Education Congress 2016, India’s biggest  thought leadership platform on Education industry was held on May 26 - 27, 2016. Organized by Franchise India to showcase a product or service in the education space, suppliers and allied industries. This national event was a grand success with over 400 successful educationists, school & college principals, manufacturers, industry veterans, key suppliers, consultants and individuals belonging to the Education category attended the event from across the country. The conference talked about all aspects of Education sector in India and provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading educationists and an understanding around how they are re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.\r\n\r\nAlong with the Congress, Annual Indian Education Awards 2016 were also took place. The Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in Education space. The award ceremony was aimed at felicitating people who have contributed towards the growth of Education Industry in India. From Achievers, Innovators to Suppliers, the awards applauded their efforts in making the Education presence felt in this increasingly competitive world\r\n', 'Indian Education Congress 2016, Indian Education Awards 2016, Times Now, Indian Education Congress Promo, Education Convention, Education Industry conference, Indian Education exhibition, ET Now Promo, Business Conference, Education Summit', '0.45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4360, 'A', '2016-06-15 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2251, 'bcS8nQry-kE', NULL, 'The Evolution of Franchising', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India Holdings Limited speaks about the evolution of franchising that how businesses has evolved and has given new parameters to franchising. Although, one thing remains the same and i.e. the hunger people have for new opportunities and how entrepreneurship and franchising is empowering people of India.', 'World Franchise Congress 2015, Franchise India', '24:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2386, 'A', '2016-06-18 11:53:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(2252, '9cM7ubHw4tI', NULL, 'The Legalities of Franchising', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Mr. Rod Young, Chairman, DC Strategy, Australia speaks about the legalities about franchising, describing about what should be there in your franchising document while going from a dispute.', 'World Franchise Congress 2015, Franchise India', '20:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2193, 'A', '2016-06-18 12:04:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2253, 'WuVdfRLl10E', NULL, 'En Route to Sustainable Franchising', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Gaurav Marya, Chairman, Franchise India Holdings Ltd. speaks about the so far exciting journey he had, from starting franchise India 19 years back and encouraging people to franchise. Mr. Marya in his speech spoke that apart from new franchise models and strategies, we also need to understand the consumer behaviour and a sustainable way to deploy franchising in it.', 'World Franchise Congress 2015, Franchise India, Gaurav Marya', '20:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2703, 'A', '2016-06-18 12:10:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2258, 'QJhdS84OQdg', NULL, 'Krish Iyer lauds FDI as a progressive step ', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'With India allowing 100 per cent FDI in processed food retailing, US retail giant Walmart\'s India CEO at Indian Retail and eRetail Congress and Awards 2016 said the group will evaluate opportunities in the segment while it gears up for the next phase of opening up of new cash and carry stores in the last quarter of next year.\\r\\nWalmart currently operates 21 cash and carry stores under the brand \'Best Price\' in nine Indian states, and plans to open 50 more stores by year 2020. Krish Iyer, Walmart India President & CEO discusses Walmart\'s interest in selling food products directly to Indian consumers via Omni-channel, opening 50 more stores by year 2020, and future plans.\\r\\n', 'FDI, Krish Iyer, Walmart, Retail, Walmart India, eRetail, eCommerce, Retail and eRetail congress 2016, Omni-channel, Union Budget, Foreign Direct Investment', '2:58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2784, 'A', '2016-06-23 17:43:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2255, '1ElQTsuBgdY', NULL, 'Development courts the franchisee but Operations marries them', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Mr. Sandeep Kulhalli, Senior Vice President &ndash; Retail, Marketing, & jewellery Division, Titan Industries Ltd. moves forward with the session with his enlightening insight about the retail industry and what help does titan provides under operations to a franchisee\r\n ', 'World Franchise Congress 2015, Franchise India', '23:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3278, 'A', '2016-06-18 13:38:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2257, 'zk5tmEP5coE', NULL, 'More than channel, retail is about 360&#8304; consumer experience  ', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'The marketplace has to be device diagnostic or environment diagnostic as at any point of time, the company might be in customer\'s pocket in form of a smartphone, said Ambareesh Murthy of PepperFry, while talking at 5th Indian Retail congress. Leading the online furniture and home products marketplace, Murthy believes that it is important for companies to interact with consumers through 360 degree view of customer\'s life and is no longer about online or offline.', 'Indian Retail Congress, Pepperfry.com, Ambareesh Murthy', '4:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5636, 'A', '2016-06-23 17:39:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2259, '4VXeuXt69rU', NULL, 'Why was Being Human demerged from Mandhana Industries?', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Being Human clothing has been de-merged from Mandhana Industries and would now be marketed and managed by Mandhana Retail Venture Limited. Speaking at the 5th Indian Retail and eRetail Conference, Manish Mandhana, the Joint Managing Director of the group briefs the probable reasons behind this shift. Also he talks about the plans to scale up Being Human Clothing and take it to global level along with exploring newer sub-categories within the label. ', 'Manish Mandhana, Mandhana Industries Limited, Being Human, Salman Khan, Brand Licensing in India, eRetail, eCommerce, Retail and eRetail congress 2016, Omni-channel retail', '3:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2989, 'A', '2016-06-23 17:50:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2260, 'V-p8Z-XL3JI', NULL, 'Lacoste on aggressive expansion: Rajesh Jain ', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Initially launched as the polo club brand, Lacost has re-christined itself into a lifestyle brand, while going aggressive on retail expansion. The retailer has plans to open around 6 to 8 new stores in 2016-17, while projecting itself as accessible luxury brand, said Rajesh Jain, Managing Director & Chief Executive Officer, Lacoste India - Sports and Lesiure Apparel Limited while interacting with Retailer at 5th Indian Retail Congress. Jain also emphasized on the presence of brand in just the right catchment and not scattered everywhere.', 'Lacoste, Lacoste India, Rajesh Jain, Indian Retail Congress, Lesiure Apparel', '4:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 6, 4318, 'A', '2016-06-23 18:09:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2261, '-ubGOQKZ9c0', NULL, 'Process 9 bridging the language barrier', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'In a country with less than 15 per cent of its population well-versed in English, Process 9 has sensed a huge opportunity for language service provider segment, which is a USD 38-billion global business, reaching 950 million mobile phones and 300 million internet connections in the country. To sell your products and services to the entire country, localisation of all communication is the only scalable solution as India is home to a large number of languages, shares Rakesh Kapoor, Co-founder and CEO, Process9.', 'Rakesh Kapoor, Process9, eRetail, eCommerce, Retail and eRetail congress 2016, Omni-channel', '3:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 3, 4916, 'A', '2016-06-23 18:14:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2262, 'aGmC36wtZFs', NULL, 'Soon to launch a dedicated line of child care products: Kama Ayurveda Co-Founder', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Retailer media caught up with RS Sodhi, Managing Director of Gujarat Cooperative Milk Marketing Federation (GCMMF), the largest food company of India, which markets the famous Amul brand of milk, milk products and other food items. In words of Sodhi, the kind of business he deals with is C2C (Cow to Consumer) what differentiates this business from rest is the supply chain which is owned by 3.5 million farmers. Elucidating on FDI policy in food retail, he said that FDI is more than welcomed in this segment until the raw material is sourced locally rather than being imported from elsewhere. ', 'Amul, RS Sodhi, FDI, Indian Retail Congress, FDI in food, dairy product, GCMMF', '3:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 2, 5695, 'A', '2016-06-23 18:23:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2263, 'Oh7iUABNXvI', NULL, 'We will go where the consumer is: Sumit Dhingra, Arvind  ', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'In the evolving retail scenario, we want to be where the consumer is, said Sumit Dhingra, Chief Operating Officer, Gant, Nautica & Aropostale (India) while talking at Indian Retail Congress 2016. Dhingra added that the brand is not married to one kind of channel. Given that technology is playing a big part, in the way people are consuming today whether the content or the merchandise, the brand is making huge strides in how we are tracking those consumer journey and fulfilling their demands. ', 'Sumit Dhingra, Gant, Nautica, Aéropostale, Indian Retail Congress, Arvind Brands, J Suresh', '3:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 4931, 'A', '2016-06-23 18:26:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2264, '4ZJys4i5IaE', NULL, 'How education industry must use social media', 8, '', NULL, '', 41, 'Team Franchise India attended Intelligentsia Summit, hosted by CIHF, CIAC Global and The Education Post, and got insights from the bigwigs of the education industry on how the industry works. Here\'s Arvind Passey, Sr Columnist, The Education Post, speaking about the importance of branding and engaging through the social media for players in the education industry.', 'Education Industry, Social media, Branding, Education', '3:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2363, 'A', '2016-08-24 17:49:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2265, 'lPlwZBxMVqY', NULL, 'Has education in India woken up to branding on social media?', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'An esteemed panel at the Intelligentsia Summit 2016 discusses how the education industry is slowly understanding the concept of branding on social media and is implementing it. Watch celebrated author Shiv Khera, BIMTECH Director Dr H Chaturvedi and Sr Journalist Arvind Passey discuss the topic.', 'Education Industry, Shiv Khera, Social media', '5:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2207, 'A', '2016-08-27 09:16:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2266, 'KaImglj0n0I', NULL, 'The offline aspects of branding your education', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Speaking at the panel discussion on \'Branding your education on social media\', Professor Furqan Qamar, Secretary General, Association of Indian Universities, tells us about the offline tasks involved in branding your education.', 'Education Industry, Offline branding, branding', '2:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2197, 'A', '2016-08-27 09:19:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2267, 'GwBgiCCOjVQ', NULL, '\\\"Banks Are No More The Place To Just Deposit Money\\\" ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Banks are no more the place to just deposit money, issue cheques or take working capital requirements. They have become very nimble, says Bipin Kaul, Zone Head for IDFC Bank, but it is also the need of the hour. With the advent of FinTech, banking saw a disruption but together they are trying to look for solutions and also addressing those solutions with technology. At IDFC,  with technology as their core DNA, startups can find the help they lack in banking and focus on other domains. ', 'IDFC Bank, Entrepreneur show 2016, FinTech, Technology', '5:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3070, 'A', '2016-09-07 16:57:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2268, '1xUdAShLhxQ', NULL, 'Harnessing The Power Of Influence ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Unveiling his product that can harness \'the power of influence\', Media Guru Satish Raju launched his latest venture titled \'Influencia\' at our Entrepreneur India Annual Convention 2016. Introducing the concept of thought leadership in media Raju\'s Influencia is all for people just starting out, startups and brands. You get a chance to grow within the community and have a look at where you stand and then plan your growth accordingly. Influencia wants to help those who want to explore whether you\'re ready to startup or not.', 'Entreprenuer India 2016, Satish Raju, Influencia, Startups', '4:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2035, 'A', '2016-09-07 17:02:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2269, 'zQo_GhJ-5UA', NULL, 'IoT, The Next Big Thing ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Saurav Kumar is the cofounder and CEO of Cube26, an India based technology innovation firm focused on revolutionizing the user experience across multiple devices and platforms. We caught up with him to know more about his company and opportunities in IOT space.', 'Cube26, Saurav Kumar, Home Automation, IoT, Entrepreneur India 2016, Internet of Things, Startups, Iot Startups, Tech Entrepreneurs', '3:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1638, 'A', '2016-09-10 15:08:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2270, 'jx2hXls7_u4', NULL, 'We Don\'t Lack Talent, What We Lack Is Infrastructure And Training ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Rahul Bhardwaj, Co-founder and COO of Junglee Games is an active investor and entrepreneur, having previously Co-founded Product Mango and Vayyoo, and has led Fortune 50 Enterprise divisions with Global SaaS solutions. While interacting with Entrepreneur Media, Bhardwaj shares his views on gaming entrepreneurship and what all opportunities lie for the aspiring ones.', 'Entrepreneur India 2016, Junglee Games, Rahul N Bhardwaj, Gaming Entrepreneurship, Entrepreneurs, Gaming Startups, SaaS, Young Entrepreneurs ', '5:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2687, 'A', '2016-09-10 15:10:38', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2271, 'NAZAqoqgbzw', NULL, 'How schools need to adapt technology in their systems', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'At the Indian Education congress, 2016, Dr. Bindu Rana, MD & CEO, Millennium Education Management Pvt Ltd  shares her views on technology in education. According to her a child would be deprived of his basic learning if a school is not using technology in it\'s teaching process. At MEM, the technology and pedagogy are blended together which eventually helps the business grow.', 'Technology in education, Bindu Rana, Education', '4:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2647, 'A', '2016-09-10 15:34:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2272, '2LP9Q2er8Aw', NULL, 'How knowledge with action can empower the world', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'At the Indian Education Congress, 2016, Prof. Dinesh Singh, Former Vice Chancellor, University of Delhi talks about knowledge which needs to be connected with action. He also suggested that good ideas should be collected in an interactive way and blended with technology to prosper learning.', 'Dinesh Singh, Technology in education, knowledge', '4:51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3061, 'A', '2016-09-10 15:38:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2273, 'G7OwpFGI70Y', NULL, 'How technology has become an integral part of learning', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'At the Indian Education Congress, 2016, Director, Secretary & Chairman-Education Committee, PHDCCI, talks about the need for linking industry and academy for professional education. He also points on using different technology in education to bring about better learning outcomes.', 'PHDCCI, education, technology in education', '2:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1979, 'A', '2016-09-10 15:41:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2274, 'sst-GUbeR8U', NULL, 'Role of technology in education', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'At the Indian Education Congress, 2016, Ms Prachi Jain Windlass, Director-Education, Michael & Susan Dell Foundation talks about her mission of transforming lives of children living in urban poverty.  She also tells that with changing times, technology is being rightly used to support education in India.', 'Education, Michael & Susan Dell foundation, Technology in Education', '2:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2726, 'A', '2016-09-10 15:45:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2275, 'fgziTPYfBbQ', NULL, 'Digitalisation in education: Breaking the walls of classroom', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Prof (Dr.) B P khandelwal, Board and working committee member, The WPS Society shares that technology should be used in a discretionary way as a complement to the system of learning. He also shares that government of India and corporates should work together to help in fund raising for the education startups as a part of their CSR activity. ', 'Education startups, The WPS society, Technology in Education', '3:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3182, 'A', '2016-09-10 15:47:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2276, '26HQuXPCNIg', NULL, 'Byju Is Reinventing How Students Learn, Through Its Learning App', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Byju Raveendran, Founder & CEO, BYJU, an edtech company, is an entrepreneur by chance and a teacher by choice. Since its launch last year, the learning app has already seen phenomenal engagement, with 5 million downloads and more than 200,000 paid annual subscribers. During an interaction with Entrepreneur Media, Raveendran reveals what make investors fund their venture, expansion and growth plans.', 'Education Technology, Startup, Entrepreneur India 2016, Entrepreneur, Apps, Technology, Online Education ', '3:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2412, 'A', '2016-09-12 15:56:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2277, '8Y4KF6aiyTs', NULL, 'Entrepreneur India 2016 (ET Now Episode)', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Entrepreneur India 2016, India\'s biggest thought leadership platform on Entrepreneur industry was held on August 23 -24, 2016 at Hotel Pullman & Novotel, Aerocity, New Delhi. Organized by Franchise India, the 6th National Convention on Entrepreneurship has become the marquee entrepreneurship event on building enterprising entrepreneurs in India. The event attracted over 500 leading entrepreneurs and members from the Indian investor community together with CEO\\\'s and professionals leading Growth oriented organizations. \\r\\n\\r\\nAlong with the Congress, Annual Entrepreneur India 2016 Awards were also took place. The Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in Entrepreneurial space. The award ceremony was aimed at felicitating successful startups, Entrepreneurs and the people who are supporting them. From Achievers, Innovators to Suppliers, the awards applauded their efforts in making the Entrepreneurs presence felt in this increasingly competitive world.\\r\\n', 'Entrepreneur India 2016, Entrepreneur Awards, Entrepreneur Convention, Entrepreneur Summit, Entrepreneur Magazine, Start up funding, Pitchroom, Entrepreneur Exhibition, Entrepreneur Conference, Business Conference, ET Now', '24:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3581, 'A', '2016-09-14 16:54:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2278, 'QeoADwTnvaY', NULL, '&quot;There\'s A Huge Volume Of Jobs Which Are Going To Be Impacted Just Like This&quot;', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'AI has evolved and will evolve and we are definitely moving towards a more robotic future but artificial intelligence does not have to be necessarily creepy. It is being used in different sectors and will have huge impact on our day to day lives in days to come. But to what extent? Kaiesh Vohra, CEO and Co-founder of Lucep, is already striving to improve human-machine relationship and has answers to questins like above which he shares with us at Entrepreneur India Annual Convention 2016.', 'Entrepreneur India 2016, Kaiesh Vohra, Lucep, Artificial Intelligence, Entrepreneurs, Entrepreneurship ', '5:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2461, 'A', '2016-09-15 09:43:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2279, 'O64h07M-4yE', NULL, 'RISING TIDE OF EDUPRENEURS ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Amit Gupta Chairman Education Committee PHD Chamber of  Commerce & Industry, member school education committee FICCI and in Management Committee of ASSOCHAM. He has depth understanding of Education landscape from K-12 to higher Education.  Amit worked with CBSE for their foray into the development of an international curriculum adapted for students studying in Indian schools outside of India. Talking at Franchise India, he shares K-12 has big return and investment.', 'Franchise India 2015, Amit Gupta, Education Committee', '7:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2870, 'A', '2016-09-19 18:43:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2280, 'RA7T636Jsk4', NULL, 'THE GREAT ENTREPRENEURIAL VISION ', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Arnav Saluja, Chairman, Beverly Food and Beverages, the master franchisee for Mr Sub in India was himself present at the establishment during the blogger\'s meet and he shared his views and ideas on the business. He said that they were planning to establish 200 outlets across India by the end of fiscal year 2020. At Franchise India, he speak about transforming the speed and scale of entrepreneurship.', 'Franchise India 2015, Mr Sub, Arnav Saluja', '3:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3390, 'A', '2016-09-19 18:48:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2281, 'A4g-3xI1TjU', NULL, 'Opportunity trends in beauty & wellness ', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Arpit Sharma, Chief Executive Officer & Co-Founder, Sevenseas Spa is a passionate and dedicated to the industry of wellness; and have a deep understanding of the correlation between wellbeing and profitability and work closely with spa partners to build their business. His approach puts a emphasis on sound financial structures, best-of-breed management systems ,personnel development and brand building prowess. Speaking at Franchise India, he speaks about the health care franchising is on rise.', 'Franchise India 2015, Arpit Sharma, Sevenseas Spa', '4:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4565, 'A', '2016-09-22 12:31:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2282, 'KZejUEU0Ee8', NULL, 'Rising edupreneurs ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Nischal Narayanam, Managing Director, Nischal Smart Learning Solutions Pvt. Ltd is a renowned mathematical genius and the youngest ever to clear the Chartered Accountant examination at the age of 19. He has also established Nischal A+, a franchise and school partnering business model designed with a motto of being easily accessible to each and every child irrespective of any area/place, and Nischal Foundation to help the deserving individuals for their education and to promote literacy. At Franchise India, he talked that business with new technologies and digitization.', 'Franchise India 2016, Nischal Narayanam, Nischal Smart Learning Solutions Pvt. Ltd', '10:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3788, 'A', '2016-09-22 12:35:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2283, 'NJdJ5eJ9iOc', NULL, 'We Focus On Leveraging New Trends in Mobile Communication', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'With many accolades to their credit in terms of technology innovation, ICICI Bank stands first, not just by Indian standard, but also according to global standards. We at ICICI have been developing technologies since the inception, which have now become a norm in the banking industry. One of this included country\'s first mobile banking application, iMobile, launched in 2008 and the very recent \'Software Robotics\' for Power Banking operations. Introducing their latest innovation, Chanda Kochhar, MD & CEO, ICICI Bank talks at length at an event held in Mumbai.        ', 'Banking,Payment Gateways,Technology Innovation, ICICI Banks, Robotics, Mobile Banking, Mobile Apps, FinTech', '8:51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3180, 'A', '2016-09-22 17:16:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2284, 'S9BMCseUF_c', NULL, 'Unveiling True potential of Service Industry - Part 1', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'B.K Soni, Chairman & MD, Eco Reco talks about a fabulous concept that follows a reverse angle to create opportunities through buying all electronic appliances at the end of its life cycle from the consumers and create collection points by giving opportunities to franchisees. The next speaker Jitendra Jha, AVP, Neo Growth shares that how his firm provides unsecure business loans to merchants and start ups and recollects the capital through their in house collections model.', '13th International Franchise and Retail Show', '15:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4343, 'A', '2016-09-24 11:03:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2285, '8P2Rfs1NwG8', NULL, 'Unveiling True potential of Service Industry - Part 2', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'In an intriguing start, Abhiraj Bahl, Co Founder, Urban Clap shares the initial stages about starting Urban Clap which is a B2C service portal in which customers can hire from plumbers to wedding photographers and how he overcome the issues to survive amidst the competitors. The next speaker Kanika Tekriwal, Founder, JetSetGo shares about the marketplace they run for private jets and helicopters that can increase the reach of private jets and helicopters at remote locations giving a sigh of ease to the end consumer.', '13th International Franchise and Retail Show', '15:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2518, 'A', '2016-09-24 11:05:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2286, 'nyxLNPvLFXA', NULL, 'Future of Education Business', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'S. K. Rathor, Founder & MD of SANFORT Group of Schools started his career as Computer Engineer in one of the top IT Company of the country in March, 1991. After four and half years of his services in 1995, he started his own Computer Company with a little investment. He served many of the reputed corporate & PSUs. Speaking at Franchise India, he shares K-12 education investment and returns.\\r\\n\\r\\n', 'Franchise India 2015, S K Rathor, Sanfort Group', '16:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4553, 'A', '2016-09-24 18:13:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2287, '_vpeuQCLHdw', NULL, '2020 vision of entrepreneurship ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'B. S. Nagesh, founder of Trust for Retailers and Retail Associates of India and the Non-executive Vice-Chairman, Shoppers Stop he has been with department store since its inception in 1991. He has been selected as one of the top 50 managers in India in a survey of Managers who can influence Indian business in the 21st Century. At Franchise India, he talks about the maximizing the economic power of SMEs.', 'Franchise India 2015,  Mr. B. S. Nagesh, TRRAIN', '10:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 3581, 'A', '2016-09-24 18:18:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2288, '8NezDdE91tQ', NULL, 'Trends in Franchising ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Gaurav Marya, started his first business at the age of 16. It was not until the age of 24; Gaurav discovered his real passion in franchising. He was exposed to it for the first time while on a business trip to United States in 1998 when franchising was the buzzword over there. It was then when he dreamt similar happenings in India. The dream turned into reality in 1999 when he founded his own company.\\r\\n\\r\\nToday widely known for initiating the franchise revolution in India. At Franchise India, he shared what news is concepts and sectors in franchising.', ' Franchise India 2016, Gaurav Marya ', '15:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2824, 'A', '2016-09-28 12:18:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2289, 'Uc3F9PXYCvo', NULL, 'Technology Improves Productivity ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Qualified Executive MBA from IIM Kolkata and Masters in Operations, IR and Social Work from Premier Institute, Udaipur, Nitin Sharma is a competent professional with over 17 years of cross-cultural experience in operations, implementation, retail and project management. Sharma has joined Vakrangee as Vice President and is handling ATM business vertical. Talking at Franchise India, he talked about business future through technology. ', 'Franchise India 2016, Nitin Sharma, ATM Business', '3:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2670, 'A', '2016-09-29 10:30:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2290, '2JzGE1xX-V8', NULL, '\\\"Beyond the business,Investors invest in people\\\"', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'When pitching to an investor, the tone is always business, but rarely do we find entrepreneurs sharing their story or just talking about themselves. This is an important part, which Ameera Shah believes many budding founders fail to bring in their pitch. The founder of Metropolis Healthcare talks in depth with Entrepreneur India about how investors invest in people looking at their capability.', 'Ameera Shah, The Vault, Entrepreneurs ', '1:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2655, 'A', '2016-10-01 09:30:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2291, 'zduL9fySQtI', NULL, 'Here\\\'s how to impress the CEO of People\\\'s Group to get funding ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'When it comes to valuating a startup, Anupam Mittal has a thesis which he likes to follow. For him its all about the potential market size, the team and catching the ongoing trend just at the right time, about which the founder and CEO of People Group talks at length in a conversation with Entrepreneur India.', 'Anupam Mittal, The Vault, Entrepreneur India ', '2:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2584, 'A', '2016-10-01 09:33:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2292, 'H3HXF0xcWk4', NULL, '\\\"An entrepreneur\\\'s best pitch is showing his/her passion to the investor\\\"', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Just thinking about pitching to an investor could give founders head spin but according to MohitGoel, CEO, Omaxe Limited it nothing more than showing how passionate you are about the idea behind your startup. Goel shares with Entrepreneur India how to make the perfect pitch.', 'Mohit Goel, The Vault, Entreprenuer India ', '2:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2329, 'A', '2016-10-01 09:35:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2293, 'AfO8hs_3W0c', NULL, '\\\"If you\\\'re not solving a problem, you should not have an enterprise\\\" ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Valuation is a metric which involves a lot of diligence and thought process, and an investor must be very careful when evaluating a startup. With the ability to make or break a startup, founder and CEO of The Beer Caf, Rahul Singh in a conversation with Entrepreneur India explains how he chooses a startup for funding.', 'Rahul Singh, The Vault, Entrepreneur India ', '1:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1957, 'A', '2016-10-01 09:38:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2294, 'ER2Bx4NWtmU', NULL, '\\\"Startups must focus on their revenue to attract valuation\\\" ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Amidst all the thing startups remember to cover when approaching an investor, one thing they tend to forget about is their revenue but it is this revenue that will bring them their desired valuation, says Sudip Bandyopadhyay, Group Chairman, Inditrade Capital. He shares more about how startups should come for angel rounds once theyve clogged enough revenue, in a conversation with Entrepreneur India.', 'Sudip Bandyopadhyay, The Vault, Entrepreneur India ', '2:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1368, 'A', '2016-10-01 09:42:14', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2295, '5d3E1o1mWEE', NULL, 'An entrepreneur should never think of an exit ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'If an entrepreneur is trying to solve a real problem and is passionate, he would never think of exiting the business, says Vivek Bhargava, CEO, iProspect. He elaborates on the topic and how startups can pitch better and at the right time to investors in his conversation with Entrepreneur India.', 'Vivek Bhargava, The Vault, Entrepreneur India ', '2:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2620, 'A', '2016-10-01 09:44:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2296, 'Z3g2uO9RLIg', NULL, 'Technology & Business ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Ashish Arora comes with over 18 years of experience in sales, marketing and business operations and has led critical business units at HCL and Sify. He has been instrumental in drawing a strategic roadmap for Airtel Corporate Business - the B2B arm that caters to growing businesses and entrepreneurs in India. Under his leadership, Airtel Corporate Business has witnessed exponential growth. At Franchise India, he talked about business leaps with technology.', 'Franchise India 2015, Ashish Arora, Airtel', '9:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2271, 'A', '2016-10-01 09:47:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2297, 'nB0G0ITejQ4', NULL, 'Rise of Education biz ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Hari Krishna Maram, Founder CEO, BIIMS & Imperial College of Business Studies has a 17 years of experience (10 years in Corporate and 7 years in Academia). Speaking at Franchise India, he reveals new opportunities in skill development &vocational education. \\r\\n\\r\\n', 'Franchise India 2015, Hari Krishna Maram, Imperial College', '17:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2585, 'A', '2016-10-01 09:50:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2298, 'm4x-7zYHnDg', NULL, 'Strategy for entrepreneurship ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Established in 2013 by corporate honcho Bommanahalli Babu with two other investors, Attica Gold keeps on rousing and test pioneers in the private area to discover inventive approaches to satisfy unmet group needs and to lead the way towards better arrangement of business and marketing strategies. Speaking at franchise India, he speaks about enterprise strategy and policy developments and government\\\'s role in fostering entrepreneurship.\\r\\n\\r\\n', 'Franchise India 2015, Bommanahalli Babu, Attica Gold', '4:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2832, 'A', '2016-10-03 09:55:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2299, 'DPoATJOJKr8', NULL, 'Benefits in Healthcare biz', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Sameer Kaul, COO Metropolis Healthcare Ltd..has recently been recognized by IBM as one of the top 50 CMOs in India for successfully leveraging marketing and technology for business success. He has previously worked with Asahi India Glass Ltd. , Dr. Lal path labs, VJ Technology inc. USA and Oberoi Hotels & Resorts. At Franchise India, he talked about emergence of retailing in health and wellness segment. ', 'Franchise India 2015, Sameer Kaul, Metropolis Healthcare Ltd', '15:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3213, 'A', '2016-10-03 10:01:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2300, 'z_1NvEvKVk4', NULL, 'Manish Manhana on impact of Salmans person life on Being Human brand ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Being Human Clothing has been the first ever brand extension of Salman Khans Being Human Foundation through licensing. While the brand has created ripples in the market, it witnessed a dip while the actor was undergoing court hearings. Speaking at the 8th Brand Licensing Conference, Manish Mandhana, the Managing Director of Being Human Clothing briefs the probable reasons behind this, while also briefing about the soaring fan following of Salman that is the target group of the clothing label. ', 'Manish Mandhana, Mandhana Industries Limited, Being Human, Salman Khan, Brand Licensing in India, brand licensing, Brand Licensing Congress 2015, Licensing & Merchandising', '17:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2411, 'A', '2016-10-04 11:52:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2301, 'oT0zyTDq8w0', NULL, 'Indian Restaurant Congress & Awards 2016 (Times Now Episode)', 7, '', NULL, '', 36, 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2016, a thought leadership platform on Restaurant industry was held on August 29-30, 2016. This congress organized by Franchise India is the biggest platform to showcase a product or service in the restaurant, supplier and allied industry. This national event was a grand success with over 400 successful restaurateurs, industry veterans, key suppliers, consultants and individuals belonging to the F&B category attended the event. The congress also provided an opportunity to explore more than 50 leading franchise concepts with wide ranging investments. The conference theme was #DO THE NEW and it informed delegates on all aspects of restaurants business in India such as selecting the right food concept, writing a restaurant business plan, choosing the right location, creating a menu, the food and safety regulations, hiring right people, marketing etc. Indian Restaurant Congress 2016 also facilitated \\r\\n\\r\\nAlong with the Congress, Annual Indian Restaurant Awards 2016 were also took place. The Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in restaurant space. The award ceremony was aimed at felicitating restaurant and food service brands for varied award-categories that have done exceptionally well in their respective business segments. The awards applauded their efforts in making the Restaurateurs presence felt in this increasingly competitive world.\\r\\n', 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2016, Indian Restaurant Awards 2016, Restaurant Convention, F&B Convention, Business Conference, F&B Exhibition, Business Expo, Indian Restaurant Exhibition 2016, Priyank Sukhija, Riyaz Amlani, Chef Harpal Singh Sokhi, Times Now, Fine Dine Summit, Bar Summit, Chai & Bun Summit', '23:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4318, 'A', '2016-10-04 14:54:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2302, 'ay7-KqE013c', NULL, 'Licensing in global markets ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'There exist a bevy of brands that have carved a niche for themselves in native market and are all set to take a plunge into global scenario. Sunny Chau, Director, Thailand at Hong Kong Trade Development Council explains the strategies home-grown brands should follow while slating expansion for global landscape. ', 'Sunny Chau, HKTDC, Hong Kong Trade Development Council, Brand Licensing in India, brand licensing, Brand Licensing Congress 2015, Licensing & Merchandising', '17:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1411, 'A', '2016-10-05 13:37:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2303, 'Jk-Y0_6GTi8', NULL, 'The entrepreneurial ideation', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Krishnaprasad Rai, fondly known as KG Rai has been an industry veteran with a career in both private as well as public sector organizations. His core expertise lies in the retail business and planning. Prior to heading the retail business and marketing functions at Essar Oil, KG Rai has worked with companies such as Reliance Industries Limited and Bharat Petroleum in their retail functions. At franchise India, he talked about the power of technology for innovation and entrepreneurship', 'Franchise India 2015, Krishnaprasad Rai, Essar Oil Limited', '10:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2853, 'A', '2016-10-05 13:40:52', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2304, '8GzQWzV1bJw', NULL, 'Making beauty salon a premium opportunity', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Naunihal Singh, started on the route of being a Medical Rep and went on to make one of India\\\'s fastest growing wellness brands \\\"Strands\\\". He started working on expansion and opened the first franchise outlet in Patiala, but soon realized the importance of the challenges a franchise arrangement offers. He gives numerous training and development sessions by international experts of Matrix to Team Strands to get them tuned to the very best happening in the trade globally. Talking at Franchise India, he shares managing standards, hygiene and regulations in beauty services.', 'Franchise India 2015, Naunihal Singh, Strands', '15:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3777, 'A', '2016-10-05 13:43:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2305, 'SXCisu2tFtA', NULL, 'Bridging the gap between Franchisor and Franchisee', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Chekuri Swarochish, Founder, Penser Analytics talks about the cloud based software that his team has created to analyze and overcome the barriers while franchising any business. This software would not only help the franchisor but will also play a key role in enhancing the franchisees business.', 'Start-up Summit 2015', '10:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2137, 'A', '2016-10-05 13:47:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2306, 'M1pI67bzQjE', NULL, 'Deploying Capital to Upscale Entrepreneurship ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Rahul Khanna, Managing Partner, Trifecta capital talks about the drift that has been observed in the capital that is coming in the country to fund innovations and entrepreneurship. Following after Alok Mittal, Ce-Founder & CEO, Indifi Technologies Pvt. Ltd. shares peculiar views about how specific start-ups should be while spending the funding raised. The session moves on with Ramesh Dharmaji, Chief General Manager, SIDBI talks about the loans they provide to start-ups and what are the schemes that have competitive rate of interests.', 'Rahul Khanna, Start-up Summit 2015', '14:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2356, 'A', '2016-10-05 13:49:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2307, 'CVr3bUEp-KU', NULL, 'Boosting licencing in India ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Martin Brochstein founded in 1985, the International Licensing Industry Merchandisers Association (LIMA) which is the primary trade organization for the worldwide licensing industry, in 2008 after 12 years as Executive Editor of The Licensing Letter, a New York-based newsletter that covers the global licensing business. He was also Editorial Director of the parent publishing company, EPM Communications. He also compiled the publications industry numbers and edited EPMs other licensing-related publications, including International Licensing. At Franchise India, he spoke about bringing International best practices to Indian business. \\r\\n\\r\\n', 'Franchise India 2015, Martin Brochstein, SVP Industry Relations and Information, LIMA Worldwide', '14:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4176, 'A', '2016-10-13 13:13:01', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2308, 'iDHOiCfEG-E', NULL, 'Women entrepreneur ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Dr. Shabnam Sharma\\\'s entrepreneurial learning started early as she began assisting her family in their exotic fruit farming business in a small town of Fazilka in Punjab. She fulfill her father\\\'s dream and pursue a degree in Dental Surgery (BDS). During her visits to US, she got introduced the concept of Robotics based hands-on learning idea mooted by MIT. In 2006, she co-founded Techtronics Education, partnered with LEGO and started offering Robotics based hands-on learning solutions to schools. Speaking at Franchise India, she talked about how women entrepreneurs most suitable business candidates. ', 'Franchise India 2015, Shabnam Sharma, RoboGenius', '7:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5166, 'A', '2016-10-13 13:15:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2309, 'KtfLpAo6slQ', NULL, 'How to make big for entrepreneurs ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'B. S. Nagesh, founder of TRRAIN- Trust for Retailers and Retail Associates of India. Also, the Non-executive Vice-Chairman, Shoppers Stop he has been with department store since its inception in 1991. He has been the guiding force from the first store set-up in Andheri, Mumbai, where the store has now reached a national presence with 74 stores in the 35 cities spread across India. Commencing his career in 1982 with Blow Plast Ltd - the manufacturers of VIP luggage and Leo toys, Nagesh has also worked with Orson sales Ltd (1986-1988) and Carona Ltd (1988-1991). He joined the K. Raheja Group in 1991 as a General Manager, to set up the Group\\\'s retail business. Speaking at Franchise India, he shares how to make India an easier place to do business.', 'Franchise India 2015, B. S. Nagesh, TRRAIN', '4:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3457, 'A', '2016-10-20 11:14:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2310, 'MHb3rk8Te7E', NULL, 'Vocational education business', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Jaipuria Institute of Management Delhi/NCR established by Seth Anandram Jaipuria Education Society is run by the Jaipuria family with 111 years of excellence in Industry and education. The group has also promoted Ginni Filament Limited, which is a reputed company in textiles & garments manufacturing and marketing. The institute is committed to build Excellence in Education, unleash the best creative & analytical potential in the field of Management and allow the students to evolve into professionals at par with the industry standards to face the challenges of knowledge economy. At franchise India, he talked about new opportunities in vocational and skill development.', 'Franchise India 2015, Shishir Jaipuria, Seth Anandram Jaipuria Education Society', '7:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4136, 'A', '2016-10-20 11:16:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2311, '04yLXDccmi4', NULL, 'Importance of market analysis for start-ups', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Vinod Keni, Serial entrepreneur, Angel Investor & Co-founder, Peachtree capita Founders with Shailesh V Singh, Executive Director, Seedfund Ventures,  Ajay Ramasubramaniam , Director, Zone Start-ups & Prof. Arya Kumar, Director, Lal Bahadur Shahtri Institute of Management, Delhi. On a panel discussion on what, is it they really look for, when they are looking at early stage investments? How important is the team. How important is the concept. How important is ability to analyze the market and come up with new opportunities and how important it is to bring-in partners.', 'Franchise India, Opportunity Show 2015, Vinod Kenoi, Shailesh V Singh, Ajay Ramasubramaniam, Arya Kumar', '17:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2350, 'A', '2016-10-20 14:28:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2312, '3jUiPU3CS38', NULL, 'How to choose between and accelerator, incubator or an investor', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Vinod Keni, Serial entrepreneur, Angel Investor & Co-founder, Peachtree capita Founders, Pranay Gupta, Co-founder, 91 Springboards, Ajay Ramasubramaniam , Director, Zone Start-ups and Shailesh V Singh, Executive Director, Seedfund Ventures. Discusses the most asked query by every entrepreneur, What is more beneficial for a start-up, either go directly to the investor or an accelerator/incubator.', 'Franchise India, Opportunity Show 2015, Vinod Kenoi, Shailesh V Singh, Ajay Ramasubramaniam, Pranay Pandey', '21:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1557, 'A', '2016-10-20 14:31:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2313, 'fcMJCre963c', NULL, 'What needs to be done to improve Indian healthcare?', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Speaking at Samvaad, an event at Management Development Institute, Gurgaon, Sanjeev Navangul, MD, Janssen India, tells us what needs to be done to take Indias healthcare to the next level and make it better.', 'Healthcare, Johnson and Johnson, Janssen India\\r\\n\\r\\n', '4:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2014, 'A', '2016-10-21 10:21:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2314, 'n93bzfxS938', NULL, 'Johson & Johnsons Janssen is working on disease interception', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'Speaking at Samvaad, an event at Management Development Institute, Gurgaon, Sanjeev Navangul, MD, Janssen India, talks about how Johnson & Johnson is one step ahead in medical technology in India to fight diseases.\\r\\n\\r\\n', 'Johnson and Johnson, Disease Interception, Healthcare, Janssen India', '2:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2139, 'A', '2016-10-21 10:24:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2315, 'HuE85eLsv-o', NULL, 'Panel discussion on challenges in E-commerce ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India with Tinku Singh, Group President & Chief Strategy Officer, SRS Group, Ravi, Logistics businessmen, Shivanandan Pare, Head, Trendin.com and Anushree Shrivastava, DGM IT/ New Ventures/ IRCTC, Delhi. In a panel discussion on retail grocery stores, entering e-commerce and the challenges they face.', 'Franchise India Show 2015, Franchise India, E-Commerce, Ritu Marya, Tinku Singh, Ravi, Shivanandan Pare, Anushree Shrivastava', '23:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3600, 'A', '2016-10-21 10:29:06', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0),
(2316, 'r2e2OdDTqLo', NULL, 'Panel discussion on how E-commerce supports a business', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India with Tinku Singh, Group President & Chief Strategy Officer, SRS Group, Ravi, Logistics businessmen, Shivanandan Pare, Head, Trendin.com and Anushree Shrivastava, DGM IT/ New Ventures/ IRCTC, Delhi. In a panel discussion on on how E-commerce supports a business adding more revenue and turnover.', 'Franchise India Show 2015, Franchise India, E-Commerce, Ritu Marya, Tinku Singh, Ravi, Shivanandan Pare, Anushree Shrivastava', '14:58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3736, 'A', '2016-10-21 10:31:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2317, 'SAb3NhgCGdI', NULL, 'Difference between building a brand and building a franchisee brand explained ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Subir Saha, CEO, Yotto Labs with his presentation Brand baja de, explains how building a successful franchisee brand is completely different from building a brand itself.', 'Franchise India Show 2015, Franchise India, Subir Saha', '20:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1849, 'A', '2016-10-25 11:23:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2318, '7GSM1sgNPdo', NULL, 'Technology: Decreasing costing of the product', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Sudhanshu Malhotra, CEO, Webcom Technologies explains how technology can improve productivity and simultaneously reduce the costing.', 'Franchise India Show 2015, Franchise India, Sudhanshu Malhotra', '15:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1289, 'A', '2016-10-25 11:27:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2319, 'gmdOYTpkH7o', NULL, 'Why do we need licensing agents? ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Series of headaches and futile brain wracking sessions can be avoided when a licensing agent steps in the process of licensing deals to make the business venture successful. Theres a lot more in store as Pritti Ravindra, Director, Brandspoke gives great insights at Brand Licensing Conference 2015. ', 'Pritti Ravindra, Smiley Classic, Brandspoke, Martin Brochstein, LIMA Worldwide, Brand Licensing in India, brand licensing, Brand Licensing Congress 2015, Licensing & Merchandising', '10:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2485, 'A', '2016-10-25 11:30:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2320, 'gjnr106jL0Q', NULL, 'What it is to be a licensee in India? ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Speaking at the 8th Brand Licensing congress, Chris Evans, MD, Oxford Ltd., Hardik Vasa, co-founder, Vasa International and Lubeina Shahpurwala, co-founder Mustang Socks emphasize on the challenges of operating in licensed merchandise space of India and how to address those challenges while integrating licensing with main-stream retail. ', 'Chris Evans, Oxford Ltd, Lubeina Shahpurwala, Mustang, Hardik Vasa, Vasa International, Brand Licensing in India, brand licensing, Brand Licensing Congress 2015, Licensing & Merchandising', '23:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2663, 'A', '2016-10-25 11:33:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2321, 'B2lnTId1xQE', NULL, 'Why is licensed property successful? ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'It is obvious that the largest amount of volume is generated through character and entertainment licensing. But thats not the whole story, there are many other aspects of licensing and each of them have their own positives and target audiences, says Chris Evans, MD, Oxford Ltd. while emphasizing on the reasons behind success of a licensed property. ', 'Chris Evans, Oxford Ltd, Manish Mandhana, Being Human, Salman Khan, Rohit Bal, Brand Licensing in India, brand licensing, Brand Licensing Congress 2015, Licensing & Merchandising', '24:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1784, 'A', '2016-10-25 11:37:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2322, 'wbuBq5oN3GM', NULL, 'Beauty Salon business a Premium Opportunity ', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'In an interaction with Beny Sachdeva, Assistant Editor, The Franchising World, Samir Srivastav, Chief Executive Officer, Jean-Claude Biguine India speaks about his global premium \\\"Biguine\\\" hair and spa offerings and make it accessible to consumers in the country.', 'Franchise India 2015, Samir Srivastav, Jean-Claude Biguine India', '10:14', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3450, 'A', '2016-10-25 11:58:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(2323, 'pn_EXa7S8Xo', NULL, 'Emerging Health & wellness retailing', 9, '', NULL, '', 42, 'In a panel discussion with Beny Sachdeva, Assistant Editor, The Franchising World, Sameer Kaul - COO Metropolis Healthcare Ltd, Vijay Shanker, Chief Operating Officer, New U, Dabur India Ltd., Naunihal Singh, Chief Executive Officer, Strands Salons Pvt. Ltd., Sameer Kaul &quot;COO,  Metropolis Healthcare Ltd Arpit Sharma, Chief Executive Officer & Co-Founder, Sevenseas Spa,Cathal Kiely, Managing Director, UTime Fitness, Hong Kong and Satya Sinha, Founder & Director, Chisel Fitness LLP, New age Fitness with Virat Kohli talks about new trends in health ,beauty and wellness in business opportunities.  ', 'Franchise India 2015, Vijay Shanker, New U, Dabur India Ltd, Jean-Claude Biguine India', '14:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4809, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:01:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2324, 'aheAEZ2PgZc', NULL, 'Issues relating to legal agreements between Franchisee and Franchisor', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Rod Young, Chairman, DC Strategy, Australia along with panel members Nishith Desai, Founder, Nishith Desai Associates and M. S. Ananth, Senior Member, Nishith Desai Associates  talk about various legal processes involved between a franchisee and a franchisor business. They also talk about building a robust business model and the legal aspects involved in franchising. They speak about the dispute resolution that can be availed either by the franchisee or the franchisor. ', 'Franchise India, World Franchise Congress 2015, , DC Strategy, Nishith Desai, Nishith Desai Associates , M. S. Ananth', '20:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2374, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:07:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2325, 'oqTanXn0DLQ', NULL, 'Do Businesses and A-Listed companies go public to raise Capital?', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Rod Young, Chairman, DC Strategy, Australia along with panel members Nishith Desai, Founder, Nishith Desai Associates and M. S. Ananth, Senior Member, Nishith Desai Associates  talk about how A listed companies and businesses have the desire of going public to raise capital, but do not have a clear business plan in mind on how to utilise the capital further. They also talk about the possibilities why companies raise capital that can be to clear debt through banks or individuals. According to them, there needs to be a core of profitability before companies think of going public.   ', 'Franchise India, World Franchise Congress 2015, DC Strategy, Nishith Desai, Nishith Desai Associates , M. S. Ananth', '15:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2415, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:12:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2326, 'x3KgyU44_qA', NULL, 'Need of constant communication between Franchisor and Franchisee', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India expresses that once the business has taken off,  a franchisor should always be ready to hand hold franchisee and there should be a proper system, culture to talk openly with the franchisee. Also, Vasanth Kumar, Executive Director, Max Retail, introduces the brand and its franchising model. ', 'Franchise India, World Franchise Congress 2015, Ritu Marya, Max Retail, Vasanth Kumar', '14:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2543, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:14:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2327, 'Hl6MYOvRVnY', NULL, 'Advantages of going Omni-Channel ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India talks to Vasanth Kumar, Executive Director, Max Retail about the way forward in the franchise business. As per Vasanth, the brand is looking forward to go Omni-channel which will enable the franchisees to connect with the whole network of products. Dr Om Manchanda, CEO, Dr Lal Path Labs feels going forward huge investment will happen in franchise space and he believes that business relation with customer is moving from transaction to relationship model. Sunchitra Rajendra, VP & Head HR, PepsiCo India believes that technology is a big enabler in the franchise ecosystem. K.B. Kachru, Chairman, Carlson Rezidor Hotel Group, South Asia says issues between the franchisees regarding advertising and marketing are resolved by a nominated body. ', 'Franchise India, World Franchise Congress 2015, Ritu Marya, Max Retail, Vasanth Kumar, Dr Om Manchanda, Dr Lal Path Labs, Sunchitra Rajendra, PepsiCo India, K.B. Kachru, Carlson Rezidor Hotel Group', '16:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3326, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:16:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2328, 'dfMU-Tu3m7U', NULL, 'Standardisation is an important component in franchise business model ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Shilpa Gupta, Head Retail, FMCG, Gems & Jewellery Division, FICCI introduces the discussion panel, starting  with Madhur Taneja, CEO, Essar Oil, who shares his thoughts on how Essar Oil has evolved in the business of Franchise. He explains companys statistics and future plans. Sandeep Ahuja, CEO, VLCC throws light on how VLCC communicates its service category and Standardisation of services to its service providers. Gaurav Mahajan, President, Raymond Group talks about its franchise model and about counterfeiting in the apparel business. ', 'Franchise India, World Franchise Congress 2015, Shilpa Gupta, FICCI, Madhur Taneja, Essar Oil, Sandeep Ahuja, VLCC, Gaurav Mahajan, Raymond Group', '18:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4674, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:18:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2329, '2S6FhcoSxpo', NULL, 'How is Omni channel disrupting the franchise Ecosystem ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Shilpa Gupta, Head Retail, FMCG, Gems & Jewellery Division, FICCI introduces Rod Young, Chairman, DC Strategy, who talks about the franchise model importance in India and the best practices that can be implemented. As every retailer is using the Omni-channel route, Gaurav Mahajan, President, Raymond Group discusses about how franchisees are taking the route and are they trained enough to do so. Sandeep Ahuja, CEO, VLCC explains how the brand is looking at fast and safe delivery. ', 'Franchise India, World Franchise Congress 2015, Shilpa Gupta, FICCI, Sandeep Ahuja, VLCC, Gaurav Mahajan, Raymond Group, Rod Young, DC Strategy', '13:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3685, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:21:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2330, 'YKJvvMqX9Ak', NULL, 'World Franchise Congress strengthens the franchise Eco System ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Gaurav Marya, Chairman, Franchise India talks about how the first World Franchise Congress is special. Also he talks about how such forums can help franchisors, franchisees and brands to understand and learn about the changing trends and needs of consumers. Gaurav Marya shares the joyous journey that Franchise India has mapped in the last 18 years. ', 'Franchise India, World Franchise Congress 2015, Gaurav Marya ', '20:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2042, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:23:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2331, 'cJVCTejkFcc', NULL, 'Operation framework: the backbone of any retail operation ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Devangshu Dutta, CEO, Third Eyesight talks about the importance of operations framework for any retail brand. He also shares that for any brand both, franchisee and franchisor have to be very strong. Anuj Jain, CEO, JSL lifestyle ltd and JSL Architecture ltd talks about how operations have contributed to his business and how it has a role to play in the growth in future. Murali Parna, CEO, Sagar Ratna Restaurants Pvt Ltd, talking about his business model and being a service oriented business, how he addresses the daily challenges when it comes to operations. ', 'Franchise India, World Franchise Congress 2015, Devangshu Dutta, Third Eyesight, Anuj Jain, JSL lifestyle ltd, Murali Parna, Sagar Ratna Restaurants Pvt Ltd', '18:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2046, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:25:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2332, 'eQETyigRe28', NULL, 'Retail brands should work towards smooth operation work frame', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Devangshu Dutta, CEO, Third Eyesight introduces Sandeep Kulhalli, Senior Vice President, Retail & Marketing, Titan, who talks about how the brand talks about the various elements of success in operations that his brand undertakes for maintaining a product which is valuable and has customer appeal and talks about the franchise opportunity. Unnat Varma, Managing Director, Pizza Hut (India Subcon) at Yum Restaurants International expresses his views on various learning that has helped Pizza Hut tackle the issues in operations and the way forward.  C K Kumaravel, CEO & Co founder, Naturals Salon & Spa shares about the various hurdles that the brand faced in operations and the future opportunity in stored. ', 'Franchise India, World Franchise Congress 2015, Sandeep Kulhalli, Titan, Devangshu Dutta, Unnat Varma, Pizza Hut, Yum Restaurants, C K Kumaravel, Naturals Salon & Spa  ', '23:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2671, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:30:31', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2333, '3WpPZFlA1S0', NULL, 'World Franchise Congress all about binding the Franchise Industry  ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India welcomes members of Franchise industry of India and oversees and expresses that the World Franchise Congress is an effort of bringing the franchise industry together.  Ritu explains that there is an evolution happening in the franchise industry on a rapid scale, whether it is for franchisee or franchisor. She also introduces Entreprenuer media and talks at length about it.', 'Franchise India, World Franchise Congress 2015, Ritu Marya', '12:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2407, 'A', '2016-10-25 12:32:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2334, 'Zj8Fx6y2cB4', NULL, '\\\"If you have a family, place your family before your business\\\" ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Time management is the biggest challenge a woman entrepreneur faces according to the executive director of Singapore-based I Can Read Chan Huang Yee. Chan said women need to be multi-talented! On one hand, meet their professional goals and on the other, be a mother, a wife and a daughter \\\" all a successful one. ', 'Chan Huang Yee, I Can Read, Entrepreneur India ', '4:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3102, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:28:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2335, 'Qv73XJeaxWE', NULL, '\\\"If pains me to see Indians pay through its nose for diseases from unclean water\\\"', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Swajal, which started its water ATMs to provide India pure water with the right amount of TDS & the pH requisite. Vibha calls this initiative one that caters to the growth of Internet of Things in India. The company is actively looking for franchise partners and wants to impact the lives of millions of Indians. ', 'Vibha Tripathi, Swajal, Entrepreneur India ', '4:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3214, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:32:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2336, '3MbJQi6AXtU', NULL, 'Discussing the Retail mantra (Part 1)', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India with Anupam Bansal, ED, Liberty Group, Nissan Joseph, MD, Crocs India, Rajesh Vohra, CEO, Chicco India in a panel discussion on three element of retail. How good is retail as an opportunity today as compared to what it was 5 years ago considering the rise of ecommerce and how the retail franchise model is affected, and importance of location selection for a retail store. ', 'Franchise India Show 2015, Franchise India, Ritu Marya, Anupam Bansal, Nissan Joseph, Rajesh Vohra', '18:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3053, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:35:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2337, 'Bz9yM_hqJ6s', NULL, 'Franchising and its future in India', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India with Jason Araghi, CEO, Green Beans Coffee, San Francisco, Jimmy, Murli Parna, CEO, Sagar Ratna Restaurants Pvt. Ltd. Nissan Joseph, MD, Crocs India, Adarsh Nigam, Head Corporate & Marketing, Talwalkars in a panel discussion on India as a market in basic terms and as well as in franchising terms. Moreover, sharing their views on where they see on-the-ground franchising happening and where do they see franchising a couple of years down the line.', 'Franchise India Show 2015, Franchise India, Ritu Marya, Jimmy, Jason Araghi, Nissan Joseph, Murli Parna, Adarsh Nigam', '35:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 7, 7, 35, 2903, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:37:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2338, '2Z4OaSRx2uw', NULL, 'Kumar Vishwas speaks about his journey and entrepreneurship in India', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Kumar Vishwas, National Spokesperson in Charge of funds, Overseas & Campaign, AAP in a dialogue with Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India talks about entrepreneurship in India. His life as an entrepreneur from a doctorate in Hindi literature to a Professor and then as a politician and what it takes to the change the course of ones career and go on to another career and then build further. ', 'Franchise India Show 2015, Franchise India, Kumar Vishwas, Ritu Marya, Entrepreneur India', '18:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3391, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:39:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2339, '0Sy0rZiuDvg', NULL, 'Discussing the Retail mantra (Part 2)', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India with Yogeshwar Sharma, Director, Select Citywalk, Asheeta Chhabra, Head-Business Development, Chhabra 555Fashion Pvt. Ltd. and Supal Doshi, Director, The Golden Time in a panel discussion on three element of retail. How good is retail as an opportunity today as compared to what it was 5 years ago considering the rise of ecommerce and how the retail franchise model is affected, and importance of location selection for a retail store. ', 'Franchise India Show 2015, Franchise India, Ritu Marya, Yogeshwar Sharma, Asheeta Chhabra, Supal Doshi', '16:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 3, 3, 15, 3754, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:41:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2340, 'EbEKquk1wc4', NULL, 'Discussing the franchising funda of F&B world (Part 1)', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Samir Kuckreja, CEO, Tasanaya Hospitality with Sam Chopra, Chairman, CybizCorp, Karan Tanna, CEO, Yellow Tie Hospitality LLP, Shikha Nath, Brand Director, Copper Chimney, Uday Mathur, Co-Founder, Tea Trails, Jason Araghi, CEO, Green Beans Coffee and Brian Laliberte, CEO, Green Beans Coffee on a panel discussion on what is the correct time for a brand to start franchising, what are the critical element of franchise mode, which ensures success for both franchisor and franchisee? What are the key challenges that come across while franchising and what are the new trends in the F&B sector.', 'Franchise India Show 2014, Franchise India, Samir Kuckreja, Sam Chopra, Karan Tanna, Shikha Nath, Uday Mathur, Jason Araghi, Brian Laliberte', '8:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3525, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:43:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2341, 'hSAHiAh8omQ', NULL, 'Discussing the franchising funda of F&B world (Part 4)', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Samir Kuckreja, CEO, Tasanaya Hospitality with Sam Chopra, Chairman, CybizCorp, Karan Tanna, CEO, Yellow Tie Hospitality LLP, Shikha Nath, Brand Director, Copper Chimney, Uday Mathur, Co-Founder, Tea Trails, Jason Araghi, CEO, Green Beans Coffee and Brian Laliberte, CEO, Green Beans Coffee on a panel discussion on what is the correct time for a brand to start franchising, what are the critical element of franchise mode, which ensures success for both franchisor and franchisee? What are the key challenges that come across while franchising and what are the new trends in the F&B sector.', 'Franchise India Show 2014, Franchise India, Samir Kuckreja, Sam Chopra, Karan Tanna, Shikha Nath, Uday Mathur, Jason Araghi, Brian Laliberte', '13:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3245, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:45:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2342, '2dZ8kdEC_84', NULL, 'Discussing the franchising funda of F&B world (Part 3)', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Samir Kuckreja, CEO, Tasanaya Hospitality with Sam Chopra, Chairman, CybizCorp, Karan Tanna, CEO, Yellow Tie Hospitality LLP, Shikha Nath, Brand Director, Copper Chimney, Uday Mathur, Co-Founder, Tea Trails, Jason Araghi, CEO, Green Beans Coffee and Brian Laliberte, CEO, Green Beans Coffee on a panel discussion on what is the correct time for a brand to start franchising, what are the critical element of franchise mode, which ensures success for both franchisor and franchisee? What are the key challenges that come across while franchising and what are the new trends in the F&B sector.', 'Franchise India Show 2014, Franchise India, Samir Kuckreja, Sam Chopra, Karan Tanna, Shikha Nath, Uday Mathur, Jason Araghi, Brian Laliberte', '12:51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3535, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:46:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2343, 'B41hAo9pIvw', NULL, 'Discussing the franchising funda of F&B world (Part 2)', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Samir Kuckreja, CEO, Tasanaya Hospitality with Sam Chopra, Chairman, CybizCorp, Karan Tanna, CEO, Yellow Tie Hospitality LLP, Shikha Nath, Brand Director, Copper Chimney, Uday Mathur, Co-Founder, Tea Trails, Jason Araghi, CEO, Green Beans Coffee and Brian Laliberte, CEO, Green Beans Coffee on a panel discussion on what is the correct time for a brand to start franchising, what are the critical element of franchise mode, which ensures success for both franchisor and franchisee? What are the key challenges that come across while franchising and what are the new trends in the F&B sector.', 'Franchise India Show 2014, Franchise India, Samir Kuckreja, Sam Chopra, Karan Tanna, Shikha Nath, Uday Mathur, Jason Araghi, Brian Laliberte', '18:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3679, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:49:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2344, 'ffEJ4hHzUJY', NULL, 'Estate Awards 2015 Felicitation Ceremony Part 1	', 3, '', NULL, '', 20, 'Considered the Oscars of Indian Real Estate Industry, the 2015 Estate Awards powered by Franchise India began with much furor. The award show witnessed the graceful presence of eminent dignitaries from the sector Dr. Anant Raghuvanshi, Executive Director DLF LTD., Mr. Sam Chopra, President NAR India & Chairman REMAX India along with Mr. Yogeshwar Sharma, Executive Director Select City Walk. Abhishek Goyal, Managing Director, Antriksh Group & Mr. Prashant Managing Director Chintels India felicitated countrys leading real Estate Brands for their magnificent contribution towards the growth in Indian Real Estate.  ', 'Estate Awards 2015, REMAX India, Franchise India, DLF Limited, New Mumbai  Realty, Uday Homes, Mahagun Moderne, Junction Mall, Bharti Realty Limited, SMCReal Estate Advisors, Raheja Developers, Puravankra Projects Limited, DLF Garden City Indore, Amani Spaces Limited', '16:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3667, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:58:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2345, 'tQgG88blgDs', NULL, 'Estate Awards 2015 Felicitation Ceremony Part 2', 3, '', NULL, '', 20, 'With the overwhelming participation and support the second phase of the exclusive Estate Awards 2015 fast forwarded to witness the cheerful moments of rewards and recognition which will be proudly sealed in the history of Indian Real Estate Industry and will be remembered in the days to follow. The awards show gave many industry veterans and peer members come together to applaud the best in realty. ', 'Indian Real Estate, Realty Awards, Real Estate Brands India, EstateAwards2015, KPMG India, PNB, Housing Finance Limited, DLF Luxury & Hospitality, M3M Group , DLF Mall of India, Raheja Developers, Chintels, Sarvome Developers, Siddha Real Estate Development, Acme Group, Suryaa Divine Homes, MG Housing, KumarBuilders, Gulshan Homes, Omkar Realtors', '12:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1914, 'A', '2016-10-28 15:59:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2346, 'eOvv4qkHP08', NULL, 'Estate Awards 2015 Felicitation Ceremony Part 3', 3, '', NULL, '', 20, 'When two significant people share the stage, it definitely rocks! The third phase of the exclusive Estate Awards 2015 powered by Franchise India was honored by Ms. Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief Franchise India and Mr. Sachin Marya, President Franchise India. They have been instrumental in encouraging the countrys vast diversity of Entrepreneurs who took the challenging paths and have been dedicating their lives to bring forth these special moments of pride across Indian Real Estate Industry for truly making it a global phenomenon.   ', 'Indian Real Estate, Realty Awards, Real Estate Brands India, EstateAwards2015, Palladium Constructions, PNB Housing Finance, Tata Steel, Adytum Designs, Invest Advice, Sohrab Dalal, Antriksh Group, Abhishek Goyat, ACMEGroup, DLF Mall of India, Pushpa Bector, DLF Utilities ', '8:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 2607, 'A', '2016-10-28 16:01:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2347, 'fgXZWLIyyz0', NULL, 'Urgent need to focus on bringing quality talent for any company', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'According to the panelist, Animesh Kumar, Group Head &quot; HR & Corporate Services, IDFC & Co-CEO, over 80% of employment that is provded in a formal workforce comes from small and medium enterprises and often from Micro SMEs. As per him, any company should focus on bringing quality talent for supreme output. He says if the company is willing to pay 50% more than what it pays to its talent, it will increase the output by 150%. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Animesh Kumar, IDFC Bank', '9:04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1871, 'A', '2016-11-08 12:18:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2348, 'FrXKPFSdBD8', NULL, 'Networking is the key in any business ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Ashwin Sanghi, Entreprenuer and Writer, Chanakyas Chant, The Rozabal Line etc, shares that luck comes through people and in business luck comes through networking, which leads to opportunities. He further shares the 12 steps of good luck in business. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Ashwin Sanghi', '19:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1348, 'A', '2016-11-08 12:20:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2349, 'RMgsFDeeGRw', NULL, 'Book keeping is more important than book reading ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Ashwin Sanghi, Entreprenuer and Writer, Chanakyas Chant, The Rozabal Line etc, shares the number of rejecting which his book, The Rozabal Line and other famous novel faced before getting published. He also shares his wisdom on what convinces him on being a writer. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Ashwin Sanghi, The Rozabal Line', '19:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2397, 'A', '2016-11-08 12:22:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2350, 'BWY9zLUDVFc', NULL, 'Engaging talent from small medium business is very important ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Asif Merchant, Managing Director, Catwalk Worldwide, shares that companies should not just look at countries like China for products, but should take the moral social responsibility of establishing the business in India, so that it can further benefit lot of investors and create employement for many. Some of the examples he took were of Fab India and Amul. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Asif Merchant, Catwalk Worldwide', '6:26', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1583, 'A', '2016-11-08 12:30:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2351, 'umixPio5Fkc', NULL, 'Awards presentation under different categories ', 6, '', NULL, '', 32, 'Ashwin Sanghi, Entreprenuer and Writer, Chanakyas Chant, The Rozabal Line etc along with Ravishankar D, Founder Director at Brickwork Ratings India Pvt Ltd and CK Kumaravel, CEO & Co- founder, Naturals Salon & Spa give away small business awards under various categories to individuals representing their respective businesses. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Ashwin Sanghi, The Rozabal Line, Brickwork Ratings India, Naturals Salon & Spa, CK Kumaravel', '18:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2399, 'A', '2016-11-08 12:31:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2352, 'x3EVdNLK05M', NULL, 'Future belongs to those who believe in their dreams', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'CK Kumaravel, CEO & Co- founder, Naturals Salon & Spa, talking his own example of expanding his brand brick by brick, passes a message for all potential business wizards to think big, think fast and think ahead. He further quotes, Big dreams are for big people and small dreams are for small people. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, CK Kumaravel, Naturals Salon & Spa', '4:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2475, 'A', '2016-11-08 12:33:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2353, 'RD-HfeSfcz8', NULL, 'Introduction to Brickwork Handbook for MSMEs', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Ravishankar D, Founder Director at Brickwork Ratings India Pvt Ltd introducing his brand and talks about the micro and small medium enterprises and shares that it is important for SMSEs to be conscious of the perspective of the bankers or perspective of the rating agency. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Ravishankar D, Brickwork Ratings', '14:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2367, 'A', '2016-11-08 12:35:04', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2354, '_DrVD8uonYA', NULL, 'Events is considered a different business than others ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Deepak Choudhary, Director & CEO, Event Capital introduces his brand and shares highlights of his professional background. His idea of starting Event Capital was to create events for every industry and provide capital for those events. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Deepak Choudhary, Event Capital', '6:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2546, 'A', '2016-11-08 12:37:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2362, 'mtfIrjLCrqw', NULL, 'Entrepreneurs should be daring enough to take a plunge ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'G Ramachandran, Director, Gold Gym, discusses about a role of an employee and role of an entrepreneur. According to him, when an entrepreneur commits a mistake, it is called experience and when professionals commit a mistake, its called non performance leading to termination. Entrepreneurs should be prepared for taking a calculated risk and should take a plunge. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, G Ramachandran, Gold Gym', '13:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2245, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:19:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2356, 'IZ5ASCzEzGQ', NULL, 'Entrepreneurs should have the courage to build a brand ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Hanuman Tripathi, Founder & GMD, Infrasoft Technologies, introduced his brand and also stated that focus is what made them grow over time amid the negativity of the business world. Focus can lead to profits, it can enhance the research & development, training becomes easier and the customers trust the brand. According to him when an entrepreneur locks his/her focus on making the business world class and takes up the challenge, the brand will itself grow. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Hanuman Tripathi, Infrasoft Technologies', '17:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1856, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:02:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2357, 'DTRDhdcJAfU', NULL, 'Small Business Entrepreneurs: the next big thing ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Hanuman Tripathi, Founder & GMD, Infrasoft Technologies introduces himself with his past experience and according to him Silicon Valley and the revolutions in US for so many years will be witnessed in India. As per NASCOM, for the last 25 years has caused huge amount of significant policy differences because of which India is reaching $100 Billion mark.          ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Hanuman Tripathi, Infrasoft Technologies', '17:03', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2082, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:04:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2358, 'xN7kCg-zEtA', NULL, 'An overview of SIDBI', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Jatinder Aggarwal, Deputy General Manager, SIDBI, talks about the companys inception, objectives, ownership etc. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Jatinder Aggarwal, SIDBI', '12:18', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1637, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:05:59', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2359, 'dxWlOPV4rI8', NULL, 'Companies always look for talent which can scale up the business', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'K.A.Narayan, President-HR, Raymond, shares his professional experience and also expresses that any company, irrelevant of their scale and size need talent that can create magic. It is always important to translate the business further through the quality talent. He also takes an example of a case study to understand the functioning of a brand while hiring talent. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, K.A.Narayan, Raymond ', '9:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2877, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:07:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2360, 'MaSHJdieexo', NULL, 'Creating Entrepreneurs is about creating the right leaders', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Kashiff Khan, Founder & Chairman, The K Group talks about the challenges of being an entrepreneur. He takes his own example and expresses that an entrepreneur has to be totally involved, which becomes difficult at times. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Kashiff Khan, The K Group', '2:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1766, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:09:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2361, '7ioo9YCWQXQ', NULL, 'Making Social Service Easily Accessible ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Manish Handa, Principal, Conexus Social Responsibility Services Pvt. Ltd, gives a perspective of social enterprise, social structure and social entrepreneurs and talks about the social business. He further gives an introduction to his company and how it contributes to social service. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Manish Handa, Conexus Social Responsibility Services', '11:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1460, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:11:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2363, '1XeJWIIB2LU', NULL, 'A low Business Startup Making its Presence Felt ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Neha Juneja, Co-founder, Greenway Appliances &quot; Greenway Grameen talks at length about her brand and as people still cook on mud stove, they introduced low smoke cook stoves as a perfect replacement. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Neha Juneja, Greenway Appliances, Greenway Grameen  ', '3:04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2130, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:22:41', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2364, '3uhFCq-acRo', NULL, 'Overcoming Challenges in the Tea Segment ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Parag Desai, Executive Director &quot; Sales & Marketing, Wagh Bakri Tea, shares that small businesses have a lot of scope to build their mark. He further introduces his brand and shares various details like history, present turnover, statistics and more. He further explains the various segments that WBG has in a pyramid model format and various challenges that the brand faced while scaling up. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Parag Desai, Wagh Bakri Tea', '15:11', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2457, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:26:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2365, 'oqQjaDX1Dfo', NULL, 'Investors play a key role in business growth', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Paula Mariwala, Executive Director, Seedfund, spoke about investment and funding. She also spoke about why investors and entrepreneurs need to come together. According to her investors will come onboard to scale up the company and gift it as termed Hockey Growth. She shares various ways of getting investors and their type.  ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Paula Mariwala, Seedfund', '6:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1586, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:29:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2366, 'n3ZOjq21smI', NULL, 'Encouraging Micro and Small entrepreneurs to take barcode', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'R.B.Gupte, Director, MSME-DI, Mumbai, talks about the seven components of national manufacturing competitiveness program. He says public procurement policy and public sector enterprises want entrepreneurs of certain qualities/parameters according to a qualifying check list. He says a barcode assists the buyer to trace from where the product has been purchased. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, MSME-DI, R.B.Gupte', '13:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2600, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:44:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2367, 'UMk0mUx8kFE', NULL, 'MSME development Act: the way forward ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'R.B.Gupte, Director, MSME-DI, Mumbai talks about his company and also introduce some of the features under the MSME development act. The term SSI was replaced by Micro small & medium enterprises.  ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, R.B.Gupte, MSME-DI', '16:04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1574, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:46:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2368, 'X-CY3XPPFbg', NULL, 'MSME playing pivotal role in Business Eco system ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Rajendra Kumar Sinha, DGM, Business Head (SME &quot; Maharashtra & Goa), SBI, gives an insight to the role of SMEs as they contribute towards countrys GDP and employment.  Overall he explains various facts and details related to SMEs and MSMEs. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Rajendra Kumar Sinha, State Bank of India, SBI', '21:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2083, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:48:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2369, 'MR4OQqZMjSQ', NULL, 'Small Business Congress 2014: A Prologue   ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India gives an introduction to Small Business Congress 2014 and states that the initiative is to help small businesses flourish their feet and empower themselves. She further discusses about the statistics of SMEs in India. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Ritu Marya ', '11:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1925, 'A', '2016-11-08 13:50:47', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2370, '2SJ9jKjQg-k', NULL, 'Small Business Enterprise: A Platform to Widen the Horizon ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Sachin Marya, President, Franchise India, shares that the key idea of starting SBC 5 years ago was to bring all small businesses under one roof to share their thoughts, ideas and understand the way forward. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Sachin Marya', '9:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 3535, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:29:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2371, 'OjSWZnrv2pQ', NULL, 'National Small Industries Corporation Strengthens the Entrepreneur Entity ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Sanjay Bhondekar, DGM, National Small Industries Corporation (NSIC) shares an insight on the credit flow that all entrepreneurs follow. He shares as per the MSME Act 2006, the micro, small & medium enterprises need to register themselves with the district industry sector. Once entrepreneurs are registered under the central government scheme, they are entitled to use numerous facilities. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Sanjay Bhondekar, National Small Industries Corporation', '14:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 3368, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:30:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2372, 'bd0hB95TEqg', NULL, 'Growing transformation in Society and Consumer Spending power ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Santosh Nair, AVP &quot; Sales & Leasing &quot; Retail, Phoenix Mills Ltd, before introducing his brand and how it is assisting the retail sector, talks about the consumer. As per him, todays consumer is asperational, young, focused and talented. He further says that it is the customer who is bringing a transformation in his/her requirements. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Santosh Nair, Phoenix Mills', '15:52', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3289, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:32:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2373, 'jSD2HkPfg4g', NULL, 'Social Ventures Have Become Really Impactful ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Satish Kataria, Co-founder, Catapooolt, talks about social ventures and explains the way they create an impact in the consumers life. According to him, social ventures have not just been making products and building services, but in a way have helped many people in getting efficient in their skills. Moving forward, he talks about car funding and its aspects. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Satish Kataria, Catapooolt', '6:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3608, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:34:22', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2374, 'H5eFByOEEkQ', NULL, 'Working on the Business is more essential than working in the Business ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Saurabh Mukherjea, CEO, Ambit Capital, introduces himself and says that in the learning stage, he had to be involved in every situation, from tracking the curious boy to coordinating for lunch. He also stated that the company was not gain profitability. Agreeing to the recommendation of his friend, he attended a course for Small Business owners which benefited him in many ways. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Saurabh Mukherjea, Ambit Capital', '3:32', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4575, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:37:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2375, 'Ew0T01HxCaI', NULL, 'Personal Computers Changed the trends in Business ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Shaji Varghese, Partner, EQ India Advisors Pvt Ltd, discusses about the changing times and multiple technological changes happening all around and new business models being formed. As per him, eBusiness has really picked up pace in the last few years and he explains some of the drivers which drive eBusiness in India. ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Shaji Varghese, EQ India Advisors', '8:53', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5093, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:39:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2376, 'KIELM_NXOc0', NULL, 'Entrepreneurs Journey is Full of Surprises ', 6, '', NULL, '', 30, 'Subramani Ramchandrappa, Chairman & Managing Director, Richcore Lifesciences, compares the blife of an entrepreneur with the lifecycle of a frog. According to him, learned people talk about having a mission, vision, strategy and structure, which will lead to execution. He introduces his company and says that an entrepreneur should be clear on what and why he/she is doing.  ', 'Franchise India, Small Business Congress 2014, Subramani Ramchandrappa, Richcore Lifesciences', '11:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4007, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:41:55', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2377, 'GaWOH0CBaU8', NULL, 'Kumar Vishwas speaks about his journey and entrepreneurship in India (Part 2)', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Kumar Vishwas, National Spokesperson in Charge of funds, Overseas & Campaign, AAP in a dialogue with Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India talks about entrepreneurship in India. His life as an entrepreneur from a doctorate in Hindi literature to a Professor and then as a politician and what it takes to the change the course of ones career and go on to another career and then build further.', 'Franchise India Show 2015, Franchise India, Kumar Vishwas, Ritu Marya, Entrepreneur India', '8:46', 'V', NULL, 'en', 4, 4, 20, 3324, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:45:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2378, 'YOTQ46TkSek', NULL, 'Kumar Vishwas speaks about his journey and entrepreneurship in India (Part 3)', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Kumar Vishwas, National Spokesperson in Charge of funds, Overseas & Campaign, AAP in a dialogue with Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India talks about entrepreneurship in India. His life as an entrepreneur from a doctorate in Hindi literature to a Professor and then as a politician and what it takes to the change the course of ones career and go on to another career and then build further.', 'Franchise India Show 2015, Franchise India, Kumar Vishwas, Ritu Marya, Entrepreneur India', '16:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3591, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:47:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2379, 'lUSo1APcK4I', NULL, 'How to garner retail profit through licensing', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'India has a nascent yet promising licensing market with a worth of around $1 billion. The rising middle class, more disposable income and increasing aspirations are fueling the market thus making a lucrative market for retailers and manufacturers, says Martin Brochstein, SVP Industry Relations and Information, LIMA Worldwide while speaking at Brand Licensing Conference 2015. ', 'Martin Brochstein, LIMA Worldwide, Brand Licensing in India, brand licensing, Brand Licensing Congress 2015, Licensing & Merchandising, Rocky Star, Fashion licensing, Gaurav Gera, Samir Jain, Chhota Bheem', '22:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2133, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:50:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2380, 'pVdUejggRUY', NULL, 'How to evaluate a potential licensee? ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Among the bevy of brands seeking to become a product licensee or promotional licensee, the process to pick a potential licensee is a brain wracking process for a licensor, as a licensee can make or break the brand, says Anurag Sachdev, Country Head, Rovio while speaking at Brand Licensing Conference 2015. ', 'Anurag Sachdev, Rovio, Martin Brochstein, LIMA Worldwide, Vishal Sinha, Sanjeev Kapoor, Yannick Colaco, NBA, Angry Birds, Brand Licensing in India, brand licensing, Brand Licensing Congress 2015, Licensing & Merchandising', '15:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2177, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:52:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2381, 'Zr0kgjUig3E', NULL, 'How is Masterchef Sanjeev Kapoor increasing retail presence through licensing? ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Speaking at Brand Licensing Conference 2015, Vishal Y Sinha, Business Head of Sanjeev Kapoor Brand brief on how the label is scaling up its retail presence through licensing deals. He also talks about the concept of celebrity licensing and the retail potential of Sanjeev Kapoor Brand.', 'Anurag Sachdev, Rovio, Martin Brochstein, LIMA Worldwide, Vishal Sinha, Sanjeev Kapoor, Yannick Colaco, NBA, Angry Birds, Brand Licensing in India, brand licensing, Brand Licensing Congress 2015, Licensing & Merchandising', '16:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1840, 'A', '2016-11-08 14:54:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2382, 'mNoNJBcOzk0', NULL, 'Beauty industry stays unaffected by economic distress: Stephanie Sherlock', 9, '', NULL, '', 43, 'Stephanie Sherlock, CEO, Avention Global, Australia, speaks about her brand and what interests her in the Indian beauty and cosmetics market. Stephanie is looking for partners for her brands Architects of Skin as she sees huge potential in the country.', 'International beauty brands, Beauty industry, Opportunity India', '5:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3047, 'A', '2016-11-16 16:57:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2383, 'V6g6YDzm7QM', NULL, 'What catches the eyes of education investors', 8, '', NULL, '', 39, 'Ashish Mittal, Founder, Turning Ideas Ventures tells us what he looks for in an education startup in order to invest in it.', 'Ashish Mittal, Education Congress 2016, Turning Ideas Ventures, Education, Franchise India ', '2:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2031, 'A', '2016-11-16 17:09:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2384, 'JwF4tHggsl4', NULL, 'This 29-year Old Wants to Bring Cloud Platform For Driverless Cars to India', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'The founder of BestMile, a cloud platform for the operation and optimization of autonomous vehicle fleet, wants to tap the nascent Indian market with the right business partnership. The Lausanne-based startup raised a seed funding of $2.5 million this August. The Swiss company based out of United States is looking to scale its team internationally, accelerate development and boost growth.', 'BestMile, Civil Engineering, India, Switzerland, Partnerships, Logistics, Cloud Platform, Driverless vehicles, Autonomous Vehicles', '3:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1730, 'A', '2016-11-17 16:32:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2385, 'JWaSTx15iXI', NULL, 'Indian Public Transport System Needs to be Strengthened, Bruhwiler Has Some Tips', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'The Deputy Director of Zurich Transport Authority, which is the largest public transport association in Switzerland, was in India recently. In a chat with Entrepreneur India, he spoke of what India could ape from the west to improve its public transport system and encourage citizens to shun private vehicles. Dominik Bruhwiler has worked with the Zurich Transport Authority for nearly 15 years and is involved in decision regarding the planning and infrastructure provisions for public transportation in Zurich.', 'Public Transport, Urban Mobility, India Transportation, railways, buses, cars, vehicles, Motors Act, India, Switzerland', '3:36', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3509, 'A', '2016-11-17 16:34:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2386, '6q1WI1oGilM', NULL, '\\\"FNP caters to classes and not masses\\\" ', 1, '', NULL, '', 11, 'Vikaas Gutgutia, Founder & MD, Ferns N Petals Pvt. Ltd talks about Ritz, the wedding venue destination, along with other details like USP, number of attendees who can be accommodated, kinds of events and future plans of the brand. He also gives an insight on the brands franchise details. ', 'FNP, Ferns N Petals, Ritz, Wedding venue, Ambience Island Gurgaon, Vikaas Gutgutia, Franchise India ', '10:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2712, 'A', '2016-11-24 17:11:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2387, 'T62O1GlfTrw', NULL, 'Shopping in Malls is more preferable than shaopping online ', 3, '', NULL, '', 18, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India discusses about the changing trend in shopping and debating on how mall owners are undertaking innovative steps to maintain a hefty footfall. Yogeshwar Sharma, Executive Director, Select CityWalk states that consumers are already aware of the brands ahead of the mall owners. Dinaz Madhukar, Sr Vice President at DLF Luxury Retail and Hospitality and Head DLF Emporio & DLF Promenade says that she always selects the brand for the mall very carefully. She also said owners may visualise what they think customer wants, but overtime mall develops its own personality. Pushpa Bector, Executive Vice President & Head, DLF Mall of India emphasised the importance experience that a customer carries with him/her. She further introduced MOI and its levels.  ', 'Estate Summit 2015, Ritu Marya, Yogeshwar Sharma, Select CityWalk, Dinaz Madhukar, DLF Emporio, DLF Promenade, Pushpa Bector, DLF Mall of India', '22:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4787, 'A', '2016-12-02 14:43:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2388, '3aq7AqIvcHs', NULL, 'Omni-channel retiling is here to stay ', 3, '', NULL, '', 18, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India discusses about eCommerce and asks the panel on how eCommerce has changed their perspective of taking their respective mall forward in terms of choosing the brand, in the way of placement and presence of the store in the mall. Pushpa Bector, Executive Vice President & Head, DLF Mall of India, states that Omni channel retailing will be the driving force for the retail ecosystem.  Dinaz Madhukar, Sr Vice President at DLF Luxury Retail and Hospitality and Head DLF Emporio & DLF Promenade, shares that brands today are creating an experience for the consumers though their omni channel presence. Yogeshwar Sharma, Executive Director, Select CityWalk says that though online business is flourishing at a fast pace, but brick and mortar has its own importance.', 'Estate Summit 2015, Ritu Marya, Yogeshwar Sharma, Select CityWalk, Dinaz Madhukar, DLF Emporio, DLF Promenade, Pushpa Bector, DLF Mall of India', '21:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4569, 'A', '2016-12-02 14:45:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2389, '7r7wDtiUnWY', NULL, 'This Entrepreneur Is Moving Mountains To Tap Water In The Mountains ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'An engineer, innovator, and an education reformist originally from the Trans Himalayan region of Ladakh in India, Sonam Wangchuk has done what no social entrepreneur has done in the world. rnWangchuk is the the winner of the international Rolex Award of Enterprise 2016 for his solution to freeze glacial meltwater into towering conical mounds resembling Tibetan religious stupas. These ice stupas behave like mini-glaciers, slowly releasing irrigation water for the growing season.rnWith his Rolex Award funds Wangchuk intends to create up to 20 ice stupas, each 30 metres high, and initiate a substantial tree-planting programme on the desert near their school once the new water supply system is established.rn', 'Ladakh, Ice Stupas, Sonam Wangchuk, India, Artifical Glaciers, Rolex Award of Enterprise 2016\\\\r\\\\n', '6:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2961, 'A', '2016-12-02 15:50:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2413, 'BWkau2VIoDc', NULL, 'Learning soft skills are as important as ranking for students', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Ms Martine Reicherts, Director General, EU, Education & Culture opens the session and talks about ranking, as she acknowledges that ranking is very important in India. She also said that in Europe, ranking is not given that much importance. She believes education and learning is not just limited to having a ranking system, it is also about learning and soft skills. She gave an in-depth brief about U-Multirank, an education system stated in Europe. Cesare Onestini, Deputy Head, Delegation of the European Union to India introduces Dr Mrs Pankaj Mittal, Additional Secretary, UGC, talks about the various programs that UGC has which are joint research programs, gyan scheme and regulation on maintenance of standards for promotion of academic collaboration  between Indian and foreign universities. She further talks about whatsapp courses. Prof Furqan Qamar, Secretary General, AIU, shares insight on association of Indian universities view over internationalisation and its various perspective. According to him, the new age internationalisation is driven by motivation. ', 'Martine Reicherts, Education, Innernationalisation, Cesare Onestini, Mrs Pankaj Mittal, UGC, Whatsapp courses, FICCI, FICCI Higher Education Summit 2016', '17:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3858, 'A', '2016-12-16 12:24:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `fihl_podcstvideo` (`sno`, `videoID`, `podcast_id`, `title`, `category`, `image`, `image_path`, `maxresimage`, `subcategory`, `description`, `keyword`, `duration`, `podcast_type`, `podcast_link`, `pod_lang`, `total_comment`, `total_votes`, `total_value`, `views`, `status`, `create_date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `fbshare`, `twittershare`, `linkedinshare`, `whasupshare`) VALUES
(2390, '5JHODFJGFVg', NULL, 'Real Estate: A potential Dynamic Sector ', 3, '', NULL, '', 18, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India shares that apart from sectors like restaurant, wellness, retail and eCommerce, it is the real estate sector that brings along its own surprises, which makes it difficult to predict. She further says that Franchise India forum always stood for three things which are transparency, professionalism and understanding the consumer behaviour. Consumers have really changed their perspective in the last few years. She also introduces entrepreneur India and talks about it. ', 'Estate Summit 2015, Ritu Marya, Franchise India, Entrepreneur India, Real Estate', '12:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3405, 'A', '2016-12-02 16:15:08', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2391, 'wH3nNGXlXhQ', NULL, 'Realtors and Estate Professionals Should Collaborate to Succeed', 3, '', NULL, '', 18, 'Sam Chopra, Chairman & Founder, RE/MAX India introducing himself and also states that real estate as a profession is noble. He further talks about NAR India (National Association Realtors of India) and what it does for real estate fraternity.', 'Sam Chopra, RE/MAX India, Estate Summit 2015, Real Estate, Franchise India \\r\\n\\r\\n', '14:24', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2812, 'A', '2016-12-02 16:17:29', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2392, 'Is_cAgd7_xE', NULL, ' We Focused on Customer Centricity and Delivery model for Customers  ', 3, '', NULL, '', 18, 'Shaji Varghese, General Manager & Business Head, PNB Housing Finance Limited introduces PNB Housing and shares a presentation that shows the transformation of PNB Housing and how its assisting the Real Estate fraternity. He also stated that his company mainly focuses on customer centricity and delivery model that suits the customers needs and requirements. ', 'Shaji Varghese, PNB Housing Finance Limited, Estate Summit 2015, Real Estate, Franchise India', '6:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3902, 'A', '2016-12-02 16:19:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2393, 'n__x40XG0MQ', NULL, 'Commercial real estate bounced back with 17% growth', 3, '', NULL, '', 18, 'Neeraj Bansal, Partner Advisory Services & Head \\\" India BCRE Sector, KPMG India, introduces the panel and states that real estate contributes around 6-7% to the economy. Ananta Raghuvanshi, Executive Director, DLF Limited talks about her outlook for 2016 for retail, commercial and residential sectors in real estate. According to her the commercial real estate has already bounced back with 17% growth. Prashant Solomon, President, Chintel Developers says main reason for private equity and investors coming from abroad is because India is a very promising and upcoming economy. He further explains why certain projects got delayed which were because of lack of infrastructure and delays in getting approvals or clearance. Shaji Varghese, General Manager & Business Head, PNB Housing Finance Limited talks about large economic indicators and customer sentiments in the real estate sector. Sorabh Dalal, Managing Director, Designplus Associates Services Pvt Ltd says there has been a definite rise in the interest for the commercial projects. Atul Banshal, President Finance & Accounts at M3M India says that from finance perspective, RBIS rate cut has given a solid brick to the entire real estate industry.   ', 'Neeraj Bansal, KPMG India, Ananta Raghuvanshi, DLF Limited, Prashant Solomon, Shaji Varghese, PNB Housing Finance Limited, Atul Banshal, Estate Summit 2015, Real Estate, Franchise India', '20:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 10, 10, 50, 6542, 'A', '2016-12-02 18:48:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 1, 0),
(2394, 'dsq4r088gdA', NULL, 'Research plays a pivotal role for developers and consumers alike ', 3, '', NULL, '', 18, 'Neeraj Bansal, Partner Advisory Services & Head &quot; India BCRE Sector, KPMG India talks about the changes done by the RBI in terms of risk weight age and loss to value ratio.  Shaji Varghese, General Manager & Business Head, PNB Housing Finance Limited says that affordability is about 40 to 50% ones income can be towards EMI taken against property. Earlier the banks use to provide loads for 20 years, but now they have re-designed it to 30 years. According to him this will expand a large market size. Ananta Raghuvanshi, Executive Director, DLF Limited and Sorabh Dalal, Managing Director, Designplus Associates Services Pvt Ltd talk about the changes that have taken place in the last few years from the development and architectural stand point.  Atul Banshal, President Finance & Accounts at M3M India states that once the consumer or developer is in the market, research has to be perfect and the differentiation factor should always be there.  ', 'Neeraj Bansal, KPMG India, Ananta Raghuvanshi, DLF Limited, Prashant Solomon, Shaji Varghese, PNB Housing Finance Limited, Atul Banshal, Estate Summit 2015, Real Estate, Franchise India', '17:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5124, 'A', '2016-12-05 11:22:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2395, 'IX_1zplNoIo', NULL, 'Projects making financial and economic sense attracts banks to finance', 3, '', NULL, '', 18, 'Neeraj Bansal, Partner Advisory Services & Head &quot; India BCRE Sector, KPMG India says many investments which have been done are in the debt nature and the debt has a cycle to itself, because of which projects gets delayed. According to Shaji Varghese, General Manager & Business Head, PNB Housing Finance Limited lot of banks headline for large size of NPA (Non Performing Asset) like 3 to 4%, but when it comes to mortgage asset, which is amounting at 10 lakh crore has its own NPA ratio. Prashant Solomon, President, Chintel Developers talks about pooling of skills and how more and more developers are looking at co branding and pooling of skills as well to finish a project. ', 'Neeraj Bansal, KPMG India, Prashant Solomon, Shaji Varghese, PNB Housing Finance Limited, Estate Summit 2015, Real Estate, Franchise India', '10:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4224, 'A', '2016-12-05 11:23:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2396, '4vVoYgov10s', NULL, 'Eduprenuers are greatly contributing to the education sector  ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Neeta Arora shares her views on rising tide of eduprenuers changing the tide of education business. As per her the potential for edupreneuers is limitless and they are the change agents who possess the vision to make education for meaningful for students. Eduprenuers are redefining the learning experience and with the advent of 3G or 4G internet connectivity and internet enabled television has given a boost to video based learning in schools. She further discusses about education and its properties.                ', 'Neeta Arora, Eduprenuers, Startup summit, Delhi Summit 2015, Franchise India ', '10:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2726, 'A', '2016-12-05 15:01:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2397, 'b5ck9-jK-u0', NULL, 'Franchising in India is as old as Franchise India', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Ritu Marya, Editor- in- Chief, Franchise India talks about the Delhi show and expresses that Franchising in India is as old as Franchise India. She further says that there are three mantras for the Global franchise industry, which are planet, profitability and partnerships. ', 'Ritu Marya, Franchising, Delhi Summit 2015, Franchise India, Startup Summit \\r\\n\\r\\n', '14:28', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2456, 'A', '2016-12-05 15:04:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2398, 'vaU0eXJ9198', NULL, 'Uniqueness in a brand is what attracts the customers', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Beny Sachdeva, Franchise India talks to Khanindra Barman (Kay), Chief Executive Officer, Wurfel Kuche, who explains the procedures that his brand follows while giving customer acquisition to its franchisees on a country level. Itisha Chauhan, Founder, JetSetGo talks about her experience with two franchisees who were college pass outs and wanted to get into the sector. ', 'Beny Sachdeva, Khanindra Barman, Wurfel Kuche, Itisha Chauhan, JetSetGo, Franchising, Delhi Summit 2015, Franchise India, Startup Summit ', '16:59', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2329, 'A', '2016-12-05 15:09:37', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2399, 't4BOt3za6X4', NULL, 'Main focus for Franchisees should be to keep their customer happy', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Beny Sachdeva, Franchise India talks to Mike Hanrahan, Founder, Maid 2 Clean, who shares the story behind conceptualising his brand. After realising the need, he, along with his wife developed an agency concept and not time for money business. He further says that people starting a business should understand what customers need.  His brand is a agency concept in the domestic sector. He also adds how he is planning to enter Indian market. ', 'Beny Sachdeva, Mike Hanrahan, Maid 2 Clean, Franchising, Delhi Summit 2015, Franchise India, Startup Summit ', '8:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2840, 'A', '2016-12-05 15:11:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2400, 'tDwsCFN83VM', NULL, 'Team is the most vital element for building any company ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Punita Kapoor, Franchise India introduces Ramesh Dharmaji, Chief General Manager, SIDBI, who further introduces the brand he represents., Shreevats Jaipuria, Vice Chairman, Seth MR, Jaipuria Schools, talks about the challenges, transformation and ideation that a startup goes through and how Jaipuria School being a startup existed among the big players in the education ecosystem. Rahul Khanna, Managing Partner, Trifecta Capital, Siddhant Rana, Head Business Development, Exclusively.com along with Manav Sethi, Group CMO & Head Digital Strategy, Askme and Alok Mittal, Ce- Founder & CEO, Indifi Technologies Pvt. Ltd talk about how marketing and strategy planning helps a startup to get in the big league. The panel also talks about do investors play a role in bringing teams together. As per them, team is a very important aspect for building a company. ', 'Ramesh Dharmaji, SIDBI, Shreevats Jaipuria, Jaipuria Schools, Rahul Khanna, Manav Sethi, Askme, Alok Mittal, Startups, Franchising, Delhi Summit 2015, Franchise India, Startup Summit ', '21:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4499, 'A', '2016-12-05 15:13:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2401, 'CpElyddGarI', NULL, 'Master Franchise builds the foundation of running a business', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Sana Chopra, Executive Director, Carls Jr. Restaurants LLC, through her presentation talks about the master franchise and what role it plays in building a web for any business. She explains that a Franchisor can give a master franchise, which further has three choices to expand. These options include regular franchise, multi unit franchises and areas to develop. She also talks about the difference between a franchise and a master franchise. ', 'Sana Chopra, Carlâ€™s Jr. Restaurants LLC, Carlâ€™s Jr, Franchisor, Franchise, Master Franchise, Delhi Summit 2015, Franchise India, Startup Summit', '26:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2702, 'A', '2016-12-05 15:16:26', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2402, 'sv2yF5M0gQc', NULL, 'micro, small and medium enterprises can encourage entrepreneurship  ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Shri Kalraj Mishra, Honble Union Minister, Ministry of Micro, Small & Medium Enterprises talks about how Franchise India through its events is giving a chance to budding entrepreneurs to undertake franchises of brands. According to him micro, small and medium enterprises can be a way to increase manufacturing in a big way and can be a gateway to increase entrepreneurship in India. ', 'Shri Kalraj Mishra, Micro, Small & Medium Enterprises, Franchise, Entrepreneurship, Delhi Summit 2015, Franchise India, Startup Summit', '17:08', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2426, 'A', '2016-12-05 15:18:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2403, '3aCBVAmVoz4', NULL, 'Credibility of the parties involved in important while signing a franchise agreement ', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Safir Anand, Partner, Anand and Anand, talks about the various steps that either a Franchise or a franchisor has to undertake after narrowing down a business. According to him, partner search is a key aspect that should be considered along with other elements. He shares that it is the credibility of the parties involved in a dealing that differentiates between a good and bad business. He further shares the constituents of an agreement along with Swapnadip Ghosh Mazumdar, General Manager-Merchandising & Licesnsing Business at Universal Music Group and Chris Evans, Managing Director, Oxford Ltd. ', 'Safir Anand, Anand and Anand, Swapnadip Ghosh Mazumdar, Universal Music Group, Chris Evans, Brand Licensing, Delhi Summit 2015, Franchise India, Brand Licensing India ', '14:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3260, 'A', '2016-12-05 15:21:24', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2404, '23bvBPL1mWw', NULL, 'We have Pepperfry studios where customers can see and feel the product', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Ambreesh Murthy, Co Founder, Pepperfry.com, talks about his company and says he believed in 3 fundamental tenets while starting the company, which were solidly Indian company, being an honest and fun loving company. He further talks about his target audience and other aspects. ', 'Ambreesh Murthy, Pepperfry.com, Online furniture, Interior Decoration, Franchise India, Indian Retail Congress 2016 ', '4:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2515, 'A', '2016-12-08 02:01:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2405, 'bSAX-obmqIQ', NULL, '\\\"100% FDI in food marketing: a progressive step ahead\\\"', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Krish iyer, President and CEO, Walmart India, talks about 100% FDI in food marketing being a positive step forward. He further talks about the food sector trends in the modern retail and other topics.  He says, going forward, more retailers need to focus on food safety. ', 'Krish iyer, Walmart India, Union Budget 2016, FDI, Franchise India, Indian Retail Congress 2016 ', '2:58', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 8, 2644, 'A', '2016-12-08 12:06:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2406, 'xUvU5tBsT6o', NULL, '\\\"We want to expand Being Human at a Global Scale\\\"', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Manish Mandhana, Joint Managing Director, Mandhana Industries Limited & Being Human, spoke about the group and its various attributes. He further talks about Being Human as a brand, with its product extension. He is all set to have an international expansion. ', 'Manish mandhana, Mandhana Industries Limited, Being Human, Clothing, Accessories, Indian Retail Congress 2016, Franchise India', '3:29', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1641, 'A', '2016-12-08 12:05:46', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2407, '0lMcehRsjzU', NULL, '\"People today are more exposed and receptive to International brands\"', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Rajesh Jain, MD and CEO, Lacoste, India, Sports and Leisure Apparel Limited starts talking about the brands journey in India. He further said that it is word of mouth, products and stores that play a significant role in attractive a customer. ', 'Rajesh Jain, Lacoste India, Apparels, Clothing, Accessories, Indian Retail Congress 2016, Franchise India', '4:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2742, 'A', '2016-12-08 12:20:21', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2408, 'l9P8l3pyG3o', NULL, '\"Mobile and Internet are the medium to target Tier II and III cities\"', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'Rakesh kapoor, Co-founder and CEO, Process9, give an introduction to the brand and its mission and process. He further says that brands today are using internet and mobile phones in order to reach its customers in Tier II and III cities. ', 'Rakesh kapoor, Process9, Software, Indian Retail Congress 2016, Franchise India', '3:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2184, 'A', '2016-12-08 12:24:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2409, 'y6A41CY4zC0', NULL, '\\\"Food products should be sourced locally and not be exported\\\"', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, 'RS Sodhi, Managing Director, Gujarat Cooperative Milk Marketing Federation (GCMMF), talks about FDI with reference to food marketing. He also spoke about the latest trends in food retail in India and shared that food marketing is growing at a tremendous pace.   ', 'RS Sodhi, GCMMF, Amul India, Indian Retail Congress 2016, Franchise India', '3:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2847, 'A', '2016-12-08 12:26:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2410, 'KD1WS113kh8', NULL, '\\\"Trends today are becoming global because of ever growing social media\\\"', 5, '', NULL, '', 27, ': Sumit Dhingra, Chief Operating Officer, Gant, Nautica & Aeropostale (India) feels what is important for any brand is to understand the need of the consumer and fulfilling it. When it comes to competition, whether the brand is international or not, it will increase. He feels more the competition, more you have to work hard to deliver excellence to the consumers. He further shares his brands expansion plans.', 'Sumit Dhingra, Nautica, Gant, Aeropostale India, Apparel Brands, Clothing, Indian Retail Congress 2016, Franchise India', '3:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2159, 'A', '2016-12-08 12:28:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2411, 'L_mu6q-L5QA', NULL, 'Todays Wellness Industry is all about Diversity   ', 9, '', NULL, '', 44, 'Mr Kabir Bedi, Actor and Kavya introduce the Salon Show 2016 and offer an appreciation for the sponsors of the event. Following this Ms Ritu Marya, Editor in Chief, Franchise India talks about the beauty and wellness industry. According to her, the beauty industry is giving a potential platform for the stylists to turn into icons for the salons.  She further explains that there is a huge amount of cross learning and diversity happening in the industry today. This followed the award giving ceremony under various categories. ', 'Kabir Bedi, Bollywood Actor, Ritu Marya, Franchise India, Wellness Industry, Salon Show 2016, Salon Business ', '13:54', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4819, 'A', '2016-12-15 13:24:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2412, 'h3JdLqRFGcI', NULL, 'Three things to follow while starting at the young age', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Neel Ghose, Founder, Robin Hood Army and also the Vice President of International Operations at Zomato talked about the core things that the young age entrepreneurs should follow while starting in the early age. He also emphasized upon execution, hands-on on the field and get your hands dirty to know the feasibility of an idea among other things.   ', 'Young age entrepreneurs, starting from the scratch, three things to follow.', '1:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2327, 'A', '2016-12-16 12:11:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2414, 'vN9m3F0uGic', NULL, '\\\"We will have 20 world class universities in India with full autonomy\\\"', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'As per Mr Prakash Javadekar, Union Minister for HRD, GOI, sustainable process for any country is possible if it has good research and innovation driven universities. He further shares four ways to achieve sustainable prosperity, which were and can be practiced.  Stating that India has good universities, he expressed the desire of having 20 world class universities, 10 in private and 10 in public sectors with full autonomy. The minister also spoke about Governments initiative like Uchchatar Avishkar Yojana, IMPRINT India and Higher Education Finance Agency (HEFA). ', 'Prakash Javadekar, HRD, FICCI, FICCI Higher Education Summit 2016, Uchchatar Avishkar Yojana, IMPRINT India and Higher Education Finance Agency (HEFA)', '15:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4809, 'A', '2016-12-16 12:27:19', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2415, 'fmLi9deidik', NULL, 'How can India be a preferred destination for higher education', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Sunil Kant Munjal, Chairman, Hero Corporate Services says the ability to multitask can only be witnessed in India and nowhere else. According to Prof Ashish Nanda, Director, IIM Ahmedabad, India as a country is very good at offering professional services in tourism, education and healthcare. He further added that India should not favour many policies and should allow educational institutions in all different sectors to experiment. Francisco Marmolejo, Higher Education coordinator, The World Bank, says there are two elements that work for India, which is strengthening higher education, pairing it with accountability. Maintaining regulations and learning for others success and failure is also very important.  According to Subhash Ghai, Filmmaker and Founder, Whistling Woods International Ltd, Indians are great learners and Indias best quality is to face crisis, another quality is that an Indian can work anywhere in the world. Indians master the art to unlearn, learn and relearn. Indian Education policy needs to be altered. Also emphasis should be given to the teachers development program.   ', 'FICCI, FICCI Higher Education Summit 2016, Sunil Kant Munjal, Hero Corporate Services, Ashish Nanda, IIM, Indian Institute of Management, Francisco Marmolejo, The World Bank, Subhash Ghai, Whistling Woods International Ltd', '8:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 5827, 'A', '2016-12-16 12:29:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2416, 'OiNFvV0oXso', NULL, 'Today there is lot of scope of upward mobility ', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Mr Suchindra Kumar, Director, Advisory Services, EY, through his presentation talks the about future of jobs and its imperatives on Indian Higher Education. Dr Rajesh Tandon, Founder President, PRIA, UNESCO Co &quot; Chair, gives his suggestions on the perspective models for higher education. According to him, the purpose of higher education is not just learning to do, but learning to be. Ms Takyiwaa Manuh, Director, Social Development Policy Division, UNECA, Ethiopia shares her experience as a university professor and the importance of higher education. She further talks about ECA and its responsibilities. Prof Anat Rafaeli, Director, Technion International, Israels Institute of Technology introduces herself and further gives a statistics of number of students and institutes in Israel. She speaks on Learn from the world, Learn for India. She talks about the changing culture in education with the introduction of laptops, tablets and technology. As per her, teachers should educate pupils to learn and think. Mr Yudhister Bahl, Sr Vice President, New Business Ventures & Operations, Laureate Education India, talks about how Laureate is contributing in the evolving models of the education sector. According to him higher education should focus of leadership, communication skills, empathy and ethics. He talks about LPA (Laureate Professional Assessment) and explains it in detail. ', 'Suchindra Kumar, Dr Rajesh Tandon, UNESCO Co, Takyiwaa Manuh, UNECA, Prof Anat Rafaeli, Israelâ€™s Institute of Technology, Yudhister Bahl, Laureate Education India, FICCI, FICCI Higher Education Summit 2016', '31:17', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 6147, 'A', '2016-12-16 12:31:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2417, 'nkXd5xChKas', NULL, 'Indian-American venture capitalist Kanwal Rekhi calls Flipkart a foolish startup ', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'In a chat with Entrepreneur, Rekhi said the likes of Flipkart and Ola who want the Indian government to set a fair pricing to protect them from international competitors in the domestic marketplace are trying to give away their freedoms and become China.  ', 'Flipkart, Kanwal Rekhi, Venture Capitalist, Indian startups, eCommerce startups, Amazon, Snapdeal, Sachin Bansal, Binny Bansal, VCs, India\\r\\n\\r\\n', '4:45', 'V', NULL, 'en', 5, 5, 25, 2072, 'A', '2016-12-29 17:28:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2418, '-TslUaWNPaE', NULL, '\\\"Brands like Saravana Bhavan and Paradise Biryani can be Global icons\\\"', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India introduces Niren Chaudhary, President, Global KFC, referring him as the Godfather of food & restaurant industry. Niren credits Bangaluru as the first choice for Yum Brands to open their restaurants, whether it was KFC on Brigade road or Pizza Hut on Prestige road. He further shares his experience of savouring the famous thali of Saravana Bhavan in Chennai and Paradise Biryani in Bangaluru. Niren shares his own perspective and expertise on building businesses and that leaders should always look to create share hold of value and community impact, making the world a better place. Last, but not the least, Niren entertains the audiences by singing some of his favourite songs.', 'Niren Chaudhary, KFC, Pizza Hut, Taco Bell, Ritu Marya, Franchise India, Restaurant Congress 2016, Saravana Bhawan, Paradise Biryani, Restaurant Awards', '1:04:22', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4464, 'A', '2017-01-12 17:21:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2419, 'uKtH7KqtoRg', NULL, '\\\'Building brand out of comfort area by Masterchef Sanjeev Kapoor', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Masterchef Sanjeev Kapoor is the only chef in the world to have his own channel - FoodFood. He has been conferred the Best Chef of India\\\' award by the Government of India and has represented India in the World Association of Chefs\\\' Societies (WACS) in South Korea introducing ancient Indian way of Ayurvedic cooking. Speaking at RestaurantIndia 2016 Bengaluru, he shares about Building brand out of comfort area.\\r\\n', 'Sanjeev Kapoor, Restaurant India 2016, Food Business, Building Brand', '10:51', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2228, 'A', '2017-01-13 12:09:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2420, 'f1XB7NNWoPg', NULL, '\\\'How Bengaluru has grown as a food market\\\' by Chander Baljee', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Chander K. Baljee is the Chairman & Managing Director of Royal Orchid Hotels Limited, a widely held Public Limited Company which is presently operating 30 hotels, across India and East Africa. Addressing the audience at Restaurant India 2016 he shares his view on How Bengaluru has evolved as food market.\\r\\n \\r\\n', 'Royal Orchid Hotels, Chander K Baljee, Restaurant India 2016, Food Business', '12:23', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2859, 'A', '2017-01-13 12:13:44', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2421, '2CV4m1kvvec', NULL, 'An Entrepreneur should be ready to face challenges', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Subhendu Roy, Partner, A T Kearney India introduces himself and talks about the macro and micro trendsthat consumers need to be aware of and how a brand can decide whether it isbetter to go after a huge market where things are more competitive than a niche market. Dhruva Chandrie, Chief Operating Officer, Shop CJ says passion and how long can an entrepreneur stay focused are very important for a brand to build. Kuppulakshmi, Evangelist, Zoho Corporation talks about the entrepreneur sweet spot and introduces the brand. She further talks about how applications improve business solutions to set things in the right tone. Mahendra Sureka, Director, MACJ Buyer\\\'s Choice through his presentation talks about the entrepreneur sweet spot and introduces his brand. ', 'Subhendu Roy, A T Kearney India, Dhruva Chandrie, Shop CJ, Kuppulakshmi, Zoho Corporation, Mahendra Sureka, MACJ Buyer\\\'s Choice, Franchise India, Growth Summit, Franchise India 2016', '14:39', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4781, 'A', '2017-01-18 12:08:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2422, '_plQEpE45Wk', NULL, 'Building a brand is what excites the Entrepreneurs ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Anurag Mathur, Partner- Consumer & Retail Sector, PwC India says that every entrepreneur feel excited when he/she wants to build a brand. He further says that the brand value of 25 top brands in the world is equal to Indias GDP and specifies what it takes for a brand to build. Mahesh Mac Srinivasan, Country Head, BNI India talks about points for a brand to build, which includes powerful story, what the brand is doing today and vision. He further says that his brand follows VCP which is visibility, credibility and pitching. SanjayCoutinho, CEO, Baskin Robbins, gives an insight of Baskin Robbins and shares the statistics of the consumption rate among the consumers. The panel further discusses about India being a vast market and observes the international food market is built on marketing and packaging. They discuss on how brands can place themselves in the market.  ', 'Anurag Mathur, PwC, Mahesh Mac Srinivasan, Sanjay Coutinho, Baskin Robbins, Franchise India, Growth Summit, Franchise India 2016', '26:06', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3582, 'A', '2017-01-18 12:10:03', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2423, 'guVem4y0lYI', NULL, '\\\"Small Business is the heart of every country\\\"', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'Ms Ritu Marya, Editor in Chief, Franchise India welcomes the delegates and guests and further discusses about the initiatives like Made in India and Startup India and how it has become game changing and would really boost many ideas to be executed in the market. It will on a wider scale give equal opportunity to every Indian to become an entrepreneur. She further says that the show is all about opportunity.  ', 'Made in India, Start up India, Small and Medium Enterprises, Franchise India, Growth Summit, Franchise India 2016, Ritu Marya, Franchising', '10:56', 'V', NULL, 'en', 2, 2, 10, 2755, 'A', '2017-01-18 12:13:32', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2424, 'NHB7kIjCvW0', NULL, '\\\"At the end of the day its all about human excellence\\\"', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Ms Ritu Marya, Editor in Chief, Franchise India introduces Abhinav Bindra, OlympicsGold Medallist, Ace Shooter (Brand Ambassador Franchise India) and opens up by knowing about how Abhinav was introduced to shooting and what was it to win a gold medal for the country. Apart from sharing his successful story, Abhinav also said that an athlete looses more than wins and dealing with defeat is a tough phase, but at times winning is also a tough process. He also mentioned that though shooting is a private game played in public, winning the Olympics was a team effort. ', 'Startup Summit, Abhinav Bindta, Olympics Gold Medallist, Ace Shooter, Entrepreneur,Shooting Star Sports Llp, Franchise India 2016, Ritu Marya, Franchising', '18:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2867, 'A', '2017-01-20 15:13:49', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2425, 'WhGFFBqgkNU', NULL, '\\\"Luxury of poverty will make an entrepreneur more powerful\\\"', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Dr. A Velumani, PhD, Managing Director, Thyrocare introduces himself and talks about his journey over the years. He further says that a normal person will get the silver and the challenger will always get the gold that shows, a challenger can get anything in life. He also emphasised on the fact that in failure, no one bothers and when a person is successful, everyone wants to get associated. According to him, business means having low resources, yet you succeed.  He says being in comfort zone is a downfall and being in the danger zone is always a way to go up. He gives example from his life journey that every entrepreneur should follow. ', 'Dr. A Velumani, Thyrocare, Entrepreneurship, Franchise India 2016, Franchising', '25:09', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4578, 'A', '2017-01-20 15:18:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2426, 'aBWPvfjD-iw', NULL, '\\\"Motivation and knowledge helps institutes gain students\\\"', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Terry Watts, International Director, Active Learning, City of Oxford College, UK, introduces his brand and talks about the experience of venturing in India as a startupbeing a part of international market expansion. He further talks about how flexibility is very important for any company. He explains that his companylikes to work with beginners and change their life through learning. Terry says every institute should make sure that its courses are providing the right knowledge and motivation to its students, which will further win them more students. Wilson Lim ED, International Business & China, Pastamania, Singapore, introduces himself and describes about Pastamania in detail through a presentation. ', 'Terry Watts, Active Learning, Oxford College, United Kingdom, Wilson Lim ED, Pastamania, Franchise India 2016, Franchising, Entrepreneurship ', '26:34', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3705, 'A', '2017-01-20 15:24:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2427, '_m_FgZFDIEM', NULL, '\\\"Positive attitude and discipline helps establishing a business\\\"', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'Bill Redfern, Global CEO, MACJ Buyer\\\'s Choice introduces his brand and talks about because of global franchise opportunities, his company had reasonable amount of success in small home type businesses. He further says that his company promotes master franchises.  He also shares that with positive attitude and correct discipline, an entrepreneur can successfully run his/her business. Further, he talks about entrepreneurship in India. Parag Shah, Founder Director, MIDAS India, shares his experiences in life and what he thinks are important points for an entrepreneur to be successful. He feel whether it is a startup or a seasonal entrepreneur, he/she has to keep three things in mind, which are 3Cs (creativity, critical thinking, communication), trust and integrity. He says its important that the focus of a first generation entrepreneur should be to break even.  ', 'Bill Redfern, Parag Shah, MIDAS India, MACJ Buyer\\\'s Choice, Entrepreneur, Franchise India 2016, , Franchising', '17:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 4316, 'A', '2017-01-20 15:28:05', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2428, 'MpFjpTA2ofg', NULL, '\\\"An independent reader can become an independent learner\\\"', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Chan Huang Yee, Executive Director, I Can Read, talks about the company by the means of a presentation. She gives an insight to the number of students, number of centres, and the quality that they consistently follow. She further talks about the history of the company. Kenneth Wrong, CEO & Founder, Mycropore Corporation Ltd & CTO & Founder, H2O Life Source Group gives some factual insights and then talks about his company and what it does.  ', 'Chan Huang Yee, I Can Read, Education, Kenneth Wrong, Mycropore Corporation Ltd, H2O Life Source Group, Franchise India 2016, Franchising, Entrepreneurship', '34:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3714, 'A', '2017-01-20 15:33:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2429, 'euGQ6RX8EuI', NULL, 'License is an opportunity for a brand to leverage itself further ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Gargi Bhardwaj, Franchise India, gives an introduction to brand licensing and its importance among the retail eco system.  Samir Jain, COO, Green Gold Animation shares that for a brand it is very essential to reach out to its potential customers, so licensing offers a perfect opportunity for a brand owner have access to the expertise of his/her licensee in their particular category. Atulit Saxena, President - Brands at Futurebrands Ltd adds that brand licensing has really come up in a big way. He also said that consumers today are enjoying the ecommerce industry, whether it is online, offline or omni-channel. He further talks about brand licensing. Anupam Bharat, Director, Usha Shriram said licensing gives an opportunity for a brand to leverage itself and gain its ticket size.  The panelists also speak about future of Indian retail with brand licensing. ', 'Samir Jain, Green Gold Animation, Atulit Saxena, Anupam Bharat, Usha Shriram, Franchise India2016, Franchising, Entrepreneurship', '45:31', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3817, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:07:17', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2430, 'OnPnf37lpF8', NULL, '\\\"India is the biggest bicycle polo player country in the world\\\"', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Ms Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India introduces Kanwar Raghuvendra Singh Dundlod, President, Cycle Polo Federation of India and discusses about cycle polo indetail. Kanwar Raghuvendra Singh Dundlod talks about the rich history of the sport and its reach, scope and fan following in India. He also talks about licensing of cycle polo and how it is becoming bigger by everyday. ', 'Ritu Marya, Kanwar Raghuvendra Singh Dundlod, Cycle Polo Federation of India, Cycle Polo, Franchise India 2016, Franchising, Entrepreneurship', '11:00', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3135, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:10:42', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2431, 'C5bAaEERr3w', NULL, 'Brand licensing is an important element with various genres ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Gargi Bhardwaj, Franchise India, discusses about various genres of brand licensing and further discusses with Prasad Kapre, CEO & Director, Style Quotient Jewellery Pvt. Ltd about how he as a retailer is motivated towards brand licensing for jewellery. As per Prasad Kapre, brand licensing in jewellery segment is very new and says that jewellery has become a very essential part of every film.Vishal Y Sinha, Business Head, Sanjeev Kapoor Brand spoke about how his brand, being unique, understood and tapped the potential of brand licensing. Alok Kamat, Founder & Chairman, Aero Pharma Grou also spoke on why his brandtapped the brand licensing sector. According to the panelists, it was the need of the consumers, which motivated the brands to take up brand licensing. ', 'Prasad Kapre, Style Quotient Jewellery Pvt. Ltd, Prasad Kapre, Vishal Y Sinha, Sanjeev Kapoor Brand, Alok Kamat, Aero Pharma Grou, Franchise India 2016, Franchising, Entrepreneurship', '36:21', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3188, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:12:36', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2432, 'DqijRJOxmWA', NULL, 'Brand Licensing: A trump card for retailers ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Gargi Bhardwaj, Franchise India, says as retailer are adopting to brand licensing on a facepace, what actually motivated Myntra as a brand to adopt to brand licensing. Abhijeet Dabas, Senior VP- Brand Director, Myntra, talks about the problems in brandlicensing and how Myntra took on brand licensing to enhance its business. ', 'Abhijeet Dabas, Myntra, Franchise India 2016, Franchising, Entrepreneurship', '15:07', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2494, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:14:07', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2433, 'mniuatBIE6E', NULL, 'Understand Internet Protocol and its benefits        ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Nikhil Jalan , Head-Legal, Bradford License India starts the session by asking Gaurav Miglani, Knowledge Partner, Head of IP - Lex Chambers about what is IP and how it works. According to Gaurav, IP has many components, giving away the list, he also spoke about how retails are making use of IP technology. He further talks about copyright and its 5 extended branches. ', 'Nikhil Jalan, Bradford License India, Gaurav Miglani, Lex Chambers, Franchise India 2016,Franchising, Entrepreneurship', '11:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1748, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:15:56', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2434, 'chb6CXiKtkc', NULL, 'Brand today really fancy the idea of promotional licensing ', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Gargi Bhardwaj, Franchise India, introduces the panelists and talks about how to improve effectiveness of licensing programs for the brand to make a sturdy position. Anand Singh, Director - South Asia, Turner International says while licensing, things to keep in mind are whether youre building a brand or building franchises. Job Van Dijk, Chief Commercial Officer, Tempting Brands AG - Route 66 talks about the brand and how it approached the brand license sector. The panelists further talk about the benefits of promotional licensing for brands. ', 'Anand Singh, Turner International, Job Van Dijk, Route 66, Franchise India 2016, Franchising, Entrepreneurship', '33:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2794, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:18:16', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2435, 'm-pHYAuCEqk', NULL, '\\\"Today people want food, beverage and entertainment\\\"', 5, '', NULL, '', 26, 'Gargi Bhardwaj, Franchise India, discusses with Ashish Gupta, Country Manager - India/ Sri Lanka/ Bangladesh, Gameloft about gaming coming a long way forward, from manual consoles to smartphones and also asked Ashish on how licensing has benefited the gaming industry. Viraj Lamba, Director, Funbars (FLYP@MTV), spoke about the benefits that brand licensing has offered in enhancing his caf. Viraj further spoke about how people are becoming inclined towards having good food, beverage and entertainment. ', 'Ashish Gupta, Gameloft, Viraj Lamba, Funbars (FLYP@MTV), Franchise India 2016, Franchising, Entrepreneurship', '20:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3655, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:23:58', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2436, 'hOF8X7LwbTg', NULL, 'Keeping the Spirit Going', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India introduces the panellists- Reynold Fernandez, CEO-Oriental Cuisines, Mihir Desai, Co-Founder- The Bar Stock Exchange and Vipin Sachdev, MD- Tuscana Kryptos restaurant, sharing her views on how restaurant industry is growing over the past years. Mrs. Marya asks panellists to share their views on How can restaurant focus on a continuous growth focusing on important aspects that keep the spirit going for the business operators.', 'Restaurant India 2016, Food Business, Restaurant Industry, Franchising ', '07:30', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2235, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:43:25', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2437, 'WXt3CFz-tS8', NULL, 'Drawing the Market Plan', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India introduces the panellists- Reynold Fernandez, CEO-Oriental Cuisines, Mihir Desai, Co-Founder- The Bar Stock Exchange and Vipin Sachdev, MD- Tuscana Kryptos restaurant, sharing her views on how restaurant industry is growing over the past years. Mrs. Marya asks panellists to share their views on How can restaurant focus on a continuous growth focusing on important aspects that keep the spirit going for the business operators.', 'Restaurant India 2016, Food Business, Restaurant Industry, Franchising ', '06:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2497, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:45:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2438, 'sjyODwQHRE8', NULL, 'Learn & Unlearn the art of biz ', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India introduces the panellists- Reynold Fernandez, CEO-Oriental Cuisines, Mihir Desai, Co-Founder- The Bar Stock Exchange and Vipin Sachdev, MD- Tuscana Kryptos restaurant, sharing her views on how restaurant industry is growing over the past years. Mrs. Marya asks panellists to share their views on How can restaurant focus on a continuous growth focusing on important aspects that keep the spirit going for the business operators.', 'Restaurant India 2016, Food Business, Restaurant Industry, Franchising ', '02:55', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3011, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:48:43', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2439, 'NIB5uyMKNG8', NULL, 'Growth of South Indian market ', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India introduces the panellists- Reynold Fernandez, CEO-Oriental Cuisines, Mihir Desai, Co-Founder- The Bar Stock Exchange and Vipin Sachdev, MD- Tuscana Kryptos restaurant, sharing her views on how restaurant industry is growing over the past years. Mrs. Marya asks panellists to share their views on How can restaurant focus on a continuous growth focusing on important aspects that keep the spirit going for the business operators.', 'Restaurant India 2016, Food Business, Restaurant Industry, Franchising ', '05:12', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 4, 2193, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:53:23', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2440, '_MRljwXre1s', NULL, 'Overcoming Hesitations ', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Ritu Marya, Editor-in-Chief, Franchise India introduces the panellists- Reynold Fernandez, CEO-Oriental Cuisines, Mihir Desai, Co-Founder- The Bar Stock Exchange and Vipin Sachdev, MD- Tuscana Kryptos restaurant, sharing her views on how restaurant industry is growing over the past years. Mrs. Marya asks panellists to share their views on How can restaurant focus on a continuous growth focusing on important aspects that keep the spirit going for the business operators.', 'Restaurant India 2016, Food Business, Restaurant Industry, Franchising \\r\\n\\r\\n', '11:04', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2706, 'A', '2017-02-03 15:57:54', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2441, '7NKjH7Uzve4', NULL, 'Entrepreneur India Shepreneurs 2017 \\\'Making of the Cover \\\'', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Women today have learnt to align passion and power with a higher purpose. How are women, across industries and generations, redefining pathways to power to drive meaningful change in their businesses, in their personal lives and within the communities around them? Entrepreneurs annual compendium of the women who are on the verge of creating the next wave in entrepreneurship reveals how they will transform the Indian landscape. ', '#Shepreneurs  #WomenToWatch  #WomenEntrepreneurs  #PowerWomen #AnushkaSharma  #RadhikaMukherji #JwalaGutta #SanjjanaaGalrani #ShrutiShibulal', '0.38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2626, 'A', '2017-03-02 15:49:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2442, 'm8FsHnRZEjU', NULL, 'Estate Awards 2017 (ET NOW Episode)', 3, '', NULL, '', 18, 'After 8 prestigious Editions, Franchise India in media partnership with ET NOW proudly presented Asias Biggest Estate Summit- 9th Estate Awards on 28th January at Hotel Pullman New Delhi Aerocity. There were Indeed Marvellous Group of People, Individuals, Teams And Brands Behind Every Mega Structure And Beautiful Habitat Being Developed To Make The World A Better Place To Co-Exist. And To Honour Those Supremely Talented People, We Bring To You The 9th Estate Awards 2017, Where This Year\\\'s Line-Up saw The Stalwarts And Emerging Names On The Podium Rubbing Shoulders With Fame. Each year Awards attracted around 300 industry members including Developers, Builders and Real Estate professionals from various industry sectors such as law, finance, construction, development, brokerage and appraisal. The platform offers a great opportunity for delegates to not only gain new insights about what the future holds for Real Estate, in the region and beyond , but also, to build new relationships and seek new opportunities in the Real Estate industry. This year along with Estate Awards, Hotel & Resorts Award and Design & Architect awards also got introduced which got the overwhelming response from the respective industry despite being an inaugural edition.\\r\\n', 'Estate Awards, Hotel & Resort Awards, Design & Architect Awards, Maggpie, ET Now Episode, Estate Industry Awards, Estate Fraternity, B2B Awards, Franchise India Estate, Home & Residential Awards, Commercial & Retail Awards', '23:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 7674, 'A', '2017-03-03 16:21:39', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2443, 'CxxBhI12ZrY', NULL, 'Indian Education Congress & Awards 2017 Promo on Times Now', 8, '', NULL, '', 38, 'Indian Education Congress 2017, Indias biggest  thought leadership platform on Education industry was held on February 7-8, 2017. Organized by Franchise India to showcase a product or service in the education space, suppliers and allied industries. This national event was a grand success with over 400 successful educationists, school & college principals, manufacturers, industry veterans, key suppliers, consultants and individuals belonging to the Education category attended the event from across the country. The conference talked about all aspects of Education sector in India and provided a direct B2B engagement to many Indian leading educationists and an understanding around how they are re-writing and implementing new retail practices over traditional ones.\\r\\n\\r\\nAlong with the Congress, Annual Indian Education Awards 2017 were also took place. The Awards are considered to be one of the most prestigious awards that recognize Excellence in Performance in Education space. The award ceremony was aimed at felicitating people who have contributed towards the growth of Education Industry in India. From Achievers, Innovators to Suppliers, the awards applauded their efforts in making the Education presence felt in this increasingly competitive world.\\r\\n\\r\\n', 'Indian Education Congress 2017, Indian Education Awards 2017, Times Now, Indian Education Congress Promo, Education Convention, Education Industry conference, Indian Education exhibition, Times Now Promo, Business Conference, Education Summit\\r\\n\\r\\n', '0.50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 7176, 'A', '2017-03-03 16:25:02', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2444, 'v0rdZfIa5ug', NULL, '\\\'Innovating into New Markets\\\' by Karan Tanna', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Karan Tanna is the Founder & CEO at Yellow Tie Hospitality Management LLP that plans to introduce and expand various global companies in the country. Talking at Restaurant India 2016, Bengaluru, he shares what it takes to design the business structure for Indian market & looking over business operations of the company.', 'Restaurant Franchise, Restaurant India 2016, Genuine Broaster Chicken, Food Franchise', '20:42', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 3334, 'A', '2017-03-09 11:16:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2445, 'nVwnHcgj3i0', NULL, 'Why \\\'Franchise\\\' by David Griffith', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'David Griffith is the Founder and CEO of Habanero Foods International. Speaking at Restaurant India 2016, Bengaluru, he talks  Why one should franchise and how is franchising helping him grow his businesses.  ', 'Restaurant Franchise, Restaurant India 2016, Subway, Food Franchise', '8:13', 'V', NULL, 'en', 1, 1, 5, 2986, 'A', '2017-03-09 11:19:15', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0);
