(2507, '1SFPfDhGsNw', NULL, 'Execution is everything Passion, People and Profits', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'BusinessEx.com presents Entrepreneur India Congress 2017 was held on 18-19th July, 2017 at JW Marriot Hotel, Aerocity, New Delhi. The event was the host to a large number of brainstorming sessions, panel discussions and key note presentations on Entrepreneurship and related issues. Mr. Sanjay Sethi, Co-founder & CEO, ShopClues.com; shares his ideas on the importance of execution. He also shares the invaluable sequence of entrepreneurial success; Passion, People and Profits', 'BusinessEx.com, Entrepreneur India Congress 2017, BusinessEx, Entrepreneur India, Franchise India,  Sanjay Sethi, ShopClues.com, importance of execution, how to execute a business, execution tips, passion people and profits.', '9:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1687, 'A', '2017-08-11 17:02:30', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2508, 'RCad_95vXmE', NULL, 'Growth Summit Panel: Family is Everything', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'BusinessEx.com presents Entrepreneur India Congress 2017 was held on 18-19th July, 2017 at JW Marriot Hotel, Aerocity, New Delhi. The event was the host to a large number of brainstorming sessions, panel discussions and key note presentations on Entrepreneurship and related issues. A successful multi-generational business requires more than just managerial skills. Entrepreneurs in family businesses have added value and amassed wealth by having long-term vision. The Family Business Entrepreneurs will speak about how their values influence their everyday business - from managing a business, to creatively financing, and empowering their employees to think like owners. This panel will not just focus on building a family enterprise but will highlight what it takes to build long-term sustainable value. In the panel we have, Mr. Viraj Kalyani, Founder and Chairman, Kalyani Studio, Mr. Varun Chaudhary ,Executive Director, CG Corp Global; Manasi Kirloskar, Executive Director, Kirloskar Systems Ltd, Managing Trustee/CEO of Caring with Colour.', 'BusinessEx.com, Entrepreneur India Congress 2017, BusinessEx, Entrepreneur India, Franchise India, Viraj Kalyani, Kalyani Studio, Varun Chaudhary, CG Corp Global, Manasi Kirloskar, Kirloskar Systems Ltd, Caring with Colour', '55:33', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1823, 'A', '2017-08-11 17:06:13', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2509, 't6VeQNoiVE0', NULL, 'My business, New day, New way', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'BusinessEx.com presents Entrepreneur India Congress 2017 was held on 18-19th July, 2017 at JW Marriot Hotel, Aerocity, New Delhi. The event was the host to a large number of brainstorming sessions, panel discussions and key note presentations on Entrepreneurship and related issues.  Vishwas Mudagal, CEO & MD, Goodwork Labs, shares his experiences of being an Entrepreneur. A fun-to-hear story, this talk is a combination of delightful entrepreneurial thrill and priceless business wisdom.  ', 'BusinessEx.com, Entrepreneur India Congress 2017, BusinessEx, Entrepreneur India, Franchise India,  Vishwas Mudagal, Goodwork Labs, life  of an  entrepreneur, entrepreneurship tips.', '15:25', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1239, 'A', '2017-08-11 17:08:57', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2510, 'm3MlFivMWQA', NULL, 'Taxonomy of free pricing', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'BusinessEx.com presents Entrepreneur India Congress 2017 was held on 18-19th July, 2017 at JW Marriot Hotel, Aerocity, New Delhi. The event was the host to a large number of brainstorming sessions, panel discussions and key note presentations on Entrepreneurship and related issues.  Mr. Tajinder Singh Virk, Co-Founder & CEO, Finvasia, talks about the concept of Free-pricng or Zero-pricing. He starts with the basic-note telling about the discovery of zero and eloquently takes the concept to the business level.', 'BusinessEx.com, Entrepreneur India Congress 2017, BusinessEx, Entrepreneur India, Franchise India, Free-pricing, Zero priciong, how free pricing works, Tajinder Singh Virk, Finvasia\\r\\n\\r\\n', '15:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1209, 'A', '2017-08-11 17:10:48', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2511, 'jA-F3wqbrRw', NULL, 'The IPO Dilemma-Now or Never', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'BusinessEx.com presents Entrepreneur India Congress 2017 was held on 18-19th July, 2017 at JW Marriot Hotel, Aerocity, New Delhi. The event was the host to a large number of brainstorming sessions, panel discussions and key note presentations on Entrepreneurship and related issues.\\r\\n  Developing their ecosystem and engaging with investors are of paramount importance for start-ups to prosper. Collecting money from the market to fuel expansion is an evergreen way of raising funds, besides building a brand value. Mr. Satya Narayanan, Chairman and Owner, Career Launcher talks about this dilemma. He further answers the queries of the audience with emerald practicality.\\r\\n\\r\\n', 'BusinessEx.com, Entrepreneur India Congress 2017, BusinessEx, Entrepreneur India, Franchise India, Satya Narayanan, Career Launcher', '25:50', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1748, 'A', '2017-08-11 17:13:06', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2512, 'c4iXBeQRrmk', NULL, 'Entrepreneur India Awards 2017', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'BusinessEx.com presents Entrepreneur India Congress 2017 was held on 18-19th July, 2017 at JW Marriot Hotel, Aerocity, New Delhi. The event was the host to a large number of brainstorming sessions, panel discussions and key note presentations on Entrepreneurship and related issues. With providing the entrepreneurs a platform for networking and growing their business, we make sure to award the great innovators and entrepreneurs who have set high banch marks for their equally innovative successors', 'BusinessEx.com, Entrepreneur India Congress 2017, BusinessEx, Entrepreneur India, Franchise India, Entrepreneur India Awards 2017', '01:00:20', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1338, 'A', '2017-08-11 17:15:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2513, 'Vrn76EDrXfc', NULL, 'Focusing on Meta problems', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'BusinessEx.com presents Entrepreneur India Congress 2017 was held on 18-19th July, 2017 at JW Marriot Hotel, Aerocity, New Delhi. The event was the host to a large number of brainstorming sessions, panel discussions and key note presentations on Entrepreneurship and related issues. \\r\\nAbove is a key note presentation by the young and dyanamic entrepreneur Ananya Birla who is the founder, chairperson and director of Svatantra Microfinance. She talks about being an entrepreneur with a heart. The kind of entrepreneurs who make a successful high-turnover venture, but in the process make the lives of others better.\\r\\n', 'Ananya Birla,BusinessEx.com, Entrepreneur India Congress 2017, BusinessEx, Entrepreneur India, Franchise India, Svatantra Microfinance, time management', '27:05', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2007, 'A', '2017-08-11 17:16:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2514, 'WfnyVxjqQss', NULL, 'Fundraising Like a Pro ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'BusinessEx.com presents Entrepreneur India Congress 2017 was held on 18-19th July, 2017 at JW Marriot Hotel, Aerocity, New Delhi. The event was the host to a large number of brainstorming sessions, panel discussions and key note presentations on Entrepreneurship and related issues. Above is a panel discussion on one of the most important aspect of a business which is Fundraising. In the panel we have, Mr. Saurabh Arora, CEO & Founder, Lybrate; Mr. Srikumar Misra, Founder, MD & CEO, Milk Mantra; Mr. Samar Singla, CEO and Founder, Jugnoo; Mr. Sandeep Sinha, Co-founder & Managing Partner, Lumis Partners, Akshay Verma', 'BusinessEx.com, Entrepreneur India Congress 2017, BusinessEx, Entrepreneur India,  Saurabh Arora,  Lybrateâ€™ srikumar Mishra, Milk Mantra, Samar Singla, Jugnoo, Sandeep Sinha, Lumis Partners', '31:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1351, 'A', '2017-08-11 17:18:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2515, 'g95OwAUF7gc', NULL, 'Entrepreneur India August 2017 Cover Promo &quot; Behind the Scenes  ', 2, '', NULL, '', 14, 'The August Anniversary issue of Entrepreneur features the beard Chronicle in the making. Covering inspiring stories of 11 product makers which are doing great work in terms of creations. Riding high on the concepts like Make in India and Design India, these start-ups have set a great example in a tech-driven business environment. Millennials swear by their charcoal face wash. Meet the two men behind Beardo.', 'Beardo, Startup, Entrepreneur, Marico, Suniel Shetty, Ashutosh Valani, Priyank Shah \\r\\n\\r\\n', '01:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1658, 'A', '2017-08-11 17:21:20', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2516, 'V9Blhbd0UDs', NULL, '5 Secret Mantras For Entrepreneurs by Vijay Shekhar Sharma', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Vijay Shekhar Sharma feels India today is a dream come true for any tech entrepreneur. He believes it is an extraordinary time for Indians to build. His 5 cents on what every entrepreneur must do to be successful include no notifications, spending the first most productive time of the day with the internal team, shortlisting and prioritizing work, empower team and training own members than trophy hires. rn rn', 'Vijay Shekhar Sharma, VSS, Paytm, Success, Daily Routine, Entrepreneurs, Startups, Startup Life', '4:15', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 87, 'D', '2017-08-18 11:25:10', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2517, 'fMUPyB7ItDQ', NULL, 'Balancing the Interest of Franchisors, Franchisees and the System as a Whole', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'How to Create the Right Culture. The Core of the Franchise Relationship Driving unit-level economics from the Top and franchisee performance is much easier said than done. In this session, we\\\'ll explore the psychology of working with your franchise partners post sign-up and a tactical approach to help franchisees run more profitable businesses. In the panel we have, Mr. Mike Hanrahan, Managing Director, Maid2Clean; Mr. Tony White, International Franchise Specialist & Managing Director, FranGlobal (Australia); Mr. Jean Louis Poiroux, Founder & CEO, Cinq Monde Spa Paris, Mr. Sayed Habib, General Manager, Danube Homes. The panellists brainstorm about the topic and then address the queries of the audience.', 'Master Franchise Show, Franchise India, Mike Hanrahan, Maid2Clean, Tony White, FranGlobal, Jean Louis Poiroux, Cinq Monde Spa Paris, Sayed Habib, Danube Homes', '37:27', 'V', NULL, 'en', 10, 10, 50, 1848, 'A', '2017-08-18 14:43:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2518, 'Z9WE_xphc10', NULL, 'We aim to open 50 stores by 2020', 1, '', NULL, '', 11, 'In an interaction with Franchise India, Mr. Sayed habib, Danube Homes, discusses how his organisation works and why is franchising the right path for him to expand his business. Mr. Habib is a passionate & experienced international retail professional who is commercially astute, with experiences from various retail segments and product categories. A strong leader able to communicate, engage and inspire at all levels of the business.  ', 'Master Franchise Show, Franchise India, Sayed Habib, Danube Homes, FranGlobal', '08:40', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1556, 'A', '2017-08-18 14:48:40', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2519, 'whkIwN-ZPMo', NULL, 'In India, right now we have 31 cities. Our goal is to expand to 70 cities this year', 1, '', NULL, '', 11, 'In an interaction with Franchise India, Mr. Mahesh \\\'Mac\\\' Srinivasan, President, Asia Pacific & National Director, India, Sri Lanka and Singapore, BNI, throws light on how BNI works. He also explains us the way he uses Franchising to expand his business and takes it forward to say that franchising is all about Relationships.', 'Mahesh â€˜Macâ€™ Srinivasan,BNI, Master Franchise Show, Franchising, business relationships, Business Networking, FranGlobal, Franchise India', '4:57', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1554, 'A', '2017-08-18 14:53:11', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2520, 'PjFh2nonlYQ', NULL, 'Art of Business Networking', 1, '', NULL, '', 10, 'BNI (Business Network International) is a business referral organisation which aids the entrepreneurs all around the globe to connect with each other and take business decisions based on collective knowledge. Working solely on the principle of Givers Gain, BNI with its widely penetrated network, efficient support system and quality knowledge helps its members and franchisees do healthier business. Above is a presentation on BNI, followed by which Mr. Mahesh \\\'Mac\\\' Srinivasan, President, Asia Pacific & National Director, India, Sri Lanka and Singapore, BNI answers some of the pertinent questions related to business networkin and BNI.', 'Mahesh â€˜Macâ€™ Srinivasan, BNI, Master Franchise Show, Franchising, business relationships, Business Networking, FranGlobal, Franchise India, how to become BNI member, better networking', '25:49', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2065, 'A', '2017-08-18 15:03:28', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2521, 'skv4y9BXV1o', NULL, 'How Smart Cities Mission is Churning out Great Opportunities', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Dr Anne Kerr is the Global Head, Cities at the management, engineering and development consultancy Mott MacDonald that has worked on projects like Delhi Metro. Talking to Entrepreneur Media India, Kerr talks about the gaps in the existing Smart Cities project, how it can be solved and different pockets of innovation linked to it.', 'Entrepreneur, Dr Anne Kerr, Mott MacDonald, Smart Cities, Franchise India', '4:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2212, 'A', '2017-08-21 15:42:09', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2522, 'F9Bo3olHWIk', NULL, 'Setting the Scene for Restaurant Growth in East India', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Restaurant India 2017 (East Edition) was held on 22 June, 2017 at Royal Bengal Room,\\r\\nCity Centre 1, Kolkata. It was an effort by Restaurant India to bring together the dynamic food industry maestros together to a platform where they can share their ideas and trigger collective growth. Anjan Chatterjee, Founder & MD, Speciality Group of Restaurants gives a keynote address on Restaurant economics and consumer Trends in East Indian market. Followed by which, he answers a few crucial questions asked by Ms. Ritu Marya, Editor in chief, Franchise India.\\r\\n', 'Restaurant India 2017 (East Edition), Restaurant India, Indian restaurant congress, Ritu Marya, Franchise India, Anjan Chatterjee, Speciality Group of Restaurants', '57:37', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2608, 'A', '2017-08-21 15:44:33', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2523, 'x0TMj-WRqMc', NULL, 'Vijay Shekhar Sharmas 5 Secret Mantras For Entrepreneurs To Maximise Their Daily Routine', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Vijay Shekhar Sharma feels India today is a dream come true for any tech entrepreneur. He believes it is an extraordinary time for Indians to build. His 5 cents on what every entrepreneur must do to be successful include no notifications, spending the first most productive time of the day with the internal team, shortlisting and prioritizing work, empower team and training own members than trophy hires. \\r\\n \\r\\n', 'Vijay Shekhar Sharma, VSS, Paytm, Success, Daily Routine, Entrepreneurs, Startups, Startup Life, ', '4:19', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2825, 'A', '2017-08-21 15:46:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2524, 'Gl6u-cuEaSE', NULL, 'Entrepreneur - September Making of the Cover with Sanjay Dutt', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'When we thought of a man whose life has actually been one of no less than a celluloid drama we couldnt agree more on a name other than Sanjay Dutt. The aim was to unveil the rollercoaster ride of not just living a star life but a life he spent under the trauma he faced personally. The story features insights into the real life of a star who has been doing not everything right but someone who owned his mistakes. Subscribe now to know the Sanjay Dutt saga.  ', 'Sanjay dutt, entrepreneur, celebrity, #babaisback, Bhoomi, comeback', '0:48', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2249, 'A', '2017-09-05 12:38:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2525, 'oBbyhNew5i4', NULL, 'Entrepreneur Magazine Comeback Special - Making of the Cover with Yuvraj Singh', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'An entrepreneurs journey is always filled with various hurdles showing his grit to bounce back stronger each time. Yuvraj Singhs has shown the world - How to be Resilient. Entrepreneur features his journey on how he overcame major obstacles and bounced back stronger after each setback becoming an inspiration to many. Yurajs philosophy of Live|Dare|Inspire saw an extension into fashion as a natural progression. The core of the brand is rooted in his personal journey with YouWeCan &quot; an NGO he setup specifically for cancer survivors and patients. Heres what went behind the scene in our Cover shoot.  ', 'Yuvraj Singh, entrepreneur, Fashion, comeback, youwecan, sports, cricket', '0:47', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2343, 'A', '2017-09-20 15:01:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2526, 'ifWEtMQP8kU', NULL, 'Disruption Vs Distribution: Heres what Gary Vaynerchuk has to say', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Entrepreneur Indiaâ€™s editor-in-chief Ritu Marya asks Gary Vaynerchuk, founder of Vaynermedia, about how start-ups should handle distribution and disruption at Rise Conference, Hong Kong. One of the top digital influencers in the world, Vaynerchuk shares his own example of how he balanced both the aspects to build an empire worth billions. ', 'Entrepreneur India and Rise Conference, Hong Kong', '3:16', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1849, 'A', '2017-09-20 15:04:50', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2527, '1TmpePhRkVw', NULL, '#Five Tips on How Comedians can Become Entrepreneurs by Sapan Verma', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Do bad shows - you will learn a lot of things from your tanking experiences, says EICs Co-founder, Sapan Verma in conversation with Entrepreneur India.  ', 'start-up, stand-up, comedians, videos, digital videos, ad campaigns , social media, comedy sketches, East India Comedy, Sapan Verma', '3:10', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 1828, 'A', '2017-09-23 12:52:51', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2528, 'NC1VZXutpPk', NULL, 'Sapan Verma on Why Youngsters Should Follow Their Dream?', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Start young, experiment, make mistakes and learn. It better than doing a 9-5 job, says Sapan Verma, Co-founder, EIC on why youngsters should follow their dream.\\r\\n\\r\\n', 'start-up, stand-up, comedians, videos, digital videos, ad campaigns , social media, comedy sketches, East India Comedy, Sapan Verma', '1:35', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2134, 'A', '2017-09-23 12:54:35', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2529, '0QV8mdO2yns', NULL, 'Indian Restaurant Congress & Awards 2017 Episode on TIMES NOW', 7, '', NULL, '', 34, 'Indian Restaurant Congress 2017 held on 28th and 29th August at Hotel JW Marriott, New Delhi. Restaurateurs, chefs and industry leaders including Coffee Board of India CEO Mr. Srivatsa Krishna, Mr. Zorawar Kalra (Founder & MD, Massive Restaurants), Celebrity Chef Ranveer Brar, Celebrity Chef Akmal Anuar (Co-Founder & Chef, 3Fils Restaurant), Unnat Varma (MD, Pizza Hut- India Subcontinent), Ashish Kapur (Founder & Director, Moods Hospitality Pvt. Ltd.), Sameer Bhasin (CEO, Barbeque Nation) and Varun Tuli (Director, Yum Yum Cha), among others were some of the speakers at the event. The Restaurant Congress also organised a Bar & Cigar Summit and a Chai n Bun Summit on the sidelines of the two day conference.\\r\\n\\r\\nIndian Restaurant Congress also organised, Indian Restaurant Awards on 29th evening to appreciate the brands in the industry. Award honoured over 90 restaurateurs and foodpreneurs for their outstanding work and prominence by acknowledging outstanding creativity, customer service and top quality dining that is on offer throughout India. Mr. Zorawar Kalra was awarded National Restaurateur of the Year, Chef Ranveer Brar was awarded Best Chef of the Year, Mr. Priyank Sukhija of Lazeez Affaire Group was awarded Restaurant Icon of the Year to name a few.\\r\\n', 'Indian Restaurant Congress, Indian Restaurant Awards, Restaurant Convention, Restaurant Summit, Chai & Bun Summit, Bar & Cigar Summit, Times Now Episode, Zorawar Kalra, Ranveer Brar, B2B Awards, Industry Convention, Priyank Sukhija, Restaurant Fraternity, Amrita Raichand, Srivatsa Krishna, Chef Romy Gill\\r\\n\\r\\n', '22:44', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 2145, 'A', '2017-09-27 16:49:18', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2530, 'IkB5goewvvY', NULL, 'LinkedIn Co-founder Allen Blue Top Tip For an Internet Company &quot; Follow The Lean Startup Model', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Allen Blue in a conversation with Entrepreneur Indias Aashika Jain says the best description of how to start an internet company lies in a lean startup model. He believes hiring the right people from ones own network can help a company gain great scale. The social media giant that is glocalizing its operations with its collaboration with the government and private skill development organization IL&FS wants its customers to take LinkedIn into small neighbourhood. ', 'LinkedIn, LinkedIn India, Akshay Kothari, Entrepreneurs, Startups, Indian Startups, Allen Blue, IL&FS Skill Development, India, Internet Company, Social Media, Facebook, Google, Naukri.com, Skill Development, Teamlease, Monster, TimesJobs, Naukrihub, Careerjet, CareerAge, ClickJobs, Freshersworld', '05:01', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 707, 'A', '2017-10-11 17:42:34', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2531, '2a30RunxFjA', NULL, 'Pankaj Pachauris 3Cs to launch your own media startup', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'In a chat with Entrepreneur India, Senior broadcast journalist Pankaj Pachauri who launched his independent media publishing website GoNews24*7 lauded entrepreneurship in media in India but cautioned against hasty moves. Pachauri said its important for media founders to first establish credibility, invest in human capital and once their journalism becomes right, look at expansion. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe current model of media economy is collapsing all over the world because of social media. Hence, its important to be concentrate on the 3 Cs &quot; being concise, credible and co-creative, Pachauri said. \\r\\n\\r\\nCounted among the top 10 media startups in 2017, GoNews24*7 is one to watch out for. \\r\\n\\r\\n', 'Journalism, Businesses, Indian business, India, entrepreneurship, Pankaj Pachauri, broadcast journalism, Hindi journalism, Entrepreneur India, Aashika Jain, NDTV, BBC, news channel, app, journalist, media startup, media publishing', '2:41', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 830, 'A', '2017-10-29 10:22:53', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(2532, '7WO5ume1BKk', NULL, 'Mithali Rajs Top #3 Tips For Women To Lead', 2, '', NULL, '', 15, 'Mithali Dorai Raj, the first captain to lead India to an ICC ODI World Cup final twice, believes in pursuing what she wants to do.\\r\\n\\r\\nRegarded as one of the greatest cricketing batters, Raj has set a precedent for women to choose their dreams over societal expectations. \\r\\n\\r\\nThere are few things in life you can achieve when you have to take decisions. I have taken a decision to pursue my career and struggled a lot, faced a lot of challenges. I dont just consider societal norms, Raj told Entrepreneur India in an exclusive chat.\\r\\n', 'Mithali Raj, Cricket, Indian Cricket, ODI, Women Crickets, Sports, Women in Sports, Leaders, Inspirational Leaders, World Cup, ICC, BCCI, Women Entrepreneurs', '2:38', 'V', NULL, 'en', 0, 0, 0, 783, 'A', '2017-10-29 10:46:45', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0),
